(1255, '2021/12/14', '5:18 p.m.', '4', '10', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Lucy found it difficult using the 6 times tables to solve a long multiplication problem today (9x6). &nbsp;She was able to recognise that going to 10x6 and subtracting was a useful strategy, however, she found it very difficult to work out how to subtract 6 from 60. &nbsp;NW encouraged Lucy to use her fingers which she was reluctant to do, but with strong direction from Naomi to reattempt slowly with 1:1 correspondence, Lucy was able to calculate the correct answer. &nbsp;It was helpful for Lucy to see the way in which the times tables will now begin to form just one part of more complex equations.</p><p>When completing long multiplication, Lucy is forgetting to ‘drop a 0’ in the tens row', NULL, NULL, '2021-12-14 17:18:58', '2021-12-19 15:36:00'),
