(1282, '2021/12/17', '3:33 p.m.', '4', '10', 'Annika Spedding', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ou, er, oo, ur, ir, ee, ear, ow, wor</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>NOTES:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Annika and I started our lesson off strong with a good OPR/WPR. She remembered her \'er\' sounds well, and applied them correctly in our \'er\' bingo game.<br><br>Annika and I enjoyed a wonderful origami activity where we followed along a video to create an origami christmas tree. It was wonderful to see how Annika made this activity.&nbsp; We then finished the lessons with more games of \'er bingo\'. Annika would sound out the word then connect it to a sentence that demonstrated meaning.</td></tr></tbody></table>', NULL, '2021-12-17 15:34:28', '2021-12-17 17:58:02'),
