(1297, '2022/01/04', '10:32 a.m.', 'Summer', '3', 'Owen Mclaren', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Spiel Part 1-3</strong></p><p><i>Owen is very behind. His CA is 12 years old and his RA is 6-7 years old. He has been kept back from graduating into high school. He struggles a lot with cementing the concepts in his head so it is something we have had to take slowly.&nbsp;</i></p><p><strong>Writing</strong></p><p><i>We\'ve done a bit of writing around his hobby, Pokemon, and he understood more solidly the concept of symbol and representation when using Pokemon symbols as an example. I have also eased him into handwriting some facts about his Pokemon, as he was very resistant to handwriting at first.</i></p>', NULL, '2022-01-14 10:33:34', '2022-01-14 10:41:39');
