(1298, '2022/01/04', '10:42 a.m.', 'Summer', '4', 'Owen Mclaren', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Spiel 3-6</strong></p><p><i>Owen is able to identify how to break words down into syllables, and how words are made up of individual speech sounds, however his lack of knowledge regarding phonograms with multiple sounds makes it very difficult for him to even break the words down sometimes. He would truly benefit from regular long-term tutoring to help with phonograms.</i></p><p><strong>Spelling</strong></p><p><i>Owen is able to spell 3 letter words quite confidently, but needs major help with scaffolding anything more than 3-4 letter words. He is not aware of silent sounds, and struggles with SFE and more complex phonograms such as /dge/ and /igh/. Using Pokemon once more, he was', NULL, '2022-01-14 10:43:03', '2022-01-14 10:47:08'),
(1299, '2022/01/18', '12:52 p.m.', 'Summer', '5', 'Owen Mclaren', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Spiel section 7-9</strong></p><p><i>Owen found these sections quite challenging and combated nervousness with distraction. Today it was about learning how to pay attention when we needed to. Knowledge questions were asked frequently to try and keep him focused. We completed segment/repeat/blend activities as well as first stage of marking, which was to underline multi-letter phonograms. Owen was able to complete the tasks but struggled with some knowledge questions, specifically how to define an oral and written phonogram review, so multiple knowledge questions were repeated. He is not at the stage where he would be able to confidently spell words and mark them, so we will continu', NULL, '2022-01-18 12:52:58', '2022-01-18 13:15:34'),
(1300, '2022/01/18', '1:15 p.m.', 'Summer', '1', 'Flynn Ascencio-Lane', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Segment, count and blend sounds in given words', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Assessments</strong></p><ul><li>Morrison-McCall</li><li>PAST</li><li>Waddington reading</li></ul><p><i>Flynn was definitely not excited to come to holiday tutoring, however after his mum left, he warmed up and became more talkative! By the end of the lesson he was smiling and laughing. He was quite confident in his reading and PAST but needed some explanations with certain PAST tasks. His spelling seems to be his weakest skill at this point, but he has an understanding of phonemic sounds which does help him with spelling. He doubled L in “told” and “sold” but otherwise was able to successfully complete 10 words. His attention span lacked a bit during the spelling test so we were o', NULL, '2022-01-18 13:18:00', '2022-01-18 13:25:28'),
(1301, '2022/01/19', '10:30 a.m.', 'Summer', '6', 'Owen Mclaren', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from two syllable word - Kilpatrick Level D', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Handwriting</strong></p><ul><li>Pokemon</li></ul><p><strong>Phonemic Awareness</strong></p><ul><li>Kilpatrick D1</li></ul><p><strong>Spiel Review 1-3</strong></p><ul><li>Overview of components</li></ul><p><strong>Marking&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Double phonos</li><li>Rule 4</li><li>A-G: 1</li><li>read, segment, count, blend</li><li>circle vowels</li></ul><p><strong>OPR</strong></p><ul><li>a, c, t, r, s, e, o, i, u, w</li><li>a &amp; c &nbsp;- multisounds, voice/unvoiced</li></ul><p><i>Owen was less resistant to complete activities today. He was able to understand how to mark double phonograms /sh/ /ee/ /th/ /ow/ with some scaffolding, and to mark r.4 also with some scaffolding. H', NULL, '2022-01-19 10:30:48', '2022-01-24 16:25:55'),
(1302, '2022/01/19', '12:31 p.m.', 'Summer', '2', 'Flynn Ascencio-Lane', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Assessments:</p><ul><li>Stimulus set</li><li>OPR</li><li>WPR</li></ul><p><i>Flynn had an anxiety attack today when trying to complete the stimulus set. He started to throw materials across the room and was not able to make eye contact. However, we talked about how it was ok to be nervous and ok to feel upset. He was informed that any time he felt nervous, he could say the special code word “penguin” and we would stop and do something else for awhile. However, it was made clear that he still had to do at least 3 tasks every lesson so we sat down and decided to work on his schedule. He was allowed to pick where in the schedule he wanted to complete his tasks. After this and a few games, Fly', NULL, '2022-01-19 12:32:22', '2022-01-19 12:35:44'),
(1303, '2022/01/20', '3:09 p.m.', 'Summer', '7', 'Owen Mclaren', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Handwriting</strong></p><ul><li>Pokemon</li></ul><p><strong>Phonemic Awareness</strong></p><ul><li>Kilpatrick D1</li></ul><p><strong>Spiel Review 1-3</strong></p><ul><li>Overview of components</li></ul><p><strong>Marking&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Double phonos</li><li>Rule 4</li><li>A-G Page 2</li><li>read, segment, count, blend</li><li>circle vowels</li></ul><p><strong>OPR</strong></p><ul><li>g&amp;e &nbsp;- multisounds, voice/unvoiced</li></ul><p><strong>Reading</strong></p><ul><li>Title: \"I don\'t want to read this book\"</li></ul><p><i>Owen was again less resistant to complete activities today. He continued to mark double phonograms /ou/ /ou/ with less scaffolding, and to mark r', NULL, '2022-01-20 15:10:17', '2022-01-20 15:14:47'),
(1304, '2022/01/20', '3:14 p.m.', 'Summer', '3', 'Flynn Ascencio-Lane', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Assessments:</strong></p><ul><li>OPR</li><li>South Australia Spelling</li><li>Burt Word Reading</li></ul><p><i>Flynn continues to have behavioural issues, very likely linked to anxiety. For the last 2 days, his issues seem to have been triggered by fear of failure and frustration that he is “not good enough”. This results in physical reactions where he will throw objects off the table (like a cat). Today, we discussed that it was ok to feel frustrated and it was ok to want to stop but that he needed to not wreck items. Instead, it was fine for him to use our code word “penguin” whenever he wanted to take a little break. He was encouraged to use words, not throw things. Flynn also ', NULL, '2022-01-20 15:15:38', '2022-01-20 15:22:12'),
(1305, '2022/01/21', '10:29 a.m.', 'Summer', '8', 'Owen Mclaren', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Segment, count and blend sounds in given words', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Kilpatrick D1</strong></p><p><br><strong>Overview of components</strong></p><p><br><strong>Handwriting</strong>: Pokemon</p><p><br><strong>Focus on phonograms</strong> a, c, g, e &nbsp;- multisounds, voice/unvoiced</p><p><br><strong>WPR/OPR:</strong> a, c, g, e, qu, p, b, d, ee, th, sh</p><p><br><strong>Marking:</strong> A-G: 3</p><ul><li>Double phonos<br>r.4<br>/c/ /g/ second sounds&nbsp;<br>Read<br>Segment<br>Count<br>Blend</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i>Owen has become much more confident in marking and although he still struggles with reading, there seems to be very little resistance! He was able to quickly understand how to mark second sounds and seems to have grasped the link b', NULL, '2022-01-21 10:31:36', '2022-01-24 16:26:12'),
