(1314, '2022/01/24', '11:02 a.m.', 'Summer', '9', 'Owen Mclaren', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from two syllable word - Kilpatrick Level D', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Kilpatrick D1</strong></p><p><br><strong>Handwriting</strong>: Pokemon</p><p><br><strong>Focus on phonograms</strong> a, c, g, e, u, s &nbsp;- multisounds, voice/unvoiced</p><p><br><strong>WPR/OPR:</strong> sh, th, ee, qu, u, s, a, c, g, e</p><p><br><strong>Marking:</strong> A-G 4</p><ul><li>Double phonos<br>r.4<br>syllables<br>Read<br>Segment<br>Count<br>Blend</li></ul><p><strong>Reading</strong></p><ul><li>“I don\'t want to read this book” - Max Greenfield</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i>Owen is now confident with marking double phonograms, though he has yet to learn them off by heart. He continues to struggle with reading but doesn\'t seem as opposed to giving it a go. He is also rec', NULL, '2022-01-24 11:02:59', '2022-01-24 13:47:09'),
(1315, '2022/01/24', '1:47 p.m.', 'Summer', '4', 'Flynn Ascencio-Lane', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Segment, count and blend sounds in given words', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Assessments:</strong></p><ul><li>Morrison McCall</li><li>South Australia Spelling</li><li>Holborn</li></ul><p><i>Flynn did not have major issues today during the lesson, but I have observed that once his parent is there, he exhibits more negative behaviour. At the end of the lesson, once he sees his parent, he may become a bit rude towards the tutor. However, he completed his tasks fine with minimal drama after we devised a schedule which broke up the tasks into small pieces with multiple breaks in between. Right now what seems to work is breaking things up into 5-10 minute intervals. He is generally fine with his reading and spelling, though he does hesitate a little when reading', NULL, '2022-01-24 13:48:33', '2022-01-24 14:02:13'),
(1316, '2022/01/24', '2:02 p.m.', 'Summer', '5', 'Flynn Ascencio-Lane', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Segment, count and blend sounds in given words', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Assessments:</strong></p><ul><li>Morrison McCall</li><li>South Australia Spelling</li><li>Holborn</li></ul><p><i>Flynn continued to be low drama today and displayed enthusiasm when talking about his favourite lego movie. We worked on some words he has been struggling with in the assessments such as:</i></p><ul><li>told</li><li>sold</li><li>van&nbsp;</li><li>vax</li><li>jam</li><li>jay</li></ul><p>Flynn completed the above list without complaint and with little struggle! We also completed OPR:</p><ul><li>ee, qu, th, sh, v, e, j, y, r</li></ul><p>Flynn sometimes struggles between the use of /y/ and /e/ to make the /ee/ sound at the end of words.</p>', NULL, '2022-01-24 14:02:58', '2022-01-24 14:15:08'),
