(1338, '2022/02/07', '5:15 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Arki Young', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: kn ew ow ti ea er ough oa a o x ur th ng au dge</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 20 2 23 29</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: except-suffer</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Type &amp; Structure Lucky Dip. Bonus point for using a spelling word. Revise each sentence by checking for: capital letters, full stops, comma, spelling.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>AY was co', NULL, '2022-02-07 17:15:57', '2022-02-07 17:51:33'),
(1339, '2022/02/08', '3:29 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Max Shapiro', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-44</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ow ou ay oy</td></tr><tr><td>When writing ow Max asked, \"is it the w or o that comes first?\". He also swapped around o and u in ou as well as reversing his u. When I let him know he had gotten it back to front and asked him to rewrite the phonogram, he only corrected his u formation.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Using words day say lay tray pay:</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: Teach rule 18. Put r18 words on board and have MS spot the pattern. Articulate the rule. Have MS articulate the rule back. Give MS a nonsense word \"tay\" and get him to write it down, applying rule ', NULL, '2022-02-08 15:30:10', '2022-02-08 18:21:28'),
(1340, '2022/02/08', '3:31 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Esther McIver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>oo, ai, a, or, th, ea, ar, ch, ui</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule Review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>4, 19</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>took, again, inform, both, heart, month, children, child, build, built</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>WRITING:</p><ul><li>Refresh sentence types/structure (using manipulatives)<ul><li>Discuss differences/similarities</li></ul></li></ul><p>READING:</p><ul><li>The Lost Bear (Fitzroy Reader #12)</li></ul><p>NOTES:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>It was lovely to see Esther back a', NULL, '2022-02-08 15:31:38', '2022-02-08 16:49:42'),
(1341, '2022/02/08', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 30-50</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ea au wh ed ew gu ey igh&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 17 26 29 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: member-return</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Types: Sentence type and structure lucky dip.</td></tr><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Review compound sente', NULL, '2022-02-08 15:36:42', '2022-02-08 18:04:34'),
(1342, '2022/02/08', '4:29 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'MAD MINUTE MATHS FACTS TO 50', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luca came in today requesting to do some work on multiplication. I gave him a multiplication grid that he finished completely within 10 min. He is doing incredibly well to remember his tables! Luca seemed to really enjoy the fact that he could do them so fast!<br><br>Luca and I then completed some mental maths activities to speed up his processing skills. We played the Decimal Escape room (identifying equivalent decimals) which Luca struggled a little with, followed by a few rounds of WAFF, that Luca remembered and picked up quite quickly.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-02-08 16:29:33', '2022-02-08 18:07:27'),
(1343, '2022/02/08', '4:29 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Ava brought some school work to be checked as she was hesitant with the last question.&nbsp;<br>This particular problem was easy to solve by using equations, and since Ava and I hadn\'t had the time to properly look at it, she was having this setback.&nbsp;</p><p>We started to look at equations and then moved to operation with integers as I could notice a little bit of practice with those and BODMAS.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-08 16:29:58', '2022-02-22 14:24:06'),
(1344, '2022/02/08', '4:30 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Shay Douglas', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Factorise algebraic expressions by identifying numerical factors', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject:</td><td>Year 10 Maths</td></tr><tr><td>Focus:</td><td>Reviewing assumed knowledge for Shay\'s upcoming unit.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Activity:</td><td>Goal setting -- what does SD hope to achieve, what does he want to focus on, how are we going to achieve those goals.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Goal: To pass maths</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Goal: To do maths more than english in tutoring, with exceptions based on assignments.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Goal: To support school work/see things in tutoring&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Goal: Follow up + revise what\'s been done in class.&nb', NULL, '2022-02-08 16:30:20', '2022-02-08 18:11:44');
