(1345, '2022/02/08', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Lachlan Prior', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>First lesson so didn\'t want to throw too much at him. Worked well with OPR and WPR. Realised as we were doing dictaion that we haven\'t looked at certain rules so will follow that up next week&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-08 16:31:11', '2022-03-01 09:58:15'),
(1347, '2022/02/08', '7:57 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', 'Writing - Capitalisation & Punctuation', 'Capitalise first words of sentences', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>T1W1–Concentration levels were high. On task. Able to deal with distractions.&nbsp;</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>PA&nbsp;</strong>DK 1 final phoneme deletion Level 2</p><p>&nbsp;All words were not overly familiar to Andrew today and he attempted each willingly. Missed the vowel sound when deleting final phoneme fro words with 3 letter blend as initial sounds.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;<strong>OPR</strong><br>All consonants + a e I o u y er ir ur wor ear ed&nbsp; ng ee&nbsp;ea&nbsp; wh&nbsp; &nbsp;wr&nbsp; oo oa oe or ar j dge ck ch tch ey kn (new)</p><p><br><strong>WPR</strong> er ir ur wor ear dge ck ch tch ea qu ey kn ed&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW focus&nbsp; -lines start at top', NULL, '2022-02-08 19:57:57', '2022-02-08 20:14:48'),
(1348, '2022/02/09', '2:06 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>office area introduction&nbsp;</li><li>assessment.&nbsp;</li><li>Phonological awareness: Callum needs help on syllable deletion and phoneme deletion. He does not have a strong sense of individual sounds.</li><li>oral phonogram review: e, j, u, y need prompts.</li><li>written phonogram review: e, i, y, u, qu. He showed the same problems with same phonograms.&nbsp;</li><li>Spelling: Callum needs help with spelling. His spelling age is between 8 years and 9 years old. &nbsp;He need help with multi letter words such as fifth and arrange.</li><li>Reading: reading age 10-13.&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-02-09 14:07:04', '2022-02-15 18:57:28'),
(1349, '2022/02/09', '3:21 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Banjo Mills', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>T1W1</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>PA&nbsp;</strong>DK D1 L4 D syllable deletion&nbsp;</p><p>B able to easily syllabify compound words. Move on the phoneme deletion</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>OPR&nbsp;</strong>a e I o u y + consonants + th sh ee B was able to say 1st sounds only except for a and c.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>WPR&nbsp;</strong>clockface focus&nbsp;a e I o u&nbsp; f c g d qu</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>H/W&nbsp;</strong>start at 2pm forms f and o incorrectly</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Rule Review</strong></p><p>Rule 1. + review of vowels v consonants. Practised sorting</p><p>Wrote vowels into workbook</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Spelling Dictation</strong></p><p', NULL, '2022-02-09 15:22:03', '2022-02-10 11:48:51'),
(1350, '2022/02/09', '3:25 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Lilly Oettle', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Spelling Assessment for Ayres Placement', 'Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment - List 1', 'Laree Thorsby', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-09 15:25:31', '2022-02-17 11:37:03'),
(1351, '2022/02/09', '3:27 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Connor and I were working on:</p><ul><li>Clock faces.</li><li>Elapsed time.</li><li>Long additions and subtractions.</li><li>Operations with integers.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Overall, Connor did great work, he was focused during the first 40 minutes of the lesson and then had to start to use some board games to attract his attention and complete the activities related to operations with integers.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-09 15:27:43', '2022-02-22 14:41:36'),
(1352, '2022/02/09', '3:28 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>CVC spelling game.</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-38</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: th ow ou ch ay ai er&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Phonogram focus: ch</td></tr><tr><td>SD: much, such, school, chef</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>MB was able to do this easily when not distracted. Keeping him on task was immensely difficult.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>MB was emotional when he came to tutoring today. He initially gave me the silent treatment until I coaxed him into talking about Monopoly Deal (which he was upset he wasn\'t able to play at tutoring).', NULL, '2022-02-09 15:28:04', '2022-02-11 13:24:31'),
(1353, '2022/02/09', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>office introduction</li><li>assessment</li><li>Phonological awareness: Phoebe is quite good at this part except the phoneme segmentation, which means we will need to gain more awareness on individual sounds and practice phonemes counting.&nbsp;</li><li>OPR: Phoebe has confusion between b and d. she is not familiar with phonogram qu.&nbsp;</li><li>WPR: qu, j, ee.&nbsp;</li><li>Spelling: She is between below 6 and 6 years and 10 months. She is confused with some vowels, such as a and u, e and a, e and y. She is not aware of multi letter phonograms such as ay.</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-02-09 15:30:29', '2022-02-15 19:38:50'),
(1354, '2022/02/09', '3:31 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Toby Webb', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-09 15:31:52', '2022-02-09 15:31:52'),
(1355, '2022/02/09', '4:27 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Challenge: breakable</td></tr><tr><td>Using the given definition of the suffix \"able\", explain how the suffix changes the meaning of the verb \"able\"</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 45-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ough si ci au ed ph ey ie ew ei</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: NA</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Section N</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></t', NULL, '2022-02-09 16:27:03', '2022-02-11 13:21:26'),
(1356, '2022/02/09', '4:27 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>a, er, ou, o, i, c, or, y, e</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rules:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>4, 5, 6, 17</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>water, round, cost, price, become, class, horse, care, try, move</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>WRITING:</p><ul><li>Refresh sentence types</li><li>Refresh sentence structure</li><li>Sentence lucky dip</li></ul><p>NOTES:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luke did a fantastic job with his OPR/WPR/SD today. We did this on the balance board and while playing soccer. Luke\'s concentration ', NULL, '2022-02-09 16:27:48', '2022-02-09 18:05:53'),
(1357, '2022/02/09', '4:32 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Locate number in a number line.', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>In our first lesson, Jacob and I were working on place value.&nbsp;</p><p>We started by telling the numbers, 10 of millions.&nbsp;</p><p>Long additions and subtractions. Carrying and borrowing.</p><p>Jacob did a good job. However, sometimes I could notice a lack of confidence which we will be working during the term.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-09 16:32:52', '2022-02-22 14:49:11'),
(1358, '2022/02/09', '5:38 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Vincenzo Vella', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>For our first lesson of the school year, Vinnie and I started by doing long additions and subtractions, we did this using 5-6 and sometimes went to use negative numbers.&nbsp;<br>The student did a great job despite the fact that starting the lesson he was confused.&nbsp;<br>Moreover, Vinnie brought an assignment from school which was about decimals, fractions, and percentages. The level of difficulty on this wasn\'t very hard. Some of the problems were more appropriate for year 5-6 students.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-09 17:38:02', '2022-02-27 17:24:08'),
(1359, '2022/02/10', '7:48 a.m.', '1', '1', 'Chester Vincent', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Basically followed the same lesson as last week. Going very slowly through it to not rush to him. Is getting stumped on \"ou\". &nbsp;And worked well when we read the fox book. worked slowly through it but seemed to enjoy it &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-10 07:48:42', '2022-03-01 09:40:40'),
(1360, '2022/02/10', '8:50 a.m.', '1', '1', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Decimals', 'Operations with decimals', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We started our work with decimals.</p><p>We focused on place value with decimals and making additions and substractions with them.&nbsp;<br>In the last 20 minutes of the lesson we were working on counting in groups as next week, we will be working on multiplications with decimals.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-10 08:50:51', '2022-02-27 17:38:30'),
(1361, '2022/02/10', '2:17 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Mia Harvey', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Started on module 10, asked her to circle any question she didn\'t understand and after giving the first and second questions a good look she circled the first 5 questions. We dropped down to module 9 and gave it another go, when I left her with it she started to circle more of the questions. i soon realised that she just didn\'t understand the question because she was just struggling to read the question such as \"calculate the following\" after i read the questions out for her she had no problems with doing basic maths equations. she was working really well with modules 8 and 9 with only a few slip-ups with the real-world problems. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-10 14:17:44', '2022-03-01 09:30:43'),
(1362, '2022/02/10', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '1', 'James Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week One</td></tr><tr><td>Tuesday, 8 February 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Challenge word: De/cem/ber r. 26, 4, 3</td></tr><tr><td>VD: Use challenge word in an oral sentence</td></tr><tr><td>Able to ID all markings and rules, prompting with order and numbers.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: oo ng kn ou th oa ea ch er ai ee ar&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Prompting with oo first round of OPR, then S/C after.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 9</td></', NULL, '2022-02-10 15:30:06', '2022-02-10 17:08:15'),
(1363, '2022/02/10', '3:34 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Adjectives - describe nouns', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T1W2/3</p><p><strong>Focus: Building a language bank</strong></p><p>Review POS</p><p>Thesaurus online</p><p>Dictionary online</p><p><strong>Focus: Descriptive language:</strong></p><p><strong>Write one sentence to describe the paper flower.</strong></p><p><strong>Find alternative words for flower….etc</strong></p><p><strong>Read sentences below. Identify a key word or phrase.</strong></p><p><strong>Find alternate words for????</strong></p><p>Her last smile to me wasn’t a sunset. It was an eclipse, the last eclipse, noon dying away to darkness where there would be no dawn.</p><p>My Uber driver looked like a deflating airbag and sounded like talk radio on repeat.</p><p>The old man was bent ', NULL, '2022-02-10 15:34:05', '2022-02-22 10:28:43'),
(1364, '2022/02/10', '3:36 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick: H1</p><p>Handwriting: Cursive /a/</p><p>Morphology: Donah 24, “usual\"</p><ul><li>Reuben completed this task entirely without any prompting! He has improved greatly in comparison with last year in both eagerness and quality of work.</li></ul><p>Ayres: P, spend - usual</p><ul><li>Reuben is very advanced with spelling and has been placed in Section P. All his words were correct, except for “awe”, which was spelled as “woh”.</li></ul><p>Writing: Text Types - Narrative</p><ul><li>Beginning/Middle/End</li><li>Reuben understood these concepts well and was able to explain the purpose and detail of “Beginning” through the animation “Naruto” by Masashi Kishimoto. Japanese culture is som', NULL, '2022-02-10 15:36:56', '2022-03-07 09:53:04'),
(1365, '2022/02/10', '3:37 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematical Assessment', 'Key Maths', 'Algebra', 'Problem solving - oral response to questions & activities presented via easel', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Lucy\'s first day back at tutoring - chatting about beginning of high school. &nbsp;Currently completing topic reviews including vertical addition and BODMAS. &nbsp;Lucy says she is feeling confident with what she is currently working on in class.</p><p>Lucy engaged intently in the assessment task today and was often able to back up her responses with a brief explanation.</p><p>To continue this assessment next week.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-10 15:37:43', '2022-02-11 22:19:03'),
(1366, '2022/02/10', '3:38 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Represent and solve simple addition and subtraction problems using a range of strategies', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>As today was our first lesson of the year, Sofia and I were working on additions with and without carrying, we did this using up to 6 digit numbers.&nbsp;<br>Moreover, we were working on bar graphs and how to do additions and subtractions with those.&nbsp;<br>Sofia did a good job and was engaged with the lesson. She enjoys playing the money game and UNO. I used these two to keep working on adding with carrying.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-10 15:38:25', '2022-03-03 10:17:13'),
