(1373, '2022/02/11', '7:32 a.m.', '1', '1', 'Charlotte Kratz', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>er, u, ie, ew, th, ough, ou</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>3, 4, 6, 17</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>prison, engine, visit, guest, guess, department, obtain, family, favour</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>READING:</p><ul><li>Read ORF #620 - discuss inferred meaning (we will write an ending to this next week</li></ul><p>NOTES:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>It was wonderful to see Charlotte back at tutoring again this week. She did an amazing job remembering her phonograms, bu', NULL, '2022-02-11 07:32:20', '2022-02-11 08:43:22'),
(1375, '2022/02/11', '11:05 a.m.', '1', '1', 'Lottie Young', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Read words aloud - accurately, automatically, with expression (connected text)', 'Text of Choice (see notes)', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', 'In Progress', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Lottie read all ten pages of Chapter Two in ‘Billie B Brown The Cutest Pet Ever’. &nbsp;This was the most accurate and fluent reading I have observed of Lottie to date. &nbsp;Some prompting was required for multi-syllable words (encourage to read one syllable at a time - repeated difficulty with the word ‘Noah’) and to read words to the end (often missing the final suffix sounds).</p><p>Played Silent Final ‘e’ (SFe) Fish - matching the CVC and SFe Job One words (eg at/ate, grip/gripe). &nbsp;Lottie took time to quietly decode the words she needed to ask for and was able to do so accurately. &nbsp;When asked to read the words as flashcards at the end of the game, she was unable to recognis', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-11 11:06:51', '2022-02-11 13:00:06'),
(1376, '2022/02/11', '1:22 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Archie Lester', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rules 2 & 3: c and g say their second sounds when followed by e, i or y', 'Giants and Cyclops - Apply Rules 2 and 3 to identify hard and soft sounds of c and g', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Began the lesson with a game of Giants and Cyclops - Archie had some difficulty applying known concepts when decoding unfamiliar or pseudo words. &nbsp;Was able to apply rules 2 and 3 without hesitation.</p><p>Move up Phonological Awareness level from F2 next lesson. &nbsp;Nil difficulties with Set 13 and Mixed Level on F2 Page 159.</p><p>OPR and WPR - most fluent to date. &nbsp;This was seamless and accurate. &nbsp;(au, aw, or, igh, e, g, wor, ur, ed, qu, ea)</p><p>Word decoding - sound and say index card words (errors made on assessments at the end of 2021). &nbsp;law, child, worm, fur, bread, author.&nbsp;</p><p>Spelling Dictation (back of Spelling Notebook) - Rule 19 words, au/aw word', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-11 13:22:35', '2022-02-11 21:03:34'),
