(1417, '2022/02/17', '3:35 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Prepositions - tell the position in time & space', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T1W2/3</p><p><strong>Focus: Building a language bank</strong></p><p>Review POS</p><p>Thesaurus online</p><p>Dictionary online</p><p><strong>Focus: Descriptive language:</strong></p><p><strong>Write one sentence to describe the paper flower.</strong></p><p><strong>Find alternative words for flower….etc</strong></p><p><strong>Read sentences below. Identify a key word or phrase.</strong></p><p><strong>Find alternate words for????</strong></p><p>Her last smile to me wasn’t a sunset. It was an eclipse, the last eclipse, noon dying away to darkness where there would be no dawn.</p><p>My Uber driver looked like a deflating airbag and sounded like talk radio on repeat.</p><p>The old man was bent ', NULL, '2022-02-17 15:35:58', '2022-02-22 10:31:26'),
(1419, '2022/02/17', '3:38 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematical Assessment', 'Key Maths', 'Measurement', 'Problem solving - oral response to questions & activities presented via easel', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Lucy did very well to remain focused for the duration of this assessment task today, completing three sections of the Key Maths assessment task.</p><p>Lucy is quick to lose confidence when I ask her to repeat an answer due to difficulty hearing. &nbsp;Lucy certainly has a bank of problem solving skills, however, she finds it very difficult to access these across different settings. &nbsp;For example, during lessons on worded problems, Lucy knows that she can use modelling and drawing pictures to fully understand the given problem. &nbsp;When presented with a problem in the assessment today, she did not think to access this strategy independently, but she was able to do so when I prompted ', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-17 15:38:40', '2022-02-17 17:14:54'),
(1420, '2022/02/17', '3:46 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick: H1</p><p>Handwriting: Cursive /b/</p><p>Reuben did an excellent job with /a/ but struggled with uppercase /b/. He was a good sport about it!</p><p>Morphology: Donah 24, the prefix “com”</p><p>Ayres: P, complaint - beautiful + awe</p><ul><li>Reuben was able to spell “awe” correctly this week, and had no problems with the rest of the dictation words.</li></ul><p>Inference: Set P1, Item 1 &amp; 2</p><ul><li>Reuben understood this task excellently, but needed prompting on explaining why he concluded in the ways he did.</li></ul><p>Writing: Text Types - Narrative</p><ul><li>Beginning/Middle/End</li><li>Today we focused on Middle (Conflict) and End (Resolution), however ran out of t', NULL, '2022-02-17 15:46:33', '2022-03-07 09:56:10'),
