(1428, '2022/02/18', '10:04 a.m.', '1', '2', 'Lottie Young', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Read words aloud - accurately, automatically, with expression (connected text)', 'Text of Choice (see notes)', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Tardy', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Lottie was able to complete Kilpatrick medial sound deletions in two-syllable words with only some finger scaffolding. &nbsp;Last lesson she was unable to do this without the written words to help her grasp the concept of the sound being deleted.</p><p>She read Billie B Brown with some difficulty today - a notable amount of guessing words with regular prompting needed to sound out or look at one syllable at a time.</p><p>Continued difficulty reading silent final ‘e’ words accurately. &nbsp;Read Magic Bridge cards x3 at end of lesson to practice. &nbsp;Increased accuracy with observable conscious engagement in the task.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-18 10:07:03', '2022-02-18 10:20:00'),
