(1467, '2022/02/22', '9:16 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Henry Badcock', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Count collections to 100 by partitioning numbers using place value.', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Number and Place Value</p><ol><li>Identifying “friends of…\" using counters and recording in his workbook to create a table. H. was able to recognise a pattern after completing “friends of 10/11/19” This will be used to assist with mental computation of numbers to 10 and across 10.&nbsp;</li><li>Place Value - H can read numbers to 9 thousand + easily, however, he was not consistently able to break the number down into the ‘value’ for each place.&nbsp;</li><li>Activity: Roll die and write the numbers onto the PV card (1000/100/10/1) eg 6 5 3 4. H was encouraged to articulate the number fully as he wrote the number down. Eg 6 lots of 1000, 5 groups of one hundred, 3 lots of 10, 4 ones/units.', NULL, '2022-02-22 09:18:08', '2022-03-06 20:29:59'),
(1468, '2022/02/22', '9:52 a.m.', '1', '2', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Nouns - name people, places, things, ideas', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T1W2</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR a e I o u y ow ou oo ea ew ui ough ey ie ei ti si ci sh&nbsp;</p><p>WPR – ow ou&nbsp; oo a e I o u y sh ti si ci&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD – cow slow sound (cantaloupe) you country fruit juice grew new hot open do &nbsp;</p><p>Parts of Speech</p><p>Verbs</p><p>Nouns/pronouns</p><p>Adjectives</p><p>Adverbs</p><p>Worksheets identify POS in sentences.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Writing Process</p><ol><li>Sentence Assessment</li><li>Sentence Structure - Simple sentences elements</li><li>Sentence Types - Fact/command/question/emotion</li></ol><p>Sentence structure simple 1 idea independent clause. (Blocks )</p><p>Assessment -of simple sentences only</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p', NULL, '2022-02-22 09:52:45', '2022-02-22 10:11:48'),
(1469, '2022/02/22', '10:08 a.m.', '1', '1', 'Zac Pharaoh', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Create simple financial plans', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Covered topics:</p><ul><li>Personal finance: Different sources of income, jobs, and assets.&nbsp;</li><li>Investments: Profit and loss.&nbsp;</li><li>Planning personal budgets.&nbsp;</li><li>Calculating percentages.&nbsp;</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-02-22 10:12:34', '2022-02-22 10:19:30'),
(1470, '2022/02/22', '10:31 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 25: Write ck to say /k/ after a single vowel saying its first (short) sound', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T1W3</p><p>The focus for X this term is APPLICATION of his knowledge of phonics and rules. X has a good basic knowledge of both of the concepts but does not apply this when writing. He experiences anxiety over spelling and therefore chooses language based on the ease of spelling. Our focus is to increase his confidence through consistent application of the common rules.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Focus: Rules 23/25 + tch</p><p>Explore &nbsp;3 ways to write ‘j’ (j,dge, g+eiy), &nbsp;2 ways to write ‘ch (ch tch), 3 ways to write ’ck\' (c k ck +qu next time)</p><ol><li>Isolate the end sound in words ending with dge/tch/ck</li><li>Form a table where we write the rule for each end sound (not qu)<', NULL, '2022-02-22 10:33:24', '2022-02-24 12:25:42'),
(1471, '2022/03/30', '10:57 a.m.', '1', '1', 'Jett Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Simplify algebraic expressions involving the four operations', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>In our first lesson of the year, we did a quick review of the 4 operations with algebraic expressions.</p><p>At the beginning of the lesson, he was slightly confused. &nbsp;This was because of the lack of practice.&nbsp;</p><p>We were working on each operation while looking at the operations with fractions, integers, and index law.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-22 10:59:10', '2022-02-22 11:10:41'),
(1472, '2022/02/22', '2:32 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Max Shapiro', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Challenge: out &amp; own</td></tr><tr><td>Connected with picture: 3 stick people, 2 of whom say the same sound at the same time.</td></tr><tr><td>Continue with sound/symbol talk. Talk about reversal and compare ow vs wo.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>MS was pretty good with this! He seemed to remember the activity from last week. He first ID\'d the letters. Then I told him the word had a different number of sounds and asked him to sound it out. MS sounded it out correctly and ID\'d 2 sounds. I showed him the ou phonogram card and asked him to underline the phonogram', NULL, '2022-02-22 14:32:18', '2022-02-22 17:38:57'),
(1473, '2022/02/22', '2:33 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Apply index laws to numerical expressions with integer indices', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>We did today a checklist. This was about the different mathematical and algebraical operations that we have to reduce and expand algebraic expressions.&nbsp;<br>Isaac was doing a good job. However, I could notice some lack of practice with fractions and index law.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-22 14:34:15', '2022-02-22 14:37:08'),
(1474, '2022/02/22', '3:15 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Jett Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Linear & Non-Linear Relationships', 'Linear & Non-linear equations', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today we were working on simultaneous equations.&nbsp;<br>I showed the three methods to solve simultaneous linear equations with two variables. Substitution, Reduction/Elimination, and graphics. I decided to only work on Substitution as it is the longest but easiest of the three methods. In the beginning, he was confused, however, we were looking at the process very slow and doing multiple examples.&nbsp;<br>Jett was showing some confidence at the end of the lesson and was feeling excited that he understood the process. Even though we both agreed on he needs more practice and completes the homework.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-22 15:15:29', '2022-02-27 13:46:11'),
(1475, '2022/02/22', '3:28 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: ea 61-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ea 61-70&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PROMPT CARDS ON BOARD</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 6 4 18</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: money-breakfast</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr>', NULL, '2022-02-22 15:28:19', '2022-02-22 17:42:17'),
(1476, '2022/02/22', '3:28 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Stella Bowerman', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Went back to the drawing board today with Stella. Seemed to do the job. Was mostly written theory-based as I explained exactly how addition worked and the importance of place value. Seemed to get it because she pulled herself up on it towards the end of the lesson as we answered some word problems on the board&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-22 15:28:45', '2022-03-01 10:05:06'),
(1477, '2022/02/22', '4:28 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Shay Douglas', 'Mathematics', 'Linear & Non-Linear Relationships', 'Linear & Non-linear equations', 'School-assigned worksheet/task', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Year 10 Maths</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Consolidate understanding needed for SD\'s maths class on Thursday.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Exercises from SD\'s textbook (accessed via canvas)</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>The exercises Shay wanted to solve/review mostly made use of concepts he\'s familiar with; expansion, solving for x, solving simultaneous equations.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Shay was second-guessing himself a lot today. In some ways this is good, as self-checking is definitely something he needs to work on when he goes too quickly. However, today he was solving equations at a good speed and question', NULL, '2022-02-22 16:28:50', '2022-03-03 15:01:19'),
(1478, '2022/02/22', '4:30 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Lachlan Prior', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Went through phonos 1-28 and he got them all right so I told him if he got them all right we could continue with his animal and story. Worked well but had to keep him when I could tell he wasn\'t using his imagination as much as he could. Got there eventually but seemed like he needed a big push sometimes.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-22 16:30:24', '2022-03-01 09:59:09'),
(1479, '2022/02/22', '4:32 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'BODMAS', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today we were working on:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Solving sums with integers.</li><li>Applying the sign law to solve BODMAS problems.</li><li>Use the number line in a practical way.&nbsp;</li><li>Worded problems with additions and subtraction using integers.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Overall, Ava did a great job. She was able to solve 10+ steps BODMAS problems, and correctly solved Level 3 problems. However, with problems with a level of difficulty &nbsp;2 and 1, she showed some hesitation and forgot to apply the basics of BODMAS.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-22 16:32:16', '2022-02-27 13:53:33'),
(1480, '2022/02/22', '4:36 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Banjo Mills', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 1 > 30', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>PA DK D syllable deletion</p><p>OPR/WPR&nbsp;</p><p>a e i o u y b d c g qu th ee sh ow</p><p>Review vowel sounds - flashcards&nbsp;</p><p>SD - as part of POS</p><p>sound for spelling/read for reading</p><p>Rule 4 review</p><p>Roll the dice game</p><p>Read flashcards.</p><p>Writing&nbsp;</p><p>Parts of Speech- nouns/verbs Add to lists. Follow Spelling dictation pattern</p><p>Sentences</p><p>Write 2 sentences&nbsp;</p><p>Reading</p><p>In the fog.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-22 16:37:30', '2022-02-22 16:46:30'),
(1481, '2022/02/22', '4:47 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Read words aloud - accurately, automatically, with expression (connected text)', 'Fitzroy Readers - Levels 31 > 40', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>T1W3</strong></p><p><strong>OPR</strong><br>All consonants + a e I o u y er ir ur wor ear ed&nbsp; ng ee&nbsp;ea&nbsp; wh&nbsp; &nbsp;wr&nbsp; oo oa oe or ar j dge ck ch &nbsp;ey kn&nbsp;</p><p><br><strong>WPR</strong> kn dge ea ey qu ck th &nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW focus&nbsp; -lines start at top. Andrew formed all his WPR letters correctly except ‘d’ and ‘g’</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Rule Review</strong></p><p>Rule 4 flashcards and counters&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Spelling Dictation</strong> Ayres – hat child (not rule)&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Marked all phgs in words.&nbsp; Cannot use a ruler.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Parts of Speech</p><p><strong>Verbs/nouns – coloured paper ', NULL, '2022-02-22 16:47:55', '2022-02-24 13:03:34'),
(1482, '2022/02/22', '4:55 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Brock is such a pleasant kid!</p><ol><li>OPR &nbsp;th, ng, ay, u, ou, ow, oo, ar</li><li>WPR th, ng, ay, u, ou, ow, oo, ar</li><li>Rule introduction: rule 10.&nbsp;</li><li>Rule review: rule 4 and rule 11. Brock couldn\'t remember them yet he did learn them last term. So we will need to integrate these knowledge into his daily activities.&nbsp;</li><li>SD: clothing-beginning. Brock does not remember what syllables are. We will have to enhance this. He got a bit unfamiliar with marking too.&nbsp;</li><li>Reviewed sentence types and simple sentence. He needs help with the concept of simple sentence. &nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-02-22 16:56:41', '2022-03-22 09:15:37'),
(1483, '2022/02/22', '5:33 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Measurement', 'Tell time to the minute and investigate the relationship between units of time', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>This lesson was conducted online due to Heather being stuck in quarantine.<br><br>Luca and I completed a quick round of Mad Minute Math. The online log came up with some difficult numbers, so we didn\'t time it, but Luca did well to come up with the answers.<br><br>Luca and I looked at time today, using the clock to tell time. We discussed how things can be read as \'6:45 pm\' \'quarter to 7\' \'15min to 7\' or \'1845\'. We looked at the various ways to write this, how to easily convert between the time.<br><br>Luca struggled a little with \'military time\' (24hr time). We looked at how this worked on an analog clock, writing in the numbers we needed, and the', NULL, '2022-02-22 17:34:04', '2022-02-22 17:39:29'),
(1484, '2022/02/22', '5:34 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Linear & Non-Linear Relationships', 'Linear & Non-linear equations', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-22 17:34:35', '2022-02-27 13:57:50'),
(1485, '2022/02/22', '5:35 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Jeanica Cilliers', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Seems to understand the concepts of + - x pretty well but doesn\'t understand division at all. If the equation is set out in an unfamiliar way such as missing numbers, she doesn\'t understand what it\'s asking. Is carrying in addition but not showing the working out. Nailed the fractions, she only asked \"which part do i shade\" and then answered all the other fraction questions right. Seems to be trying to do all the equations in her head rather than writing things down to help.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-22 17:35:25', '2022-03-01 09:57:28'),
(1487, '2022/02/23', '7:48 a.m.', '1', '2', 'Darcy Callaghan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked well through Kilpatrick to begin with and raced through the OPR and WPR on the tricky ones. Tried to work through quite a few spelling words which he did well.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-23 07:48:42', '2022-03-01 09:49:22'),
(1488, '2022/02/23', '1:50 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Angel King', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR</p><p>A e I o u y wr&nbsp; wh ea oo ai ay oi oy</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>WPR ea &nbsp;wh wr&nbsp; u o I e a y oo ay ai oi oy&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review Rule 4 – game&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD:&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Music duty again&nbsp;<strong>away begin</strong> reset <strong>clover </strong>over</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Sentence dictation:</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Begin to jump over the log.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Nouns/verbs/adjectives)</p><p>(Shade words in sentence)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Game</strong>: Spin a star/Roll the die&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Reading:</strong></p><p>OF&nbsp;</p><p>Fitzroy level 11/12</p><p>.&nbsp;</p><p>HW Worksheet + Fitzro', NULL, '2022-02-23 13:50:35', '2022-02-24 12:53:09'),
(1489, '2022/02/23', '3:27 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'BODMAS', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today we were working on BODMAS and Integers.&nbsp;</p><p>Connor has been showing great progress on BODMAS and integers. He accurately answered most of the problems during the lesson. Connor no longer mixes the sign and when needs to apply the sign law, he does it correctly.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-23 15:27:06', '2022-02-27 17:00:04'),
(1490, '2022/02/23', '3:28 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Segment, count and blend sounds in given words', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phoebe usually has a short time of concentration. I have to keep using incentives and games motivate her.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>review Spiel part 1</li><li>Spiel part 2 to part 5. Phoebe knows individual sounds in a word, sometimes she just need clarification of basic concepts.</li></ol><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Part 2</p><p>sounds of speech---phonemes---vowels(unblocked)/consonants(blocked)</p></td></tr><tr><td>a, m, l, v, o, e, r, g</td></tr><tr><td>consonants---unvoiced/voiced---voice box vibrates or not</td></tr><tr><td>z, t, i, ch, r, k, j, e, sh, p, h, o</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>P', NULL, '2022-02-23 15:28:23', '2022-02-23 16:43:00'),
(1491, '2022/02/23', '3:29 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Toby Webb', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Went through the phonos pretty quickly. Apparently, he went to a speachy and learned all of the basic phonos and all their sounds. Quickly went onto rules 2 and 3 and finished it off with the giants and cyclops game.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-23 15:29:02', '2022-03-01 10:08:57'),
(1492, '2022/02/23', '3:31 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Lilly Oettle', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR – vowels + ai ay oi oy ea oa ou ow ti</p><p>WPr as above</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review – 4&nbsp;</p><p>Spelling – restrain aboard afraid elect election&nbsp;</p><p>Intro to marking&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OF – 1 min Fitzroy 41&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW 1 min Fitzroy</p><p>Spalding RC grade 3 no2.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>T1 W2</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR vowels + ea ou ow er ir ur wor ear ti si ci&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>WPR ea ow ou er ir ur wor ear ti ci si&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD eat bread steak now know sound soul you country her first nurse works early na/tion facial ses/sion vi/sion</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Parts of Speech Activity:&nbsp;</p><p>Create word banks for each POS. thes', NULL, '2022-02-23 15:31:00', '2022-02-24 12:08:26'),
(1493, '2022/02/23', '3:31 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-38 + intro to 5 sounds er</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ou ay ai ow ch ar&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>MB commented \"I don\'t remember, even though I did them at school\"</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>5 sounds of er game to consolidate learning. MB could sound out the words when prompted. Required some prompting from me to recognise other multi-letter phonos in the words and sound accordingly.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Writing: Add sentences to each section of the st', NULL, '2022-02-23 15:31:36', '2022-02-23 17:48:03'),
(1494, '2022/02/23', '4:21 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Stated Purpose & Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Had a conversation with AZ about his ability re:OPR and have decided to do OPR fortnightly.</td></tr><tr><td>OPR: N/A</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: aw gu dge oo ti eigh or ea ai kn si ur ey&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>AZ did well in his WPR.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 4 14 11</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: lose-entertain</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ay', NULL, '2022-02-23 16:21:54', '2022-02-23 17:44:56'),
(1495, '2022/02/23', '4:33 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today we concentrated on working on worded problems with multiplications and divisions. All the work involved the 6, 5, and 4 times tables.&nbsp;<br>At the beginning of the lesson, Jacob wasn\'t sure about which operation he would need to use to solve the problem. I think this difficulty is more related to reading comprehension than mathematical understanding. Next week we will be working on the same but, we will be using different times tables.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-23 16:33:03', '2022-02-27 17:06:25'),
(1496, '2022/02/23', '5:32 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>SPELLING:</p><p>OPR/WPR:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>oo, sh, ur, ay, igh, th, ir, c</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rules:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>4, 13, 17, 18</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>spell, poor, finish, hurt, maybe, across, tonight, tenth, sir</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>WRITING:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Adjective worksheets<br><br>Look at types of adjectives, then manipulate sentences to include them</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>NOTES:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Today\'s lesson was held on zoom due to H', NULL, '2022-02-23 17:32:48', '2022-02-23 17:52:37'),
(1498, '2022/02/24', '7:51 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Chester Vincent', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked through the phonos really well still got stumped on the \"ou\". Only had to do one dictation word because he got 1 on the dartboard. We finished the fox book which he seemed to enjoy. Worked slowly through it but was very good at sounding out the words. finished off with some darts with the proper board because he insisted \"it\'s how the cowboys do it\"</p>', NULL, '2022-02-24 07:51:19', '2022-03-01 09:46:31'),
(1499, '2022/02/24', '8:52 a.m.', '1', '3', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Describe, continue, and create number patterns resulting from performing addition or subtraction', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We did today an introduction to algebra.&nbsp;<br>I asked James to pick three fruits and then only used the initials of each fruit. Then 3 did, A + A + A + A = 4A. After this, I gave a value to each letter and ask James to find the hidden value.&nbsp;<br>The student found this activity interesting. However, James continues saying, “ I can\'t do this” as soon as the level of difficulty increases very little.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-24 08:52:30', '2022-02-27 17:50:03'),
(1500, '2022/02/24', '12:09 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>South Australian Spell Test as informal assessment.</p><p>Went through words X struggled with and examined them. X was able to identify mistakes and rules he should have applied once we were outside the whole “this is a spelling assessment” mindset.&nbsp;</p><p>Identified he struggles with choosing end sounds - ck tch, ch dhe ge, and beginning/mid sounds c/k/j/gi/ge/gy.&nbsp;</p><p>OF - Discussed the importance of doing 20 mins of reading a day - any type of reading.</p><p>OF 400 1 min cold read and send for HW</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-24 12:10:23', '2022-02-24 12:31:56'),
(1501, '2022/02/24', '12:43 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Eleanor Stam', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 31 > 45', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>&nbsp;</p><p>Today we reviewed phgs1-45, completed a short WPR and wrote some words using first and second vowel sounds.</p><p>REviewed prior knowledge of rule 4 by playing the flashcard version of spin a star.&nbsp;</p><p>Oral Fluency Fitzroy book 11</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-24 12:43:45', '2022-02-24 12:45:18'),
(1502, '2022/02/24', '12:46 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Eleanor Stam', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR</p><p>A e I o u y wr&nbsp; wh ea oo ai ay oi oy</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>WPR ea &nbsp;wh wr&nbsp; u o I e a y oo ay ai oi oy&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review Rule 4 – game&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD:&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Music duty again&nbsp;<strong>away begin</strong> reset <strong>clover </strong>over</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Sentence dictation:</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Begin to jump over the log.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Nouns/verbs/adjectives)</p><p>(Shade words in sentence)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Game</strong>: Spin a star/Roll the die&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Reading:</strong></p><p>OF&nbsp;</p><p>Fitzroy level 11/12</p><p>.&nbsp;</p><p>HW Worksheet + Fitzro', NULL, '2022-02-24 12:47:08', '2022-02-24 12:51:41'),
(1503, '2022/02/24', '2:15 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Mia Harvey', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked well with the card game and we moved on to talking about multiplication. It seems she understands how to count up in groups but never actually made the connection with multiplication. When I wrote out some times tables for her to answer she did them pretty easily once she made the connection that it\'s the counting stuff she does at school.</p>', NULL, '2022-02-24 14:15:27', '2022-03-01 09:34:51'),
(1504, '2022/02/24', '3:29 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Today we worked on adding fractions.</p><p>We did this by using visual aids and we did this using fractions with different denominators. However, the denominators were multiples.&nbsp;</p><p>2/7 + 3/14&nbsp;</p><p>When the denominators were multiple of 2, 3, and 5, Sofia had no problems doing the operations. Even though, if those were multiples of 6, 7, 8 and 9 she had serious difficulties.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-24 15:29:27', '2022-03-03 10:34:30'),
