(1507, '2022/02/24', '3:34 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Reading - Literary Appreciation & Quality Literature', 'Identify elements in fine (imaginative) literature - metaphors, similies & personification', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>W3/4</p><p>Similes – definitions</p><p>Practice generating some</p><p>Identifying common ones</p><p>Use in appropriate contexts.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing prompts used to stimulate narrative writing task – must utilise descriptive language and similes</p>', NULL, '2022-02-24 15:34:58', '2022-03-06 20:58:54'),
(1509, '2022/02/24', '3:39 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Seth Vanderlaan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Not really sure how much we got done today. Seemed to get through a heap of phonogram cards but that was pretty much it. Got him to copy my spelling on a few words but not really sure it did anything. His mum sat in on the lesson so will have to wait for when we\'re both alone to see how ,uch i\'m actually able to teach him.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-24 15:39:02', '2022-03-01 10:05:37'),
