(1515, '2022/02/24', '4:50 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Connect the compound interest formula to repeated applications of simple interest', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Callisto had a homework assignment to complete on the topics of simple and compound interest and effective interest. She did most of the work without any assistance. I showed her how to do some parts on the Classpad. Her calculations were precise and she set her work out thoroughly and logically. She used the checklist on the front of the assignment sheet to make sure that the presentation of her work was to a high standard.</p>', '<p>Callisto had a homework assignment to complete on the topics of simple and compound interest and effective interest. She did most of the work without any assistance. I showed her how to do some parts on the Classpad. Her calculations were precise and she set her work out thoroughly and logically. She used the checklist on the front of the assignment sheet to make sure that the presentation of her work was to a high standard.</p>', NULL, '2022-02-24 16:50:58', '2022-03-10 18:09:57'),
(1516, '2022/02/24', '5:25 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Maricha Cilliers', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>struggled with the times and the division. Didn\'t understand division at all. All of the worded questions she nailed. After about 5 mins of explaining she was able to answer all the division questions she circled and skipped during the assessment.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-24 17:25:50', '2022-03-01 10:00:48'),
(1517, '2022/02/25', '7:44 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Archie Lester', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<ol><li>Phonological Awareness &nbsp;- &nbsp;moved up to G1</li><li>OPR – or, ew, ui, ck, ie, dge, ti, au, aw, igh, wor, ed, qu, c, a, e, g, ur, ea</li><li>WPR – ur, or, ew, ui, ie, dge, ti, au, ed, qu, c</li><li>Spellcheck: fur, worm, author, bread, law, child</li><li>Spellcheck: cream, pain, dirt, burn, talk, chalk, walk, quiz, tune, were, where, wear, there, their, they’re, to, too, two</li><li>Spelling notebook: &nbsp;Add ‘wear’ to ea page, add ‘alk’ list - walk, talk, chalk</li><li>Discuss ‘r controlled vowel’ spelling patterns and /r/ after a vowel sound – In Australian English we don’t hear the /r/ until there is a vowel after it.&nbsp; fur &gt;furry, wear &gt; wearing, care &gt; cari', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-25 07:44:19', '2022-02-25 13:04:31'),
(1518, '2022/02/25', '7:49 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Gus Pettit', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'BODMAS', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>, this morning Gus and I were working more on his confidence rather than algebra. I did most of the work and give him very detailed explanations about year 5/6 maths concepts.&nbsp;</p><p>It was a bit curious when Gus said, “you make this too easy”. I was trying to combine what Gus should know from year 7 and working on those gaps from previous years. As we have discussed before, I reckon these gaps are a consequence of the misused of Pathways, dyslexia and perhaps low working memory. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Once you have the results of the maths assessments that Gus has done at school this year, it will be great if I could get a copy of those. In that way, I won’t repeat the topics when he do', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-25 07:49:25', '2022-03-06 18:52:59'),
