(1521, '2022/02/25', '1:14 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Lottie Young', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Read words aloud - accurately, automatically, with expression (connected text)', 'Text of Choice (see notes)', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', 'In Progress', 'Attended Tardy', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Read final chapter of Billie B Brown ‘The cutest pet ever’ - notably increased confidence. &nbsp;Support needed to decoding a number of multi-syllable words. &nbsp;At times, not reading the ‘s’ suffix on the end of words and at other times adding an ‘s’ suffix not needed.</p><p>OPR &gt; a-e, e-e, i-e, o-e, u-e, y-e (MSL sound pack cards)</p><p>WPR &gt; a-e, e-e, i-e, o-e, u-e, y-e, a, e, i, o, u</p><p>Word decoding - Magic Bridge SFe (Job 1 - long vowel sound) and CVC (short vowel sound) - read for reading (sound as needed when error made)</p><p>Spelling dictation - trip, ate, gripe, ran, cope, dime, tape, rip, code, spin (Magic Bridge words)</p><p>Sentence dictation - Nate went on a trip', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-25 13:15:00', '2022-02-25 13:53:50'),
