(1525, '2022/02/25', '4:34 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Annika Spedding', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>SPELLING:</p><p>OPR/WPR:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>oo, a, c, ou, y, e, ow, u, i, o,&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule review:</p><ul><li>Rule 4</li></ul><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>be, ago, now, we, you, last, good, he</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>WRITING:</p><ul><li>Parts of Speech<ul><li>Recap Nouns - name nouns in images</li><li>Introduce Adjectives - describe nouns in images</li></ul></li></ul><p>NOTES:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>This lesson was conducted via Zoom as Heather was in quarantine.<br><br>Annika did really well with her OPR/WPR today. She flew through her words with eas', NULL, '2022-02-25 16:38:34', '2022-02-25 16:48:03'),
(1526, '2022/02/25', '5:28 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'BODMAS', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>We continued our work on BODMAS and integers.&nbsp;</p><p>Today in every single problem I used integers. Moreover, in the last 20 minutes of the lesson, we went to the driveway to solve problems and to do the challenge.&nbsp;</p><p>Archie was able to solve a multistep problem with BODMAS and integers; however, when he had to do +6753-9186 he was confused. Hence we made a small pause to solve a couple of problems like those and then Archie continued to solve the problem.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-02-25 17:28:27', '2022-03-06 20:03:53'),
(1529, '2022/02/27', '5:24 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Vincenzo Vella', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions, Decimals & Percentages', 'Equivalent fractions, decimals & percentages', 'School-assigned worksheet/task', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We continued with Vinnie\'s school work.&nbsp;<br>The number of problems in the booklet is about 500. However, some of the problems aren\'t very challenging. Particularly, considering that Vinnie was able to solve harder problems last year.&nbsp;<br>I showed Vinnie different ways to solve the problems, including graphs, cross multiplications, and ratios. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-27 17:25:03', '2022-02-27 17:30:00');
