(1530, '2022/02/27', '5:25 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Vincenzo Vella', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions, Decimals & Percentages', 'Fractions, decimals & percentages as part of a whole', 'School-assigned worksheet/task', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Continued working on the school assignment.&nbsp;<br>The student was informed that his maths grade for term 1 is going to be heavily taken from this task.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-27 17:25:50', '2022-02-27 17:33:05'),
(1531, '2022/02/28', '7:54 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Darcy Callaghan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Page 18. Worked well throughout the phonos. Got stumped on the ow and the ou. Arrived late so didn’t have time for dictation so we just played wordle and read just shocking instead. Page for page. He seems to be rushing through it and guessing words. If he doesn\'t know a word he\'ll just give it a guess and then carry on which i have to pull him up on. almost wants to show he can read fast rather than fluently. Finished on page 18.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-28 07:54:07', '2022-03-01 09:50:14'),
(1532, '2022/02/28', '8:52 a.m.', '1', '1', 'Flynn Ascencio-Lane', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Stuggled to get a lot done today. He\'s a really smart kid but cant focus on anything for more than 20 secs. Only said the first sound for all the phonos, tried to go throught the vowel sounds with him but kept drifting off. Decided to work on Rule 2 and 3. seemed to understand it very quickly but was stumped with a few words on the hard g\'s. finished off with talking about the solar system because he went to the toilet and came back with the solar system diarama.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-28 08:52:09', '2022-03-01 09:51:10'),
(1533, '2022/02/28', '10:01 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from two syllable word - Kilpatrick Level D', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-28 10:02:51', '2022-02-28 18:20:38'),
(1534, '2022/02/28', '10:02 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Freya McIver', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Ellie Connor', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-02-28 10:04:10', '2022-02-28 18:21:30'),
(1535, '2022/02/28', '11:01 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Jacob Tipping', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick<br>H1<br>Jacob found deleting consonants from initial blends quite tricky, but was able to deduce when he made a mistake</p><p>OPR/WPR<br>w<br>v<br>p<br>x<br>ow<br>th<br>ee<br>sh<br>y<br>u<br>Initially struggled with /y/ and /u/ but got the hang of it after OPR. Confused about direction of /p/ vs /q/. Jacob was a little confused with the direction of /k/, but self-corrected quickly.</p><p>Handwriting focus<br>/b/ &amp; /c/</p><p>Donah 22</p><p>Rule 5, 6, 18</p><ul><li>SD: A-G<br>by<br>have<br>are<br>had<br>over<br>must<br>make<br>street<br>say<br>come</li></ul><p>Today, we dialled back as Jacob had extensive difficulties with Section H last week.</p><p>Inference Key Notes<br>Le', NULL, '2022-02-28 11:01:51', '2022-03-07 10:50:04'),
(1536, '2022/02/28', '11:06 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR: /b/ /a/ /t/</p><ul><li>Stella is still very nervous about /b/ vs /d/ but has increased confidence from last week.</li></ul><p>Donah: 23</p><p>SD:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>at</li><li>bat</li><li>tab</li><li>on</li><li>it</li></ul><p>Stella struggled a lot with spelling this week and most of the lesson was spent dictating and correcting. She does not seem to retain information very well in terms of decoding and letter formation.</p>', NULL, '2022-02-28 11:06:31', '2022-03-07 09:36:49'),
(1537, '2022/02/28', '11:12 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Tyler Van Nimwegen', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Essay Structure', 'See Notes', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><i><strong>Beginning:</strong></i></p><ul><li>Watching cooking show, became inspired and hungry</li><li>Bought noodles and chicken</li><li>Technique: Mention a clock ticking too slowly as a SYMBOLISM of impatience</li><li>Technique: \"I was a hungry whale or hippo\" as a METAPHOR for hunger</li><li>Technique: Mention \"sunny yellow noodles\" as a METAPHOR for happiness</li></ul><p><i><strong>Middle:</strong></i></p><ul><li>Spilled noodles in kitchen</li><li>Felt impatient and angry</li><li>Slipped</li><li>Cleaned</li><li>Took 40 mins until everything was fixed</li><li>Technique: \"I was a flaming bull by the time everything was cleaned up. Forty minutes is a long time.\" as a METAPHOR for anger', NULL, '2022-02-28 11:13:07', '2022-02-28 11:14:20'),
(1538, '2022/02/28', '11:15 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Callen Bartlett', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR: 39-45</p><p>Morphology: Donah 23, “long”</p><p>Rule 7 SFE</p><p>SD: H - law-love</p><p>Callan struggled with “a” in “law” and spelling “call”.</p><ul><li>Inference: Level 1 Set P1 Item 3</li></ul><p>OF: 511&nbsp;</p><ul><li>SC: “waters/water” “conditions”</li><li>Error: “occur”</li></ul><p>Writing: Creative</p><ul><li>Callan was very enthusiastic about storyboarding and wrote a plan without complained. We went through the Writing Process, picked the main plot and wrote planning points. Callan wrote a lot!</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-02-28 11:16:01', '2022-03-07 09:17:01'),
(1539, '2022/02/28', '11:21 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Finnlay Williams', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Essay Structure - Body Paragraphs', 'Compose TEEL paragraphs: topic, evidence, explanation, link/transition', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><i><strong>Dystopian Lit</strong></i></p><ol><li>Warning (Convention &amp; Context)</li><li>Hope (Protagonist &amp; Audience)</li></ol><p><strong>Intro-</strong><br>Write second/last</p><p><strong>Body-</strong><br>Convention</p><ul><li>Scene name:</li><li>Technique:</li><li>How it emphasises convention:</li></ul><p>Context</p><ul><li>Scene name:</li><li>Technique:</li><li>Link to context:</li><li>Audience emotional response:</li></ul><p><strong>Conclusion-</strong><br>Add statement on hope</p>', NULL, '2022-02-28 11:22:27', '2022-02-28 11:28:55'),
(1540, '2022/02/28', '11:29 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>SD</strong></p><ul><li>folks</li><li>everyone</li><li>search</li><li>desire</li><li>fifth</li><li>too/toe/two/to</li><li>they\'re/their/there</li></ul><p><i>The last two parts of S.D were words that Adelaide found very confusing! We went through the differences and introduced some tips and tricks to differentiate. For example, To is 1 but Too is more than one. Toe has an /e/ that looks like a toe with a nail. Two has a /w/ which has 2 corners at the bottom (2 shoes). They\'re = they are, and there has an /r/ that goes over the e. Their has an /i/ that looks like a person!</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>OPR: 16-30</li><li>WPR: c, g, s, e, u, i, a</li><li>Reading: OF 500</li></ol><p>&nbs', NULL, '2022-02-28 11:29:29', '2022-03-02 11:57:43'),
(1541, '2022/02/28', '11:34 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Nina Gust', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick<br>H1<br>For Nina, this took a minute to register for the first word, but was able to successfully complete the rest.</p><p>OPR/WPR<br>a<br>e<br>a<br>g<br>b<br>d<br>c<br>i<br>o<br>s<br>Nina’s handwriting is improving and getting smaller in size.</p><p>Handwriting focus<br>/c/</p><p>Donah 21<br>Nina is exceptional at morphology exercises!</p><p>Rule 5, 6</p><p>SD: A-G<br>good<br>last<br>of<br>out<br>ton<br>Nina continued with some trouble with “good” and “last” – &nbsp;again, god and larst.</p><p>Oral Fluency<br>100<br>Nina continues to improve and has had less errors.</p><p>Writing Program Section<br>Alliteration - /c/ words<br>Notes<br>Nina did so well! She was creative and in', NULL, '2022-02-28 11:34:45', '2022-03-07 12:01:38'),
(1542, '2022/02/28', '3:28 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>phonological awareness: Thomas is aware of individual sounds in words and can segment, count and blend words well.（sheep/cash）</li><li>OPR 1-26 phonograms. Thomas need help with multi sounds phonograms especially u.&nbsp;</li><li>WPR 1-26. Thomas is confused with b and d a bit. His handwriting is not legit, which we will need to focus on. (b,d,g,y).&nbsp;</li><li>rule page one. Consonants.&nbsp;</li><li>readind：the Wiz Kids stage 2 book 1. Thomas needed to sound out some words to be able to read.(Hot, got)</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-02-28 15:28:20', '2022-03-22 09:30:26'),
(1543, '2022/02/28', '3:28 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>public holiday 14 Mar</p>', NULL, '2022-02-28 15:28:21', '2022-03-22 09:35:15'),
(1544, '2022/02/28', '3:35 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Hanna Synnott', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked well with the phonos, gave a good crack at the ones she didn\'t know but on the second pass of them, she was able to get a few right. The ou was difficult for her so didn\'t get that right. WPR was good, she got them all right but was a headache to get her to actually do it. I\'ve realised the way to get her to do work is to just give her an ultimatum with something really hard and boring and something fun and easy, in turn, she thinks she\'s tricking me. finished off by reading the big fat cow goes kapow, seemed to really enjoy it so we continued even after i said it was time to pack up and read the entire thing.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-28 15:35:15', '2022-03-01 09:56:38'),
(1545, '2022/02/28', '3:35 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Elsa Clennett', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: a th ea ck er ear ai ch ew ui ph augh ce</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: a th ea ck er ear ai ch ew ui ph augh ce</td></tr><tr><td>EC all over her phonograms. She picked up the new ones easily.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 4 11 28</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: laughter-notice</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro:NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentences: Oral work with sentence of NM\'s choosing. Dictate', NULL, '2022-02-28 15:35:24', '2022-03-07 16:08:36'),
(1546, '2022/02/28', '3:35 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Charlie Burton', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>o, ch, oo, oa, i</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule Review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>4, 11, 29</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>chosen, chose, choose, coarse, column, correct, current, desirable, desire</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>WRITING:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Recap of rubric planning<br><br>Demo of rubric planning for persuasive essay<br><br>Begin persuasive essay planning in preparation for NAPLAN</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>NOTES:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Charlie did ', NULL, '2022-02-28 15:36:13', '2022-02-28 16:39:35'),
(1547, '2022/02/28', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Zac Pharaoh', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Investigate and calculate percentage discounts of 10%, 25% and 50% on sale items', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Zac and I continued our work on personal finance.&nbsp;</p><p>Today Zac brought his laptop and were working on <i>excel.&nbsp;</i></p><p>I showed Zac how to calculate percentages using excel and how to copy and paste formulas on this program. We did a problem with, how to make budget estimations to calculate future revenue.&nbsp;</p><p>His homework is to create a table in Google sheets and calculate averages using this in Google sheets.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-02-28 16:31:11', '2022-03-06 20:53:11'),
