(1554, '2022/03/01', '7:54 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Tiki Salt', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Got the wordle in 3 goes. Worked well through OPR, through a few older ones in there to see how he goes and a few stumped him. \"ay\" and I threw \"augh\" in there as a challenge. &nbsp;WPR he got stumped on a few, \"ay\" and \"tch\". Dictation was good but he put in \"gn\" instead of \"gu\" and nearly did it twice. Finished off with playing more wordle because there wasn\'t enough time for reading.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-01 07:54:13', '2022-03-01 10:07:27'),
(1556, '2022/03/01', '11:12 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'Study Skills', 'Research', 'See Notes', 'See Notes...', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', NULL, '<p>T1 W4&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Homework – write a paragraph on 8-10 significant events in 1600s world wide.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>X had already started. We discussed using the who/what/where/when/how questions to get started. Encouraged him to research using simpler reference material by adding for students to his key word search terms.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Hi Xave,</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Thanks for bringing your homework today. You managed to get some great information into your paragraphs.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Remember the questions to use to quide you (purple sheet I gave you).</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Who/what?</p><p>When?</p><p>Where?</p><p>Why? or Purpose? or Reason?</p><p>W', NULL, '2022-03-01 11:12:37', '2022-03-06 20:53:57'),
