(1561, '2022/03/02', '2:06 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR: a, c, d, g, o</p><ul><li>Today we started focusing on clockface letters with their first sounds only. Stella still genuinely struggles with /d/ and /g/, so it seems to just be a matter of repetition.</li></ul><p>Handwriting: /d/</p><p>Donah: 24</p><p>Spelling Jumps:</p><ul><li>ad</li><li>dag</li><li>cad</li><li>doc</li><li>gag</li><li>cog</li></ul><p>SD:</p><ul><li>do</li><li>go</li><li>dog</li><li>god</li><li>dad</li></ul><p>Stella struggles majorly with spelling and today was no exception. She was able to confidently create 2-letter words and needed a lot of encouragement and scaffolding.</p><p>OF: 100</p><ul><li>Reading at this stage has proven to be too advanced. Had a discussion', NULL, '2022-03-02 14:06:27', '2022-03-07 09:41:29'),
(1562, '2022/03/02', '2:06 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Tyler Van Nimwegen', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose informative paragraph', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Coaching Lesson</strong></p><p><i><strong>\"Autobiography\"</strong></i><br>Personality qualities:</p><ul><li>Kind<br>Quiet<br>Funny<br>Enthusiastic<br>Easygoing<br>Humble</li></ul><p>Hobbies:</p><ul><li>Foodie<br>Mixing drinks<br>Video games<br>Listening to music<br>Horror movies</li></ul><p><i>Using the Writing Process, Tyler and I planned out his next assignment for an Autobiography sub-topic. We began with decoding the questions, brainstorming, and ended the lesson by composing 2 paragraphs for answering 2 sections. As usual, Tyler found it difficult to talk about himself – however, compared to last year, he has become much more receptive and less self-critical. He has also been', NULL, '2022-03-02 14:07:03', '2022-03-02 14:10:53'),
(1563, '2022/03/02', '2:11 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Callen Bartlett', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR: 39-45</p><ul><li>Callan still has trouble with the 5 “ers”, but is now more confident and recalls them faster!</li></ul><p>Handwriting: Cursive /d/</p><p>Morphology: Donah 24, “send”</p><p>Rule: 4, 26, 7</p><p>Ayres: H, then - one</p><p>Inference: L1 SP1 T1</p><ul><li>Callan did excellently with his inference exercise and listened very carefully without me having to re-read more than twice.</li></ul><p>OF: 500</p><ul><li>Callan\'s fluency has greatly improved from Wk 1.&nbsp;</li><li>SC: “upward”, “produce”</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-03-02 14:11:30', '2022-03-07 09:20:21'),
(1564, '2022/03/02', '2:11 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Finnlay Williams', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose informative paragraph', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Dystopian Literature</strong></p><ul><li>Genre conventions</li><li>Protagonist</li><li>Concept of Hope</li><li>Concept of Warning</li></ul><p><i>Finnlay has a solid understanding of dystopian literary conventions! He is going to be studying the film Gattaca over the next 2 weeks so we prepped and quizzed his knowledge and familiarity of the genre.</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Essays - Introduction and Conclusion</strong></p><p><i><strong>Writing Program</strong></i></p><p><i>Finnlay expressed weakness regarding intros and conclusions, so we explored in depth. We applied his knowledge to the exercises in the Writing Program and he did well!&nbsp;</i></p><p><i>Our sample topic was', NULL, '2022-03-02 14:11:55', '2022-03-02 14:23:36'),
(1565, '2022/03/02', '2:14 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Max Shapiro', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Max did not want to be at tutoring today. George spoke to me on arrival and asked about getting Max an earlier time, possibly with another tutor, so that Max\'s medication hasn\'t worn off yet. She said it\'s about 50/50 as to whether she can get him up the stairs to tutoring. Max was very hesitant to leave George\'s side and followed her around silently for a good while. He was on the verge of tears and kept repeating that he didn\'t want to go into the room. George told him that he had to complete the hour.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>George also mentioned that Max had slept poorly the last two nights. I brought him, George and Luna into the room and tried', NULL, '2022-03-02 14:15:28', '2022-03-02 14:39:18'),
(1566, '2022/03/02', '2:15 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 36-52</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: au ai oy ir aw ear ea ew&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 19 29 6&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: chance-contains</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SM took a long time today. We finished at about 4:15. Sophie was working hard, but she got very muddled very often. We sounded out and modelled the words on my fing', NULL, '2022-03-02 14:16:27', '2022-03-02 14:40:48'),
(1567, '2022/03/02', '2:17 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Shay Douglas', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Factorise algebraic expressions by taking out a common algebraic factor', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Year 10 Maths</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Consolidate understanding needed for SD\'s maths class on Thursday.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Various exercises from the Cambridge maths textbook.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Review distributive law -- SD had completely forgotten how to apply the distributive law and needed prompting. Various expansion/factorisation problems around this theme.</td></tr><tr><td>We had a small hiccup due to the internet being down across Tasmania. SD couldn\'t access his online learning resources, so we used one of ET\'s textbooks. This was difficult as SD did not know exactly what he w', NULL, '2022-03-02 14:17:45', '2022-03-02 14:42:50'),
(1568, '2022/03/02', '3:20 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'BODMAS', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'To Be Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we kept working on BODMAS.&nbsp;<br>Connor hasn\'t grasped this mathematical method; when we do 2 or three operations he\'s able to solve the problems correctly. However, if we increase to 5 or 6 operations at the same time, he struggles with this. And the same happens if we use integers. Doing easy to average problems the student is able to do them almost without a problem. Even though, I consider Connor is capable of solving at least above average problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-02 15:20:41', '2022-03-03 10:01:07'),
(1569, '2022/03/02', '3:26 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>phonological awareness: modeling the work Cash for segment, count and blend sounds, coach the word Sheep.&nbsp;</li><li>introduced to phonograms. Multi sound phonograms and multi letter phonograms.&nbsp;</li><li>OPR 1-26</li><li>WPR form clock face letters</li><li>SD: me</li><li>oral sentence using the word me.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>It was easier to manage Phoebe on zoom. she was quit focused and could preciesly say individula sounds. She needed help with multi sound phonograms such as a, e, i, o, u, x, s, c, qu, y.</p>', NULL, '2022-03-02 15:27:08', '2022-03-02 15:37:22'),
(1570, '2022/03/02', '3:28 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Lilly Oettle', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Adjectives (describe nouns) + Adverbs (describe verbs and some adjectives)', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR vowels + ea ou ow er ir ur wor ear ti si ci ey ew ui&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>WPR ey ew ui&nbsp; er ir ur wor ear ti ci si ow ou ea</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD they key money threw new fruit juice were thirst purse world earth station spacious mission</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Parts of Speech</p><p>Verbs</p><p>Nouns/pronouns</p><p>Adjectives</p><p>Adverbs</p><p>Use spelling words to add to POS sheets.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Writing Process</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Sentence Structure - Simple sentences elements using blocks</li><li>Sentence Types - Fact/command/question/emotion NW</li><li>Compound sentence structure using FANBOYS.</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-02 15:28:19', '2022-03-06 20:51:02'),
(1571, '2022/03/02', '3:28 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick E3 F1</td></tr><tr><td>MB very okay with E3, 100% accuracy. F1 he had 80% accuracy.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-44</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ar ch ou ow ay ai er&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>5 sounds of er game</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 4/markings review. MB very fidgety and hard to keep on task. Although he said he didn\'t remember these rules and seemed resistant to SD, once I got him started he was okay.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: me-it</td></', NULL, '2022-03-02 15:28:56', '2022-03-02 17:04:51'),
(1572, '2022/03/02', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 30', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Following up on our work from last week, Jacob and I moved today to solve multiplications involving the 7,8 and 9 times tables.&nbsp;</p><p>Also did a review on the 3, 5 and 6 times tables.&nbsp;</p><p>Jacob did a good job, he was able to count in groups forward and was able to regroup. However, when he had to count backwards, this was difficult for him.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-02 16:31:33', '2022-03-06 21:15:32'),
(1573, '2022/03/02', '4:32 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick<br>H1</p><p>OPR/WPR</p><ul><li>oo</li><li>ou</li><li>ch</li><li>ar</li><li>oi</li><li>oy</li><li>ai</li><li>ay</li></ul><p><br>Was a bit confused with /oo/ and /ou/ continues to be complicated.</p><p>Handwriting focus<br>Cursive /c/</p><p>Donah 23 \"lay\"</p><p>Rule 18</p><p>SD: H</p><p>men<br>man<br>for<br>ran<br>run<br>was<br>that<br>his<br>led<br>lay</p><p>Oral Fluency<br>500<br>Excellent! No errors.<br>Inference L1 SP1 I 1-4<br>Wobbly on I1 but rest was perfect</p><p>Writing Program Section<br>Creative<br>Planning! Adelaide is so creative with imagination and we addressed fantasy conventions this week.</p>', NULL, '2022-03-02 16:32:06', '2022-03-16 15:13:33'),
(1574, '2022/03/02', '4:32 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 52-70 shuffled</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 52-70</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 4 6 14 2 17</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: salary-secure</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Have Angus explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ayres words in sentences.</td></tr><tr><td>Writing Process: Gave Angus choice of 3 activities. He chose to continue with the Viking source work. Went through and IDd main ideas for all sections and had Angus make note of main', NULL, '2022-03-02 16:32:50', '2022-03-02 17:31:49'),
(1575, '2022/03/02', '5:32 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Vincenzo Vella', 'Mathematics', 'Percentages', 'Connection between percentages, fractions and divisions', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Vinnie and I continued working on his very long math assignment.&nbsp;</p><p>I had to ask Vinnie to focus on his work. He was making silly mistakes today. Vinnie wasn\'t applying the mathematical concepts, he was trying to do everything by memory and heavily relying on the calculator.&nbsp;</p><p>I showed him the “rule of three” process, this is a short way to do a cross-multiplication with ratios. Apparently, this worked and Vinnie was able to solve the problems accurately.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-02 17:32:11', '2022-03-03 10:06:45'),
(1576, '2022/03/03', '7:50 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Chester Vincent', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Not much change from last week, showed improvement over the vowels. Did well in dictation, only a few letters in the wrong place, went over\'bed\' again because last time got them reversed. Did some reading to finish off a book.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-03 07:50:41', '2022-03-16 09:04:10'),
(1577, '2022/03/03', '8:54 a.m.', '1', '2', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Decimals', 'Operations with decimals', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'Followup', '<p>We were working on science, we did the <i>Electro potato.&nbsp;</i></p><p>With this simple experiment, Nate and I were working on regrouping decimals and how to make long additions and subtractions with these.&nbsp;</p><p>El trabajo de Nate fue increible!&nbsp;</p><p>The student was totally engaged and enjoyed the lesson a lot, he made a great comment; <i>Neve and I are very good people and tutors, I like being here with you two. &nbsp;</i></p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 08:54:44', '2022-03-06 20:23:02'),
(1578, '2022/03/03', '8:57 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose third-person narrative paragraph', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 08:58:26', '2022-03-03 08:59:18'),
(1579, '2022/03/03', '9:48 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Jett Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Solve 1 to 2 steps equations', 'Textbooks, problems on the board, made up problems', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Jett brought school work, it was all about solving linear equations with 3 to 4 steps and 2 worded problems at the end.&nbsp;</p><p>The student was able to solve quickly and correctly foundation to average problems. With the problem above and well above average he made a couple of mistakes which I let him know and worked on those. Regarding the worded problems, Jett had some difficulties. He wasn\'t able to create the equation to solve the problem.&nbsp;</p><p>We will be working on this during the rest of the term. Mr Sam Young, Jett\'s maths\' teacher recommended working on this more. And also mentioned in the email that around the year a significant part of the work to do in the classroom ', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 09:49:48', '2022-03-06 21:05:48'),
(1580, '2022/03/03', '9:49 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'BODMAS', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Ava and I were working on BODMAS using integers and did a little bit of algebra at the end of the lesson.&nbsp;</p><p>She can easily do foundation to average problems, and sometimes above and well above average problems. However, sometimes she seems to be having difficulties with standard problems. Ava goes straight to solve what seems more complicated on the problem and forgets the hierarchy of the operations.&nbsp;</p><p>At the end of the lessons, we did a little work on formulas. For example if a= 1 b=-2 and c= ½ find the value of 3b-2c and so on. I also explained to Ava the difference between X^3 and 3X.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 09:52:07', '2022-03-06 20:59:51'),
(1581, '2022/03/03', '9:52 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Solve 1 to 2 steps equations', 'Textbooks, problems on the board, made up problems', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>As Isaac still having some difficulties with equations, today we were working very hard on this.</p><p>I solved one equation on the board and labelled every single term, constants and variables. After doing this, Isaac could see more clearly how to eliminate the terms from one side of the equation and find the value of the variable.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 09:53:10', '2022-03-06 21:10:53'),
(1583, '2022/03/03', '10:42 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'Trigonometry', 'SOH CAH TOA', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>We were looking at how to use SOH CAH TOA to solve problems related to plumbing.</p><p>Fin had forgotten how to solve this kind of problem. However, after a quick review, he started to do a great job.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 10:43:39', '2022-03-26 10:45:23'),
(1584, '2022/03/03', '10:47 a.m.', '1', '1', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Investigate and calculate percentage discounts of 10%, 25% and 50% on sale items', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Work done:</p><ol><li>Simple interest.</li><li>Linear equations with 3 to 4 steps.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>Nicholas mentioned that today he was working on simple interests at school. Therefore, &nbsp;we were working on this formula today. We started by checking on finding the percentage of a quantity. After this, we moved to use the formula to calculate simple interest. While we were working on simple interest, I found that Nicholas forgot how to solve an equation. Because of that, we moved to work on equations.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 10:48:20', '2022-03-03 10:56:58'),
(1585, '2022/03/03', '10:48 a.m.', '1', '2', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Solve 1 to 2 steps equations', 'Textbooks, problems on the board, made up problems', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we continued working on equations.&nbsp;</p><p>I explained to Nicholas how in year 9 most of the topics are related to equations.</p><p>Nicholas is able to solve 1 to 2 steps equations without much trouble. However, when we moved to 5+ steps equations, Nicholas has some hesitations which we need to work on.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 10:49:17', '2022-03-06 18:01:32'),
(1586, '2022/03/03', '10:49 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Compare, order, add and subtract integers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 10:50:08', '2022-03-06 11:49:58'),
(1587, '2022/03/03', '3:27 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick: H1</p><p>Handwriting: Cursive /c/, /d/</p><p>Morphology: Donah 24, 25, “pair”</p><p>Ayres: P, flight - entrance</p><p>Inference: L1 S1 I 3&amp;4</p><p>Writing: Text Types - Narrative</p><ul><li>Foreshadowing</li><li>Plot progression</li><li>Narrative structure</li><li>Reuben engaged enthusiastically in a discussion regarding the meaning of a “hook” in the Beginning section of a narrative</li><li>Emotional reaction: Audience</li><li>Intertextuality: Chakras</li></ul><p>Reuben was very lively and involved regarding narrative and analysis today! He was able to tackle the complexity of the literary areas listed above. However, writing long texts still seems to be a difficult task,', NULL, '2022-03-03 15:27:03', '2022-03-07 10:01:52');
INSERT INTO `attens` (`id`, `date_created`, `time`, `term`, `lesson`, `student_name`, `subject_name`, `concept_name`, `conceptDetail`, `learningActivity`, `tutor_name`, `tutor_evaluation`, `student_self`, `student_attendance`, `homework_completed`, `weekly_lesson`, `homework_assignment`, `email_school`, `comment`, `commentPrivate`, `notesAttendance`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1589, '2022/03/03', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Seth Vanderlaan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 15:30:50', '2022-03-03 15:30:50'),
(1590, '2022/03/03', '3:31 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>As I could notice that Sofia keeps doing additions and subtractions from left to right, today we were working on this. Sofia and I spent a good part of the lesson on the board, after solving many problems, Sofia was able to perform the operations correctly. Sometimes she gets confused with borrowing; she forgets to change the 10\' 100\'s column number.&nbsp;</p><p>After this, we were working on the times\' tables, 5, 6 and 7. She didn\'t like it and was disengaged with this. Sofia many times said, “ I hate maths”.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 15:31:31', '2022-03-26 11:10:51'),
(1591, '2022/03/03', '3:39 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Reading - Literary Appreciation & Quality Literature', 'Identify elements in fine (imaginative) literature - metaphors, similies & personification', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>W3/4</p><p>Similes – definitions</p><p>Practice generating some</p><p>Identifying common ones</p><p>Use in appropriate contexts.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing prompts used to stimulate narrative writing task – must utilise descriptive language and similes</p>', NULL, '2022-03-03 15:39:43', '2022-03-06 21:04:15'),
(1592, '2022/03/03', '3:42 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Naomi Wright', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 15:42:56', '2022-03-03 15:42:56'),
(1593, '2022/03/03', '3:42 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematical Assessment', 'Key Maths', 'Applied Problem Solving', 'Interpret given problems and apply computation skills and conceptual knowledge to produce a solution.', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', '<p>Lucy completed the final few Applied Problem Solving tasks in the Key Maths assessment today. &nbsp;Results of the assessment should be ready for next lesson.</p><p>A full game of Numero was played in which Lucy began generating multi-layered equations using random wild cards. &nbsp;Lucy has not had the confidence to approach this independently in the past. &nbsp;Little to no prompting was required. &nbsp;</p><p>Whilst Lucy found it difficult to recall the terms proper and improper fractions and mixed numbers, she was able to complete conversions quickly after a review. &nbsp;Additionally, she was able to apply the newly learned process of simplifying fractions independently and confident', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 15:42:57', '2022-03-03 17:48:26'),
(1594, '2022/03/03', '4:28 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Chelsea Cooper', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Four</td></tr><tr><td>Tuesday, 1 March 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick F1</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #5</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Challenge word: coming (intro rule 11)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: th aw ey wor ou sh ear ng ur ea au or ck wh</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Struggled with au/aw/or/wor, as well as ey, ck cue and hesitation with ear. Think CC may have found it difficult having so many phonograms.</td></tr></tbod', NULL, '2022-03-03 16:43:33', '2022-03-03 17:39:45'),
(1595, '2022/03/03', '4:50 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Connect the compound interest formula to repeated applications of simple interest', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Callisto has missed 2 Maths lessons this week due to illness and will miss another tomorrow because of an appointment. Her teacher provided her with the information that Inflation and Depreciation were the topics that were covered in her absence. We went over the information from the teacher PowerPoint to introduce these topics and then Callisto worked on the examples from the textbook that were listed on the class checklist.</p>', '<p>Callisto has missed 2 Maths lessons this week due to illness and will miss another tomorrow because of an appointment. Her teacher provided her with the information that Inflation and Depreciation were the topics that were covered in her absence. We went over the information from the teacher PowerPoint to introduce these topics and then Callisto worked on the examples from the textbook that were listed on the class checklist. I have emailed a copy of the teacher PowerPoint to Callisto and her dad so that she can use this resource to help with the catch up process</p>', NULL, '2022-03-03 16:50:33', '2022-03-10 18:11:22'),
(1596, '2022/03/03', '5:01 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'Ratios', 'Using Ratios to Find Amounts', 'Textbooks, practice papers, school work', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Finlay was 25 min late today.</p><p>We were working on Displacement, Velocity and Time. How to use these ratios on plumbing-related problems.&nbsp;</p><p>Finlay enjoyed the lesson and said that last year it was explained in a complicated way but the way I did it, it was much simpler. The student was able to solve problems related to those ratios.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-03 17:01:50', '2022-03-06 18:29:12'),
(1597, '2022/03/03', '5:33 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Extend and apply the index laws to variables, using positive integer indices and the zero index', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', '<p>Nicholas and I continued our work on inequalities.&nbsp;</p><p>He understands how this process works and can partially solve the inequation. He correctly uses the process to solve an equation for inequalities.&nbsp;</p><p>We need to keep working on how to present the answer to inequality as a family/group and not as a single number. Moreover, we need to work on how negative signs can alter the orientation of inequality when multiplying or dividing by it.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><p>During the last 25 minutes, we were doing some school work. We worked on the surface area of pyramids and cones. Hi knows very well how to create the net of a volumetric shape, but sometimes mixes the measurements up', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-03 17:33:40', '2022-03-06 11:48:18'),
(1598, '2022/03/03', '5:39 p.m.', '1', '4', 'James Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Ellie Connor', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Four - Catch Up</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 21 March 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick F1 (multisyllabic)</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #8</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: ng a gu or ph aw ck oe ey au</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Challenge word: running (r.9)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 9</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: stopping, stop, walk, talk, chalk, grant</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><t', NULL, '2022-03-03 17:40:19', '2022-03-21 08:42:14'),
(1599, '2022/03/04', '7:46 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Archie Lester', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<ol><li>OPR – or, ew, ui, ck, ie, dge, ti, au, aw, igh, wor, ed, qu, c, a, e, g, ur, ea</li><li>WPR – or, ck, dge, au, aw, wor, ed, qu, c, a, g, ea</li><li>Spelling notebook: u-e word list: ute, mute, cube, June, tune</li><li>Discuss /u/ saying /U/. &nbsp;Archie sounds /U/ words as /y/ &nbsp;/oo/. &nbsp;Looked at ‘yoo’ and ‘you’ and ‘yoot’ and explained that the /U/ sound is made of two consecutive sounds /y/ /oo/ just as Archie pronounces them, however, they are represented by one symbol.</li><li>Read for spelling and read for reading analysed words.</li><li>Spelling notebook:&nbsp; add folk to Rule 19 list. &nbsp;Sentence given for context and definition - The folk from the residential hom', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-04 07:46:58', '2022-03-04 13:32:29'),
