(1603, '2022/03/04', '8:26 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Measurement', 'Compare 12- and 24-hour time systems and convert between them', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luca and I started with a multiplication challenge today, where Luca was timed completing a tables grid. He had 8 minutes to complete it, and did so with ease. Next week we will pull the time back again.<br><br>Luca was struggling to grasp that 00:00 was midnight, as he often assumed that this was 12pm (rather than 12 am). We looked at it again, and agreed it was very confusing. We drew out a map of the hours in each day, and saw that 00:00 was when no hours and no minutes had passed. Luca seemed to understand this after our chat, and was able to convert from analogue to digital and 24hr time with ease.<br><br>Luca also enjoyed beating me at a game', NULL, '2022-03-04 08:35:31', '2022-03-04 08:53:37'),
(1604, '2022/03/04', '8:53 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Joshua Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><i>LESSON CONDUCTED BY JUNO GALANG ON BEHALF OF HEATHER WHO WAS IN QUARANTINE</i></p><p><strong>NOTES (JG):</strong></p><h2>Science of Persuasion:</h2><p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cFdCzN7RYbw\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cFdCzN7RYbw</a></p><p>We opened the lesson with a discussion on how Josh identifies “persuasive writing” and “persuasion” in general, including specific ways to utilize persuasion. Josh’s thoughts included:</p><p>- Emotive</p><p>- Personal&nbsp; - depends on topic - group based/target audience</p><p>- Using words to foster trust – including evidence</p><p>We then briefly went through how the PEEL structure is reflective of persuasion when it comes to es', NULL, '2022-03-04 09:19:21', '2022-03-04 09:24:59'),
(1605, '2022/03/04', '9:19 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>LESSON CONDUCTED BY JUNO GALANG AND HEATHER WAS IN QUARANTINE</p><p>OPR/WPR:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>th, e, o, ee, u, ai, ng</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule Review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>9, 17</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>these, those, club, seen, see, felt, full, fail, setting, set,&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>WRITING:</p><ul><li>adjective activities to encourage Luke to begin using adjectives in sentences</li></ul><p>NOTES:</p><p>Luke was very enthusiastic regarding phonograms and spelling! He stumbled a little through the following phonogra', NULL, '2022-03-04 09:20:01', '2022-03-04 09:32:11'),
