(1607, '2022/03/04', '3:27 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Adjectives - describe nouns and some adjectives', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Gave Nate a rhyming challenge. Read from The Cat on the Mat is Flat and discussed. Brainstormed rhyming words on the whiteboard. NM modelled creation of rhyme.</td></tr><tr><td>NM and NB created a story together, with NM coaching and NB suppyling the rhyme. When I changed this to a more scaffolded approach, NB immediately abandoned the rhyming structure.</td></tr><tr><td>Repeated the actiivty on paper, composing first draft of the short rhyme.</td></tr><tr><td>Composed second \'good\' copy. Fix spelling errors and missed words.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Adjective work sheet -- using adjective to show mood. Gloomy vs vibrant worksheet, discuss the effect', NULL, '2022-03-04 15:27:23', '2022-03-04 18:26:43'),
(1608, '2022/03/04', '3:34 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Connor Thompson', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Essay Structure', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Connor came to class with his essay from last week. He had completed a first draft! Connor requested that we revise, edit and \'highlight\' his primary and secondary sources. He didn\'t have any primary sources but his source for information on the inventions of the 1920s counted as a secondary source.</td></tr><tr><td>Connor and I attempted to work through the revising steps of the Writing Process. This was quite difficult due to Connor\'s ability level. I would give him an instruction, e.g. We are going to check sentence structure:,\" but it was a struggle to revise these sentences because Connor couldn\'t identify when a sentence had incorret structur', NULL, '2022-03-04 15:34:09', '2022-03-04 18:16:09'),
(1609, '2022/03/04', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'BODMAS', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>We were aiming to master BODMAS.</p><p>Archie and I were solving multiple problems with BODMAS and integers, from foundation to well above average problems. He was able to solve all of them; however, sometimes I helped him with the sign law.&nbsp;</p><p>We started to work on finding the formula for instance; numbers in 1, 2, 3, 4 and the output 5, 7, 11 formula Yx3 + 2. We will be working on this next week.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-04 16:31:09', '2022-03-06 20:12:43'),
