(1617, '2022/03/06', '8:28 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Develop confidence with number sequences to and from 100 by ones from any starting point.', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', '<p>During our first lesson, Nate and I were working on place value.&nbsp;</p><p>Nate was very excited about having maths tutoring.&nbsp;</p><p>He said that sometimes he feels he\'s not good with maths because he takes too long to solve problems and also mentioned that divisions are hard for him.&nbsp;</p><p>Before we work deep on Nate\'s suggestions, I want to work with numbers and place values. This will be not only with whole numbers but also with decimals.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-06 20:29:40', '2022-03-06 20:35:45'),
(1618, '2022/03/06', '8:30 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Banjo Mills', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 31 > 45', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>T1W4 –&nbsp;</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>PA&nbsp;</strong>DK D2 1 &nbsp;syllable deletion of a non-compound word.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>OPR&nbsp;</strong>a e I o u y + c b d s g qu f + th sh ee ow ou ch ar</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>WPR&nbsp;</strong>clockface focus&nbsp;ch ar ow ou th sh ee qu a e I o u y</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>H/W&nbsp;</strong>2 oclock. Placed clock on table focus on e</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Rule Review</strong></p><ul><li>Review of vowels v consonants. Practise sorting individual letters/red counters on vowel sounds of cvc words.</li><li>Review of 1st/2nd /3rd sounds.&nbsp;</li><li>Rule 4 review using counters and flashcards</li></ul', NULL, '2022-03-06 20:31:39', '2022-03-06 20:33:30'),
(1619, '2022/03/06', '8:35 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Andrew Allan', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'Not Returned', 'Cancelled', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Andrew absent due to isolating.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-06 20:36:35', '2022-03-06 20:37:16'),
(1620, '2022/03/06', '8:36 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Harlow Booy', 'Mathematical Assessment', 'SENA 1', 'SENA 1', 'SENA 1', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Harlow recognises very well the concept of number and applies this when she is required to do so.&nbsp;</p><p>Her mental computation is within the average range, she uses addition and subtraction as reciprocals. However, for multiplication and division, she required more input to solve the problems during the test.&nbsp;</p><p>Harlow and I will start our work with place value, later will do adding and subtraction strategies and counting in groups, and at the end of the term, we will move to modelling with word problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-06 20:40:20', '2022-03-06 20:42:51'),
(1621, '2022/03/06', '8:40 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Harlow Booy', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Count collections to 100 by partitioning numbers using place value.', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', '<p>Harlow and I were working in place value.</p><p>We mostly used Syllabus 2A to consolidate Harlow\'s knowledge in this area. Harlow did a great job, she mentioned that doing maths only with me was much better than school. Apparently, at school Harlow finds it quite hard to concentrate.&nbsp;</p><p>We did place value from ones to tens of thousands and also were looking at <i>what happens if we have 10\'s 10\'s; and 10\'s hundreds.&nbsp;</i></p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-06 20:41:13', '2022-03-06 20:48:11'),
(1623, '2022/03/06', '9:07 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Sentence Construction & Vocabulary', 'Elements of a complex sentence > Capital letter, one independent clause, one dependent clause containing a subordinate conjunction, ending punctuation', 'Recognise/Analyse/Model/Compose compound sentences that include subject nouns/pronouns and subordinating conjunctions if, after, when, than, unless, because, however', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T1W4&nbsp;</p><p>OPR a e I o u y ow ou ough ea ew ui ay ay oi oy or au aw ti si ci&nbsp;</p><p>WPR – oi oy ay ai or aw au ew ui&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD –painted away toy boils order author jaw fewer suitcase&nbsp;</p><p>Identify Parts of Speech</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The Writing Process</p><ol><li>Sentence Structure - Simple sentences elements&nbsp; + compound. Use HW sentences to make compound sentences.&nbsp;</li><li>Sentence Types - Fact/command/question/emotion</li></ol><p>Sentence structure simple (Blocks ) and Compound + intro to complex.&nbsp;</p><p>Using task cards.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Homework –&nbsp;</p><p>Task card 20 complex sentences plus sentences from spelling wo', NULL, '2022-03-06 21:07:50', '2022-03-06 21:09:20'),
(1624, '2022/03/06', '9:15 p.m.', '1', '4', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Investigate number sequences involving multiples of 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, and 9', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', '<p>On our 4th lesson of the term, we did an online lesson as James and Fiona were in Canberra :D&nbsp;</p><p>Despite I had planned to work on Factors, operations with decimals and introduce solving for the unknown, we only could work on factors. However, the work done was very important and significant. James showed a great ability to count and regroup. At the end of the lesson, I suggested to James, if he wouldn\'t complain as much as he does, probably he would have fewer problems with maths. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-06 21:17:38', '2022-03-06 21:23:16'),
(1625, '2022/03/07', '1:39 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Lottie Young', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Read words aloud - accurately, automatically, with expression (connected text)', 'Text of Choice (see notes)', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Lottie and I had a focused discussion on the benefits (as proven by scientific research) of handwriting and the impact this process has on many integral learning functions such as supporting the storage and retrieval of information in the memory, connecting speech sounds with their written symbol, reading, writing and spelling. &nbsp;A piece of Graham and Gentry research was shared as was the Ed360 podcast with the Reading League (sent to Mo after the lesson).</p><p>Began a new Billie B Brown book - The Birthday Mix-Up. &nbsp;Lottie is increasingly fluent, however, a number prompts and reminders needed to check mispronunciations. &nbsp;Lottie is guessing unfamiliar words, but she is able ', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-07 01:39:59', '2022-03-07 01:52:46'),
