(1634, '2022/03/07', '2:45 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We started the lesson a bit late as the parents have not arranged for zoom meeting. Their camera had problem so I could not see Mia, which made it hard for Mia to concentrate.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Phonological awareness-Kilpattrick level E-Mia could precisely delete sounds.&nbsp;</li><li>Challenge word-bread. Mia needed help for segmenting sounds in this word, she could not recognize r and ea.&nbsp;</li><li>OPR-1-20. She picked up quite quick for this. She needed reminds for vowels a, e, i, o, u</li><li>WPR-1-20.</li></ol><p>We did not have time for other parts and I could not really see her written phonograms.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-07 14:49:05', '2022-03-22 09:24:19'),
