(1636, '2022/03/07', '2:05 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Jacob Tipping', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick H1<br>Jacob is incredibly good at deleting first sounds from initial consonant blends! He has had no difficulty in completing this task.</p><p>OPR/WPR<br>1. th<br>2. u<br>3. ow<br>4. ou<br>5. er<br>6. ir<br>7. ur<br>8. wor<br>9. ear<br>10. ee<br>Notes<br>Jacob needed plenty of scaffolding for the 5 sounds of “er”, but stayed positive throughout!</p><p>Donah no. 25<br><br>Rule Outline<br>8, marking in brackets</p><p>Ayres Section A-G&nbsp;<br>Jacob did an excellent job, no errors!<br>big<br>bag<br>beg<br>bog<br>bug<br>moth er<br>three<br>land<br>cold<br>hot</p><p>Inference Key Notes<br>Level 1 Set p1 Item 5<br>Great job, no errors!</p><p>Oral Fluency 514<br>Jacob wanted to finis', NULL, '2022-03-07 15:43:26', '2022-03-07 16:39:04'),
