(1658, '2022/03/08', '3:56 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Banjo Mills', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'Not Returned', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Banjo refused to get out of the car today. It has been a constant battle for his Mum each week. B has been great when in his lessons - engaged and participates fully but has been very tired on occasion. He has a full schedule of soccer, swimming and an active outdoor life. Mum stated that Banjo has also been refusing school. She wishes to explore cancelling the term.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-08 15:56:44', '2022-03-08 15:59:30'),
(1659, '2022/03/08', '4:26 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Lachlan Prior', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked well all lesson, smashed through the hponos and did well with ht e ones he didn’t really know. Spent most of the rest of the lesson on the writing process and the draft. Seems to be doing well but am struggling to get much imagination and adjectives out of him. left the next few pages of drafts for homework.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-08 16:26:41', '2022-03-16 08:59:42'),
(1660, '2022/03/08', '4:29 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Shay Douglas', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Essay Structure', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Science</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Shay\'s Assessment due on 10 Mar (2 days from now)</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Independent research/study</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Shay asked if he could have some independent study time today to work on his science assignment. He had to create a science report around an experiment they completed in task.</td></tr><tr><td>Shay had already completed most of the assignment, but had the reflection and another section to complete. Given that I\'ve spoken to Meg and she\'s expressed that she\'s happy for Shay to decide how his lessons can best support him, I was happy to give Sh', NULL, '2022-03-08 16:29:59', '2022-03-08 17:26:30'),
(1661, '2022/03/08', '4:30 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 50', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luca and I strarted out our lesson by completing some multiplication drills. Luca can complete his 12x12 grid in just under 7 min, so we randomised the numbers and tried once again. It seems he is remembering his tables by patterns rather than individually, as it took him 10 min 3 sec to complete this with randomised numbers.&nbsp;<br><br>I then gave Luca the task to arrange numbers in ascending order. I gave Luca this task using a mixture of numbers (whole, decimal and fractions). Luca completed this well, but struggled with converting his fractions to decimals in most instances. We refreshed this a number of times, and Luca eventually understood ', NULL, '2022-03-08 16:30:38', '2022-03-08 17:41:07'),
(1662, '2022/03/08', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Simplify algebraic expressions involving the four operations', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today, we worked on number and algebra, we covered:</p><ul><li>Identifying equivalent expressions.</li><li>Operations with algebraic expressions.</li><li>Simplifying alike terms.</li><li>Index law, multiplication, division and power of the power.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Textbook: Essential Mathematics 7 page 266 (all of it)&nbsp;</p><p>Overall, the student did a great job. She has no difficulties making single operations with algebraic expressions. We need to keep working on long expressions, particularly on those involving BODMAS and the sign law.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-08 16:31:03', '2022-07-02 08:51:57'),
(1663, '2022/03/08', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Nouns - name people, places, things, ideas', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>Phonological awareness: Kill pattrick F1</li><li>Challenge word comfort</li><li>OPR/WPR: a, e, i, o, u, c,s,z,k,x,g,j, qu. Callum needs lots of help with phonograms u, e, i, o, y, c, s, z, x, qu, g. &nbsp;</li><li>New phonograms introduction sh,ee,th,ow,ou</li><li>SD rule page 1. We have done consonants and rule 1-3.&nbsp;</li><li>homework: ORF and rule 2 and rule 3 activity.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>I need to talk to Callum about what his needs are for school. MAybe academic coaching?</p>', NULL, '2022-03-08 16:31:48', '2022-03-22 09:20:54'),
(1664, '2022/03/08', '4:36 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 8: There are five ways to write the /er/ sound - Her first nurse works early.', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>T1W5</strong></p><p><strong>PA DK D2 syllable deletion</strong></p><p><strong>Syllabification:&nbsp;</strong><i>wizard dinosaur Madagascar</i> – Clap/stamp/counter in cup/fingers</p><p><strong>Rhyme:</strong> Andrew to generate rhyme for <i>look kick back</i> – finds this difficult still.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>OPR</strong><br>a e I o u y er ir ur wor ear ed ea&nbsp; wh&nbsp;wr&nbsp; oa oe&nbsp; aw au ew ui&nbsp;ar j dge ck ch&nbsp; ey kn&nbsp;</p><p><br><strong>WPR</strong>kn dge j ck ch&nbsp; ey ea er ir ur wor ear&nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>HW&nbsp;</strong>focus line letters start at top.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Rule Review</strong></p><p>Rule 8- 5 sounds of', NULL, '2022-03-08 16:36:26', '2022-03-08 17:44:42'),
(1665, '2022/03/08', '3:53 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics & Morphology - The Vocabulary of Word Structure', 'Morphemes - Words consist of distinct parts each of which have their own meaning > base words/word roots + affixes - prefixes/suffixes', 'Improving Morphemic Awareness > Oral (Sandra Donah)', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>OPR</strong><br>1. a<br>2. c<br>3. d<br>4. g<br>5. o<br>Notes<br>Stella’s /a/ formation has greatly improved! However, she is very resistant to writing.</p><p><strong>WPR</strong><br>Notes<br>Handwriting - /a/ We focused on formation, especially lowercase.</p><p><strong>Donah no. 25&nbsp;</strong><br>Notes<br>Stella definitely improved in concentration today compared to last week! However, she seems to be easily discouraged whenever she makes a mistake and needs a lot of encouraged.</p><p><i>Stella continues to struggle with /g/ and /d/, however since our focus has been on /a/ for the last two weeks, she is exhibiting higher levels of confidence when recognising and forming. Her a', NULL, '2022-03-08 16:44:17', '2022-03-08 16:46:15'),
(1666, '2022/03/08', '4:47 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Tyler Van Nimwegen', 'Study Skills', 'Research', 'See Notes', 'See Notes...', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Coaching</p><p>Work Studies</p><p>Tyler requested help today with his Work Studies assignment.&nbsp;</p><p>We examined several job careers and Tyler was encouraged to ask questions about careers he was unsure of. We then defined and summarised the different careers and compared them with his Autobiography planning, categorising careers and juxtaposing with what he considered his strengths and weaknessses. We also worked on his typing skills, as he had bought his laptop. His improved reading skills helped him to recognise longer words such as “technician”, “developer” and “manager”.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-08 16:48:18', '2022-03-08 17:33:36'),
(1667, '2022/03/08', '5:34 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Inequalities', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>We focused today on Inequalities.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>What is an inequality.</li><li>Difference with equations.</li><li>Methods to solve an inequality.</li><li>Practice problems.</li></ul><p>Textbook: Essential Mathematics 10 pages 21 and 22. Homework on page 22.&nbsp;</p><p>Isaac did a great job today. We found that labelling each expression from the begging helps a lot. The student was able to solve moderate to complex problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-08 17:34:12', '2022-03-15 11:50:20'),
(1668, '2022/03/08', '5:34 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Callen Bartlett', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Coaching<br>Callan came for homework help today with reading and language. We completed two tasks.</p><p>Reading:<br>Create an artwork of the setting of a book you are reading.</p><p>To make this activity more productive, we focused on a Narrative Text Type, specifically narrative text structure. A discussion regarding plot, characters and genre of the book Arkanae was carried out before the drawing.</p><p>Language: Draw a Venn diagram to compare when it is appropriate to use formal language and when it is acceptable to use information language. Include both spoken and written examples.</p><p>Callan struggled with spelling \"formal\", \"church\", \"political\", \"tutor\" and \"bully\", which we add', NULL, '2022-03-08 17:35:04', '2022-03-21 09:22:40'),
(1669, '2022/03/08', '5:36 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Finnlay Williams', 'English', 'English Literature', 'Film Study', 'See Notes', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Powerpoint - Dystopian Lit<br>Children of Men</p><p>Finnlay and I worked together on his class assignment today. We explored the following areas and wrote 1 paragraph each:</p><p>Dystopian Conventions<br>Identify 3 significant dystopian convenions within the story, describe how these are represented</p><p>Representations of a theme<br>Finnlay was able to complete this task using general statements, however we explored how to elaborate and fill out his paragraph using examples from the text, and specific explanations on how to link his examples to dystopian themes.</p><p>Technique: Symbolism<br>After the first task, Finnlay understood that elaboration was key, and successfully applied exam', NULL, '2022-03-08 17:50:29', '2022-03-08 18:46:59'),
(1670, '2022/03/08', '5:50 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Luke Vandenberg', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick H1<br>Notes<br>Luke is really excellent with this task! He has no problem distinguishing between consonant blends.</p><p>OPR<br>1. aw<br>2. au<br>3. ph<br>4. ck<br>5. ed<br>Notes<br>Perfect!</p><p>WPR<br>Notes<br>Luke hesitated on /ck/ but eventually got it correct – otherwise, all was perfect.<br>We also focused on cursive /c/ today, which Luke was enthusiastic about.</p><p>Donah no. 23<br><br>Rule Outline 17, 4<br>Notes<br>Luke requested coaching help with spelling homework in class, so we completed 2 days of his overdue work for SD. His teacher had marked his mistakes of “squosh” and “eletic” as correct, so we fixed those errors. He also had trouble spelling “kangaroo”, whic', NULL, '2022-03-08 18:07:48', '2022-03-08 18:18:48'),
