(1685, '2022/03/09', '4:40 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phoebe is obsessed with slime videos so I used this as an incentive to keep her working. She loves dance and does not want to come for tutoring. She gets frustrated when she doesn\'t know the sounds. She likes hands on activity such as drawing and folding.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Phonological awareness: Kilpatrick F1</li><li>chllenge word: bread</li><li>OPR: a, e, i, o, c, k, s, z, x, j, g, qu</li><li>WPR: rule page one -consonants-rule 1 puzzle game</li><li>SD: rule page one- rule 2-sorting activity</li><li>Marking: underline multi letter phonograms and write number on top of a phonogram that does not say its first sound.&nbsp;</li><li>Oral sentence: using the word pencil to make an oral sentenc', NULL, '2022-03-09 16:40:52', '2022-03-09 16:48:20'),
(1686, '2022/03/09', '5:31 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 23: Write dge to say /j/ after a single vowel saying its first sound', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', NULL, '<p>Review of rules 23/25</p><p>Application of, articulation of when to apply and why.&nbsp;</p><p>X can articulate and model correct use with encouragement.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Emailed Fern - English teacher who sent a copy of the English assessment task for the class novel The Big Dry.&nbsp;</p><p>We discussed the rubric, went through the task, brainstormed different methods of presentation - powerpoint/mind map/essay/video/ character interview etc</p><p>Xavier identified 4 character traits for George and agreed to colect further evidence using the sheet given by his teacher.</p><p>Reveiwed Xave\'s current knowledge of TEEl paragraph structure and practised composing topic sentences and', NULL, '2022-03-09 17:32:43', '2022-03-09 17:41:02'),
(1687, '2022/03/10', '7:20 a.m.', '1', '3', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Develop confidence with number sequences to and from 100 by ones from any starting point', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Today we only focused on place value with 6 digit numbers.&nbsp;</p><p>In the end, I was asking Nate to demonstrate his understanding of place value by showing one number in a variety of ways.</p><p>Nate was fully engaged with the lesson, he was very talkative and let me know what he does at school.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-10 07:20:53', '2022-07-03 10:16:13'),
