(1689, '2022/03/10', '7:58 a.m.', '1', '5', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - segment words, write phonograms, analyse marking, apply rule, blend sounds (see notes)', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>SD<br>first sent cent mile seem even without afternoon Friday wife consider referee proceed (procide)<br><br>Writing<br>Essays - TEEL<br>Evidence &amp; Explanation<br>Today, Jimmy and I looked at the processes of Explanation and Evidence in a deeper manner. We discussed how to write an explanation in 4 steps - decoding, focus, bias, and linking to the topic sentence. We also discussed the CRAP method for Evidence - Currency, Reliability, Authority and Purpose.<br><br>For this task, we used a sample question regarding friendship, turned it into a topic sentence, and wrote supporting sentences. We then checked it against the aforementioned criteria. As always, Jimmy was pleasant and eager t', NULL, '2022-03-10 07:59:39', '2022-03-21 10:16:28'),
