(1692, '2022/03/10', '3:26 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>We were looking at fractions today.</p><p>In the beginning, Sofia was very disengaged with the lesson; I had to pause the lesson for a moment to play a couple of times UNO and then I promised that if she would pay attention and solve a couple of problems, we could play the money game at the end of the lesson.&nbsp;</p><p>Sofia is not ready yet to work with fractions, despite the fact she knows how a division work and is capable of doing divisions, we need to work more on this and also include some more work on multiplications.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-10 15:26:48', '2022-03-26 11:19:52'),
(1693, '2022/03/10', '3:27 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', 'Reading - Comprehension > Text Type & Mental Actions', 'Stated/Implied/Inferred Meaning', 'Key Into Inference', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Reuben</p><p>Kilpatrick: H1</p><p>Handwriting: Cursive /e/</p><p>Morphology: Donah 25<br>joy + ful<br>en + joy<br>en + joy + ed</p><p>Ayres: P<br>beauty<br>beautiful<br>enjoy<br>awe<br>vacation</p><p>Inference: L1 S1 I 5<br>Reuben is excellent at inference and continues to be able to articulate why he has mad the conclusions he has.</p><p>Writing: Text Types - Narrative</p><p>Plot progression<br>Narrative structure<br>Reuben was able to articulate each section of a narrative! He also eagerly discussed the emotional reaction of the audience as sparked by future plot twists. We also planned out somewhat of a film and narrative \"assignment\" after 3 episodes!</p>', NULL, '2022-03-10 15:27:33', '2022-03-28 13:49:57'),
(1694, '2022/03/10', '3:33 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose first-person narrative paragraph', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Cara composed a short first person narrative, completing each step of the writing process. Focus was on using descriptive language, similes and alternatives to common parts of speech.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-10 15:33:23', '2022-03-16 15:19:08'),
(1695, '2022/03/10', '3:33 p.m.', '1', '5', 'James Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Ellie Connor', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Five</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 10 March 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick F1</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #5</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Challenge word: nervous / forgotten (intro/recap rule 11 and rule 10)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: th ng o ck au aw or wh ee ea ir c&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Best OPR/WPR we\'ve done all term! JC didn\'t need prompting with any phonos (except pronunciation of \'ng\' and prompt with cue for \'ck\'). Beautiful handwriting for WPR (especially&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"tabl', NULL, '2022-03-10 15:33:40', '2022-03-10 17:17:03'),
(1696, '2022/03/10', '3:33 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Seth Vanderlaan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked really well today. Didn\'t want to come in for a long time until I convinced him that we could just get it all done quickly. Got through all of phonos and he did well. Got confused with the d and b but quickly corrected himself. Focused on the few he got wrong and wrote words up on the board to help him remember, we turned those words into sentences which i copied into his book and which he wrote on the small whiteboard.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-10 15:33:53', '2022-03-16 09:05:36'),
(1697, '2022/03/10', '3:36 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>NSPM 3A - add labels to previously completed workings for worded problems. &nbsp;(p32, 35)</p><p>Solve worded problems using modelling provided - complete labels and workings (pages 33, 34)</p><p>Prepare models to represent the information provided in worded problems. &nbsp;Lucy initially prepared a comparative model but quickly recognised it wasn\'t the right one. &nbsp;When I asked what model she thought might be best, she answered without thought, “One with a split.” At the conclusion of her workings, Lucy then noted that she could add to this revised model to include additional information supporting the answering of the second question. &nbsp;It was rewarding to see Lucy recognise the', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-10 15:36:51', '2022-03-10 16:46:54'),
(1698, '2022/03/10', '4:25 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Sentence Construction & Vocabulary', 'Sentence structure - there are three ways to construct a sentence > simple, compound, complex', 'Recognise/Analyse/Compose/Model simple/compound/complex sentences that demonstrate meaning & usage of unfamiliar spelling words', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Finn struggled to come up with an idea and to put pen to paper. We began the process by looking at the elements of &nbsp;a narrative . Finn was bale to articulate these.</p><p>When it came time to put pen to paper and to make a mindmap or timeline he became very complacent and reluctant. We discussed why he became anxious about handwriting and it came back to spelling. He is extremely concerned about getting it right and does not want to make a mistake.&nbsp;</p><p>I encouraged him to not focus on spelling but on sounds. As long as we could read it back then we can edit it at the end. The focus was on getting ideas down.&nbsp;</p><p>I set finn the task to complete his narrative for homewo', NULL, '2022-03-10 16:25:25', '2022-03-16 15:15:09'),
