(1700, '2022/03/10', '4:29 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Samuel Lamont', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked well through the phonos, got stumped on the new ones i put in, and then didn\'t really want to put them into words nor write them down. &nbsp;struggled a bit with the wordle and couldn\'t really think of any 5 letter words and needed a lot of persuading to get any. Did well on WPR and dictation. Created all the words into one sentence and finished off with a game.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-10 16:29:52', '2022-03-16 09:07:54'),
(1701, '2022/03/10', '4:32 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'Chance & Data', 'Everyday chance', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today\'s lesson was completely different from any other.</p><p>Finlay came to tutoring not knowing what was going to happen with his apprenticeship.&nbsp;</p><p>We had a long conversation about what could be the best for his future. Finlay was told at college that he wasn\'t enrolled in Maths in the workplace, instead, he is in General Maths - Methods 2.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-10 16:32:38', '2022-03-26 10:53:26'),
(1702, '2022/03/10', '5:02 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Connect the compound interest formula to repeated applications of simple interest', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Callisto missed all of her Maths lessons last week but has managed to get to class this week. We therefore backtracked to do the work that she missed last week which was on the topic of depreciation. We looked first at Straight Line Depreciation and then Reducing Balance Depreciation. We will continue some more work on depreciation next week, combining the 2 measures by graphing them.</p>', '<p>Callisto missed all of her Maths lessons last week but has managed to get to class this week. We therefore backtracked to do the work that she missed last week which was on the topic of depreciation. We looked first at Straight Line Depreciation and then Reducing Balance Depreciation. We will continue some more work on depreciation next week, combining the 2 measures by graphing them.</p>', NULL, '2022-03-10 17:02:34', '2022-03-10 18:08:54'),
(1703, '2022/03/10', '5:31 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Describe, continue and create patterns with fractions, decimals and whole numbers resulting from + & -', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'In Progress', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Lesson\'s topics:</p><ul><li>Multiple Steps Equations.</li><li>Inequalities.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>The student did great work with multiple steps equations. Nicholas can solve problems related to this topic by plying distributive, index and sign law.&nbsp;</p><p>In the second part of the lesson, I introduce inequalities to Nicholas. We were looking at the main similarities and differences with equations.</p><p>All the problems solved during the lesson were made-up.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-10 17:31:22', '2022-03-27 19:15:52'),
(1704, '2022/03/10', '5:32 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Maricha Cilliers', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked well through division, seemed to be quite confident with it now, and worked through the problems quite fast. Moved on to working through the module and started working through how to plus and subtract fractions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-10 17:32:10', '2022-03-16 09:17:55'),
(1705, '2022/03/11', '7:48 a.m.', '1', '5', 'Gus Pettit', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Gus continued doing diagnostic tests at school. As the main topic included in these tests is operations with whole numbers, we were working on this today.&nbsp;</p><p>We started by doing long additions and subtractions; sometimes Gus got confused with borrowing, and a couple of times started the operations from left to right. Then we moved to long multiplications by 1 and 2 digit numbers.&nbsp;</p><p>The student understood very well the concepts, at the end of the lesson he didn\'t need much guidance to solve the problems.&nbsp;</p><p>We didn\'t have enough time to work on divisions and word problems,&nbsp;</p><p>As Gus was able to solve two hard problems, he didn\'t get any homework.&nbsp;<', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-11 07:48:45', '2022-03-27 19:50:00'),
(1706, '2022/03/11', '7:55 a.m.', '1', '5', 'Charlotte Kratz', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>SPELLING:</strong></p><p>opr/wpr:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ng, th, oy, ew, er, augh,&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule Review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>4, 6</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>length, long, strength, strong, destroy, newspaper, daughter, naughty, caught, taught</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>WRITING:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Continue writing an ending to ORF #620 - focus on believable story writing</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>NOTES:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody', NULL, '2022-03-11 07:56:07', '2022-03-11 08:54:12'),
(1707, '2022/03/11', '10:13 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Luke Vandenberg', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick: H2<br>Luke is great at these! May need to bump him up.</p><p>Handwriting: Cursive D<br>Luke was very enthusiastic about this activity and did a lovely job.</p><p>Morphology: Donah 26&nbsp;<br>\"sun\"</p><p>OPR/WPR<br>qu<br>ph<br>ck<br>ed<br>wh<br>oa<br>ui<br>or<br>ew<br>aw<br>Excellent! Luke is also taking pride in his presentation with handwriting and margins.</p><p>SD:<br>city<br>only<br>where<br>week<br>weak</p><p>Inference: L1 S2 I 6</p><p>OF:&nbsp;<br>skipped \"between\"<br>Luke\'s prosody and fluency is rising and he is gaining confidence, however still needs some help with focusing on the correct lines.</p><p>Writing<br>Sentences: \"winner\".</p>', NULL, '2022-03-11 10:14:40', '2022-03-28 10:06:21'),
(1708, '2022/03/11', '10:14 a.m.', '1', '5', 'Luke Vandenberg', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Read words aloud - accurately, automatically, with expression (connected text)', 'Oral reading fluency practice passage - Spalding Level 500', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick H1<br>Luke is really excellent with this task! He has no problem distinguishing between consonant blends.</p><p>OPR<br>1. aw<br>2. au<br>3. ph<br>4. ck<br>5. ed<br>Luke hesitated on /ck/ but eventually got it correct – otherwise, all was perfect.<br>We also focused on cursive /c/ today, which Luke was enthusiastic about.</p><p>Morphology<br>\"find\" - finds, finding</p><p>Rule 17, 4</p><p>SD<br>Luke did spelling homework in class, so we completed 2 days of his overdue work for SD. His teacher had marked his mistakes of “squosh” and “eletic” as correct, so we fixed those errors. He also had trouble spelling “kangaroo”, which we broke up into two parts: “kanga” + “roo”, allowing Lu', NULL, '2022-03-11 10:15:26', '2022-03-28 10:14:56'),
(1709, '2022/03/11', '10:15 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Hunter McNees', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR<br>b d er ir ur wor ear ai ay<br><br>Handwriting /b/ /B/<br><br>SFE 1, Rule 4<br><br>SD<br>day eat sit Jim gym (jim) bed see out like<br>Hunter also volunteered to spell “sea”!<br><br>OF 100<br>skipped: is&nbsp;<br>error: planets nearest visible<br><br>Writing<br>Creative writing - Planning<br>Hunter planned his story about Bob the Bearded Baby with his 2 sidekicks. He also invented super powers for Bob, which include a nappy tornado!</p>', NULL, '2022-03-11 10:17:00', '2022-03-21 10:12:09'),
(1710, '2022/03/11', '2:30 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Molly Jackson', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute vowel phoneme - Kilpatrick Level J', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick J</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-58</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ear ou ch oo or au aw ed ui oa gu ph</td></tr><tr><td>Lots of thinking time and errors today, not sure why.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 20 17 29 4 31</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: small-express</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Had to teach Molly a few rules on the fly as I forgot about r. 30 and 31… but Molly picked these up beautif', NULL, '2022-03-11 14:30:48', '2022-03-11 17:40:09');
