(1712, '2022/03/11', '3:28 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Connor Thompson', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Adjectives - describe nouns and some adjectives', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Story Cubes</td></tr><tr><td>3 sentence stories using the Story Cubes. NM model creation of three sentence story both orally and on the whiteboard. CT chose to write three one sentence stories instead. Identify beginning, middle and end in each story.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Chose one of the one sentence stories and expanded into three sentences. NM model EXTENSIVELY on the whiteboard and create own from \"there was a plane that crashed\'. Explicitly told Connor what each sentence was to include (1 = establishes the object, 2 = the action, 3 = describes the object after the action.</td></tr><tr><td>Show Connor a photograph of a burning fire and have h', NULL, '2022-03-11 15:28:36', '2022-03-18 16:12:47'),
(1713, '2022/03/11', '3:29 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Annika Spedding', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Annika started by giving me an OPR today, and seemed to remember her phonograms well (I would get them wrong to watch her correct me).<br><br>Annika needed a quick recap of SFE, but seemed to remember this quite well.<br><br>Annika was able to easily explain and sort words between Job 1 and 2. Annika was also able to explain the rules when prompted.<br><br>Annika was able to accuratley explain what is required in a sentence, and the basic structure of a sentence (including identifying nouns &amp; verbs).</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-03-11 15:29:22', '2022-03-11 17:37:38'),
(1715, '2022/03/11', '4:30 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 20', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'In Progress', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>MMM - Archie rated 3/5 his feelings about MMM success. &nbsp;Extraordarily impressive improvement in total number completed score compared with 22 and 25 Feb. &nbsp;Focus needed on subtraction but this score may have reflected distractions in environment as well.</p><p>Introduced Archie to modelling for problem solving. &nbsp;80c total spend, 1 bag of chips worth 3 freddo frogs. &nbsp;Share the 80c among 4 total units = 20c per unit. &nbsp;Total chips 80c. &nbsp;Archie then applied this process to solving Singapore worded problems (page 8 in exercise book). &nbsp;Used division and multiplication &nbsp;(instead of repeated addition - discussed most efficient process), and subtraction with ', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-11 16:30:18', '2022-03-11 17:32:20'),
(1716, '2022/03/11', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Joshua Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Josh did a solid OPR today, and continued this through to his spelling dictation. Josh was able to accurately explain a number of rules which has been a struggle for him in the past.<br><br>Josh and I spent a lot of time discussing why \'liking\' is necessary in persuassive texts. Josh feels that this is not an essential part of persuasion, and argued that this is all about power. I explained the situation of lawyers where forming relationship influences the outcome, to which he countered that there is still a power un-balance. I will recap this again next week, but hopefully spend less time debating the accuracy of the science.</td></tr></tbody></ta', NULL, '2022-03-11 16:31:19', '2022-03-11 17:43:19'),
(1717, '2022/03/15', '7:51 a.m.', '1', '5', 'Tiki Salt', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tiki was pretty much asleep when they came in. tried to get some energy out but failed slightly. Worked through some phonos after wordle, threw some hard ones in there such as \'augh\' just to stump him. Worked well through dictation got \'though\' and \'view\' wrong. worked through an unpunctuated passage together. only picked up most of the full stops and capitals but that\'s in, no commas or apostrophes.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-15 07:51:17', '2022-03-16 08:58:29'),
(1718, '2022/03/15', '12:03 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Vincenzo Vella', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Investigate and calculate percentage discounts of 10%, 25% and 50% on sale items', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', '<p>Following up Vinnie\'s maths teacher recommendations, today we worked on:</p><ol><li>Finding the percentage of a quantity.</li><li>Best buy.</li><li>Increase/discount of a product.</li><li>Calculating taxes.</li></ol><p>Vinnie is using a workbook from Taroona; we have been using this since the beginning of the year. He had a pop-up quiz which didn\'t go as good as it could be. If the student would have been able to read a bit more careful questions, I\'m confident he could have had a better grade. Vinnie solves the same kind of problems with me without many difficulties. However, it seems to be that he has some difficulties focusing within the classroom.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-15 12:04:45', '2022-03-15 12:14:52'),
(1719, '2022/03/15', '3:03 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Max Shapiro', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Max did not come to tutoring today, George said he was crying in the car and wouldn\'t come up so I had a \"substitute\" for the lesson (Luna).</td></tr><tr><td>I tried to do some handwriting work with Luna but she was not having it. I also had no idea what to do with her as she isn\'t my student! We played the \"add medial sound\" game and Luna could blend CVC words. She exhibited reversals in many of her letter writing (n, a) and would not listen to me when I tried to get her to learn.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-03-15 15:03:00', '2022-03-15 17:20:46'),
(1720, '2022/03/15', '3:17 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Jett Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Linear & Non-Linear Relationships', 'Linear relationships (Co-ordinates, Cartesian Plane)', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', '<p>As per teacher recommendation, today we worked on graphing linear equations.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Gradient.</li><li>General equation of a line.</li><li>Graphing a line.</li><li>Finding the equation of a line from the graph.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-15 15:17:28', '2022-03-23 22:06:47'),
(1721, '2022/03/15', '3:17 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Jett Knighton', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-15 15:17:28', '2022-03-23 22:10:30'),
(1722, '2022/03/15', '3:26 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Esther McIver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>SPELLING:</p><p>opr/wpr:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ee, our, ai, ay, ea, y</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule Review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>5, 6, 18, 19, 29</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>climb, coffee, colour, contains, daily,day, eagle, fancy, fly, forest</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>WRITING:</p><p>Parts of Speech:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Revise adverbs - explain their use in sentences. Get EM to sentences that include adverbs.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Sentence Structure:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Loo', NULL, '2022-03-15 15:26:18', '2022-03-15 16:31:10'),
(1723, '2022/03/15', '3:29 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 51-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: dge ed gu kn gn ie ei</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 3 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: forest-hotel</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Compose sentences', NULL, '2022-03-15 15:29:36', '2022-03-22 17:11:38'),
(1724, '2022/03/15', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Stella Bowerman', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>worked really well through the end of the division sheet. Began with the worded problems which we walked through together. She didn\'t really seem like she knew what was happening until I was feeding her the questions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-15 15:30:02', '2022-03-16 09:11:28'),
(1725, '2022/03/15', '4:25 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Lachlan Prior', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked well through phonos. Tried out some new ones and seemed to get it quite quickly. Im noticing a lot of spelling mistakes in his drafts so am going to let him finish and note all the spelling mistakes and use that as dictaion instread of the aryes words next week.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-15 16:25:03', '2022-03-16 09:01:34'),
(1726, '2022/03/15', '4:29 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Game (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luca and I started our lesson today with some multiplication drills once more. Luca seemed to do well with this, but struggled with the timer. He was able to complete his grid in 11min 5 sec.<br><br>Luca and I looked at improper fractions once again, and spoke about the working out behind this. Luca mentioned he was multiplying the denominator up until it reached the numerator (giving him the whole number), then counted the remainder to give him the new numerator. We spoke about how it\'s much easier to divide the numerator by the denominator to give us the whole, then using the remainder as the new numerator. He said this was way much easier, but s', NULL, '2022-03-15 16:29:45', '2022-03-15 17:16:27'),
(1727, '2022/03/15', '4:30 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve worded problems using four basic operations + modelling', 'Text Book  - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Shannon and Ava let me know an exam is coming soon and it\'s about word problems with whole numbers and square numbers and roots.&nbsp;</p><p>Ava and I jumped to do a quick check on the 4 operations with whole numbers; then used the Asian Education Y 6 and 5 textbooks to solve high standard word problems. Ava did a great job in this part. However, when it was a combination of more than 3 operations she was a bit confused.&nbsp;</p><p>Then we were working on square numbers which were very easy for this gifted student. Afterwards, we moved on to roots.&nbsp;</p><p>We were working on decomposition using prime numbers. Ava easily understood this concept and had no problems finding square and cubic roots.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-15 16:30:01', '2022-07-02 08:44:47'),
(1728, '2022/03/15', '4:30 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Shay Douglas', 'Mathematics', 'Linear & Non-Linear Relationships', 'Linear relationships (Co-ordinates, Cartesian Plane)', 'School-assigned worksheet/task', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Maths</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Gradient/slope</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Worksheet from school on board/on page.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Shay requested to work on&nbsp; gradients/slopes in linear equations as he was finding it troubling. We used a worksheet that had been provided by his teacher on Canvas. Shay was required to find the slope from two given points/x and y ints</td></tr><tr><td>Shay and I had a lot of trouble with this! Even though it was simple in concept, he struggled with a) representing the line on the graph correctly, b) correctly identifying which was the 1st/2nd point and c) subs', NULL, '2022-03-15 16:30:50', '2022-03-22 17:17:48'),
(1729, '2022/03/15', '4:33 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Stated Purpose & Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Cards 1 - 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callum is very willing to learn and he has been working hard through his homework. He has gained the awareness of individual sounds since he started with Educate Tutoring. He started to form the sense of syllables and sounds in words.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Phonological awareness: F1</li><li>1 minute-write as much words as he can&nbsp;</li><li>OPR/WPR: c, s, z, k, x, j, qu, sh, ee, th, ow, ou</li><li>SD: rule page 1---rule 4. Callum has grasped the marking system and he can analyze simple words with my help, which is a big progress compared to the time when he just started without any knowledge of phonological awareness.&nbsp;</li><li>Homework: review open and closed syllables.&nbsp;<br><br>&nb', NULL, '2022-03-15 16:33:53', '2022-03-22 09:21:25'),
(1730, '2022/03/15', '4:38 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 8: There are five ways to write the /er/ sound - Her first nurse works early.', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>OPR</strong><br>a e I o u y er ir ur wor ear ed ea&nbsp; wh&nbsp;wr&nbsp; oa oe&nbsp; aw au ew ui&nbsp;ar j dge ck ch&nbsp; ey kn&nbsp;</p><p><br><strong>WPR</strong>kn dge j ck ch&nbsp; ey ea er ir ur wor ear&nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>HW&nbsp;</strong>focus line letters start at top.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Rule Review</strong></p><p>Rule 8- 5 sounds of er</p><p>Rule page continue next two lines.&nbsp;</p><p>herd third purse search worm&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Spelling Dictation</strong> Ayres A-G&nbsp;</p><p>father bird (cool) earth (feed) fur worm&nbsp;</p><p>Marking – A has yet to be introduced to double underlining phgs not saying a usual sounds. Go back to', NULL, '2022-03-15 16:38:24', '2022-03-22 12:08:32'),
(1731, '2022/03/15', '5:42 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Purpose for learning phonograms - To connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling', 'See notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Brock likes math and he does not like spelling. He has low interest in English, hence he cant\'t remember what we have learned. The key thing to do is to make the lesson more attractive to him, maybe combine with math?</p><ol><li>Phonological awareness: H1</li><li>OPR/WPR: igh, y, ng, ch, wh, ed,ew, ui. Brock needed help with wh, ed, ew and ui.&nbsp;</li><li>SD: rule 17, 5, 6, and 9. Brock cannot recall the rules but he does understanding the rule when reminded. He needs more challenge tasks such as sentence writing along with parts of speech.</li><li>Syllable types review and sfes.&nbsp;</li><li>Homework: OFR 210-IN</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-03-15 17:43:59', '2022-03-22 09:18:15'),
(1732, '2022/03/15', '6:42 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Jeanica Cilliers', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Go through a few sheets of all operations. She had a bit of trouble carrying the numbers over and borrowing. Wasn’t sure what are where to carry or borrow. Actually wanted to do the division before anything else and did pretty well at it all. Didn’t get time to go over the worded questions. Worked well with the Uno game, finished off the multiplication sheet. Need to work on place value next week because it was getting a little out of place. Did the worded problems which she was very determined to complete by herself but looked at me a few times when she was unsure.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-15 18:42:05', '2022-03-16 09:16:26'),
(1733, '2022/03/15', '6:43 p.m.', '1', '1', 'Joseph Martin', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-15 18:43:08', '2022-03-15 18:43:08'),
(1734, '2022/03/15', '10:17 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Donah 6<br>Stella continues to be great at these morphology exercises!<br><br>OPR<br>a, c, d, g, o, f<br><br>WPR<br>a, f, c, o<br>Stella made absolutely beautiful /f/s this week! She needs some work shortening the line on /a/.<br><br>Handwriting Sheet /c/<br>Stella did her best with /c/ formation, though became frustrated at one point. She was told to keep her sheet neat and afterwards did her best to colour in neatly.<br><br>Reading<br>bug<br>C<br>red<br>cat<br>Stella had a bit of trouble reading “red” as she was not sure if it was /d/ vs /b/, but was amazing at the rest of the words! We need to continue to address /b/ vs /d/.</p>', NULL, '2022-03-15 22:17:30', '2022-03-28 14:00:19'),
(1735, '2022/03/15', '10:17 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Tyler Van Nimwegen', 'Study Skills', 'Research', 'See Notes', 'See Notes...', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>This week, Tyler and I did a coaching session for Work Studies. We addressed:</p><ul><li>My career - plan goals - 4 things to know about future career</li><li>Brainstorm - education level, interests, skills, salary</li><li>Career interests in connection to hobbies/personality</li><li>Career desires&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Tyler, as usual, joked around at first due to initial discomfort when talking about himself, however soon opened up about what he is most passionate about (cooking). This exercise was great to go through together because the judgment-free environment in tutoring actually allows Tyler to talk about what he wants to do in the future, even if he may not feel as if he currently ha', NULL, '2022-03-15 22:17:53', '2022-03-22 18:35:31'),
