(1748, '2022/03/16', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Long Division - Solve problems involving division by a two-digit number including those that result in a remainder', 'Text Book  - Exercises, questions, activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Today, Jacob and I were working with divisions and I introduced Jacob to decimals.&nbsp;</p><p>We did many drawings on the board to find how many groups of X we can find in Y. Doing this activity was really helpful as it let Jacob understand the process behind making divisions. Once we did this activity, we started to do divisions with reminders and this let us move to the concept of decimals.&nbsp;</p><p>Then, we moved to make additions and take away with decimals. We looked at the process of carrying and borrowing with decimals.&nbsp;</p><p>All the problems we solved on the board and in Jacobs\' notebook were made-up problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-16 16:31:00', '2022-06-02 20:58:01'),
(1749, '2022/03/16', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'Followup', NULL, '<p>OPR 27-70</p><p>Intensive application of when to use the different phgs for vowel sounds:</p><p>Tricks - most common to least common, eliminate, apply rules you know, write it down - does it look right???</p><p>&nbsp;a a_e ay ai ea ey eigh ei</p><p>Rule 4, 7 (1), 18,&nbsp;</p><p>e e_e ee ea ie ei ey&nbsp;</p><p>Rule 4,7(1), 12</p><p>O o_e ow ou oa oe ough&nbsp;</p><p>Rule 4, 7(1)&nbsp;</p><p>Xavier was able to use the table we constructed to assist him to spell words correctly. Articulated his process with unfamiliar words eg dec<strong>ei</strong>t - eliminated ie as it followed a letter c, eliminated e (r.4) as sound was not at end of a syllable, eliminated ey as not at end of a base wo', NULL, '2022-03-16 16:31:13', '2022-03-16 17:41:32'),
