(1752, '2022/03/16', '5:44 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - segment words, write phonograms, analyse marking, apply rule, blend sounds (see notes)', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>SD<br>hour our (owe) wife state July head story open short lady consider (concider) proceed (procede) curious<br><br>Writing<br>Origin Story - Orcs using Hydra\'s sea to pay debt to Human council&nbsp;<br>Character sheet planning&nbsp;<br>Worldbuilding setting&nbsp;<br>Descriptive language - Royal order of adjectives<br><br>This week, we focused on Jimmy\'s story which he had begun planning last fortnight. We created four more character sheets and started on Worldbuilding, specifically immediate settings, plants, and a physical description. Jimmy seemed excited when it came to actually imagining the world he was creating - I think worldbuilding is a big part of his enjoyment! He was able to', NULL, '2022-03-16 18:01:03', '2022-03-21 10:17:06'),
(1753, '2022/03/16', '6:01 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Nina Gust', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>H2<br>Nina did great! However, she had trouble with splitting initial consonant blends with /l/ as the second sound.</p><p>OPR/WPR<br>th<br>ow<br>ee<br>sh<br>qu</p><p>Handwriting<br>/F/ /f/<br>We are focusing on Nina\'s /f/ formation! She has come into tutoring forming her /f/ from the bottom up so we are continuing to correct to \"candycane\" /f/!</p><p>SD<br>you&nbsp;<br>your (yoru)<br>old (olld)<br>good s.c<br>red<br>of<br>be<br>but<br>the<br>this</p><p>OF<br>fall s.c<br>error able = about</p><p>Writing -&nbsp;<br>Letter to future self<br>Simple sentences</p>', NULL, '2022-03-16 18:20:29', '2022-03-21 10:35:13'),
(1754, '2022/03/17', '7:24 a.m.', '1', '4', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Represent and solve simple addition and subtraction problems using a range of strategies', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', '<p>We started to work on solving word problems with additions and substructions.&nbsp;</p><p>First, we focused on modelling; creating a picture/diagram to help us understand which operation we need to do to come up with the answer.&nbsp;</p><p>Also, before Nate looked for keywords and try to figure out what to do, he needed to slow down a bit and read the whole word problem once (and even better, twice). This helped Nate to get the bigger picture to be able to understand it a little better too.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-17 07:24:02', '2022-07-03 10:27:39'),
