(1757, '2022/03/17', '8:02 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Tyler Van Nimwegen', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick: H2<br>Tyler completed this task with no problem!</p><p>Handwriting: /a/ /u/ /d/<br>Tyler tends to create these letters VERY similarly! We discussed that he needs to close his /a/, that /u/ was a line letter, and that /d/ needed to be a tall letter, otherwise the words are also hard for him to read.</p><p>Morphology: Donah 26</p><p>OPR/WPR<br>sci<br>eu<br>ge<br>rh<br>aigh<br>sc<br>pn<br>Tyler did excellently, and was only confused with /ge/, originally forming as /gi/ before self correcting.</p><p>SD:<br>city<br>only<br>where<br>week<br>weak</p><p>Inference: L1 S2 I 6</p><p>OF: 700<br>s.c \"abdomen\" \"antennae\"&nbsp;<br>Tyler has increased so much with his prosody and fluency!</p', NULL, '2022-03-17 08:02:58', '2022-03-28 14:07:35'),
