(1763, '2022/03/17', '10:05 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Chelsea Cooper', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Six</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 28 March 2022</td></tr><tr><td>Catch-up from 17/3/22</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #7</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Challenge word: Sat ur day r. 26, 18</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: th aw er oo or ay ou our ea au</td></tr><tr><td>Struggled with aw/or/au/ou/ow</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 26, 5, 18, 4, 6</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: without, afternoon, Friday, hour, our, wife, state, July, head</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></', NULL, '2022-03-17 10:06:16', '2022-03-28 18:31:41'),
(1764, '2022/03/17', '1:14 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Zac Pharaoh', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Investigate and calculate percentage discounts of 10%, 25% and 50% on sale items', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Not Returned', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today we worked on percentages.</p><p>How to calculate a percentage.</p><p>Increase/decrease by percentage.</p><p>Relationship between percentage and fractions.</p><p>Due to Zac\'s learning difficulties, it\'s necessary to explain to Zac with many details and slow.&nbsp;</p><p>I did many drawings on the board to help Zac understand those concepts and to work out the practice problems.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Lesson No 6 was delivered on 21.03.2022</p>', '2022-03-17 13:16:02', '2022-07-03 20:41:13'),
(1765, '2022/03/17', '2:09 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Mia Harvey', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>was a bit of a struggle in this lesson. Her attention span with certain tasks tends to be quite short so I give her a little time to get it out of her system mid-task. Worked well on long addition but seemed like it was all very new to her. She did well but struggled to understand the importance of starting from the right and going left. she quickly understood where to put the carried number. we ended up doing a question for a question, she would write me one and I would write her one.</p>', NULL, '2022-03-17 14:09:38', '2022-04-06 15:09:32'),
(1766, '2022/03/17', '3:22 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick: H2<br>Reuben has moved up to H2 and has been doing very well!</p><p>Handwriting: Cursive /f/<br>Reuben actually asked for help with Fs, which was nice! He doesn\'t usually ask for help. We revisited /e/ as he struggled with uppercase E</p><p>Morphology: Donah 26 and affixes: \"trouble\"</p><p>Ayres: P<br>vacation<br>trouble<br>troubling<br>important<br>importance<br>carry<br>carried</p><p>Inference: L1 S1 I 5</p><p>Writing: Text Types - Narrative</p><p>Plot progression<br>Narrative structure</p><p>Reuben helped complete a film summary chart of the last 3 episodes of Naruto by by Masashi Kishimoto. We broke down the narrative - Beginning (Hook), Middle (Conflict), End (Resolution)', NULL, '2022-03-17 15:22:12', '2022-03-28 13:53:25'),
(1767, '2022/03/17', '3:22 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<ul><li>Check on long additions and subtractions.&nbsp;</li><li>Times tables.</li><li>Long multiplications by 1 digit number.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Sofia did a great job today, she was talking for most of the lesson about her work in a Caffe in Kingston beach.&nbsp;</p><p>I used this conversation to make up the problems we solved on the board.&nbsp;</p><p>Even though the student didn\'t like doing long multiplications, she was able to accurately solve the problems. We used 2\'s 3\'s and 4\'s for most of them.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-17 15:22:52', '2022-03-26 11:25:47'),
(1768, '2022/03/17', '3:27 p.m.', '1', '6', 'James Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Ellie Connor', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Six</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 17 March 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #7</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Challenge word: lick, duck, peck, knock, back</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: ui ck tch sh igh wh ed ew oa gu</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>JC did an amazing job with his OPR/WPR again. He was super quick and accurate with OPR and able to answer my K&amp;A questions. Handwriting was also really good.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 25, 13, 17, 5, 6</td', NULL, '2022-03-17 15:27:50', '2022-03-17 16:38:37'),
(1770, '2022/03/17', '3:33 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Paragraphs - Two or more sentences about a topic presented in a logical order of ideas with appropriate indentations and margins', 'Think aloud when identifying the topic in two or more given sentences and whether they are related', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Persuasive Writing</p><p>Elements - opinion/reason/example/conclusion</p><p>Purpose - express your opinion ;prove it is true; give facts; convince the reader.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Use prompt cards to practise a piece of persuasive &nbsp;</p><p>Write a draft and revise.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-17 15:33:07', '2022-03-17 16:30:48'),
(1771, '2022/03/17', '3:36 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Seth Vanderlaan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Seth was very excited to begin the lesson this afternoon. Worked really well with the phonos, only got him to say the first sounds but did well with all of those. Still got stumped on the b and the d but quickly correct4d himself. Was able to make connections from last week\'s work with the \"y for yo-yo\" did some WPR with a few of the double letter phonons and made some words from them, out of those words we made some sentences which I wrote on the board and he copied on the small whiteboard. need to start being more strict on how he writes them in because I\'ve been telling him to just write it big or small. finished off with just playing around with the ball and a bit of free time.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-17 15:36:51', '2022-04-06 14:51:59');
INSERT INTO `attens` (`id`, `date_created`, `time`, `term`, `lesson`, `student_name`, `subject_name`, `concept_name`, `conceptDetail`, `learningActivity`, `tutor_name`, `tutor_evaluation`, `student_self`, `student_attendance`, `homework_completed`, `weekly_lesson`, `homework_assignment`, `email_school`, `comment`, `commentPrivate`, `notesAttendance`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1772, '2022/03/17', '4:09 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 20', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Final results of Key Math Assessment processed today. &nbsp;See 25-page report on file. &nbsp;Lucy is performing in the average range for her age group, however, her age equivalent for maths is 10 years 4 months.</p><p>Lucy achieved full marks on addition, multiplication and division in MMM. &nbsp;There were only four incomplete problems in subtraction.</p><p>Lucy is becoming increasingly confident and fluent when problem solving with modelling. &nbsp;She is also beginning to confidently describe the meaning of the model elements and how they relate to the given problem and values.</p><p>Create a fraction as part of a whole (folded piece of paper in half then in quarters - same amount but', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-17 16:23:36', '2022-03-17 18:28:58'),
(1774, '2022/03/17', '4:24 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose first-person narrative paragraph', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Writing - Finn presented his draft of his narrative.</p><p>We discussed the steps of the writing process and worked through them systematically - compose/revise/edit/publish.</p><p>Finn revised his sentence structure and edited punctuation at the same time. Initial draft had very little punctuation. As he had typed his draft into a computer he had very few spelling errors, apart from an incorrect word or two. eg another/other.</p><p>Once we completed the revision process we read the text aloud and made further adjustments to punctuation based on flow. The final edit was to correct spelling. A final read to check. F. to type it up as homework.</p><p>Spelling - looked at different ways to w', NULL, '2022-03-17 16:24:20', '2022-03-18 10:02:24'),
(1775, '2022/03/17', '4:27 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Samuel Lamont', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Did well with all th phonos to begin with. \"ou\" he didn\'t get right even after I explained it a few times so we\'ll work on that in the future. Played a quick game of chess, and did around 10 words of dictation after WPR. Got most of them right, he struggled with which \"ea\" or \'ae\' to use in a few words. Made them into sentences but needs to work on his handwriting and setting out his sentences, kind of just writes what he thinks and doesn\'t really make sense.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-17 16:27:08', '2022-04-06 14:54:15'),
(1776, '2022/03/17', '4:34 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'Percentages', 'Word problems with percentages', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>School assignment.&nbsp;</p><p>Finlay and I were working on his college textbook (Compendium - John Sort). This was about percentages, finding the percentage of a number, increasing and decreasing by a percentage.&nbsp;</p><p>Fin was able to do most of his work independently, my supervision was minimum. However, it was one problem where the student needed a lot of my help. It was about transforming from percentage to fraction and then using this on a word problem.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-17 16:34:06', '2022-03-26 10:59:36'),
(1777, '2022/03/17', '4:46 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Depreciation', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Callisto had an assignment on compound interest and depreciation which is due tomorrow. We worked on this and completed it in 45 minutes. Callisto was confident in her approach to most of the problems and only needed some small prompts on occasions. She remembered things that her teacher had said about problems which should only ever be done on the calculator. One of the questions required some calculator skills that had been learnt by the class when Callisto was absent. We worked through these but she probably needs some further practice to cement this understanding. We finished by doing some of the questions from the textbook that Callisto had missed while absent from school.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-17 16:46:10', '2022-03-17 18:21:29'),
(1778, '2022/03/17', '5:21 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Maricha Cilliers', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-17 17:21:02', '2022-03-17 17:21:02'),
(1779, '2022/03/17', '5:29 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving the four operations', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'In Progress', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Lessons\' topics:</p><ul><li>Inequalities.</li><li>Volume.</li></ul><p>We continued our work on inequalities/inequations. Our work was on, finding the answer as a family, including and not a number within the answer, and one step inequations.&nbsp;</p><p>Nicholas mentioned that his maths teacher got COVID and for that reason hasn\'t had time to answer my email. We moved to work on finding the volume of composite shapes.&nbsp;</p><p>We used Cambridge, Essential Mathematics 9.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-17 17:29:57', '2022-03-27 19:28:26'),
(1780, '2022/03/18', '7:33 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Charlotte Kratz', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>SPELLING</strong>:</p><p>opr/wpr:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>er, e, y, ai, c, kn, ow</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule Review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>4, 5, 6, 24</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>answer, reply, sail, sale, cities, city, known, know, several, desire</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>READING</strong>:</p><p>Quality Literature:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Mental Actions<br>Introduce and apply to ORF #620. Discuss meaning behind them, and bring actions to front of mind to aid with inference.</td></tr></tbody></table></', NULL, '2022-03-18 07:33:06', '2022-03-18 08:58:25'),
(1781, '2022/03/18', '7:48 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Gus Pettit', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving division by a one digit number, including those that result in a remainder', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Following up on our work from last week, Gus and I started by working on long divisions by one digit.&nbsp;</p><p>Sometimes it was hard for Gus to follow the process to solve a division. I provided a very detailed explanation to Gus with counters and some shapes to let him understand how a division works.&nbsp;</p><p>Then, Gus was able to solve long divisions without much guidance.&nbsp;</p><p>Once we finish our work with divisions, we moved to word problems. The problems were with the four operations and Gus could use the calculator. I wanted to see that Gus could know which operations and how many steps were required to solve the problems.&nbsp;</p><p>A small homework was assigned.&nbsp', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-18 07:48:07', '2022-03-27 19:59:32'),
(1783, '2022/03/18', '10:18 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Lottie Young', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Read words aloud - accurately, automatically, with expression (connected text)', 'Text of Choice (see notes)', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Billie B Brown - The Birthday Mix Up – Chapter Two (read in 7 minutes using green lens overlay).</p><p>Identify ai or ay on WVC sorting cards – sound and blend. &nbsp;Discuss when to use which and why.&nbsp;</p><p>Spelling dictation using some WVC words &nbsp;- say said, pay paid may mail ray rain lay laid (discuss sounds of ai in said and connection in meaning).</p><p>Repeat the following sentences and record: &nbsp;</p><p>I will lay down for a sleep when I return from posting the mail in the rain. (NW composed.)</p><p>I have paid, and I said to the shop keeper, may you show me where you keep the cans of beans. (Lottie composed.)</p><p>Lottie was very slow to record these sentences - it ', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-18 10:19:37', '2022-03-18 12:03:39'),
(1784, '2022/03/18', '12:07 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Archie Lester', 'English', 'Writing - Sentence Construction & Vocabulary', 'Attributes of a declarative sentence (capital letter, subject noun + action or linking verb, full stop) - States a fact or opinion', 'Articulate/explain the attributes of a declarative sentence - including the difference between fact and opinion', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Began lesson with word decoding cards: &nbsp;Homophones – laminate, read and compose oral sentences – for to, too, two, here, hear, your, you\'re, there, their, they\'re, where, wear, were. &nbsp;Archie experiences a lot of confusion around the use of these words. &nbsp;This was a most fruitful discussion.</p><p>OPR and WPR - ie, ei, ey, e, ea, th, o, er, wh</p><p>Spelling dictation - to, too, two, here, hear, there, their (they), they\'re (they are)</p><p>Discussion re the meaning of the word ‘articulate’ as an adjective and articulate (verb). &nbsp;For example, Archie is articulate.&nbsp; Archie can articulate. &nbsp;Parse these sentences with colour coding on the board.</p><p>Identify the', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-18 12:08:18', '2022-03-18 12:30:18'),
(1785, '2022/03/18', '1:45 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Esther McIver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-18 13:46:04', '2022-03-18 13:46:46'),
(1786, '2022/03/18', '1:46 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Charlie Burton', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-18 13:47:33', '2022-03-18 13:50:16'),
(1787, '2022/03/18', '1:47 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Charlie Burton', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-18 13:48:05', '2022-03-18 13:51:13'),
(1788, '2022/03/18', '2:27 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Molly Jackson', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute vowel phoneme - Kilpatrick Level J', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick J</td></tr><tr><td>Molly has come along well with her ability to substitue medial vowel sounds. Time to move up a level to segmenting consonant blends.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-58 +&nbsp; intro 59-63</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ed ew ui oa gu ough oe ey igh&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Morrison McCall. Molly did okay, however I noticed that almost immediately after she made an error (which she knew she had made), she suddenly seemed very unsure of herself for all words and completely retreated into herself.</td></tr></tbody><', NULL, '2022-03-18 14:27:31', '2022-03-18 16:11:07'),
(1789, '2022/03/18', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Annika Spedding', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>SPELLING</strong>:</p><p>opr/wpr:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>oo, a, c, ou, y, e, ow, u, i, o,&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule work:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SFE - Job 1 and 2 - refresh and make reference pages</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>WRITING</strong>:</p><p>Sentence structure:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Recap sentence structure - what is needed in any sentence. Simple Sentences</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>NOTES</strong>:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Annika was in quite an energetic mood today, and was quite difficult to settle into her lesson.<br><b', NULL, '2022-03-18 15:30:23', '2022-03-18 16:22:46'),
(1790, '2022/03/18', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Connor Thompson', 'Mathematics', 'Data Representation and Interpretation', 'Mean, median & range', 'Practice Page', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>School was POINTLESS (!!!!!) todau (not boring!!!).</td></tr><tr><td>Connor had brought in his data worksheet from school. Worked through those questions, looking at modes, bimodals, multimodals.</td></tr><tr><td>Looked at the mean. Impressed upon Connor the need to write down his workings, which he was predictably unenthused about.</td></tr><tr><td>Some of the problems in Connor\'s worksheet required a level of strategy/puzzle elements that he found tricky. E.g., the question requiring him to fill in a table twith the data set, range and mode (with some numbers filled in and some to be worked out) was tough for him.</td></tr></tbody></table></figur', NULL, '2022-03-18 15:30:56', '2022-03-18 16:27:44'),
