(1795, '2022/02/18', '4:31 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Joshua Zeeman', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Mentally summarise narrative paragraph identifying the main idea/theme', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Today Josh mentioned that he was feeling quite low about his creative writing work in his English classes. We spoke about this together, and started looking at some creative tasks to try and boost his confidence in this area. Josh was able to completley design up a block layout for 4 houses and a commercial property, with a range of different specifications (as this is the field he is interested in long term). We spoke about how this is a creative task, and he did quite well with this activity.&nbsp;<br><br>Josh also mentioned he started, and is enjoying reading, a book called \'The Inner Game Of Tennis\' regarding the psychology of sport. He seems t', NULL, '2022-03-18 16:31:49', '2022-03-18 17:44:30'),
(1796, '2022/02/18', '4:32 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Solve 1 to 2 steps equations', 'Textbooks, problems on the board, made up problems', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Archie mentioned that at school he\'s working on long divisions and multiplications. He mentioned that these topics aren\'t very challenging and he\'s able to do more complicated problems.&nbsp;</p><p>Considering the student\'s progress and that in mental computation and solving problems involving the four operations, I decided to start to work on linear equations.&nbsp;</p><p>Before starting to dig down on equations, Archie and I spent about 30 minutes reviewing index and sign law, BODMAS and adding/taking away algebraic expressions.&nbsp;</p><p>I introduced equations to Archie and were solving 1 step equations involving only additions and substructions. However, we used fractions and decima', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-18 16:32:35', '2022-03-23 21:12:14'),
(1797, '2022/03/18', '4:53 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Joshua Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-18 16:54:20', '2022-03-18 16:55:01'),
(1798, '2022/03/21', '7:32 a.m.', '1', '5', 'Darcy Callaghan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked well through the phonos. Didn\'t manage to get the \'ough\' sounds even after I went through them. Did a few for WPR and he got all of them right. Was running out of time so decided to start reading matilda to get a bit of reading in. seems to rush the words still but is doing a better job at using the full stops and commas. still tries to guess the words rather than trying to sound them out only able to pull him up on it when i can see the book too so next week he will bring in his version of matilda too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-21 07:32:03', '2022-04-05 18:45:56'),
(1799, '2022/03/21', '8:45 a.m.', '1', '7', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from two syllable word - Kilpatrick Level D', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Seven</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 21 March 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick D1</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #7</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>OPR/WPR: gu ph oe ey</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Review SFE jobs - sort cards into relevant job</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Pip &amp; Tim - \"The Rat\"</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Homework: SFE job 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>LP was really good with PA and MA, I was impressed. Lots of prompting needed with OPR/W', NULL, '2022-03-21 08:45:13', '2022-03-21 09:43:59'),
(1800, '2022/03/21', '10:04 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>public holiday</p>', NULL, '2022-03-21 10:05:04', '2022-03-22 09:28:07'),
(1801, '2022/03/21', '9:28 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Luke Vandenberg', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick H2</p><p>Notes Luke seemed to struggle more with initial consonant blends in which /r/ was the second sound, however he does very nicely with /l/ as a second sound!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR WPR</p><p>55-63</p><p>1. ck<br>2. gu<br>3. wr<br>4. gn<br>5. kn</p><p>Luke was a little bit confused with /g/, reading the /u/ as an /n/. However overall, Luke did great! He made no substantial errors and was confident.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule</p><p>26, 18, 19</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD</p><p>soon<br>C a m e<br>Sun day r.26 (caps), 18 (ay)<br>show<br>Mon day r.26 (caps), 18 (ay)<br>moon<br>yet<br>Find r. 19 (/i/ says I bc it’s followed by 2 consonants)<br>Giv e 2<br>new<br>&nbsp;</p><p>OF<br>500<br', NULL, '2022-03-21 10:18:15', '2022-03-28 10:24:56'),
(1802, '2022/03/21', '10:47 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Jacob Tipping', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Components - read accurately, recognise words automatically, read without hesitation, read with expression', 'Articulate/explain the meaning of fluency and list components', 'Juno Galang', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Public holiday</p>', NULL, '2022-03-21 10:49:23', '2022-03-21 10:50:07'),
(1803, '2022/03/21', '2:16 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 1: Write qu to say /kw/ > q is always followed by u', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'To Be Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Mia is a very talkative little girl who loves drawing. She performances a good and legit handwriting.&nbsp;</p><p>Phonological awareness: Kilpattrick F1.&nbsp;</p><p>I spy with words---Mia likes this game and like every kid, she likes to win. She looked tired and did not want to stand up and jump around.</p><p>OPR---try not to moo oral phonogram review game. She loves this game and showed progress in the multi sound phonograms.</p><p>WPR/SD: rule page one, rule 1-3. Mia absorbs knowledge quickly and she usually comprehends fast.</p><p>Homework about rule 1-3 will be sent to home.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-21 14:16:00', '2022-03-22 09:28:48'),
(1804, '2022/03/21', '2:27 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Gabriel Bohm', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked really well with the phono cards. Got confused with a few, still getting stumped on \'ou\'. Worked through some words that have the phonograms in them rather than going from the ayres words. Was able to figure out quite a few words after the first few when he realised he could just say words that rhyme. tried to play four-letter wordle for a bit but wasn\'t really able to think of any words other than the ones he could see around the room. continued with his imaginary animal which we made a storyboard for.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-21 14:27:15', '2022-04-05 18:38:13'),
(1805, '2022/03/21', '2:32 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Harlow Booy', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Count collections to 100 by partitioning numbers using place value', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>We continued working with place value and now we were using place value to add numbers. I showed Harlow how we use place value to carry numbers over the next column number.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>This lesson was delivered on 18.03.2022</p>', '2022-03-21 14:32:08', '2022-07-02 10:58:13'),
(1806, '2022/03/21', '2:32 p.m.', '1', '3', 'Harlow Booy', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Develop confidence with number sequences to and from 100 by ones from any starting point', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>After SENA 1 from last week, Harlow and I were working on place value, we did up to 1000\'s column and did many problems related like these:</p><p>If we have 4561, how many do we have in the 1000\'s, 100\'s, 10\'s and 1\'s?&nbsp;</p><p>Comparing numbers, 6524, 6254, and 4652 which number has the highest/lowest 1000\'s, 100\'s, 10\'s and 1\'s.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>The lesson was delivered on 04.03.2022</p>', '2022-03-21 14:32:08', '2022-07-02 10:34:19'),
(1807, '2022/03/21', '3:31 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Solve 1 to 2 steps equations', 'Textbooks, problems on the board, made up problems', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>We picked our work today from what we did on Friday.&nbsp;</p><p>Went straight to solve 1 step equations on the board involving the 4 arithmetical operations.</p><p>Archie showed a good understanding of this kind of equation. In the next 30 minutes of the lesson, we spent time-solving multiple steps equations with whole numbers.&nbsp;</p><p>When we problems required to use one +, and 2 or more times and divisions, Archie solved the problems correctly. Sometimes I helped him with the negatives but he did most of the job. However, when doing more than 2 two additions/take away, he had some difficulties; particularly with integers.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-21 15:31:24', '2022-03-23 21:40:18'),
(1808, '2022/03/21', '3:31 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Charlie Burton', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>SPELLING:</strong></p><p>opr/wpr:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>e, ea, ti, ur, er, ng</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule Review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>4, 6, 20, 22</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>extremely, extreme, fearful, fear, functional, function, furniture, future, gathering</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>WRITING:</strong></p><p>Writing Process - planning:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Continue persuasive essay planning in prep for NAPLAN</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>NOTES:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><t', NULL, '2022-03-21 15:31:37', '2022-03-21 16:20:59'),
(1809, '2022/03/21', '3:37 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Elsa Clennett', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-50</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ou ow dge eigh ea ch oi ng ed wr</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Challenge word\' dictated from rule pages: written. Also acted as a rule 9 review.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: NA</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: voyage-wrong</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use Ayres words in written sentence.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Writing Proces', NULL, '2022-03-21 15:37:09', '2022-03-29 15:05:13'),
(1810, '2022/03/21', '3:54 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Jacob Tipping', 'English', 'Reading - Comprehension > Text Type & Mental Actions', 'Stated/Implied/Inferred Meaning', 'Key Into Inference', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick H2</p><p>Suffix -<br>cut<br>cut+s<br>cut+ting<br>some + compound<br>Jacob enthusiastically filled out a morphology list with \"some\" as a base word for compound words. He was able to explain the meaning of a base word, suffix, and compound word.</p><p>OPR/WPR<br>er<br>ir<br>ur<br>wor<br>ear<br>ea<br>ng</p><p>Notes<br>Jacob is good to go with his 5 \"er\"s and will move up next week!</p><p>Handwriting<br>/g/ /f/<br>Jacob was a little confused with his /g/ formation, starting at the bottom for both.</p><p>Rule Outline<br>18, \"ay\" end of base word<br><br>Ayres Section A-G&nbsp;<br>hat<br>child<br>ice<br>play r. 18<br>sea<br>see<br>bird<br>cool<br>earth<br>feed</p><p>Inference Key Not', NULL, '2022-03-21 16:03:54', '2022-03-28 09:54:19'),
(1811, '2022/03/21', '4:29 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Connor McLaren', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Seven</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 21 March 2022</td></tr><tr><td>No LS</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #4</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Write a paragraph, consider time management. Go through all steps of the WP. Writing prompt: What dog breed is the best, and why?</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Just CM today. He brought his YuGiOh cards in, so it took a while for him to settle as he was trying to show me his cards. We did PA, MA, and then I got CM stuck into his paragraph task straight away. CM really wasn\'t keen to do a plan', NULL, '2022-03-21 16:29:11', '2022-03-21 17:21:13'),
(1812, '2022/03/21', '4:30 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Angus Singleton', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Went over NAPLAN practice today. Went really well up until we got to decimals and fractions because he said he had no idea about any of it. I gave him a refresher and then ended up spending most of the lesson on it. He was struggling to understand the equivalent fractions and decimals and how we could convert them into one another. tried to time the pages and give him at most 5 mins for every question but for some of the questions, he seemed to need a lot more than 5 mins purely because he didn\'t know how to solve the fraction questions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-21 16:30:47', '2022-04-06 15:07:32'),
(1813, '2022/03/21', '4:36 p.m.', '1', '4', 'Arki Young', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: H1. Gave Arki 3 attempts with scaffolding which helped him get in the swing of it. After this he could complete with 100% accuracy</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 45-63 + 2nd go through shuffled</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: oe ey igh kn wr au gn gu ea</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 29</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: woman-plan</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp', NULL, '2022-03-21 16:36:48', '2022-03-21 17:53:22'),
(1814, '2022/03/21', '4:46 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Lachlan Smith', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ellie Connor', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-21 16:47:00', '2022-03-21 16:47:00'),
(1815, '2022/03/21', '4:47 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'To Be Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Thomas can be quite hyperactive sometimes when he is in a good mood. He shows frustration &nbsp;a lot when he can\'t remember something he has learned. I usually go easy on him about this.&nbsp;</p><p>I had to ask him to deep breathe to be calm in the middle of the lesson. He then calmed down and concentrated more.&nbsp;</p><p>Progress: Thomas can finally say the 3 sounds for u at once today. He has gained progress on the phonograms 1-26.&nbsp;</p><p>He grasped quite quickly about the rule 1-4 today, as well as the marking system.&nbsp;</p><p>OPR: he needed help with l, a, y and u.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-21 16:48:21', '2022-03-21 16:54:18'),
(1816, '2022/03/21', '5:31 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Zac Pharaoh', 'Mathematics', 'Percentages', 'Word problems with percentages', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We continued our work on:</p><ul><li>Use excel/Google sheets to calculate percentages, mean, mode, range, median.&nbsp;</li><li>Calculate profit/loss</li><li>Best buys.</li><li>Increase/decrease percentages by lower tan 1 percentages.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Overall, Zac is making progress on how to create formulas on the programs. He\'s able to follow the instruction to calculate percentages, discounts and increases of a quantity.&nbsp;</p><p>All the examples and data used were made up problems. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-21 17:31:28', '2022-03-23 20:54:01'),
(1817, '2022/03/22', '7:47 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Tiki Salt', 'English', 'Writing - Sentence Construction & Vocabulary', 'Sentence structure - there are three ways to construct a sentence > simple, compound, complex', 'Recognise/Analyse/Compose/Model simple/compound/complex sentences that demonstrate meaning & usage of unfamiliar spelling words', 'Campbell Jepson', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tiki was less sleepy this lesson and worked well to begin with. We played wordle for a bit and then moved on to the phonos for warm-up. The \"ou\' and the \'ough\' got him. On the second time round, he got them all right though with prompts. Did 9 words of dictation, he was confused a lot whenever he needed to put an \'s; sound in whether or not to use a c or an s. got him to write them all into sentences which were all good and fine and finished off with a quick game of darts</p>', NULL, '2022-03-22 07:47:27', '2022-04-05 18:51:49'),
