(1824, '2022/03/22', '2:26 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Max Shapiro', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Challenge: frown</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-39 + introduce ea aw au or ck wh. I asked Max if he would like some harder phonograms to learn and he said yes, because he felt his current ones were too easy. I gave his OPR to him shuffled today to double check if he could do them out of order (he did fine). Most of his issues with the phonograms occur in the WPR.</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ea aw au or ck wh</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>In the WPR, I commended Max on his r formation. Max said: \"I\'m doing them the right way around because I can\'t be bot', NULL, '2022-03-22 14:26:53', '2022-03-22 16:47:49'),
(1825, '2022/03/22', '3:29 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Lachlan Prior', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Bit hard through zoom today but after a while, we figured everything out and got everything working. Ran through phonos up to 40 and did well but got confused with \'ou\' \'ui\' and the \'er\' sounds got confusing for him without the prompts in front of him. moved onto WPR for the ones he got confused with and got all of them right.we then moved onto dictation with the words he misspelled in the draft of his story. a lot of them involved just adding a suffix on and wasn\'t realising the base word for most of them. finished off with a bit of reading which he did really well on but seemed to be guessing a few words and only sounding them out after I pull him up on them.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-22 15:29:56', '2022-04-05 18:56:45'),
(1826, '2022/03/22', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Esther McIver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>SPELLING</strong>:</p><p>opr/wpr:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ee, g, ow, o, i, ng, ey</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>4, 5, 6, 11</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling Dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>freeze, gentle, grow, holes, hotel, iron, living, live, monkey, myself</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>WRITING</strong>:</p><p>Writing Process:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Refresh Writing Process, and begin planning \'cat and fish\' prompt story.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>NOTES</strong>:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><', NULL, '2022-03-22 15:30:38', '2022-03-22 16:40:50'),
(1827, '2022/03/22', '3:31 p.m.', '1', '5', 'Stella Bowerman', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked on fractions today and the equivalent fractions. Worked well through the uno times tables game and is definitely getting quicker with her answers. We moved to fractions where she took a while to pick up what we were doing. She was getting confused with the equivalent fractions because the pictures i was using weren\'t relatable enough. we worked on how to put an improper fraction into a mixed number and a mixed number back into an improper fraction.</p>', NULL, '2022-03-22 15:31:26', '2022-04-06 15:03:52'),
(1828, '2022/03/22', '3:37 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>10/10 for Sophie!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: igh ey a c g au aw ea ur oo ow ou ie dge ei eigh tch augh our</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: igh ey a c g ea ow ou dge&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 5 6 11</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: iron-monkey</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></t', NULL, '2022-03-22 15:37:36', '2022-03-22 17:08:16'),
(1829, '2022/03/22', '3:42 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 46 > 54', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Brock was late today but he was in a very good concentration today. He likes the hands-on sentence structures building blocks.&nbsp;</p><p>Phonological awareness: killpattrick H1</p><p>OPR-try not to moo ch, oa, ew, s, er, gu, ph, ough</p><p>WPR ch, oa, ew, s, er, gu, ph, ough<br>Brock needed help with gu, ew, ph and ough.&nbsp;</p><p>Rule 17 review activity---drew a happy face for words that are correct, and a sad face for wrong words I wrote on the pinkboard. Brock liked this a lot. It was more efficient to help him remember rule 17.&nbsp;</p><p>SD: Section M walk-smallest<br>&nbsp;</p><p>We introduced and practiced compound sentence.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-22 15:42:45', '2022-03-22 17:46:59'),
(1830, '2022/03/22', '4:22 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Shay Douglas', 'Chemistry', 'Chemistry', 'Chemistry', 'Chemistry', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Chemistry</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Shay\'s Chemistry assignment/worksheet</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Independent study</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Shay requested an hour of independent study time to work on his chemistry assignment. He said he wanted to \"get ahead of the game\" and get it out of the way. I thought this was great time management and very responsible on his part! He needed very little assistance from me throughout the hour.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-03-22 16:22:43', '2022-03-22 17:20:12'),
(1831, '2022/03/22', '4:29 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Introduce the concept of variables as a way of representing numbers using letters', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>I decided to start working with Algebra. Probably Ava will be looking at this in some weeks and it\'s important she gets familiar with the language of algebra.&nbsp;</p><p>Even though the lesson was myself speaking, Ava was fully engaged. She finds the use of numbers and letters interesting to solve problems. Also, Ava had questions about what is the difference between 4X and X to the power of 4. Using real-life examples, I explained this to Ava.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-22 16:29:18', '2022-07-02 08:50:09'),
(1832, '2022/03/22', '4:30 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-22 16:30:24', '2022-04-12 18:08:21'),
(1833, '2022/03/22', '4:30 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 50', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luca and I started today with a randomised&nbsp; &nbsp;multiplication grid. He was able to knock most of the \'easy\' rows off in the 7min timer, but it still took him over the time limit to answer all questions (11 min 44 sec). We did this grid twice, as Luca felt he could do a lot better than the first time.<br><br>Luca mentioned that he was looking at money in school today, so our lesson was tailored around this. Luca and I looked at financial maths problems (if 4 people have varying amounts, and are trying to pay equal amounts towards a fixed figure, how many does each person need to achieve this?). Luca tried to go about this a rather complicate', NULL, '2022-03-22 16:30:45', '2022-03-22 17:39:27'),
(1834, '2022/03/22', '4:34 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callum is working very hard. He has a low level of spelling as he is not farmiliar with the phonograms yet, especially u, ch, e, and a.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>kilpatrick F1</li><li>OPR/WPR:<strong> u, x, a, e, i, ch.</strong></li><li><strong>new phonogram ea</strong></li><li><strong>Callum needed help with u, x, ch, a, and e. He has problems to say multi sounds in a row. It\'s almost like that his brain keeps cutting off on the sound sequence even if he can say individual sound perfectly.&nbsp;</strong></li><li><strong>Rule page 1. We have learned rule 1-6. Working on rule 7 (silent final e\'s).&nbsp;</strong></li><li><strong>He did not have much problems with them and had a very active learning ', NULL, '2022-03-22 16:34:09', '2022-03-22 17:53:59'),
(1835, '2022/03/22', '5:40 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Tyler Van Nimwegen', 'Study Skills', 'Research', 'See Notes', 'See Notes...', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I worked on his health assignment today which included&nbsp;<br><br>The effects of ice are:&nbsp;<br>The long term effects of ice are:&nbsp;<br>The effects of ice withdrawal:&nbsp;<br><br>We started the writing process to address his assignment, starting with planning and research. Tyler was able to use a thesaurus to help summarise his notes. He found it a bit challenging to decide which words to use in the thesaurus, but quickly asked for help and actually attempted to read the words out loud! He also brought the rubric and is now showing understanding on why the rubric is important. We went through which points he needed to address and which once were missing from his initial', NULL, '2022-03-22 17:41:10', '2022-03-22 17:42:29');
