(1836, '2022/03/22', '5:43 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Callen Bartlett', 'English', 'Reading - Comprehension > Text Type & Mental Actions', 'Stated/Implied/Inferred Meaning', 'Key Into Inference', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callan</p><p>Kilpatrick G2<br>Callan found this task a little difficult today, moreso than last week - might be tired!</p><p>OPR/WPR<br>ur<br>ea<br>ng<br>er<br>wor<br>ear<br>ir<br>Callan briefly struggled between \"ear\" and \"er\", but was able to self correct! He is now able to move on.</p><p>Cursive G</p><p>R. 4, 5, 26, SFE 1, 5<br>Focus: Rule 26 CAPITALS names, places, days, months, special events</p><p>Morphology: send<br>Callan</p><p>then<br>house<br>year<br>to<br>I<br>as<br>send<br>a lone<br>lone<br>one</p><p>Inference L1 SP2 I7<br>Callan was a little confused with today\'s excerpt, but was able to answer once it was scaffolded!</p><p>OF: 516<br>Error: \"Decided = Designed\" \"Rent levels ', NULL, '2022-03-22 17:44:10', '2022-03-28 09:31:03'),
(1837, '2022/03/22', '5:50 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Read words aloud - accurately, automatically, with expression (words in isolation)', 'Ayres Words List - Spelling Notebook', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Stella<br>Donah 7<br><br>OPR<br>a, c, d, g, o, f<br>WPR<br>d, g, o, f<br><br>Handwriting Sheet /g/<br><br>Word matching:<br>/g/, “heart” “cupcake” “bear”<br><br>Spelling<br>dad<br>dog<br>go</p><p>Stella completed all her tasks and responded especially well to being the \"teacher\". She was able to go through her phonograms and spelling, especially when made into a game-like format. She continues to struggle between /b/ and /d/, and /q/ and /g/. Her /g/ letters were especially impressive today! She was also able to articulate between upper and lowercase letters.</p>', NULL, '2022-03-22 17:51:16', '2022-03-28 14:03:06'),
(1838, '2022/03/22', '6:30 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Isaac got COVID and Jo didn\'t let us know.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-03-22 18:30:54', '2022-07-03 18:48:53'),
(1839, '2022/03/22', '6:31 p.m.', '1', '2', 'Joseph Martin', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-22 18:31:30', '2022-03-22 18:31:30'),
(1840, '2022/03/23', '9:59 a.m.', '1', '7', 'Nina Gust', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phonemic Awareness<br>Kilpatrick: H2<br>Notes<br>Fleas = Fees<br>Nina did great as usual! She took a little longer decoding but once she got into the groove, she was fine.</p><p><br>OPR<br>31-38<br>Ou Oo Ch Ar Ay Ai Oy Oi &nbsp;<br>Notes<br>This was Nina’s first time learning these phonograms and she did wonderfully! She previously thought that /ay/ was not able to be used in the middle of a word, so we went through /ay/ placements.</p><p><br>WPR<br>31-38<br>Ou Oo Ch Ar Ay Ai Oy Oi &nbsp;<br>Notes<br>I was only expecting Nina to do /ou/ /ar/ and /oo/ today, but she managed to do all 8 from the OPR! She fumbled a little with the multi sounds, but this was her first time.</p><p><br>Handwrit', NULL, '2022-03-23 10:00:18', '2022-03-28 13:42:15'),
(1841, '2022/03/23', '10:10 a.m.', '1', '7', 'Hunter McNees', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phonemic Awareness<br>Kilpatrick: G2&nbsp;<br>Notes<br>Hunter found it very hard to concentrate!<br>Fig = Fib<br>Nog = Nod<br>Cut s.c</p><p><br>OPR<br>46-54<br>Aw Au Or Ck Wh Ed Ew Ui Oa Gu<br>Notes<br>Hunter did well! He was able to state the first sound of each phonogram but needed help with the second and third sounds.</p><p><br>WPR<br>46-54<br>Ed Ew Ui Oa Gu &nbsp;<br>Notes<br>Hunter initially was confused with /ui/ and wrote as /ei/, but self-corrected! He especially enjoys the example of /gu/ in “guacamole”.</p><p><br>Handwriting Manuscript G<br>Notes<br>Hunter initially formed his uppercase “g” upside down, but we were able to correct.</p><p><br>Morphology<br>Donah no. 7<br>Compoun', NULL, '2022-03-23 10:11:59', '2022-03-28 09:45:02'),
