(1844, '2022/03/23', '3:29 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) with Stated Purpose - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We started with some physical activity today and Phoebe liked it a lot. She became excited in the class and hence, it is a bit hard to keep her concentrated after this activity. She is trying to chat all the time and do things like getting water, throwing rubbish to kill time so that she doesn\'t have to learn much. This has been a bit headache and I need to better organize the time during our lesson. Phoebe used playdo to make phonograms and she loved it!</p><p>Phonograms: Phoebe needs help with multi sound phonograms. SHould we move to this stage? or maybe stay at the basic stage where we focus on only first sound? She especially confuses with c and k.&nbsp;</p><p>We have been learning r', NULL, '2022-03-23 15:29:56', '2022-03-23 16:39:13'),
