(1846, '2022/03/23', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '6', 'Toby Webb', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-23 15:30:38', '2022-03-23 15:30:38'),
(1847, '2022/03/23', '3:31 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Toby Webb', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focused on the vowels today and all their sounds. Ran through all the sounds and got him to think of words that corresponded. Couldn\'t really think of many without a lot of prompts ad pushing. Did a heap of words with dictation and made sentences out of them all. he wrote a couple of sentences that didn\'t really make sense so got him to rewrite a few. finished off with some reading and was good but is seeming to guess the words to a point where he\'s not even trying to read it.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-23 15:31:02', '2022-04-05 18:59:45'),
(1848, '2022/03/23', '3:43 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Investigate everyday situations that use integers. Locate and represent these numbers on a number line', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Following up on our work from last week, in this lesson Connor and I worked with operations with integers and decimals.</p><p>Sometimes Connor got confused with the sign law and just added or took away integers. For instance, if he would need to solve, -4-3-2-1 = positive 10&nbsp;</p><p>Connor is progressing with decimals, he does operations correctly and in a short time. However, we need to revisit divisions later in the term.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-23 15:43:19', '2022-07-03 17:32:10'),
