(1858, '2022/03/24', '7:26 a.m.', '1', '5', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Investigate index notation and represent whole numbers as products of powers of prime numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'To Be Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we worked towards: Recognise and representing division as grouping into equal sets and solving simple problems using these representations.</p><p>We looked at:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>equal groups</li><li>partition</li><li>fact family</li><li>repeated subtraction</li><li>short division.</li></ul><p>At the end of the lesson, Nate commented that he likes being in Educate Tutoring rather than going to school. And he asked me if he just could stay there and not go to school.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 5 was delivered on 17.03.2022</p>', '2022-03-24 07:26:33', '2022-07-03 10:34:02'),
(1859, '2022/03/24', '7:54 a.m.', '1', '6', 'Chester Vincent', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Started off with the book and story that he wrote at home. Read through that for me and got stumped with the \'igh\' in right. Began the phono cards and went through the same ones with WPR. Went through OPR and WPR with no problems but the \'ou\' still is getting him. went to the dartboard to see how many dictation words we were doing and got 7. went through the marking process with him for a bit so we could work on them a bit. seemed to get it but got a bit confused when i started talking about rule 4 so going to save that for the next lesson.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-24 07:54:04', '2022-04-05 19:03:45'),
