(1871, '2022/03/26', '10:47 a.m.', '1', '7', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'Percentages', 'Word problems with percentages', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Slowly but steady, Finlay is grasping the concept of percentage. He\'s using the calculator less often and can find percentages by 10 base numbers without it.&nbsp;</p><p>Today we continued to work on his college textbook. We solved about 10 problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-26 10:48:34', '2022-03-26 11:02:44'),
(1872, '2022/03/27', '6:29 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Shape', '3D', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'In Progress', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Lesson\'s topics:</p><ul><li>Mathematical logic. (<a href=\"https://www.timestables.co.uk/)\">https://www.timestables.co.uk/)</a>&nbsp;</li><li>Volume of composite shapes.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>During the first 15 minutes of the lesson, we were working on mathematical logic by using times tables.&nbsp;</p><p>Then, we moved to work on finding the volume of composite shapes.&nbsp;</p><p>Overall, Nicholas did a good job with the second topic. However, sometimes he forgets how to combine the formulas of volume with half and other fractions of spheres and pyramids.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-27 18:30:11', '2022-03-27 19:39:53'),
(1873, '2022/03/27', '7:40 p.m.', '1', '7', 'Gus Pettit', 'Mathematics', 'Decimals', 'Operations with decimals', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we were working with fractions, operations and the relationship with percentages.&nbsp;</p><p>At the beginning of the lesson, Gus was confused with all operations. He couldn\'t recall how to perform operations with fractions. However, after a very detailed explanation involving shapes and a song, he was able to do the operations with fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>During the last 20 minutes, we were working on increasing and decreasing by percentages. I showed Gus how to do this and his homework is about this.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-03-27 19:43:18', '2022-07-02 14:06:01'),
