(1892, '2022/03/29', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '8', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick G2</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR:&nbsp; 44-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ph kn wr gu eigh ea ie ei</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule intro: Rule 12</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Rule Page 5</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use words in oral sent', NULL, '2022-03-29 15:31:35', '2022-03-29 16:57:44'),
(1893, '2022/03/29', '4:08 p.m.', '1', '8', 'Stella Bowerman', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Started off with the uno maths game and answered all the questions really quickly even 6x7 which usually gets to her. We spend the next bit filling out a multiplication treasure hunt which I gave her the times tables it was on and she had to figure it out, did pretty well at that. she ended up doing a lot of counting up from 0 which I\'ve been trying to discourage because of easier methods. moved onto NAPLAN practice which we went through pretty easily only stopping when there was a fraction question or worded question to go deeper on.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-03-29 16:10:23', '2022-04-06 15:04:48'),
(1894, '2022/03/29', '4:24 p.m.', '1', '8', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'MAD MINUTE MATHS FACTS TO 50', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>WARM UP:</strong></p><p>Multiplication grid - mixed numbers</p><p><strong>FOCUS/TASKS:</strong></p><p>Finance problem solving (how much more does each person need)</p><p>Decimal addition/subtraction</p><p>Rounding (to the nearest $10)</p><p><strong>NOTES:</strong></p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luca started with his multiplication grid again this week. He managed to completely solve the grid in 10min and 53 sec. Luca also mentioned that he is in the highest level for his multiplication at school.<br><br>Luca and I continued solving the maths problem from last week. He remembered how to do this well, and was able to correctly follow the procedure showing his working', NULL, '2022-03-29 16:33:59', '2022-03-29 17:10:59'),
(1895, '2022/03/29', '4:40 p.m.', '1', '8', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Definition - the reading of words automatically, without hesitation, and with expression', 'Articulate the definition of the term \'fluency\'', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Thomas\'s lesson was rescheduled from Monday to Tuesday this week, and me and Juno had a jointed lesson today. Thomas seemed liked it as he was quite advanced compared to Stella. He was doing very well today and actively finished all activities during our lesson!</p><p>WPR: Thomas forms certain letters in a wrong way, such as a, g. He would start from the bottom for g sometimes, so we have been working on his clock letter handwriting today and I have sent homework relating to this.&nbsp;</p><p>CVC: Thomas can clearly recognize vowels and consonants in a word. We four played strawberry smash and he did great.&nbsp;</p><p>Marking system: we practiced marking system through the first 2 pages ', NULL, '2022-03-29 16:47:05', '2022-03-29 16:57:54'),
(1896, '2022/03/29', '4:58 p.m.', '1', '8', 'Shay Douglas', 'Chemistry', 'Chemistry', 'Chemistry', 'Chemistry', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Chemistry</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Independent study for Shay\'s chemistry test on the 30/3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Activity: Note taking/refinement</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Shay had a chemistry test the next day. The test was open book, so he had brought in his notes from class and asked if he could work on making sure they contained all the information he thought he\'d need, and also work on making some of his note pages neater/easier to understand.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>E.g. his notes were very scribbly and a bit all over the place, ', NULL, '2022-03-29 17:00:45', '2022-03-29 17:26:15'),
