(1903, '2022/03/30', '3:30 p.m.', '1', '8', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We had a great lesson today!</p><p>Phoebe is a very physical student who loves hands-on activities. We have been developing a good direction for our lesson lately since I had a chat with Heather and Juno inters of Phoebe\'s learning.&nbsp;</p><p>I have been focusing on finishing a few targets each lesson and make it repetitive yet still fun. She loves handwriting, coloring, jumping activities.&nbsp;</p><p>OPR: 1-33. we used twist game for this and she loves it. Phoebe doesn\'t seem getting phonograms ow, ou, oo, ch. We will just need to focus on the first 30 ohonograms. She now knows all sounds for vowels.&nbsp;</p><p>WPR: clockface letters handwriting. a,c, d, f, g, o,s, qu. SHe did a grea', NULL, '2022-03-30 15:31:46', '2022-03-30 18:46:45'),
(1905, '2022/03/30', '4:39 p.m.', '1', '8', 'Luke Gomer', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Spelling Assessment for Ayres Placement', 'Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment - List 1', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><i><strong>SPELLING</strong></i>:</p><p>Morrison McCall Test</p><p><i><strong>WRITING</strong></i>:</p><ul><li>Grammar work - looking at grammar and punctuation in sentences</li><li>Refresh sentence types and structure - orally talk about these, then dictate them into Luke\'s book</li></ul><p><i><strong>NOTES</strong></i>:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luke and I completed a Morrison today to see where he was at. He has made a net gain of 1y10m since starting with ET (raw score went up 2y3m). Luke has made some incredible gains in his spelling work, and it was wonderful to watch the way he was sounding his words as he came across them in his writing.<br><br>Luke was very a', NULL, '2022-03-30 16:40:20', '2022-03-30 17:26:50'),
(1906, '2022/03/30', '4:57 p.m.', '1', '8', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-03-30 16:57:33', '2022-03-30 16:59:33'),
