(1943, '2022/04/05', '03:16 pm', '1', '9', 'Esther McIver', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Spelling Assessment for Ayres Placement', 'Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment - List 1', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-05 15:32:37', '2022-04-05 15:50:46'),
(1944, '2022/04/05', '03:15 pm', '1', '9', 'Stella Bowerman', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Working on the perimeter and area today. Taking a bit of time to wrap her head around it. We worked for a while on the formulas and wrote them down but didn\'t quite understand. The way to figure out the perimeter seemed to be a bit more difficult than just plus all the sides together she started multiplying by the product of two sides. by question 4 she seemed to get the hang of it and was able to answer the rest of the questions by herself. Towards the end of the lesson, she was able to accurately find the perimeter of shapes and find the area for squares and rectangles.</p>', NULL, '2022-04-05 15:35:30', '2022-04-06 15:05:47'),
(1945, '2022/04/05', '04:12 pm', '1', '9', 'Charlie Burton', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-05 16:14:37', '2022-04-05 16:15:34'),
(1946, '2022/04/05', '04:16 pm', '1', '8', 'Annika Spedding', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-05 16:16:50', '2022-04-05 16:18:25'),
(1947, '2022/04/05', '04:16 pm', '1', '8', 'Joshua Zeeman', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose third-person narrative paragraph', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Josh and I began discussing ethical standpoints again this week, and decided to formulate a game that confirms and uplifts the various standpoints of different perspectives. Josh was quite good at this activity, and was brainstorming solutions to potential problems that arose in the brainstorming session. It would be good to use some butchers paper to map out how the game will work, and perhaps present Josh with some parameters for next weeks lesson.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-05 16:17:10', '2022-04-05 16:24:57'),
(1948, '2022/04/05', '04:36 pm', '1', '9', 'Shay Douglas', 'Study Skills', 'Research', 'See Notes', 'See Notes...', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>See Neve\'s excel spreadsheet - can\'t upload lengthy comment due to server error</p>', NULL, '2022-04-05 16:37:37', '2022-04-05 17:25:47'),
(1949, '2022/04/05', '04:37 pm', '1', '9', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>PA: Kilpatrick G2 -- SM has been doing this at home, and she now has 100% accuracy! Move up a level next week.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR: 54-70</p><p>WPR: oa gu ey kn dge ei</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SM requested some eigh drills, sent home dge / eigh worksheet</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review: 5 6 12 17</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD: myself-pull</p><p>Read R&amp;S</p><p>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</p><p>Rule Intro: NA</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sentences: Use Ayres words in sentences.</p><p>Sentences: Use ie words from last week in sentences to demonstrate meaning between believe/belief. Believe/lie and brief/belief.</p><p>Talked about which part of speech believe and belief were (verb and noun respectively). Sophie really struggled to make sense of this, so I demonstrated the similar relationship between think/thought. I think this helped -- I might try and find some other word pairs that fit this pattern, and will keep demonstrating the differences in future.</p>', NULL, '2022-04-05 16:37:59', '2022-04-11 12:21:30'),
(1950, '2022/04/05', '04:58 pm', '1', '9', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Solve problems involving purchases and the calculation of change to the nearest five cents.', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-05 16:58:45', '2022-04-05 16:59:45'),
(1951, '2022/04/05', '03:35 pm', '1', '9', 'Lachlan Prior', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-05 17:35:22', '2022-04-05 17:35:22'),
(1952, '2022/04/05', '06:44 pm', '1', '8', 'Darcy Callaghan', 'English', 'Reading - Fluency & Prosody', 'Read words aloud - accurately, automatically, with expression (connected text)', 'Oral reading fluency practice passage - Spalding Level 100', 'Campbell Jepson', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'To Be Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Worked really well with the phonos this morning. Got confused between the \'ou\' and \'ough\' and took a while to figure out what the sounds for \'ed\' were. Got \'ui\' and \'ei\' wrong in WPR but understood his mistake so didn\'t have to go too deep on it. the only word in dictation he got wrong was \"importance\' as he used an \'s\' instead of \'ce\' mainly because he rushed into spelling it and didn\'t really look at my fingers. made the words into sentences that had a few spelling errors \'crumbel\'. finished off with some reading of a book he brought in which there were a few words he just guessed still and tried to rush through it.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-04-05 18:45:04', '2022-04-05 18:47:42'),
(1953, '2022/04/05', '06:53 pm', '1', '9', 'Tiki Salt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-05 18:53:58', '2022-04-05 18:53:58'),
(1954, '2022/04/06', '09:57 am', '1', '9', 'Nina Gust', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR<br>31-38<br>• (Speed) This task was completed quickly<br>• The student found some difficulty with the multiple sounds of /ou/ and the last sound of /ch/<br>• However, the student showed confidence with distinguishing between /au/ vs /aw/ and /ou/ vs /ow/</p><p><br>WPR<br>31-38<br>• (Speed) This task was completed at a regular pace<br>• They were able to complete the entire set perfectly!</p><p><br>Handwriting Manuscript I &amp; J<br>Notes<br>• (Speed) This task was completed quickly<br>• The student found some difficulty with “j” formation, starting from the bottom up<br>• However, the student showed confidence with “I”!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>S.D<br>Rule(s): Focus on marking multi phonos, r.4 and r. 8 with last week’s SD Ayres section: A-G<br>Cream | Block | Ice | Gold | Sold<br>boat | &nbsp;| &nbsp;| &nbsp;|&nbsp;<br>Notes<br>• (Speed) This task was completed at a regular pace<br>• The student found some difficulty in identifying multi phonos<br>• However, the student showed confidence in identifying multi phonos once scaffolded</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OF: 200 Line: 9<br>S.C: “float” “near” “a = his”<br>Errors: “the = a” “hiding”<br>Notes<br>• (Speed) This task was completed successfully<br>• The student found some difficulty with pronouncing /r/ as /w/ in some words<br>• However, the student showed confidence with prosody and pronouncing her words clearly<br>• They were able to complete up to the second last sentence</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing<br>Section: Simple sentences: Write a sentence with the words “gold”, “sold” and “book”<br>Notes<br>• (Speed) This task was completed quickly<br>• The student found some difficulty with “read = red” “while = will” “roc = rock”<br>• However, the student showed confidence in composing original sentences using previous SD words!<br>• They were able to complete 1 simple and 1 complex sentence<br>• Their understanding of the task was fine, but needs to be solidified in terms of identifying between sentence types<br>• Next week, we plan to address compound and complex sentences!<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-04-06 09:58:10', '2022-04-06 10:02:33'),
(1955, '2022/04/06', '05:00 pm', '1', '8', 'Max Brookfield', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'To Be Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-06 17:00:27', '2022-04-06 17:00:27'),
(1956, '2022/04/06', '05:00 pm', '1', '9', 'Max Brookfield', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'To Be Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-06 17:00:46', '2022-04-06 17:00:46'),
(1957, '2022/04/06', '05:00 pm', '1', '9', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-06 17:01:02', '2022-04-06 17:01:31'),
(1958, '2022/04/06', '07:45 pm', '1', '9', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phoebe was a handful today. She refused to learn anything. She was wining the whole time whenever I bring up a learning activity. It seems like that she has so much going on in school or home. She kept saying that she wants to quit and doesnt want to go to school and she does not want to be here for tutoring at all. She shows strong frustration when bringing up anything new.&nbsp;</p><p>She even refused to play her favoriate playdo today. We had 30 minute learning. She showed progress on the first 33 phonograms and knows all their sounds with a bit help. SHe liked to trace on line letter phonograms, but she refused to transit to the next activity from here. So we had to just play a game with her brother Toby and Campbell at the end.&nbsp;</p><p>I am quite confused with this kid and need help.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-04-06 19:46:24', '2022-04-06 19:52:31'),
(1960, '2022/04/08', '02:31 pm', '1', '9', 'Molly Jackson', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) second phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level K', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick K</td></tr><tr><td>Molly\'s going well with these! Half coached on fingers/additional sounding out step, extra step removed for second half unless needed.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR:54-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: oa gu ph ough oe ey igh wr ie dge si ti eigh ei</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 26 sfe1</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: right-march</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>POS: Verb tense. Introduce to, provide sentences and have Molly ID the tense, ID which word tells you the tense. Use Ayres words in sentences in a variety of verb tenses.</td></tr><tr><td>Sentence Types: Sentence type and structure lucky dip + model on blocks and colour code. MJ needed a fair amount of prompting for her sentence types and compound sentence.</td></tr><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Compose a \"rainbow\" sentence. Apply knowledge by moving blocks around/changing structure/removing certain words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-08 14:31:50', '2022-04-08 15:24:58'),
(1961, '2022/04/08', '03:32 pm', '1', '9', 'Connor Thompson', 'Mathematics', 'Data Representation and Interpretation', 'Mean, median & range', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Connor had brought in his data worksheet from school again to work on. When I let him know I had prepared some work on referencing, he requested we split the lesson in half for both these activities.</td></tr><tr><td>We had begun with a game of Uno. Connor tried various methods to convince me to play another game -- including that because his current score was an odd number, he \"wouldn\'t be able to focus\". He then really hammed this up and acted like he couldn\'t focus, even to the extent that he couldn\'t focus on anything long enough to see the worksheet right in front of him. This joke continued for far too long. I told Connor it was his time he was wasting, that I would wait him out, and if he wanted to waste time and never get to the referencing task that was fine by me.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Harvard referencing task - provided Connor with a worksheet and model. First showed Connor the model and walked him through it. Then coached him through his own. More needed.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-08 15:34:30', '2022-04-08 18:17:37'),
(1962, '2022/04/08', '03:35 pm', '1', '9', 'Annika Spedding', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>This was my final lesson with Annika, due to the public holiday last week!<br><br>Annika and I recapped her \'er\' sounds - she seems to be mastering these quite well! Annika has began guessing which \'er\' would be in the word (and which column it would fall into).<br><br>Annika and I looked at job 4 and 5 of SFE. She seemed to pick these up quite easily, but will certainly need recap in the new term. Annika sometimes struggles to differentiate between sounds and syllables (making job 4 a little difficult), but once prompted that these are the \'beats\' in the word, Annika is able to give the correct sounds.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-08 15:36:06', '2022-04-08 17:37:26'),
(1963, '2022/04/08', '03:34 pm', '1', '8', 'Connor Thompson', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Connor brought in a worksheet outlining his inclass essay. We created one page of notes for him, following an essay outline/plan.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-08 15:37:11', '2022-04-08 18:18:19'),
(1964, '2022/04/08', '04:33 pm', '1', '9', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-08 16:33:52', '2022-04-08 18:19:11');
INSERT INTO `attens` (`id`, `date_created`, `time`, `term`, `lesson`, `student_name`, `subject_name`, `concept_name`, `conceptDetail`, `learningActivity`, `tutor_name`, `tutor_evaluation`, `student_self`, `student_attendance`, `homework_completed`, `weekly_lesson`, `homework_assignment`, `email_school`, `comment`, `commentPrivate`, `notesAttendance`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1965, '2022/04/08', '04:35 pm', '1', '9', 'Joshua Zeeman', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose third-person narrative paragraph', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Josh and I had our final lesson for the term this week. We started planning his board game, and began designing up the board. Josh did a fantastic job coming up with these plans, and different scenarios. We used butchers paper to map out how the game will work, and wrote the rules down to the side.<br><br>Next term, Josh will need to begin writing and creating the \'ethical/religion\' cards, and the \'situation\' cards. Josh should be able to do this independantly with good detail, but may need to brush up on his knowledge by researching the frameworks again.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-08 16:36:11', '2022-04-08 17:36:53'),
(1966, '2022/04/11', '10:32 am', '1', '8', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Writing - Sentence Construction & Vocabulary', 'Elements of a compound sentence > Capital letter, two independent clauses joined by a coordinating conjunction (FANBOYS), ending punctuation', 'Articulate/Explain the elements of a compound sentence (include use of manipulatives)', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Brock is not in a good mood for learning today. He get frustrated easily as he finds remembering rules is quite hard for him. He is very dedicated even if he gets frustrated sometimes. OPR: He needs help with ough, igh, especially ey(They have the key to the valley). Rules: he is very resistant to rule review which I need to make the rule learning more interesting and see how he goes. He could not recall rule 29 and 17. Compound sentence: Brock has grasped this sentence structure very well. He needed some reminds over his capital letter at the beginning of a sentence, as well as punctuality.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-04-11 10:33:32', '2022-04-11 10:37:47'),
(1967, '2022/04/11', '10:37 am', '1', '9', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 4: vowels a, e, o, u say their second (long) sound at the end of a syllable', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Brock had a good learning today. OPR/WPR non familiar: ough, ey, kn, gn, wr. Brock is quite resistant to rule review and learning. He can articulate rule 4 but cannot remember the number. It is better to merge the rule review into activities. He is very good at syllable division and individual sounds in words. We also did sfe review today and again, he cannot recall unless giving him the instructions for it. He is very resistant on this.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-04-11 10:38:31', '2022-04-11 10:40:12'),
(1968, '2022/04/11', '10:40 am', '1', '8', 'Callum Coulson', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-11 10:41:15', '2022-04-11 10:41:15'),
(1969, '2022/04/11', '10:41 am', '1', '9', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callum is so dedicated to this tutoring although he has difficulties of remembering things. He has been struggling to say sounds in a row especially for ch, ou, ow, and u. He still needs help with all vowel sounds, qu, s, th, oo. We did clockface letter handwriting today as he forms some letters like o in a wrong way. Callum has difficulty to control his mouth muscle for certain sounds in a row and we have been practicing that today. Homework for reviewing rule 2, 3, 4 are sent home, as well as marking pinkbook page 1&amp;2.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-04-11 11:14:03', '2022-04-11 11:16:25'),
(1970, '2022/04/11', '11:16 am', '1', '8', 'Mia Harvey', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-11 11:17:51', '2022-04-11 11:23:02'),
(1971, '2022/04/11', '11:23 am', '1', '9', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Mia loves the hand-on activity---sorting and cutting for rule 2 &amp;3. She picked up quite fast. She can say at least one sound for the first 26 phonograms on her own. She liked the game for OPR---twister. WPR: Mia shows interst in handwriting and likes to compete in it. &nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-04-11 11:24:08', '2022-04-11 11:26:03'),
(1972, '2022/04/11', '03:36 pm', '1', '10', 'Elsa Clennett', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-11 15:36:52', '2022-04-11 15:36:52'),
(1973, '2022/04/11', '04:38 pm', '1', '10', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR 1-26 &nbsp; &nbsp;Mia was quite quick for picking them up and have been fluent in all multiple sounds too.&nbsp;<br>WPR: line phonograms: b, e, h, i, j, k, l, m, n, p, r, t, v, w, x, y, z &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Her handwriting is quite great for her age and level.</p><p>New phonograms: 27-34 Mia can say at least one sound for these phonograms.&nbsp;</p><p>morphology questions---Mia can pick up the words in compound words very easily.&nbsp;</p><p>We focised on CVC words by the driving and making words activity.&nbsp;</p><p>straberry smash was an activity to enhance vowels and consonants.&nbsp;</p><p>SD: hot, sad, sip, pot, got, viv, fan &nbsp; CVC words. Mia had no problem reading and writing these words<br>finding the easter eggs activity.&nbsp;</p><p>Sentence: compose sentences using CVC words<br>Mia made 2 complete sentences and wrote ‘si’ for ‘is’, but she could find the mistake and correct it by herself.&nbsp;</p><p>Reading: wizkids stage 2 book1--fluent. we need to do a higher levle for her.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-04-11 16:39:50', '2022-04-11 16:49:06'),
(1974, '2022/04/11', '04:39 pm', '1', '10', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpattrick &nbsp;F1</p><p>OPR: 1-26. Thomas need help with the 3 sounds of u still, also o, e, i, y.&nbsp;</p><p>WPR: 1-26. Thomas forms b and d in a wrong way. But he gets better at recognizing these two phonograms.&nbsp;</p><p>new phonograms:27-33: He can say at least one sound for each phonograms.&nbsp;</p><p><br>SD: vat, lid, mop, got, lot, not pop. &nbsp;finding the easter eggs. Thomas has hesitation on the word lid as he still needs a bit time on recognizing b and d.&nbsp;</p><p>morphology activity .</p><p><br>written sentences with CVC words. He use upper case letter in the middle of sentences.&nbsp;</p><p><br>reading-wizkids stage 2 book 2 1st reading. He needed to sounded out lid, mop, vat in order to read them in sentences.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-04-11 16:40:19', '2022-04-11 16:56:41'),
(1975, '2022/04/11', '04:42 pm', '1', '10', 'Charlie Burton', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose informative paragraph', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>This lesson was held via zoom as Charlie was not feeling 100% (negative RAT, but still wanted to keep safe).<br><br>We spent todays lesson discussing and looking over Charlie\'s english essay. He had done a really fantastic job of this, and the only comments were about repetitive phrases, and confusing sentences. Charlie will be going over this all again tonight, and submitting his assignment tomorrow.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-11 16:43:06', '2022-04-11 16:43:55'),
