(1978, '2022/04/12', '04:41 pm', '1', '10', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 39-54</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: or au ur ng ea ew ui</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 4 5 6</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: sew-thread</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Types: Use Ayres words in sentences to show meaning and in given sentence type.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>We had a bit of a disrupted lesson today. Sophie had had a big day at school and seemed a little off, she also struggled a little with having the phonograms out of order. A couple of times she even went to say the phonogram following it by rote. It was really good to give her this chance to work with them shuffled, though.</td></tr><tr><td>The lesson was also disrupted as we were beginning spelling by Pulse marketing next door. They started playing the music/radio incredibly loudly -- I had to set Sophie up to do some independent work so I could pop over and ask them to turn it down, but as soon as we had that sorted the music stopped!&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Homophones are proving troubling for Sophie. She finds them difficult as she often hasn\'t heard the less common word before. We had lots of conversation about these words and their different meanings,&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-12 16:43:24', '2022-04-12 17:22:51'),
(1979, '2022/04/12', '04:43 pm', '1', '10', 'Shay Douglas', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Essay Structure', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: History assignment</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Geography essay</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Shay compose and NM proofread</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Again, Shay wanted some time to do independent research on his essay. I looked over his structure and what he had written since our last lesson, and also made some proof reading notes for him to look over. This was mostly comments for him to check sentence structure, grammar, and points where he should add in some evidence/supporting sentences.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-12 16:43:44', '2022-04-12 17:30:16'),
(1980, '2022/04/12', '04:46 pm', '1', '10', 'Esther McIver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Heather Excell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>SPELLING</strong>:</p><p>opr/wpr:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ie, y, c, au, dge, er</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Rule review:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Introduce Rule 23</p><p>Recap rules 5, 6, 12, 20, 24, 28, 29</p></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Spelling dictation:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>tried, try, vein,<br>SECTION N:&nbsp; except, aunt, ant, capture, else, bridge, offer</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>WRITING</strong>:</p><p>Sentence Structure:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Recap sentence types.</p><p>Look at complex sentences - revise structure and create sentences.&nbsp;</p></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>NOTES</strong>:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Esther\'s lesson was held via zoom this week due to Esther being in quarantine as a close contact.<br><br>Esther did a really fantastic job with her spelling work today. Despite the digital divide, she was able to learn rule 23, and apply it during her Spelling Dictation.<br><br>Esther and I recapped sentence types. She learnt her simple and compound sentences nicely, but did get stuck with her complex sentences a little. It will be good to recap these next term, especially diving into more examples. Esther was able to give some solid examples of complex sentences when prompted, and certainly understood how to use a subbie in sentence work.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-12 16:47:03', '2022-04-12 16:50:17'),
