(2006, '2022/04/13', '04:38 pm', '1', '10', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 39-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ear au gu wor ea aw ew ui ir oe ey ei dge ie kn si&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: NA</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: advice-cocoa</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Discuss advice/advise and noun/verb connection and how this changes the usage of the word, give examples.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence writing: Compose written sentences using Ayres words in context.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Comprehension: Continue work with Marshall comprehension worksheet.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Good lesson with Angus today. Had to talk about the relationship between noun/verb pairs (?) and how they change with context. Angus also did better on the reading comprehension task and gave more insightful responses, perhaps helped by the recap I gave him at the beginning of the task.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-04-13 16:39:16', '2022-04-13 18:10:29'),
