(2014, '2022/05/03', '08:59 am', '2', '1', 'Henry  Badock', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Represent and solve simple addition and subtraction problems using a range of strategies', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Completed Friends of page in workbook</p><p>Focus - Relationship between addition and subtraction</p><p>H practised turning simple addtion problems to 20 into subtraction problems.</p><p>We then performed simple subtraction and used addition to check our answers.</p><p>He has not yet grasped the relationship between these functions.</p><p>Focus - Intro to multiplication&nbsp;</p><p>Henry is very negative re his ability to do multiplication. I showed him how he had already been doing it as part of our lessons each week when we played our counter game. We called it Counting in thousands/hundreds/tens etc. Today i changed the language to times/lots of etc and we performed the simple addition first and then x 1000. Henry grasped this instantly.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Next week continue construction of the number line to assist with subtraction particularly.&nbsp;</p><p>Use language of multiplication when possible.&nbsp;</p><p>review addition/subtraction relationship.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-03 09:00:04', '2022-05-03 09:11:50'),
(2015, '2022/05/03', '09:12 am', '2', '1', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Thomas has been paired up with Mia Harvey for this term but Mia did not attend the lesson today.&nbsp;</p><p>As the first day of this term, Thomas did an excellent work.&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR 1-33. He could precisely say and write all 33 phonograms we learned last term. He needed help with multi sounds ch, ow, ou, y, and u. For WPR, he wrote c in ch, z and y backwards, as in a mirror. It could be that he has visual procession issues. He could not recall qu, and c.&nbsp;</p><p>Progress: Thomas can say all 3 sounds for u with help, he can also recognize b and d.&nbsp;</p><p>SD and sentence: day, boy, paint, point. He had no problem with this and orally &nbsp;make a great compound sentence with two of the SD words.&nbsp;</p><p>ORF: Thomas needed to point at each word and was not very fluent on the second reading. He was slowed down with words vat, viv, and the. &nbsp; &nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-03 09:14:09', '2022-05-03 09:26:11'),
(2016, '2022/05/03', '09:14 am', '2', '1', 'Mia Harvey', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-03 09:15:10', '2022-05-03 09:15:10'),
(2017, '2022/05/03', '03:40 pm', '2', '1', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Stella was quite distracted today and it was hard for her to focus. She was finding any ways to avoid learning, such as asking questions that are not related to our lesson, drawing pictures on whiteboard.&nbsp;</p><p>OPR: 1-26. She can say at least one sound for each phonogram. SHe can say more sounds for multi sound phonograms when encouraged. She knows all 3 sounds for a, needs help with e and o for more sounds. She knows only one sound for u and i. SHe has a hard time with y.&nbsp;</p><p>WPR: line letter b, e, f and t.She forms b, e and f in a wrong way.</p><p>SD: sad, bed, up. STella needed help with sad and bed.&nbsp;</p><p>Reading: ORF---reading-wizkids stage 1 book1 first reading. SHe is quite resistant to reading and had a hard time with the word sat.&nbsp;</p><p>Homework-handwriting sent home.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-03 15:41:16', '2022-05-03 15:59:53'),
(2018, '2022/05/03', '04:00 pm', '2', '1', 'Brock Smith', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-03 16:01:28', '2022-05-03 16:01:28'),
(2019, '2022/05/03', '05:33 pm', '2', '1', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 46 > 54', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>1. OPR: 1-43. Callum graspped more phonograms after this school holiday. He needed help with multi sounds phonograms such as o, u, ow, c, ch, g, s, x,y and th.</p><p>&nbsp;2. WPR: 1-43. Callum was not familiar with ay.&nbsp;</p><p>3. New phonograms: ng, ea, aw, au, or.</p><p>4. SD: We dictated 10 words for rule page 2 rule 8. Callum needed help with syllybalification of words and he could not say k sound in the word perfect. We will need to teach sfes and syllable division next week.</p>', NULL, '2022-05-03 17:34:06', '2022-05-04 09:05:51'),
(2020, '2022/05/03', '05:44 pm', '2', '1', 'Esther Mclver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Student Handover</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Date:&nbsp; 13.4.2022</strong></p><p><strong>Term:&nbsp; One</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"5\"><strong>Student and Tutor Details</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Student</strong></td><td colspan=\"4\">Esther McIver</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Current Tutor</strong></td><td colspan=\"4\">Heather Excell</td></tr><tr><td><strong>New Tutor&nbsp;</strong></td><td colspan=\"4\">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\"><strong>Concepts Covered</strong></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\"><p><strong>Phonological and Phonemic Awareness:</strong></p><p>K1</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\"><p><strong>Systematic Phonics:</strong></p><p>Knows 1 – 60 (and a few between 60 and 70, but will need reminding)</p><p>Knows extra ET sounds (i.e. 5 sounds of ‘a’ and 4 sounds of ‘o’)</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\"><p><strong>Ayres Placement:</strong></p><p>Section N – last word ‘Offer’</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"5\"><p><strong>Spelling Rules:</strong></p><p>Complete list located in the front of her workbook.&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td><td>N/A</td><td>Introduced</td><td>Mastered</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Parts of Speech</strong></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Nouns</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Pronouns</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Verbs</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Adverbs</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Adjectives</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Prepositions</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Interjections</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Conjunctions (FANBOYS &amp; SUBBIES)</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Sentence Writing</strong></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Declarative Sentences</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Exclamatory Sentences</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Interrogative Sentences</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Imperative Sentences</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Simple Sentences</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Compound Sentences</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Complex Sentences</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Reading</strong></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">3 Text Types</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">5 Mental Actions</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">The Writing Process</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><strong>Notes &amp; Comments</strong></p><p><strong>Current Focuses:</strong></p><ul><li>Esther and I have been brushing up on her sentence structure work, and moving more into the paragraph writing/writing process side of things</li><li>Esther’s spelling has increased significantly over the last year – she is now sitting 3 months below her chronological age</li><li>Esther is still reading Fitzroy’s. I’d love to assess her for ORF soon, as I think it would be awesome to integrate some of these into her writing lessons as well. However, she is not very fluent with her reading. I usually send home a reader with her, and we will often recap that at the end of our next lesson.</li></ul><p><strong>General Observations/Behavioural Notes:</strong></p><ul><li>Esther LOVES drawing. I usually try and incorporate something creative into her lessons every few weeks.</li><li>Esther is incredibly well behaved, and always gives 100% to her work. She can be a little shy, but if you ask her a question, she usually gets it right!</li><li>Esther likes to also hold her fingers up when saying the sounds in words.</li></ul><p><strong>Recommendations for future lessons:</strong></p><ul><li>Continue working through spelling (as per Ayres list)</li><li>Begin looking at text types, then integrating this into the writing process (writing informative pieces about animals etc.)</li><li>Keep looking at fluency in her reading, perhaps assessing for ORF to see where she is sitting.</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-05-03 17:44:43', '2022-05-07 19:19:59'),
(2021, '2022/05/03', '05:45 pm', '2', '1', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 4: vowels a, e, o, u say their second (long) sound at the end of a syllable', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Term 2 W1</p><p>OPR -27-70</p><p>WPR – completed assessment 44-70</p><p>Rule review Rule 4 – connect 4</p><p>SD Sect H</p><p>School – soft + loaf</p><p>Sentence dictation – Andrew composed and wrote a sentence using loaf and soft.</p><p>Reading Fitzroy 32</p><p>Hw</p><p>Words using phgs from WPR assess + rule 4 + reader.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-03 17:45:48', '2022-05-03 17:47:01'),
