(2026, '2022/04/05', '05:09 pm', '2', '1', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phoebe was in a good mood today. Learning can be a bit frustrating to her, yet she could focus with encouragement today.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>OPR 1-33. She can say at least one sound for all 33 phonograms except u. &nbsp;SHe could say more sounds with help for phonograms i, o, y, ow, ou, th, ch, c. We did a bunny hopping game for multi sound phonograms u and e. She confuses the numbers and needed help with u.&nbsp;</li><li>WPR: Phoebe could not recall ee, c, qu, ow and ou.&nbsp;</li><li>new phonograms: ar, ay, ai, oi, oy</li><li>SD: rule 4 pink book page 1 marking. boy, bay, coin, car. Phoebe often confuses k with the first sound of c.&nbsp;</li><li>oral sentence. ‘I bought a car with a coin.’</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-05-04 17:10:41', '2022-05-04 18:23:35');
