(2043, '2022/05/06', '08:15 pm', '2', '1', 'Josh Zeeman', 'Study Skills', 'Research', 'See Notes', 'See Notes...', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>JZ was very chatty today! He talked me through his board game, and we discussed our next steps (creating info cards). He had lots of questions, and over the course of the lesson we discussed the economy, the upcoming election, governments and politics, and spent a lot of time talking about religion generally.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-06 20:16:53', '2022-05-06 20:18:41'),
(2044, '2022/05/07', '06:41 pm', '2', '1', 'Cara Lashmar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>phoned and emailed both parents as Cara did not attend.</p>', '<p>did not attend</p>', '2022-05-07 18:42:25', '2022-06-17 09:46:00'),
(2046, '2022/05/07', '06:43 pm', '2', '1', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Sentence Construction & Vocabulary', 'Sentence structure - there are three ways to construct a sentence > simple, compound, complex', 'Recognise/Analyse/Compose/Model simple/compound/complex sentences that demonstrate meaning & usage of unfamiliar spelling words', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Review of t1 - POS, sentence construction, sentence type, the writing process - narrative</p><p>Today we commenced Informative writing piece - Wolves chosen by Finn</p><p>Plan - Finn chose to do a mix of words and pictorial notation for his initial brainstorm.&nbsp;</p><p>Draft: Finn chose 3 headings for paragraphs - appearance, habitat, food/prey</p><p>Finn wrote an introduction summarising the basic research we did (5 mins max), and commenced his first paragraph - appearance.</p><p>Finn was easily distracted during the research component. We set strict time limits for use of the computer which Finn was to follow at home as well. This is a handwritten writing task to avoid the chance of plagiarism. Encouraging re-wording of information and not copying. Finn is very visual and uses small sketches to record his ideas.&nbsp;</p><p>Once he had composed his introduction and first sentences for Appearance, we analysed the sentence structure as a review of sentence types in a practical manner. Finn was immediately able to recognise which structure hed used and revised his sentences to ensure they were correct grammatically. As spelling is such an anxiety inducing stressor for Finn we removed the focus completely. Frequent reminders we were writing a draft were required and Finn accepted this and did not become hung up on spelling every word perfectly immediately. Huge step in getting him to put his ideas on paper.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-07 18:44:07', '2022-05-07 19:07:41'),
(2048, '2022/05/09', '11:13 am', '2', '1', 'Chester Vincent', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-09 11:14:01', '2022-05-09 11:14:01'),
(2049, '2022/05/09', '04:11 pm', '2', '2', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Thomas is a competitive kid and he focuses better in a paired lesson. Mia also got more help with the ones she is not familiar with. I believe they wwere both more motivated to do our work activities than before and this is definitely beneficial to them. Mia and Thomas helped each other with their weak spots during our lesson. They both concentrated very well. &nbsp;</p><ol><li>OPR: 1-37. Thomas reviewed all phonograms and Mia learned 4 new phonograms ay, ai, oy, and oi. Thomas is still confusing about g, b, and d. They both needed help with u, o, e, y, ch, th, oo, ow, ou. We also played a multi sound phonogram game involved the phonogram u and they both needed help recognizing the three sounds. &nbsp;</li><li>WPR: 1-37. Thomas needed help with ar. He also did much better on his handwriting today.&nbsp;</li><li>Handwriting focus: clockface letters. They did tracing and coloring.&nbsp;</li><li>Morphology activity 1. They both are quite advanced on this so we will not continue this activity next week.&nbsp;</li><li>SD: Thomas wrote she and the to review rule 4. Mia wrote coin, boy, day and paint for the new phonograms. SHe started to do her rule page one rule 4.&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-05-09 16:12:02', '2022-05-09 16:58:42'),
