(2062, '2022/05/09', '09:57 pm', '2', '1', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Shape', '2D', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Today\'s lesson was about the perimeter and area of squares, and rectangles.&nbsp;</p><p>Sofia told me she hasn\'t worked on this concept before.</p><p>The work done was foundation-level problems.</p><p>In the last part of the lesson, Sofia solved the proposed problems with ease. I consider that we need to revisit this topic later in the term.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-09 21:57:30', '2022-07-02 20:08:09'),
(2063, '2022/05/09', '09:57 pm', '2', '1', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics – Foundation', 'Shape and measurement', 'PLEASE SEE THE NOTES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<ul><li>review Pythagoras’ Theorem and use to solve practical problems in two dimensions, and for simple applications in three dimensions.</li><li>solve practical problems requiring the calculation of perimeters and areas of circles, sectors of circles, triangles, rectangles, parallelograms and composites.</li></ul><p>Due to work done the previous year, these topics weren\'t very hard for Finlay. However, I did help him to arrange some equations.&nbsp;</p><p>All the work done was from the compendium of John Short.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-09 21:58:00', '2022-07-02 18:38:30'),
(2064, '2022/05/09', '09:58 pm', '2', '1', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Sketch linear graphs using the coordinates of two points and solve linear equations', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', '<p>In this lesson, Nicholas and I worked on finding the gradient of a linear equation. We solved many problems on the board.&nbsp;</p><p>Nicholas had no problems finding the gradient by using the formula. Although, sometimes when the gradient was negative we got a bit lost. He wanted to finish the problem in a very short time. I think it was for this reason, that he didn\'t get the correct answer in those cases.&nbsp;</p><p>Homework = Essential Mathematics year 9 page 248</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson delivered on 05.05.2022</p>', '2022-05-09 21:58:27', '2022-07-02 17:01:00'),
