(2077, '2022/05/10', '09:09 am', '2', '2', 'Henry  Badock', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Represent and solve simple addition and subtraction problems using a range of strategies', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W2</p><p>Focus</p><p>Continue to explore relationship between addition and subtraction through use of ruler/number line/manipulatives and modelling patterns on board.</p><p>8+2=10&nbsp; 10-2=8&nbsp;</p><p>2+8=10.&nbsp; 10-8=2&nbsp;</p><p>Henry performed these manipulations on the board and a worksheet.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Focus – Multiplication</p><p>Cups and pop sticks used to model 4 x 2 ; 3 x 5</p><p>Explored the different ways to record this such as 2+2+2+2; 4 cups of 2 sticks, substituting lots of for cups. 4 lots of 2 and 4 x 2. See pic in book.&nbsp;</p><p>Game: bucket toss with subtraction. Begin with 20 and take away the number of counters&nbsp;</p><p>bucket. Lowest score wins. See pic&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-10 09:10:06', '2022-05-10 09:13:35'),
(2078, '2022/05/10', '02:33 pm', '2', '2', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR 1-10. hopping game. Stella can say multiple sounds for a which I think the previously practice helped a lot. She doesn\'t know qu, and needed help with second sound for s, c.&nbsp;<br>WPR 1-10. clock face handwriting game/drawing/coloring. She forms a &amp; g backwards, and forms e in a wrong way. But with help, she can do them the right way.&nbsp;<br>morphology activity 12<br>SD: rule page 1 rule 4. &nbsp;a, e.&nbsp;<br>oral sentence using SD words. She was quite good at oral sentences.<br>&nbsp;</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-10 14:34:01', '2022-05-10 20:08:27'),
(2079, '2022/05/10', '03:27 pm', '2', '1', 'Stella Bowerman', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-10 15:27:11', '2022-05-10 15:27:11'),
(2080, '2022/05/10', '03:31 pm', '2', '2', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-10 15:31:06', '2022-05-10 15:31:06'),
(2081, '2022/05/10', '03:36 pm', '2', '2', 'Esther Mclver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 55 > 70', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W2</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR ie ei ea ey gu kn gn ough sh ti si ci&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sect N Wonder – itself</p><p>R.25</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>Compose the following-</p><p>Declarative sentence:</p><p>I inspect the pear for gnats. (Simple)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Interrogative sentence:</p><p>Can you hear the thunder? (Simple)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Compound sentence:</p><p>I went to the hotel for a holiday and my friend came too. (Declarative)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Discuss POS</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Of 110</p><p>Timed read 2 errors 69 words.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Hw sheet given&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-10 15:36:01', '2022-05-10 17:20:27'),
(2082, '2022/05/10', '03:49 pm', '2', '2', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 46 > 54', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>First lesson of this term, Brock is getting used to it again. We did 1-34 phonograms for OPR and WPR. He needed a bit help with multi sounds for y, ou and oo.&nbsp;</p><p>We recapped syllables.&nbsp;</p><p>What is syllable?</p><p>Four syllable types&nbsp;</p><p>Syllable divisions.&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review: rule 4 and 13. Brock does not remember rule 13.&nbsp;</p><p>SD: for the words cause and because, Brock needed help with phonogram au. He needed help with sfe jobs too.&nbsp;</p><p>We will need to do sentences and reading next week.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-10 15:51:39', '2022-05-18 15:12:58'),
(2083, '2022/05/10', '04:00 pm', '2', '2', 'Luna Shapiro', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick F2</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Segment/count/blend: cat, fat, sat, mat – physical activity (jumping) with markers</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8 first sounds only</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 1-8</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>These letters are special because they all have the same starting point when they are written. Show the racecar tracks, tracing pages. They all have a circle!&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Trace on the tracing pages, then 2x2 boxes for: a d g s o</td></tr><tr><td>These are what we call \"little\" letters. There are also \"capital letters\". They are two different ways of writing the same letter. We are going to focus on learning little letters.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Hide and Seek.</td></tr><tr><td>Upper/lower case letter memory game</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Going to move Luna to a 45 lesson starting next week. Again she was resistant (although resistant in a different way to Max! Very jumpy/wriggly/etc.</td></tr><tr><td>Her a formation is generally okay, although sometimes she\'ll reverse it. She doesn\'t seem to notice a difference when she reverses a letter or gets it back to front.</td></tr><tr><td>Showed Luna letters. Asked her what shape she could see the letter was made up of (circle).Used stickers to mark 2 o\'clock on various laminated letters in literacy guys box. Didn\'t use 2 oclock language, just told Luna where to place the sticker. She traced beginning at the sticker. After about 3 she independently realised they all started in the same spot. Even for trickier ones like c and f, we held them up to the light so we could see that the sticker was in the same place on the letter. Then we completed the 2x2 boxes. She made some reversals.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-10 16:01:13', '2022-05-10 16:14:56'),
(2084, '2022/05/10', '04:01 pm', '2', '2', 'Elsa Clennett', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: H2</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 50-70 shuffled</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ea eigh gu kn gn ey</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 4 14&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: further-govern</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ayres words in sentences to show meaning.</td></tr><tr><td>Writing Process: Write a short, paragraph length story (using plan) in 10 minutes. Write the same story in 3 sentences in 5 minutes. Write the same story in one sentence in 3 minutes.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Quality Lit: Lamb to the Slaughter -- take home to read.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Good lesson with Elsa today, she was bit brighter and less tired than usual :-) She also got into the story activity! We talked about limiting her story not to the whole detective \"whodunit\" structure, but \"zooming in\" on a part of it -- e.g. the investigator deciding to investigate, or the moment of realisation.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-10 16:01:34', '2022-05-10 16:21:25'),
(2085, '2022/05/10', '04:01 pm', '2', '2', 'Arki Young', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose informative paragraph', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Arki brought in a task from school to work on today. He had to write a persuasive text arguing that the moon landing WASN\'T a hoax. We planned this out using my paragraph proformer and then Arki dictated it to me and I wrote it on word. He did great! The difference in his written and dictated work is amazing. He needed some editing and revision done, especially since he had a tendency to include more information than was needed. He seemed capable at identifying what was/wasn\'t relevant to answering the question, though. A good deviation from usual!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-10 16:01:50', '2022-05-16 17:55:31'),
(2087, '2022/05/10', '04:02 pm', '2', '2', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'To Be Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-50</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: See workbook</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: 9</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD:Rule Page 3</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Vocab: Use words in sentences to show meaning.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Had Sophie write in cursive which was great. The rule 9 articulation was tricky for her but she felt that the rule itself was instinctive to her. I don\'t know if the location had an impact on her? She mentioned several times how much nicer it is here at AR, more “cozy” and “quieter”.</p>', NULL, '2022-05-10 16:02:43', '2022-05-18 16:23:11'),
(2088, '2022/05/10', '04:36 pm', '2', '2', 'Shay Douglas', 'Academic Coaching', 'Independent Study', 'School Assigned Worksheet or Assignment', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>History/Geography</td></tr><tr><td>Shay\'s Assignment</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Shay had an assignment he wanted to work on from school. It required him to work in a group and determine their political utopia, and present a powerpoint on it.</td></tr><tr><td>The rubric was not available online for this assignment, so I\'ve reccommended that Shay find his hard copy and go through it as a \'checklist\' to see if they\'ve covered all the requirements.</td></tr><tr><td>I proof-read what they had done so far, and made comments where applicable. Mostly I needed to suggest that they argue their point more -- there were a lot of elements to their utopia that didn\'t seem very utopian. It needed much stronger advocating. There were also a couple of grammar/clause notes to be made.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-10 16:36:23', '2022-05-17 16:57:27'),
(2089, '2022/05/10', '05:14 pm', '2', '2', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 20: s never follows x', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>opr/wpr: 1-20. Callum needed help to say multi sounds for &nbsp;o, and qu.</li><li>Cursive handwriting: a-e</li><li>New rules: 20 and 17, sfe job 2.</li><li>SD: Section M trust to teach. Callum did not know how to write extra. He has problem to recognize the sound x..</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-05-10 17:16:36', '2022-05-10 20:02:21');
INSERT INTO `attens` (`id`, `date_created`, `time`, `term`, `lesson`, `student_name`, `subject_name`, `concept_name`, `conceptDetail`, `learningActivity`, `tutor_name`, `tutor_evaluation`, `student_self`, `student_attendance`, `homework_completed`, `weekly_lesson`, `homework_assignment`, `email_school`, `comment`, `commentPrivate`, `notesAttendance`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2090, '2022/05/10', '05:28 pm', '2', '2', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving multiplication and division', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Sketch linear graphs using the coordinates of two points and solve linear equations.</li><li>Solve linear simultaneous equations, using algebraic and graphical techniques, including using digital technology.&nbsp;</li><li>Find the distance between two points located on the Cartesian plane using a range of strategies, including graphing software.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-10 17:28:34', '2022-06-13 09:53:24'),
(2091, '2022/05/10', '07:21 pm', '2', '2', 'Joseph Martin', 'Mathematics', 'Maths methods 3', 'Quadratics', 'Factorization', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Joseph and I were working on a college assignment.&nbsp;<br>This was about quadratics including, factorizing, completing the square, sketching parables, solving wording problems and finding the domain and range of a quadratic.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-10 19:21:55', '2022-05-10 21:19:13'),
(2093, '2022/05/11', '07:45 am', '2', '2', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Adjectives - describe nouns', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>We had a challenge for Luke to write 5 nouns, verbs, and adjectives. he needed help with adj as he forgot what adjs are.&nbsp;</li><li>OPR 1-55. He needed help with some multi sound phonograms such as gu, ea, u, o, e, ou, but he is quite good for the second round.&nbsp;</li><li>WPR 1-55. He needed help to recognize phonograms aw, or, au, and needed a bit help with ew, ui.</li><li>rule review rule 19.&nbsp;</li><li>SD: section I or-best. Luke does not have the habit to say each sound of a word, but he was quite good at these words. We might have to move him up.&nbsp;</li><li>Simple declarative sentence. He made a good sentence yet he had spelling error for family(famely).&nbsp;</li><li>Writing assessment. We did complex sentence and its elements. Luke knows the concept and all elements, yet he is not familiar with an actual complex sentence.&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-05-11 07:46:57', '2022-05-11 08:57:07'),
(2096, '2022/05/11', '09:12 am', '2', '1', 'Angus Singleton', 'Mathematics', 'Calculus', 'Differentiation', 'Practice Paper', 'Campbell Jepson', 'In Progress', 'In Progress', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>test comments azul</p>', '<p>Test atten rojo</p>', '<p>test Notes</p>', '2022-05-11 09:12:47', '2022-05-11 09:15:03'),
(2097, '2022/05/11', '09:15 am', '2', '2', 'Angus Singleton', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-11 09:15:32', '2022-05-11 09:15:32'),
(2098, '2022/05/11', '03:28 pm', '2', '1', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Jimmy and I continued to work on his Animal Rights essay. Jimmy has wonderful ideas and his comprehension is fine, but his execution needs refining. At this point, he is not yet able to use more than simple vocabulary, so once we have written the essay, we we will address academic vocabulary and how to use a thesaurus.</p>', NULL, '2022-05-11 15:28:35', '2022-06-02 09:24:23'),
(2099, '2022/05/11', '03:30 pm', '2', '1', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: G</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8 , 27-40 + introduce to 41-44</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: a ch ai er ea sh ou oo c ee</td></tr><tr><td>HF: On base line -- sticker incentive for 8/10 on base line, very effective</td></tr><tr><td>Hybrid game of words at work -- use words from hand in sentence, using middle cards if wanted. Can use other words in sentence as well. Good except MB understandably needed help decoding some words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule intro using Ayres word: 5&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: an-good</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Write sentences using words, create oral sentences.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>A little rhyme from Max\'s teacher: when 2 vowels go walking, the first does the talking!</td></tr><tr><td>Max much better behaviour wise this week than last week. A bit more focused, still easily distractable but better when I got him standing up/on one leg, etc. Silent final e next week.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-11 15:30:36', '2022-05-11 17:27:12'),
(2100, '2022/05/11', '03:31 pm', '2', '3', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-11 15:31:13', '2022-05-11 15:31:13'),
(2101, '2022/05/11', '03:31 pm', '2', '4', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-11 15:31:14', '2022-05-11 15:31:14'),
(2102, '2022/05/11', '03:31 pm', '2', '2', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phoebe is in short patience today and we have only worked for 45 minutes.</p><ol><li>OPR: 19-33. She needed help with 3 sounds of ch. We did multi sound hopping game and she can remember at least 2 sounds now.&nbsp;</li><li>WPr: Phoebe forms letters in the right way and she was quite good at this.&nbsp;</li><li>new phonogram: five er.&nbsp;</li><li>SD: her first nurse works early. SHe is confused with y at the end of early as she wrote earle.</li><li>Sentence: SHe wrote I met her.&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-05-11 15:31:37', '2022-05-11 16:39:24'),
(2103, '2022/05/11', '03:32 pm', '2', '2', 'Toby Webb', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-11 15:32:24', '2022-05-11 15:32:24'),
(2104, '2022/05/11', '04:34 pm', '2', '2', 'Kaiden Reynolds', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-11 16:34:20', '2022-05-11 16:34:20'),
(2105, '2022/05/11', '04:34 pm', '2', '1', 'Angus Zeeman', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-11 16:34:43', '2022-05-11 16:34:43'),
(2106, '2022/05/11', '04:34 pm', '2', '2', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - Precisely say, write and read words in Section R', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Pop Quiz -- Some MM words. Angus still got a couple incorrect even though I KNOW we\'ve looked at them in class roughly a million times!&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 20, 2, others Angus just provide rule and I provide number</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: example-flew</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Creative Writing Task. Why you should vote for [Angus] in the upcoming federal election. Create plan covering 3 areas (why you shouldn\'t vote for the other parties, my policies, why you should vote for me) before writing the first draft.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>In his pop quiz, Angus very clearly was giving it no effort and didn’t apply anything that I KNOW he knows (e.g. rule 11, which he always spots and applies without prompting in spelling).&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Might show Angus some paragraph plans. I told him he didn\'t need to put down all the information, just dot points, but he still went the route of putting full sentence dot points on his plan. I did manage to get him away from this eventually -- but I can see why he hates planning if he always does it like this, because it really does feel like the same thing twice over!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-11 16:35:06', '2022-05-11 17:32:57'),
(2107, '2022/05/11', '04:35 pm', '2', '2', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR&nbsp;</p><p>SD</p><p>Introduced Xave to voice to text.&nbsp;</p><p>Using sentences as story starters he spoke 3 short paragraphs into his phone. We used the theme of Spooky Stories as sent to me by his teacher. Xavier experienced instant success with this and eagerly completed each task. His language choices were at a level above what he would hve chosen if he had written the paragraphs. Xavier assigned 2 short stories to dictate, email to himself and then to me for homework.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-11 16:35:22', '2022-05-16 20:13:47'),
(2109, '2022/05/12', '07:33 am', '2', '1', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving division by a one digit number including those that result in a remainder', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using made-up problems, Nate and I were working on:</p><ul><li>Apply place value to partition, rearrange and regroup numbers to at least tens of thousands to assist calculations and solve problems.</li><li>Investigate number sequences involving multiples of 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, and 9.</li><li>Recall multiplication facts up to 10 × 10 and related division facts&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Overall, Nate did a good job. Most of his answers were accurate. However, he struggles with the 6 and 7 times tables.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 1 was delivered on 05.05.2022</p>', '2022-05-12 07:33:49', '2022-07-03 11:14:58'),
(2115, '2022/05/12', '11:18 am', '2', '1', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 70', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-12 11:18:58', '2022-05-16 20:04:30'),
(2116, '2022/05/12', '11:19 am', '2', '2', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-12 11:19:32', '2022-05-12 11:19:32'),
(2117, '2022/05/12', '11:21 am', '2', '2', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving division by a one digit number including those that result in a remainder', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'To Be Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Using Singapore Education textbooks No 3 and 4 and made-up problems, Luca and I were working on:</p><ul><li>Long additions without carrying.</li><li>Long additions with carrying.</li><li>Long subtractions without borrowing.</li><li>Long subtractions with borrowing.</li><li>Long multiplications by one-digit numbers.</li><li>Long multiplications by 2-digit numbers.&nbsp;</li><li>Long divisions with 1 digit with and without reminder.&nbsp;</li></ul>', NULL, '<p>Lessons No 2 and 3 were delivered on 25.05.22.&nbsp;<br>This was because of sickness and an injured finger, I couldn\'t be at work.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-05-12 11:21:57', '2022-06-13 13:39:44'),
(2119, '2022/05/12', '01:04 pm', '2', '1', 'Nell  Brooks', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', '<p>Using the Singapore Asia Education textbook today\'s lesson was on solving problems by adding and taking away.&nbsp;</p><p>Also, I introduced divisions and were looking at the definitions and how divisions are connected to subtractions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Nell had her first lesson of the term during the Autumn holidays, 28.04.22</p>', '2022-05-12 13:04:52', '2022-07-02 22:23:47'),
(2120, '2022/05/12', '02:11 pm', '2', '1', 'Mia Harvey', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-12 14:11:43', '2022-05-12 14:11:43'),
(2122, '2022/05/12', '03:07 pm', '2', '1', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week One catch up</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 12 May 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick D1 supplemental</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #12</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>OPR/WPR: gu igh ey oo ch wr wh</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: my, up, last, not</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Use 3 words in sentences - EC can write&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>LP was an angel today! He was engaged and focused for our whole lesson, and we got so much done. It was probably the best lesson we\'ve had in a while. Really good with PA and MA, good with phonos including new ones. I was amazed at how good he was when we did SD. He did come up to the board and do a bit of \"helping\" i.e. rewriting what I wrote, while I explained the rules, but he was quiet and seemed to absorb what I was saying. Lewis was able to apply these concepts to our spelling words with a little prompting. He really wanted to draw pea-shooters, so gave me his SD words in sentences about&nbsp; pea-shooters, and drew a pic to go with it.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-12 15:08:29', '2022-05-23 17:43:55'),
(2123, '2022/05/12', '03:20 pm', '2', '2', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Since last week while we were working on perimeter and area, today\'s lesson focus was on multiplications and divisions.&nbsp;</p><p>We review adding and subtracting in groups.&nbsp;</p><p>Finding group numbers, “how many groups of X can you find in Y”&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-12 15:20:56', '2022-07-02 20:11:54'),
(2124, '2022/05/12', '03:27 pm', '2', '1', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-12 15:27:10', '2022-05-12 15:27:10'),
(2125, '2022/05/12', '03:35 pm', '2', '2', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 100', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Solved long division with base ten blocks and place value chart, so Lucy can see what parts of the number she is processing at each step of the equation (Hundreds then Tens then Ones after each subtraction) and the associated values. This was useful in many ways as Lucy had to produce a physical action for every step she completed on the equation demonstrating her understanding of the process she had completed and also checking the answer she produced.</p><p>Algebra – Key Maths Essential Resources – Review the term and definition of ‘expression’ – Algebra Concept Cluster 7 Lesson 1.&nbsp; Complete Algebra Concept Cluster 7 – Lesson 2 in exercise book.&nbsp;Review with articulation at the end making connections between the two algebraic equations provided.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-12 15:35:08', '2022-05-19 16:00:01'),
(2126, '2022/05/12', '04:21 pm', '2', '2', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Paragraphs - Two or more sentences about a topic presented in a logical order of ideas with appropriate indentations and margins', 'Answer check for understanding questions about subject of a sentence, first & third person subject pronouns, related sentences, topic', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Informative writing continued</p><p>Finn revised and edited his paragraph for a final time and then published it. (Computer.)</p><p>Spelling:</p><p>Using words from Finn’s writing I dictated them as a short Spalding spelling activity. Finn used his vowel sounds table to assist him in deciding which was correct.&nbsp;</p><p>HW</p><p>Research (5 mins max) Jupiter and plan and compose a first draft (written).</p>', NULL, '2022-05-12 16:21:44', '2022-05-26 17:41:57'),
(2127, '2022/05/12', '04:28 pm', '2', '1', 'Samuel Lamont', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-12 16:28:54', '2022-05-12 16:28:54'),
(2128, '2022/05/12', '04:33 pm', '2', '2', 'Chelsea Cooper', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 12 May 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #12</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: ur th er ng igh oo sh ay&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 17, 13, 18, 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. K - spell, poor, finish, hurt, maybe, across, tonight, tenth</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Prefixes and suffixes recap</td></tr><tr><td>Practice page</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ORF x3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>CC better with MA than PA - super quick today! Really good with phonos, SD pretty solid in terms of rhythm of the process, although did need some prompting on a couple of concepts. Recap/intro of prefix/suffixes using EP pages, did some practice, then did a worksheet. Chels used two of the words in sentences. Was going to finish with ORF, but CC really wanted to have a go at reading the last ORF in the book! She stumbled on every second word, but did get through it - even though she couldn\'t tell me much about what it said!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-12 16:33:29', '2022-05-23 18:23:20'),
(2129, '2022/05/12', '04:35 pm', '2', '2', 'James Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 12 May 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #14</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: ur th er ng igh oo sh ay&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 20, 17, 29, 4, 26</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. L - express, turn, lesson, half, father, anything, table, high, June&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Prefixes and suffixes recap</td></tr><tr><td>Practice page</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ORF x3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Homework: Prefix practice page</td></tr><tr><td>Really good with PA and MA, improving lots. No issues with phonos. James\' pencil broke as we started SD (lead was broken, wouldn\'t sharpen), so I got him a pacer, and I think it was the magic move. His handwriting was absolutely stunning after he started using the pacer. I\'m not sure whether it\'s to do with the lead density or weight of the pacer, or whether he was just going slower and focusing more... either way it\'s amazing! I was so impressed with JC SD. He was completely onto it and providing answers in Spalding-textbook perfection. Recap of prefix/suffix using tangibles, and JC grasped quickly - able to articulate. Went through homework - self-corrected errors without me saying anything. Finished with a few ORF.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-12 16:37:51', '2022-05-23 18:20:10'),
(2130, '2022/05/12', '04:38 pm', '2', '2', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics – Foundation', 'Shape and measurement', 'PLEASE SEE THE NOTES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p><strong>Similar figures and scale factors</strong></p><ul><li>review the conditions for similarity of two-dimensional figures, including similar triangles</li><li>use the scale factor for two similar figures to solve linear scaling problems</li></ul><p>Finlay brought school work to be completed on the concepts listed above. We did as much as we could, but there are some problems to be done. As always, I let Finlay know that if needed my help during the weekend, he could email his questions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-12 16:38:46', '2022-07-02 18:42:36'),
(2131, '2022/05/12', '04:56 pm', '2', '2', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Trigonometry', 'SOH CAH TOA', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callisto is well behind the rest of the class in Maths and so we had a discussion about what it was best to do. She has been concentrating on the work at the point she is up to when working in class and has thus missed teacher explanations for more advanced work. We decided that she should listen to teacher discussions of content and that we would skip some of the familiar content in an attempt to try and get her a bit more up to date. To that end, we worked on Bearings and then some Trig problems involving bearings.</p>', NULL, '2022-05-12 16:57:39', '2022-05-12 17:56:24'),
(2132, '2022/05/12', '04:37 pm', '2', '2', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from two syllable word - Kilpatrick Level D', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Two</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 9 May 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick D1 supplemental</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #11</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>OPR/WPR: gu ph oe ey ch ar</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Look at last week\'s homework</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: continue A-G - you will we an</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Dominoes</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Homework: use spelling words in sentences (handwriting focus, can draw accompanying pictures), can look/see/cover/write/check words: you, will, we, an, my, up, last, not</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Good with PA, some prompting with MA (maybe partly due to being a bit distracted). Pretty good with phonos. Needed OPR prompting with gu, ey, ch order, and prompting with most for WPR. Continued SD, recapped rules (LP not remembering straight away), might need a little practice to refamiliarise. LP seems to understand but struggles to articulate his understanding. Played dominoes while EC did homework. Used today\'s SD words + next week\'s, and added a \'cheat sheet\' for Alysia again. Feedback from Alysia that this type of homework is working really well for them both.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-12 17:35:49', '2022-05-23 17:45:36'),
(2133, '2022/05/12', '05:40 pm', '2', '2', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'English Literature', 'Genre - Poetry', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus Poetry: rhyme and structure&nbsp;</p><p>Cara read a short poem by Dorothea McKellar, which had a strong rhyming and rhythmical structure.</p><p>She analysed the language in a previous lesson so today she looked at the structure and how it influenced the emotion or feelings the piece invoked.</p><p>Cara then chose a theme from a select few - A swiftly flowing stream, and she created a short 6 line poem following the same structure as the given poem. This was challenging for Cara as she struggles with descriptive language outside a very limited range. She did demonstrate some use of similes and used alternative words for fast. &nbsp;</p><p>Cara then chose Soccer as her second theme and dove into creating a poem immediately. She consistently reviewed each step and chose better language, revised her choices for rhyme, and produced a flowing and exciting piece of writing! Cara was very proud of herself and enjoyed the process immensely.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-12 17:40:44', '2022-05-26 15:45:16'),
(2134, '2022/05/12', '06:35 pm', '2', '2', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Extend and apply the index laws to variables, using positive integer indices and the zero index', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we did a comprehensive review on index law and expansion.&nbsp;</p><p>All rules were checked and at the end, we did a quiz where Nicholas got 11/16 questions.&nbsp;</p><p>When it is necessary to apply 2 or 3 rules at a single time, Nicholas is capable of solving the problems. However, if it is necessary to use more than 3 rules he gets confused. I would like to point out that the last kind of problems are way above standard level and Nicholas wasn\'t afraid to attempt to solve the problem.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-12 18:35:07', '2022-07-02 17:06:55'),
(2135, '2022/05/13', '08:51 am', '2', '3', 'Mason Turner', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving multiplication and division', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Mason has many difficulties with equations, during both lessons he didn\'t have any confidence on what he was doing.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>On Friday 13.05.2022 Mason came in the morning and afternoon.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-05-13 08:51:10', '2022-07-02 10:11:15'),
