(2181, '2022/05/18', '03:33 pm', '2', '2', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-50 (intro 45-50)</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: th ou ch oi ea ck wh ow er ar&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: ago-this</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Game: Words at Work</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Write sentences using words, create oral sentences.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SCORE 1.5</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Put half an hour timer on my phone and told Max that if he finished spelling before it went off we could do whatever activity or game he chose afterwards. Max did wonderfully! We finished OPR-SD in a little under 25 minutes.</td></tr><tr><td>Sounded out took with first sound, blended, then sounded out again with second sound!</td></tr><tr><td>Max is going well, but I noticed in Words at Work his instinct was to ask me to read a word rather than sound it out himself (even though I picked easily decodable words for us to play with!)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-18 15:33:45', '2022-05-18 16:28:13'),
(2182, '2022/05/18', '03:36 pm', '2', '2', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Jimmy and I planned and started on his Outdoor Education project. This included showing Jimmy a practical application of the CRAP method during research, as well as how to synthesise his own knowledge with research. We also went through an overview of his English assessment and highlighted words that he thought could have been improved by using more academic writing. We then went over some spelling errors from his last draft!&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-18 15:36:22', '2022-06-02 15:02:02'),
