(2185, '2022/05/18', '04:41 pm', '2', '3', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 51-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: oe ie si ough ei ey wr&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Last weeks spelling words: example enemy exciting excite excitement fierce flies flew</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 29 10 5</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: forgot-hurry</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Vocab: Use words in sentences to show meaning. Create 3 related sentences following a beginning/middle/end structure.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>I had Angus write the words from last week\'s spelling lesson down as a quick \'pop quiz\' today in the WPR. Unfortunately some of them had already left Angus\' memory… I think, as much as he\'ll be resistant to it, I\'m going to start sending home sentence work every week. I talked to him about it a bit today and we agreed on repetitive, drill work even though it\'s a bit boring. Then I\'ll give him a quiz. Once in a while a break or something different.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Persausive writing at school. Why animals shouldn\'t be kept in zoos.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<p>Angus 15min late today (mo. rang to inform he would be)</p>', '2022-05-18 16:42:07', '2022-05-18 17:40:42'),
