(2187, '2022/05/18', '05:16 pm', '2', '3', 'Jett  Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Solve problems involving simple interest', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<ol><li>Solve problems involving simple interest.</li><li>Connect the compound interest formula to repeated applications of simple interest using appropriate digital technologies.</li></ol><p>Today we started to solve problems with the above standard level.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Pearson textbook chapter 10.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-18 17:16:59', '2022-06-11 20:00:52'),
(2188, '2022/05/18', '05:19 pm', '2', '3', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', NULL, '<p>T2W3</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Discussed his English Assessment Task and worked on creating a word bank for Sensory language. Xavier brainstormed in his work book and then entered the words into a word document. Emailed to me for record keeping.&nbsp;</li><li>Punctuation as a tool to create mood. We practiced urgency, and fear.</li><li>Spelling was integrated into all tasks. Xavier is becoming less hung up on producing work of a higher quality when spelling is taken off the table at the planning stage. Editing is still important and we continue to identify strategies to apply his knowledge.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-18 17:20:50', '2022-05-18 17:42:55'),
(2189, '2022/05/18', '05:18 pm', '2', '2', 'Thomas Anderson', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'INEQUALITIES', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', '<p>Using Essential Mathematics 10 &amp; 10A, we worked on inequalities.&nbsp;</p><p>We worked towards, solving linear inequalities and graphing their solutions on a number line. Thomas did a great job. A few times he got confused when we had to use numerals in the denominator.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 2 was delivered on 13.05.22</p>', '2022-05-18 17:36:13', '2022-07-02 12:49:34'),
(2190, '2022/05/18', '05:43 pm', '2', '3', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Writing - Sentence Construction & Vocabulary', 'Attributes of a declarative sentence (capital letter, subject noun + action or linking verb, full stop) - States a fact or opinion', 'Recognise/Analyse/Compose simple declarative sentences that include subject pronouns, present tense regular action verbs', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W3</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR</p><p>&nbsp;dge gi sh ti si ci o u y I e a s ow ou &nbsp;er ir ur wor ear or</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD Rule Review &nbsp;4, 14,11, 17</p><p>SECT Q&nbsp;</p><p>represent - entire</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing</p><p>Review first 2 complex sentence structures</p><p>Compose a complex sentence using the dependant clause “although I did not progess”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Write four quality <strong>complex</strong> sentences using the <strong>dependant clauses</strong> given.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Exclamatory Sentence</td><td>After I scored</td></tr><tr><td>Declarative Sentence</td><td>Before I went to bed</td></tr><tr><td>Interrogative Sentence</td><td>While I am waiting</td></tr><tr><td>Imperative Sentence</td><td>Even though you aren’t tired</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading OF 510&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-18 17:43:35', '2022-05-18 17:47:02'),
