(2194, '2022/05/19', '03:29 pm', '2', '1', 'James  Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week One</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 5 May 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #13</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: oa ew a ar er o ou ur ea th ti</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 17, 29, 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. L - soap, news, new, small, smaller, smallest, war, summer, above</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr><tr><td>Talk about comparative and superlative, use in sentences to show meaning. Talk about context helping us understand words</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ORF x1</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Homework: Prefix practice page</td></tr><tr><td>Good with PA and MA (some prompting), prompting with ti but otherwise fine on phonos. No cues for rules, JC was all over it and could tell me what was happening in each word. He drew a picture of things that were small, smaller and smallest, then we read for a bit.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-19 15:29:41', '2022-05-23 18:19:05'),
(2195, '2022/05/19', '03:30 pm', '2', '2', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-19 15:30:22', '2022-05-19 15:30:22'),
(2196, '2022/05/19', '03:30 pm', '2', '3', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'English Literature', 'Genre - Poetry', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus Poetry Cont.</p><p>Haiku - History/Purpose/Examine/Compose</p><p>We examined several examples of traditional and non-traditional haikus.</p><p>We explored the structure of each example, and discussed the history behind this.</p><p>Cara then experimented creating her own Haiku. As is always the case, her descriptive language choices are simplistic. Cara chose Dogs, and Grass as her themes and produced 2 simple haikus consistent with the traditional structure.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-19 15:30:34', '2022-05-26 15:52:21'),
(2197, '2022/05/19', '03:36 pm', '2', '3', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 100', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Key Maths Algebra, Concept Cluster 6, Lesson 1, practice 1 and 2 -&nbsp;</p><p>When asked what skill this activity is helping to develop, Lucy was able to say that it is a form of “algebra since it has a missing number - had to do the opposite so that you had a takeaway. &nbsp;Was given the answer and one number from the equation. &nbsp;To find the missing number, had to do a take away- the number in the sum was taken away from the answer to solve the addition.” &nbsp;Performed a take away to solve a plus. &nbsp;Much prompting needed to use this language, but Lucy understood the process once she was clear on the requirements of the task.</p><p>New Syllabus Primary Maths Level Three - Page 93 Questions 3 and 4. &nbsp;Prompting needed to use the ‘draw a picture strategy’. &nbsp;Unable to solve these problems independently. &nbsp;Initially suggested she would need division, but after talking through the problem, Lucy was able to recognise she was using multiplication.</p><p>Lucy was also encouraged to tick off when she has processed/reformatted each layer of the problem story: &nbsp;drawn a picture to reformat the information, recorded and labeled a equation to reformat and solve the question.</p><p>It was noted that Lucy needs time to think about a problem and to solve it, and also that sometimes I feel as though I might start prompting prematurely. &nbsp;Lucy didn\'t contribute her thoughts to this conversation, so unless reflections are shared, I\'ll continue giving Lucy what I think is a reasonable time to begin working in the context of a one-hour lesson.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-19 15:36:36', '2022-05-19 17:00:55'),
(2198, '2022/05/19', '03:56 pm', '2', '1', 'Seth Vanderlaan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-19 15:56:11', '2022-05-19 15:56:11'),
(2199, '2022/05/19', '04:21 pm', '2', '3', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Paragraphs - Two or more sentences about a topic presented in a logical order of ideas with appropriate indentations and margins', 'Categorise given sentences as related or not related - articulate/explain why/why not > edit for capitalisation, punctuation, spelling & grammar (English conventions)', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>&nbsp;</p><p>Informative Writing</p><p>Using the writing process throughout this session, Finn revised, editted and published his informative paragraph on Jupiter.</p><p>During the revise phase we examined sentence structure and how the structure can change the tone of the writing, and hold the reader\'s interest.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-19 16:21:43', '2022-05-26 16:00:43'),
(2200, '2022/05/19', '04:29 pm', '2', '3', 'Chelsea Cooper', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Three</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 19 May 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #13</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: igh ti ar ch ci ir th ee ai si</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 17</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. K - sir, these, those, club, seen, see, felt, full, fail</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ORF x3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Fine with PA, MA, OPR/WPR, SD. Introduced alliteration and had a lot of fun brainstorming words starting with the same sounds, then turning them into sentences.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-19 16:29:44', '2022-05-30 09:50:51'),
(2201, '2022/05/19', '04:33 pm', '2', '2', 'Samuel Lamont', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-19 16:33:13', '2022-05-19 16:33:13'),
(2202, '2022/05/19', '04:51 pm', '2', '3', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Trigonometry', 'SOH CAH TOA', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callisto is still working her way through right-angle triangle trig. We worked through some 2 triangle problems on the board and then did some examples from the textbook. Callisto is now well behind the class (at least 1 set behind).</p>', NULL, '2022-05-19 16:51:01', '2022-05-19 18:10:34'),
(2203, '2022/05/19', '05:28 pm', '2', '2', 'Nell  Brooks', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Topics covered:</p><ul><li>Carrying/Borrowing.</li><li>Word problems with + and -</li><li>Divisions with reminders.</li><li>Introduction to fractions.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Nell is improving slowly but steady. We still use counters to solve some problems, particularly, problems related to multiplications and divisions. The idea is to reduce the use of this aid and rely more on mental strategies and writing down the sums/counting we use to solve the problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson 2 was delivered on 12.05.2022</p>', '2022-05-19 17:29:40', '2022-07-02 22:37:55'),
(2204, '2022/05/19', '05:29 pm', '2', '3', 'Sofia Creek', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>I was on sick leave and couldn\'t have lesson 3. I sent several emails to Shaye but she never replied to arrange the catch-up. I let Juno, Naomi and Ellie know about this situation via email (Fri 3/06/2022 9:49 AM)</p>', '2022-05-19 17:30:23', '2022-07-02 20:22:59'),
(2205, '2022/05/19', '05:33 pm', '2', '2', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Decimals', 'Operations with decimals', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Ava wanted to practice operations with decimals as in school she\'s working with those.&nbsp;</p><p>We did a quick revision on the connection between divisions and decimals.&nbsp;</p><p>Then how a decimal can be transformed into a fraction.&nbsp;</p><p>Looked at the four operations with decimals. When we were working on whole numbers and decimals divided by decimals, we did a quick review on multiplications and divisions by 10, 100 and 1000 using decimals.</p><p>All the problems were made up of problems and a few from the internet.&nbsp;</p><p>Ava and I worked on this at the end of term 4 2021. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>This lesson was delivered on 13.05.2022</p>', '2022-05-19 17:35:04', '2022-07-02 08:30:15'),
(2206, '2022/05/19', '05:35 pm', '2', '1', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Proper, improper, mixed number, equivalent', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Shannon and Ava let me know that today we need to work on operations with mixed numbers and improper fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>Using Essential Mathematics Y 7, Ava and I started the lesson by doing a quick review on operations with fractions and how to simplify fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>Then we moved to do operations with mixed numbers and fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>Converting mixed numbers into fractions and vice-versa.&nbsp;</p><p>I looked into Google to find some word problems related to mixed numbers and fractions, in this part, we had some difficulties. However, the majority of the problems we did were high levels of difficulty.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>This lesson was delivered on 06.05.2022</p>', '2022-05-19 17:35:32', '2022-07-02 08:36:26'),
(2207, '2022/05/20', '02:31 pm', '2', '3', 'Molly  Jackson', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) second phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level K', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilaptrick K2</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 44</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ng ea au wh ed ew gu&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 8 28 9 6</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: world-list</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ayres words in sentences of different structures.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Molly was very overexcitable today and a bit silly.</td></tr><tr><td>She was okay until spelling, when she realised that we only had 30 minutes left, and then to overcompensate she got extremely speedy and her handwriting was rushed and messy. She also faltered in her sounding out. She started acting up and being silly, but when I said we were going to stop spelling and do something else better suited to her mood, she begged to keep going and promised to be sensible. She was very sweet. Spelling got finished quickly and efficiently. I think she was on a sugar high from the hot chocolate she had earlier.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-20 14:31:38', '2022-05-20 16:17:13'),
(2209, '2022/05/20', '03:32 pm', '2', '3', 'Connor Thompson ', 'Mathematics', 'Linear & Non-Linear Relationships', 'Linear relationships (Co-ordinates, Cartesian Plane)', 'School-assigned worksheet/task', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Connor brought in a number planes worksheet. I explained the cartesian plane to him, axis (using car axis as example), how you can put every possible point on a graph but rather than drawing all those dots we draw a line (because there are so many dots, at every single point, that they look like a straight line). We worked through the problems together.</td></tr><tr><td>Connor did well once he got the hang of the questions. He was having trouble when asked for coordinates outside what he had initially graphed (using the given rule box)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-20 15:33:07', '2022-05-20 16:18:35'),
