(2211, '2022/05/20', '04:20 pm', '2', '3', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 44-62</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ng ea aw au ck ed ui&nbsp; ew gu ough oe ey igh&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 11 28 17</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: great-died</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use words in sentences.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Comp: Key Into Inference one sentence activities.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Nate was really silly today. I am STILL having to really push him to write neatly during spelling. He counteracts all my instructions. E.g., he \'couldn\'t\' use his ruler to underline underneath the blue line because he couldn\'t see where his ruler was lining up. It didn\'t matter about his spelling because he could still read it. It also doesn\'t work when I erase anything not good enough, because he thinks its hilarious and starts making mistakes on purpose. I tried something different this week and purposefully made my handwriting an illegible scrawl to emphasize that legible handwriting was important. Nate said, though, that it \"doesn\'t matter, because I know what it says and I don\'t mind if it\'s messy.\" I had to bring Naomi in to prove that some people WILL mind.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-20 16:38:40', '2022-05-20 17:56:09'),
(2212, '2022/05/20', '05:02 pm', '2', '3', 'Josh Zeeman', 'Academic Coaching', 'Independent Study', 'School Assigned Worksheet or Assignment', 'See Notes', 'Will Hughes', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Josh learnt the origins of hinduism through a ted talk video, took notes of the key points of the religion incl. but not limited origins, teachings, gods, size and location. Planned to do whole sheet, only got hinduism at draft level.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-20 17:03:06', '2022-05-20 17:16:20'),
