(2215, '2022/05/23', '02:38 pm', '2', '4', 'Luna Shapiro', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick F</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8 intro first and second sounds of a and show in words (segment, count, blend baby &amp; last). She now knows all sounds for a &amp; g</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: a-qu</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Handwriting: 2 o\'clock formation, a formation practice. 2x2 boxes and independent.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luna had some persistent difficulties with her handwriting today, including reversals and \'doubling over\' the circles in her 2 o\'clock letters. Interestingly, when she used her left hand to see how \'good\' her writing was with her non-dominant hand, her formation was correct every single time (she wrote a about 4 times). I have no idea why this is the case with her left hand but not her right one.</td></tr><tr><td>She was pretty cheeky today -- insistent on playing games, wriggling about on her chair, and even locking me out of the room at one point.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-23 14:38:46', '2022-05-23 16:15:59'),
(2216, '2022/05/23', '03:29 pm', '2', '4', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>Kilpatrick F. Mia and Thomas both were good at this</li><li>Challenge words: Mia-we, Thomas-open. They both need to be familiar more with rule 4 and marking system.</li><li>OPR: 35-43: first round, we did review and second round we did a hopping game for all sounds. Mia needs more understanding on the difference between ai and ay. They both need to understand more about the concept of five different ways writing er.</li><li>WPR: 35-43: Mia was good at ai, ay, oi, and oy. Thomas could not recall ay and oy.</li><li>Handwriting foucus: line letters e and n. They both were good at these.</li><li>New phonograms: ea and ng. We learned ea with a multi sound game.</li><li>Morphology activity 3.</li><li>SD: she. again, they need help with rule 4 and marking.</li></ol><p>They both are benefiting from their paired studying, yet sometimes they suffer from frustration when they lose in a competition.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-23 15:29:22', '2022-05-23 21:31:17'),
(2217, '2022/05/23', '03:29 pm', '2', '4', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>Kilpatrick F. Mia and Thomas both were good at this&nbsp;</li><li>Challenge words: Mia-we, Thomas-open. They both need to be familiar more with rule 4 and marking system.&nbsp;</li><li>OPR: 35-43: first round, we did review and second round we did a hopping game for all sounds. Mia needs more understanding on the difference between ai and ay. They both need to understand more about the concept of five different ways writing er.&nbsp;</li><li>WPR: 35-43: Mia was good at ai, ay, oi, and oy. Thomas could not recall ay and oy.&nbsp;</li><li>Handwriting foucus: line letters e and n. They both were good at these.&nbsp;</li><li>New phonograms: ea and ng. We learned ea with a multi sound game.</li><li>Morphology activity 3.&nbsp;</li><li>SD: she. again, they need help with rule 4 and marking.</li></ol><p>They both are benefiting from their paired studying, yet sometimes they suffer from frustration when they lose in a competition.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-05-23 15:29:57', '2022-05-23 21:29:54'),
(2218, '2022/05/23', '03:30 pm', '2', '4', 'Freya McIver', 'Academic Coaching', 'Independent Study', 'School Assigned Worksheet or Assignment', 'See Notes', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>FM brought two pieces of work for us to look at together. The first was a narrative text that she had written in response to a book they were studying in class. We read through it together, and I drew her attention to checking capitals, punctuation, spelling and tense. I was really impressed with what she\'d produced for this task. The second task was the same petroglyphs assignment we looked at last week. FM had basically finished it, so we did a little revise/edit of it (i was linking to WP steps all lesson). I prompted her a little with the fluency of the text - i.e. joining some simple sentences to make compound, and in bits that weren\'t super clear e.g. who is \'they\'?</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-23 15:30:21', '2022-05-23 17:32:31'),
