(2223, '2022/05/23', '04:32 pm', '2', '4', 'Arki Young', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write additional phonograms  (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Cards 71 > 87', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: Additional phonograms</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: See workbook</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 25 22 11</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: reason-chicken</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Writing Process: Create plan for Arki\'s gravity essay</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Comp: Key into inference level 3 advertising.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Arki did well at the key into inference activities when I read them aloud for him. It became clear quite quickly that he wouldn\'t be able to decode all the words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-23 16:32:24', '2022-06-16 15:47:58'),
(2224, '2022/05/23', '04:33 pm', '2', '4', 'Zac Pharaoh ', 'Mathematics', 'OTHER', 'OTHER', 'Please read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<ul><li>Use efficient mental and written strategies and apply appropriate digital technologies to solve problems.</li><li>Recognise that the place value system can be extended beyond hundredths.</li><li>Investigate and calculate \'best buys\', with and without digital technologies.&nbsp;</li></ul>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-23 16:33:19', '2022-06-11 19:25:10'),
(2225, '2022/05/23', '04:34 pm', '2', '4', 'Lachlan  Smith', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Four</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 23 May 2022</td></tr><tr><td>LS only</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick H2 S6</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #10</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: ou er ei th or ti au ea ough ci</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 20, 4, 14, 15,&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. N - mixture, nation, pause, peace, permission, rough, social, steal, strange</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Continue work on election passage</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>No CM today (COVID), so just LS and I. It was a much quieter lesson than normal, and I was surprised by how well LS actually worked. Powered through PA, MA, phonos, SD, LS did well. Continued on with PM persuasive text. Structured intro and conc in planning doc, and then LS started his compose.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-23 16:34:29', '2022-05-23 17:26:08'),
(2226, '2022/05/23', '04:34 pm', '2', '4', 'Angus Singleton', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-05-23 16:34:37', '2022-05-23 16:34:37'),
(2227, '2022/05/23', '05:01 pm', '2', '4', 'Arlo Clark', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>Phonological awareness:</li><li>Arlo scored obtained full marks on his rhyme recognition, syllable blending, word number recognition, phoneme isolation of final sound, and phoneme deletion of final sound.</li><li>He needed help with phoneme segmentation and blending.</li><li>This means that Arlo has a good systematic awareness about most individual sounds and needs help with some confusing sounds such as th and f. It can be difficult for some young kids to say the sound th and r at a young age. Their mouth muscle is not quite ready for certain precise motions, which is normal, but we will practice this at our sessions.</li><li>&nbsp;</li><li>Oral Phonogram Review: out of 30 phonograms, Arlo could say at least one sound for each phonogram except qu. He is a bit confused with b and d, qu and up, but he could always work them out with some articulation.</li><li>&nbsp;</li><li>Written Phonogram Review: out of 30 phonograms above, Arlo wrote 27 correctly. He wrote k, th, and ch backwards. And interestingly, he wrote qu in the right way!</li><li>Spelling: From the Morrison McCall Spelling Scale test, Arlo\'s spelling age is around 6 years and 8 months, which means he is around 1 year behind. He is good at recognizing phonemes yet he needs correction on his connection between sounds and phonograms. We will be working on this in our session and help him build a strong concept of sounds and phonograms(representatives of sound/written version of sounds). For example, he wrote cee for the word sea. c and s share one same sound s, ee and ea share one same sound ee. We will be learning all these and he would be able to recognize them eventually.</li><li>Reading. According to the Burt Word Reading Test we did, Arlo\'s reading age is between 6 and 7. According the Waddington Diagnostic reading test 1 we did; Arlo\'s reading age is between 6 years 7 months and 6 years 11 months. Surprisingly, instead of decoding, Arlo reads most words in a natural way!</li></ol><p>In general, Arlo is a lovely and hardworking kid. He might write or read some words backwards(qu, b, d, th, ch, z, k), it does not necessarily mean he has dyslexia. By the way, was he diagnosed?&nbsp;</p><p>My suggestion:<br>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>We will have homework in the future and please help supervise and help him at home.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Encourage more reading at home, especially the decodable books.</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-05-23 17:01:38', '2022-05-25 09:07:37'),
(2229, '2022/05/23', '05:26 pm', '2', '4', 'Connor McLaren', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Absent with COVID</p>', '2022-05-23 17:26:48', '2022-05-23 17:56:42'),
(2230, '2022/05/23', '05:32 pm', '2', '2', 'Freya McIver', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete final sound in word or final blend - Kilpatrick Level I', 'Ellie Connor', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Two</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 9 May 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick G2</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #5</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Challenge word: information (morphology)</td></tr><tr><td>What other words can we make with the base word \'inform\'?</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: gi ow sh er ea th ng ch ee</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 4, 5, 29, 6, 13</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. Q - firm, region, religion, convict, private, command, debate, crowd, factory, publish&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use WP to start a piece of persuasive writing (relate back to the science of persuasion principles): If I was prime minister I would…</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Freya was amazing today! So nice to have her back. Really good with both PA and MA, no issues with phonograms or SD (reminder of \'gi\'). Did challenge word on the board. Extra good with SD today. Very engaged with our PM persuasive writing passage, completed a plan and related it back to persuasive principles.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-23 17:40:40', '2022-05-23 17:42:24'),
