(2297, '2022/05/30', '02:32 pm', '2', '5', 'Matthew Heard', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving multiplication and division', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<ul><li>Apply the distributive law to the expansion of algebraic expressions, including binomials, and collect like terms where appropriate.</li><li>Apply index laws to numerical expressions with integer indices.</li><li>Apply the distributive law to the expansion of algebraic expressions, including binomials, and collect like terms where appropriate.</li></ul><p>Matt is progressing positively. He\'s taking a lot less time to do the algebraic operations. Although, sometimes he forgets to apply the sign law and to do operations like -5 -12.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-30 14:32:42', '2022-06-11 17:32:20'),
(2298, '2022/05/30', '03:27 pm', '2', '5', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpattrick F. Mia and Thomas are both good at this section. we might need to move up a level.</p><p>OPR: a, e, i, o, u, b, d, g, sh, c, s, ee,th, ow. We used the try not to moo game as a competition to see who can win their first sticker for the session. They both focused very well as they are competitive. Thomas occasionally confused b and d. Mia needed help with u and ow.&nbsp;<br>WPR: a, e, i, o, u, b, d, g, sh, c, s, ee,th, ow. Thomas hesitated for b and d. He wrote sh backwards. MiA did great on this. They both hesitated for ow. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Handwriting focus: clockface d. This was a good practice for Thomas. Mia always has good handwriting.&nbsp;<br>Phonogram review: ng. Mark out ng in words. &nbsp;They are not familair with this new phonogram. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Morphology activity 4<br>SD: A-G. pink book page 1 color coded all vowels, vowels that are at the end of a syllable, and vowels that are at the end of a syllable and also say their names-rule 4 practice. &nbsp;Thomas graspped rule 4 from this. Mia is also slowly understanding rule 4. She will need more pracrice.&nbsp;</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>