(2320, '2022/05/31', '05:33 pm', '2', '1', 'Lucy Crosswell', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>The Spiel.</td></tr><tr><td>When we speak we use sounds to talk to each other [show sound card]</td></tr><tr><td>Segment and blend:&nbsp;cat dog sheep</td></tr><tr><td>Vowels and consonant sounds. Explain. Model. Lucy identify vowel/consonant sounds.</td></tr><tr><td>Explain we use letters to show sounds when we want to communicate without speaking. Letters go in words go in sentences.</td></tr><tr><td>Begin Vowels and Consonants reference page in workbook -- cat and parrot drawings.</td></tr><tr><td>OPR 1-8 + i e u, introduce 2nd sounds.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Promising lesson with Lucy today, she was pretty chatty but picked concepts up well. Got a little muddled with listening for sounds in words. Started struggling at F1 for Kilpatrick. For next week: important to get a look at her letter formation and address pencil grip. Spoke to Mel and she said Lucy used to use a pencil grip to help. Also said Lucy\'s just been put in a handwriting class that she\'s a bit miffed about, because she feels her writing is very neat (which it is -- must be a formation issue?)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-05-31 17:33:50', '2022-05-31 18:55:36'),
(2321, '2022/06/01', '07:48 am', '2', '5', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Luke started in a grumpy mood and he would not sit down. He likes to walk around and move around in the room even when he is doing his tasks.</p><p>Challenge:&nbsp;<br>3 minutes words. Luke wrote 35 words in 3 minutes and scored 33. He spelt minutes and bored wrong. (minotes/bord)</p><p><br>OPR/WPR: e, or, g, a, y, oo, th, s, er, c. He hesitated a bit for y and a.&nbsp;</p><p>y&amp;a multi sound ball game.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;parts of speech sorting activity. Luke pointed out two words that can be both noun and verb, which was great.(fish/skateboard)</p><p>writing process-first two steps. we recapped the first 2 steps.</p><p>Narrative paragraph-a scary thing happended in my holiday. Luke wrote 3 sentences. 1 simple sentence and 2 compound sentences. He needs help with punctuations within his long compound sentences.&nbsp;</p><p>Spelling mistake: &nbsp; turn-tern. woke-woak<br>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 07:50:54', '2022-06-01 08:49:48'),
(2322, '2022/06/01', '07:52 am', '2', '5', 'Darcy Callaghan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-01 07:52:51', '2022-06-01 07:52:51'),
(2323, '2022/06/01', '01:47 pm', '2', '5', 'Eleanor  Stam', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 11: Drop the silent final \'e\' when adding a vowel ending/suffix', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W5</p><p>Rule 9 and 10&nbsp; sorting</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR</p><p>Gn kn wr wh gu ph ough ow ou oe oa oo ie ei ey eigh ea&nbsp; ng ed</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD</p><p>Silent final e words as base words</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Hope (ing) have (ing) dance (er) charge (es) brake (ed) save (ed)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule teaching: 11</p><p>Words as above plus worksheet.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing</p><p>Compound sentence, focus on structure – capital, punctuation, comma, fanboy.&nbsp;</p><p>Use a word from spelling list or worksheet.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Underline the subject noun and the verb (and object noun).</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading</p><p>Silent practice – Discuss and practised fluency. Timed reads both girls improved by over 20 words a minute.&nbsp;</p><p>Reading to each other.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Game: R9/10/11</p><p>Using blue cards from box scattered upside down, roll dice with 9/10/11 on it. First to get three correct of same rule.&nbsp;</p><p>Must articulate the rule and get it right to score a point.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW</p><p>Reading last paragraphs of sheets.</p><p>Rule 11 worksheet.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 13:47:07', '2022-06-07 10:16:03'),
(2324, '2022/06/01', '01:48 pm', '2', '5', 'Angel King', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 11: Drop the silent final \'e\' when adding a vowel ending/suffix', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W5</p><p>Rule 9 and 10&nbsp; sorting</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR</p><p>Gn kn wr wh gu ph ough ow ou oe oa oo ie ei ey eigh ea&nbsp; ng ed</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD</p><p>Silent final e words as base words</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Hope (ing) have (ing) dance (er) charge (es) brake (ed) save (ed)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule teaching: 11</p><p>Words as above plus worksheet.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing</p><p>Compound sentence, focus on structure – capital, punctuation, comma, fanboy.&nbsp;</p><p>Use a word from spelling list or worksheet.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Underline the subject noun and the verb (and object noun).</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading</p><p>Silent practice – Discuss and practised fluency. Timed reads both girls improved by over 20 words a minute.&nbsp;</p><p>Reading to each other.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Game: R9/10/11</p><p>Using blue cards from box scattered upside down, roll dice with 9/10/11 on it. First to get three correct of same rule.&nbsp;</p><p>Must articulate the rule and get it right to score a point.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW</p><p>Reading last paragraphs of sheets.</p><p>Rule 11 worksheet.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 13:48:22', '2022-06-07 10:12:25'),
