(2328, '2022/06/01', '02:59 pm', '2', '3', 'Jacob Tipping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Jacob</p><p>Waddington Reading</p><p>bushes/brushes</p><p>an/a</p><ul><li>Jacob reads with high prosody and his fluency has improved greatly.</li></ul><p>----</p><p>WPR (1-30)</p><p>s.c /x/ /k/</p><ul><li>Jacob tends to sometimes forget the basics, so reminders are often needed</li></ul><p><br>----</p><p>Writing Activity: Letter&nbsp;<br>\"favrouite/favourite\"&nbsp;<br>\"quins/queens\"</p><ul><li>The word “favourite” remains a challenge for Jacob - need more work with phonogram “ou” and SFE</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>----</p><p>Oral Fluency<br>Greek Mythology<br>\"altitude/attitude\" \"labbors/labours\" \"farrest/fairest\"</p><ul><li>Jacob really loves to read and learn about mythology! He does attempt to decode instead of guess, so this is great.</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-06-01 15:04:11', '2022-06-01 15:07:12'),
(2329, '2022/06/01', '03:04 pm', '2', '4', 'Jacob Tipping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Homophones</p><p>Errors: bear | stair | road | sore | soar | disturb | complete | incomplete | paid | confront | blow</p><ul><li>Jacob did 3 sets of 10 homophones as he found it to be enjoyable! Although he made a few errors, he remained upbeat. Since this was a Zoom call, it seemed as if he had more trouble reading.</li></ul><p><br>Tense: Past/Present</p><ul><li>Jacob generally did well. At first, he needed reminding of /ed/ being a signifier for past tense, but once he understood, he remembered.</li></ul><p><br>Parts of speech: Nouns &amp; Verbs</p><ul><li>Jacob found this challenging, especially nouns. This is something we will continue to go back to&nbsp;</li></ul>', '<p>Zoom</p>', '2022-06-01 15:08:34', '2022-06-01 15:16:33'),
(2330, '2022/06/01', '03:08 pm', '2', '5', 'Jacob Tipping', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phonemic Awareness</p><ul><li>Kilpatrick Level I1</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly</li></ul><p>OPR 46-54</p><ul><li>Errors /ed oa ew ui au/</li><li>The student found some difficulty with several of the phonograms - however it had been 5 months since we last did these phonograms</li></ul><p>WPR 46-54</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /ew ui au aw or/</li><li>Errors /au/</li><li>The student found some difficulty in whether or not it was /u/ or /i/ in /au/</li><li>However, the student showed confidence in understanding that English words couldn\'t end in /u/ or /i/!</li></ul><p>Morphology Affixes</p><ul><li>Base word quiz</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly</li><li>The student found some difficulty with \"quizzes = quizzs\"</li></ul><p>Spelling Dictation</p><ul><li>Rules: 1-6</li><li>quiz</li><li>race</li><li>magic</li><li>table</li><li>cry</li><li>silly</li><li>Errors \"quiz = quwiz\"</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly.</li><li>The student found some difficulty with /b/ and /d/, which will have to be re-addressed.</li></ul><p>Inferences</p><ul><li>Set: 2 Item: 14</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly</li><li>The student found some difficulty with none of the task - Jacob is wonderful with inferences!</li></ul><p>Oral Fluency</p><ul><li>Passage: 522</li><li>Errors \"enticed\"</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly. Jacob has greatly improved with reading, especially with fluency!</li></ul><p>Writing</p><ul><li>Writing Program Section: Sentences<br>Other Activity: Nouns/Verbs/Adverbs<br>Amount Completed: We ran out of time to review, but Jacob used the spelling words \"magic\" \"party\" and \"quiet\"!</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-06-01 15:17:09', '2022-06-01 15:18:43'),
(2331, '2022/06/01', '03:28 pm', '2', '5', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 11: Drop the silent final \'e\' when adding a vowel ending/suffix', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>&nbsp;T2W5</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPr/WPR – wh wr kn gn gu ie ei ea ey&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review – 9/10</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule teaching Rule 11</p><p>SD: Rule page</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Soccer Writing task – commentator (speech) Informative/narrative.</p><p>Use the photo to decide what has happened before and after the pic was taken over a 30 sec period.</p><p>Write the action from the point of view of a RADIO commentator. Be as descriptive and precise as possible</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Intro to use of speech in text.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 15:28:28', '2022-06-07 09:57:09'),
(2332, '2022/06/01', '03:28 pm', '2', '5', 'Toby Webb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-01 15:29:22', '2022-06-01 15:29:22'),
(2333, '2022/06/01', '03:30 pm', '2', '4', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Geometric Reasoning (Y3 onwards)', 'Formulae Proofs', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Using the Singapore education textbook No 4 and 5, made-up problems and mathisfun.com, Connor and I were working on:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Choose appropriate units of measurement for length, area, volume, capacity and mass.</li><li>Investigate and calculate percentage discounts of 10%, 25% and 50% on sale items, with and without digital technologies.</li></ul>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 5 was delivered on 01.06.22</p>', '2022-06-01 15:30:40', '2022-06-13 11:57:40'),
(2334, '2022/06/01', '03:17 pm', '2', '1', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I went through overviews of 3 upcoming assignments: Religion, History and Health. Tyler\'s comprehension is fine, however he needed help with structuring mentally and how to break each assignment down into tasks</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 15:39:29', '2022-06-01 16:49:52'),
(2335, '2022/06/01', '03:48 pm', '2', '5', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-01 15:50:40', '2022-06-01 15:51:43'),
