(2337, '2022/06/01', '04:26 pm', '2', '2', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Covid</p>', '2022-06-01 16:26:28', '2022-06-02 15:07:25'),
(2338, '2022/06/01', '04:31 pm', '2', '3', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Decimals', 'Operations with decimals', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Today, Kieran was part of Jacob\'s lesson.&nbsp;</p><p>I had planned to keep working with the measurement using decimals and different units. However, we couldn\'t do this as in our short revision on what we did last week, Jacob couldn\'t remember 100% of what we did and how to convert between mm, cm, m and km.&nbsp;</p><p>We took the time and did as many problems as possible on the board; at the end of the lesson, Jacob was on fire doing 10 base multiplications and divisions with decimals. I didn\'t give him homework today, only to write down in his tutoring notebook what we did today.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-01 16:31:38', '2022-07-01 22:01:59'),
(2340, '2022/06/01', '04:32 pm', '2', '5', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose first-person narrative paragraph', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Xavier continued to work on his English essay - Creating suspense through the use of sentence structure, language and punctuation.&nbsp;</p><p>Today\'s focus was on revising the sentence structure, and editing.&nbsp;</p><p>Xavier completed more than the required words required and produced a very enjoyable and suspenseful storyline.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 16:32:25', '2022-06-07 10:03:14'),
(2341, '2022/06/01', '04:34 pm', '2', '5', 'Kaiden Reynolds', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-01 16:34:10', '2022-06-01 16:34:10'),
(2343, '2022/06/01', '04:50 pm', '2', '1', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I worked on his Religion assignment. Tyler struggles with researching and structuring an introduction, as he still needs to get used to the TEEL structure, however he really took to completing TEEL in tables, reformatting and summarising. His spelling needs a lot of work, as he has a tendency to rush.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 16:51:00', '2022-06-01 16:52:43'),
(2344, '2022/06/01', '04:52 pm', '2', '2', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I worked through an overview of his upcoming assignments: English, History, and Career. Although he is taking more responsibility for his work and deadlines, he has a bad tendency to interrupt!</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 16:53:16', '2022-06-01 16:53:38'),
(2345, '2022/06/01', '04:53 pm', '2', '2', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I started planning his Career assignment, including his future goals, his personality, his strengths and weaknesses. This was challenging for Tyler as he found it hard to talk about his own strengths and was very critical of himself!&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 16:54:05', '2022-06-01 16:54:28'),
(2346, '2022/06/01', '04:54 pm', '2', '3', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I worked on his English assignment, which was to review Migrant Literature. Tyler found this assignment challenging, as it involved a lot of thinking outside of the box and into empathy/emotional territory. We again used the TEEL tables to plan out a response, which gave him a larger sense of structure!&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 16:55:01', '2022-06-01 16:56:00'),
(2347, '2022/06/01', '04:55 pm', '2', '3', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I worked on his History assignment regarding WWII and Hitler\'s rise. Tyler was fine with comprehension but continues to be interruptive with his own thoughts. It\'s great that he is enthusiastic and speaking up, but was informed that unless he learns how to listen, he will continue to make errors.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 16:56:37', '2022-06-01 16:56:58'),
(2348, '2022/06/01', '04:56 pm', '2', '4', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I worked on his Career assignment. Tyler informed me that his goal was to become a chef! He listened a lot more this lesson as we mapped out the path to TAFE, Apprenticeships, and employment.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 16:57:34', '2022-06-01 16:57:55'),
(2349, '2022/06/01', '04:57 pm', '2', '4', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I completed his Career assignment and started on a Cover Letter at his parents\' request. This will allow him to start work experience. This also involved Tyler needing to introspect and talk about his skills and strengths. At this point, Tyler is getting used to talking more about himself, though it is still met with some resistance!&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 16:58:22', '2022-06-01 16:58:54'),
(2350, '2022/06/01', '04:58 pm', '2', '5', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I worked on his History assignment involving Pearl Harbour. Tyler is far more confident with comprehension at this point and has really taken responsibility for taking notes and listening in class! He had completed 2 pages of handwritten notes! However, the dates confused him a little bit so we went through the order of events and utilised a map in order to help him visualise. He did struggle a bit with deciding what kind of pictures and primary sources to visually include, so we went over the CRAP method.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 17:00:36', '2022-06-01 17:00:54'),
