(2360, '2022/06/01', '05:25 pm', '2', '5', 'Nina Grun', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phonemic Awareness</p><ul><li>Kilpatrick Level I1</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly</li></ul><p>OPR 39-45</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms 5 sounds of \'er\'</li><li>Errors none!</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly with no errors</li></ul><p>WPR 39-45</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms 5 sounds of \'er\'</li><li>Errors /ur/ - recognised the mistake but was unsure as to the correct one</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed at a regular pace</li><li>The student found some difficulty with /ur/</li><li>However, the student showed confidence with the rest of the phonograms</li></ul><p>Morphology Compound Words</p><ul><li>Base word Donah 15</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly with no errors</li></ul><p>Spelling Dictation</p><ul><li>Rules: 1-6</li><li>squash</li><li>magic</li><li>dance</li><li>same</li><li>fly</li><li>very</li></ul><p>Oral Fluency</p><ul><li>Passage: 208</li><li>Errors \"generate\" \"though\"</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly</li><li>The student found some difficulty with longer words</li><li>However, the student showed confidence in fluency and prosody, and has incresed in both areas dramatically</li></ul><p>Writing</p><ul><li>Writing Program Section: Words starting with M</li><li>Other Activity: Letter to Jacob</li><li>Errors \"favourite\" \"animals\" \"chickens\" \"guinea\" direction of \"J\"</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed at a regular pace</li><li>The student found some difficulty between sounding phonograms and spelling</li><li>However, the student showed confidence in composing the letter</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-01 17:27:08', '2022-06-02 08:14:56'),
(2361, '2022/06/01', '05:35 pm', '2', '4', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Shape', '2D', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using the Singapore Education No 4 Luca and I were working on the area and perimeter of squares, rectangles and triangles.&nbsp;</p><p>Also solved worded problems where the perimeter was given and one side was missing.&nbsp;</p><p>In the majority of the problems we used decimals and sometimes fractions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lessons 5, and 6 last 1.5 to cover lesson No 4.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-01 17:35:18', '2022-06-13 15:20:59'),
(2362, '2022/06/01', '06:56 pm', '2', '1', 'Finn McKenzie', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Spelling Assessment for Ayres Placement', 'Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment - List 1', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PAST -- 90/102, Finn had great phonological awareness and only struggled with sometimes not understanding my instructions.</td></tr><tr><td>OPR 29/70. Finn unfamiliar with phonograms but could work out which sounds the phonograms made by \'working backwards\' and thinking of words that contained them.</td></tr><tr><td>MM - 8.8.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>BW - 11.10-12.04 Finn could read words he recognised. He commented that he couldn\'t read the words he didn\'t know.</td></tr><tr><td>Holburn - 9.09. Interestingly, Finn easily read \'scarcely\' when it was placed in the context of the sentence, when he couldn\'t decode it in BW. Finn occasionally self corrected and it was evident that he was using the context of the other words to determine which word he was looking at.</td></tr><tr><td>Wad Reading - 9.8.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-01 18:57:21', '2022-06-10 16:09:17'),
(2363, '2022/06/02', '07:27 am', '2', '4', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Investigate number sequences involving multiples of 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, and 9', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>I could notice some hesitation last Monday (30.05.2022) in terms of times tables.&nbsp;</p><p>For that reason, today we were looking at some skip counting strategies that will help Nate to work out a multiplication sum without taking too long.</p><p>Nate found this useful and in the end, he was solving all the problems in a short time and correctly.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 4 was delivered on 30.05.2022</p>', '2022-06-02 07:27:37', '2022-07-03 11:33:16'),
(2364, '2022/06/02', '07:50 am', '2', '2', 'Chester  Vincent', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 07:50:21', '2022-06-02 07:50:21'),
(2365, '2022/06/02', '08:49 am', '2', '3', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Develop confidence with number sequences to and from 100 by ones from any starting point', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We tried to do Mad Minute facts to 20 but it didn\'t go very well. Aiming to avoid another tantrum, we started to work with rounding using whole and some decimals.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Lesson No 3 was delivered on 26.05.2022</p>', '2022-06-02 08:49:48', '2022-07-03 08:58:58'),
(2366, '2022/06/02', '09:19 am', '2', '5', 'Tyler Van-Nimwegen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Tyler and I continued to make notes and study for his Religion and History exams on Monday. While Tyler is much more dialled into taking notes and understanding information, at some point he needs to revisit spelling and sentence structures. He has trouble knowning when to start and stop a sentence, most likely due to forgetting how clauses work.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-02 09:20:29', '2022-06-02 09:22:11'),
(2367, '2022/06/02', '11:51 am', '2', '1', 'Jemima Chalk', 'Music', 'Instrumental', 'Pieces', 'Playing through (to see where we’re at / checkpoint playing)', 'Sarah Eddleston', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Technique Work:</p><ul><li>Scales&nbsp;<ul><li>worked through Cm, G major, and E</li></ul></li></ul><p>Pieces</p><ul><li>Highlightes from Frozen<ul><li>Really think about just hitting the accented Cs and blurring in between, after all, it\'s gestural</li><li>Being able to sing it will help because you won\'t have to read it so carefully</li><li>Be careful with the final quaver rest before each bar, it\'s being cut short a bit because it\'s a change in the flow of the rhythm (3, 3, 3, 3, 4)</li><li>Definitely ignore the grace notes for now, nail what\'s already written, have it confident and in time, <i>then </i>we can worry about adding them back in</li><li>Again, be able to sing those runs, or know them well enough to no longer have to count where they come in</li><li>Discussed imagining the sound of it, hearing it before you play it.&nbsp;</li><li>Get the fingering down for the super quick runs</li><li>Remember the staccato at Bar 160</li><li>On a side note, articulation and phrasing will be your best friend in this piece, it\'s aboiut knowing which notes really need to cut through and be “prioritised”</li></ul></li><li>The Ludlows<ul><li>Worked through Bar 16-17&nbsp;</li><li>Had a close look at the difference between a dotted quaver and a semiquaver vs a pair of quavers</li><li>discussed the groupings of semiquavers in each (ie. 2 + 2 vs 3 + 1)</li><li>Recognised them as skips and steps to simplify reading</li><li>Did both clapping of the rhythm and then playing it</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 11:53:42', '2022-06-02 12:05:30'),
(2368, '2022/06/02', '12:07 pm', '2', '2', 'Jemima Chalk', 'Music', 'Instrumental', 'Pieces', 'Playing through (to see where we’re at / checkpoint playing)', 'Sarah Eddleston', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Tech Work:</p><ul><li>Scales<ul><li>E major was good, Cm fine, G major still reading, added F major scale</li><li>Talked through the Circle of Fifths and Fourths</li></ul></li></ul><p>Pieces</p><ul><li>The Middle<ul><li>Worked through particularly strange rhythmic patterns</li><li>Really break them up and pencil in where the beats fall</li><li>Get used to counting them out loud so that you can hear how they sounds, saying them will help you internalise them as well</li></ul></li><li>Highlights from Frozen<ul><li>Were definitely able to clean up some of those trickier parts which was good</li><li>Reviewing the bars that we had looked at last week (eg. touching bass with Bar 89, the 3, 3, 3, 3, 4 subdividing)</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 12:07:45', '2022-06-02 12:12:45'),
(2369, '2022/06/02', '12:13 pm', '2', '3', 'Jemima Chalk', 'Music', 'Instrumental', 'Pieces', 'Playing through (to see where we’re at / checkpoint playing)', 'Sarah Eddleston', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Tech Work:</p><ul><li>Scales&nbsp;<ul><li>Quick look at the E major scale</li><li>Decided it was best to just gradually work around the Circle of Fifths and Fourths instead</li><li>Gave print out and explained the pattern around (the movement of fourths and fifths intervals)&nbsp;</li><li>Father Christmas Gave Dad An Electric Blanket for the order of sharps and keys&nbsp;</li><li>F BEAD G for the order of flats and keys, also remembered that the second last flat is the key</li><li>For this week, just focus on C major, F major, and G major</li><li>Has sheet that has the scales on them in that order, talked about enharmonics (the same pitch with different names eg. G# Ab)</li></ul></li></ul><p>Pieces</p><ul><li>The Magic Flute<ul><li>Key signature - we\'re working in G major, a good time to be doing the scale!</li><li>Worked through the top line, both parts</li><li>Was some really good sightreading thorughout</li><li>Good to be able to focus on the articulation without thinking too much about the rhythm</li><li>More tongue at the start of notes and slurred phrases, that way you can have the greatest effect with your articulation</li></ul></li><li>Siciliano<ul><li>Once again, some really good sightreading, well done!&nbsp;</li><li>Make sure that you draw out that first long C in Bar 2 and play it for its full length</li><li>The rhythm at Bar 5-7 will need more work, those tied quavers give it a very different feel&nbsp;</li><li>We looked at the semiquaver run and what it was made up of - thirds jumping up and then coming down the Bb major scale from D to D</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 12:15:14', '2022-06-02 12:27:36'),
(2370, '2022/06/02', '02:14 pm', '2', '5', 'Mia Harvey', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 14:14:55', '2022-06-02 14:14:55'),
(2371, '2022/06/02', '02:32 pm', '2', '4', 'Nell  Brooks', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 14:32:15', '2022-07-02 22:53:22'),
(2372, '2022/06/02', '03:01 pm', '2', '3', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Sick</p>', '2022-06-02 15:02:24', '2022-06-02 15:03:33'),
(2373, '2022/06/02', '03:03 pm', '2', '4', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Jimmy began his Autobriography assessment, which includes writing about a significant point in his life. Jimmy\'s vocabulary has improved, but he needs to continue to work on \"showing, not telling\". He also continues to need help with starting sentences and ideas in terms of initial execution, however once he has been helped with a few starting words, he types freely.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-02 15:04:25', '2022-06-02 15:05:11'),
(2374, '2022/06/02', '03:04 pm', '2', '5', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Jimmy continued to work on his Autobiography assignment. He needs to continue to work on capitalisation and proper nouns/pronouns and to understand when to use full stops. Time should be set apart to explain the link between sentence structure and full stop. However, he was able to recognise which words needed to be transformed into more academic language!</p>', NULL, '2022-06-02 15:05:06', '2022-06-02 15:05:36'),
(2376, '2022/06/02', '03:07 pm', '2', '3', 'Adelaide Brown', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phonemic Awareness</p><ul><li>Kilpatrick Level I1</li></ul><p>OPR 39-45</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms 5 sounds of /er/</li></ul><p>WPR 39-45</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms 5 sounds of /er/</li></ul><p>Morphology</p><ul><li>Base word earth</li></ul><p>Spelling Dictation</p><ul><li>Rules: 5 sounds of \"er\"<br>differ</li><li>butler</li><li>birth</li><li>dirt</li><li>figure</li><li>purse</li><li>worm</li><li>worry</li><li>learn</li><li>earth</li></ul><p>Inferences</p><ul><li>Set: 1</li><li>Page: 3</li><li>Item: 11-1</li></ul><p>Oral Fluency</p><ul><li>Passage: 508<br>Errors \"continental\" \"accumulation\" \"accumulated\"</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-02 15:07:49', '2022-06-02 15:09:10'),
(2377, '2022/06/02', '03:07 pm', '2', '4', 'Adelaide Brown', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Adelaide and I worked on her English assessment today, which included planning a Fantasy story. The structure was broken down into planning a beginning, middle and end, and their relevant characteristics. Adelaide came in quite confused as she had forgotten that she could create a text using a narrative structure, so further understanding and application of this structure is needed.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-02 15:12:11', '2022-06-02 15:12:30'),
(2378, '2022/06/02', '03:12 pm', '2', '5', 'Adelaide Brown', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Adelaide continued her English assessment today, which involved map creation. She had a firm grip on how she wanted the map to be and needed minimal guidance. She also worked briefly on her Humanities assignment, and we discussed how persuasive texts are not only achieved through verbal/written means, but can also be presented through visuals such as colour, framing, and composition.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-02 15:14:29', '2022-06-02 15:14:46'),
(2379, '2022/06/02', '03:26 pm', '2', '5', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>It was necessary to work today on long multiplications and short divisions with reminders.&nbsp;</p><p>Sofia told me that at school she doesn\'t do this “kind” of maths. Sofia found the concepts hard but despite this, she was engaged with the lesson and did her best to solve the practice problems.&nbsp;</p><p>I let the parent know about this situation and she said that will follow up with the teacher.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-02 15:26:44', '2022-07-02 20:36:41'),
(2380, '2022/06/02', '03:32 pm', '2', '5', 'James  Coleman', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Spelling Assessment for Ayres Placement', 'Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment - List 4', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA, MA, Morrison, Holborn, Burt, Waddington Spelling</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA, MA, Morrison, Holborn, Burt, Waddington Spelling. CA: 11y4m. Morrison McCall: 9y0m (no gain), Holborn: 8y3m (6m in 6m), Burt: 12y2m - 12y8m (2m in 6m), Wadd Spelling: 9y1m (1m in 1yr). Overall plateau, some gains in reading particularly, nothing spectacular overall. Notes/observations: huge improvement with handwriting, seems to freeze when unsure, sometimes distracted and needs a reminder to return to task at hand. Needs focus on: er/ur/ir usage, ti/sh usage (r.13, 14, 15, rule page), ou, ough, ck usage, hearing and reading consonant blends. When decoding, JC wasn\'t making connections between what he was sounding out, and a familiar word. E.g. could sound perfectly, but didn\'t blend or make connections to a word.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-02 15:32:06', '2022-06-02 19:10:09'),
(2381, '2022/06/02', '03:36 pm', '2', '5', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose first-person informative-narrative paragraph', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus - the use of speech in text</p><p>Activity: Using the soccer photo, decide what happens before during and after the scene.</p><ol><li>Write from the point of view of a radio commentator your description as to what is happening.&nbsp;</li><li>Add in a second commentator</li></ol><p>Focus -Intro to guidelines of speech in text.</p><p>Edit the above commentary script using the guidelines for correct punctuation and presentation.</p><p>Cara was highly involved in this task and took her time to make the piece interesting and descriptive, and very realisitic!!</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-02 15:36:00', '2022-06-07 09:50:55'),
(2382, '2022/06/02', '03:37 pm', '2', '5', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 100', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Mad minute maths – Facts to 100 (include corrections)</p><p>Algebra, Concept Cluster 7, Lesson 2, Independent Practice 1 - If n is x then the value of the expression is…Explain the meaning of each element in the expression n + 20 (n is age of Nadia and 20 is how many years older that Nadia her mother is)</p><p>Algebra, Concept Cluster 7, Lesson 2, Independent Practice 2 If n is x then the value of the expression is…</p><p>Bridging the ten practice – ID need in Facts to 100.&nbsp; Practiced 60 + 8 = 68, 68 – 8 = 60, 40 + 3 = 43, 43 – 3 = 40 etc.&nbsp; Also include from 68 to 60 is ? From 48 to 40 is ?&nbsp; Lucy does not yet automatically recognise the pattern nor trust the count of this pattern and today responded with ‘I don’t know’ several times.&nbsp;</p><p>Home practice is to complete Algebra Concept Cluster 7 practice papers (Key Maths) and practice paper for 6, 7, 8, 9 times tables + bridging ten subtraction equations.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 15:37:11', '2022-06-02 17:19:57'),
(2383, '2022/06/02', '03:42 pm', '2', '5', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 15:42:51', '2022-06-02 15:42:51'),
(2384, '2022/06/02', '04:22 pm', '2', '5', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose first-person informative-narrative paragraph', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus - The Writing Process - speech in writing</p><ol><li>complete the composition of &nbsp;an informative - Narrative passage</li></ol><p>Include speech.</p><p>Finn chose to write a short conversation between himself and a friend about Lego.&nbsp;</p><p>He demonstrated the use of appropriate language for a conversation and used speech marks .</p><p>2. Intro to the guidelines for presenting speech in text.</p><p>We used the above guidelines to edit and complete the piece in class.&nbsp;</p><p>2. &nbsp;Using the soccer photo, write a short commentary of what is happening. There is only one person speaking.&nbsp;</p><p>NW - add in a second commentator.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-02 16:22:51', '2022-06-07 09:45:23'),
