(2388, '2022/06/02', '04:30 pm', '2', '5', 'Chelsea Cooper', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Spelling Assessment for Ayres Placement', 'Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment - List 4', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA, MA, Morrison, Holborn, Waddington Spelling, Burt, game.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Slow on PA, needed some prompting and reminders of what the original word was. Fine with MA, then did Morrison, Holborn, Wadd spelling and Burt. CC very keen to hear about her results and explanation of \'closing the gap\' between CA and R/SA. Mentioned that she was struggling to read the words on Holborn (said she was getting a headache/sore eyes) - optomologist check? Articulately thinking of different ways to make sounds e.g. with \'fight\', Chels wrote \'fit\', but was trying to think of another way to say \'i\'. Asked me, does \"A I (letter names of \'ai\') say /i/?\" CA: 11y4m, Morrison: 8y10m (4m in 6m), Burt: 10y0m - 10y6m (15m in 6m!!!!!), Holborn: 7y6m (9m in 6m), Wadd spelling: 9y3m (-2m in 6m). Observations/focus: igh, dge, ti/sh usage (rule page, r. 13, 14, 15), eigh, tch, wh, qu, er/ur/ir usage, oa, ph, au, augh, ie, ough, contractions (didn\'t). Reading: CC reads first couple of phonograms, then guesses the rest of the word. It seems to become more elaborate as the word becomes more unfamiliar!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-02 16:30:26', '2022-06-02 19:08:57'),
(2389, '2022/06/02', '04:55 pm', '2', '5', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Trigonometry', 'Sine Rule', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>We have agreed that the best strategy for Callisto is to work on the work that the teacher is doing in class and then catch up on missed work with me. We worked on the Sine Rule today and Callisto picked this up quickly, mastering the calculations faultlessly.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 16:55:54', '2022-06-02 18:09:13'),
(2390, '2022/06/02', '05:34 pm', '2', '4', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Factorise algebraic expressions by taking out a common algebraic factor', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', '<p>After the comprehensive revision of the index law from the last lesson. Considering the 2 hours timeframe, we were working on a totally new topic, Factorization.&nbsp;</p><p>Nicholas and I solved a significant number of problems on the whiteboard, we had a refresh on distributive and commutative laws.&nbsp;</p><p>In the first hour, Nicholas was a bit confused about how to follow the process to factorise by using common factors and groups. &nbsp;However, during the second hour, Nicholas\' answers were more accurate and not very far from the ideal algebraic expression.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-02 17:34:07', '2022-07-02 17:17:11'),
(2391, '2022/06/03', '08:33 am', '2', '4', 'Gus  Pettit', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Investigate and use the properties of odd and even numbers', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>As per Gus\' school teacher\'s recommendation, we were working on prime numbers, divisibility, &nbsp;and units of measurement.</p><p>In the last 15 minutes of the lesson, we were working on multiplication and division by 10, 100 and 1000 using decimals.&nbsp;</p><p>Sometimes, I had to closely help Gus with the operations as he was moving the decimal point in the wrong direction. However, in the last practice round, he got all the correct answers.&nbsp;</p><p>Homework = convert between mm, cm, m, and km</p>', NULL, '<p>To cover lesson No 3, today we did 1.5 hours. This lesson happened on 27.05.2022</p>', '2022-06-03 08:33:57', '2022-07-02 14:29:25'),
(2392, '2022/06/03', '03:00 pm', '2', '4', 'Harlow Booy', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Explore the connection between addition and subtraction', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>While Harlow was doing MMM, I could notice that she was struggling more than usual. Hence, I decided to run a short quiz. I didn\'t mention to Harlow that it was a quiz, I just asked her to solve some long additions and subtractions on the board. Also, to create some pictures/models to solve the word problems. However, Harlow made some mistakes related to foundation skills. Because of that, I decided to go over again what we did last week. This time we went out to the driveway and did a shopping list activity to work on these topics.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-03 15:00:59', '2022-07-02 12:07:28'),
(2393, '2022/06/03', '03:28 pm', '2', '5', 'Molly  Jackson', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) second phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level K', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'To Be Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-03 15:28:27', '2022-06-10 14:40:41'),
(2394, '2022/06/03', '03:29 pm', '2', '1', 'Connor Thompson ', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-03 15:29:51', '2022-06-03 15:29:51'),
(2395, '2022/06/03', '04:27 pm', '2', '5', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving division by a one digit number including those that result in a remainder', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Aiming to master long division skills, today Nate and I were working on that one more time.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>We started with a review of skip counting.</li><li>Short division using, how many times X can fit in Y</li><li>Short divisions with reminders.</li><li>Long divisions using the bus method and without a reminder, for instance, &nbsp;432 / 3&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Nate was able to follow the process with guidance. However, he wasn\'t able to do it totally on his own and when the division requires beyond the 6 times tables, Nate has some difficulties. There\'s necessary to keep working on this and revisit this topic later in the year.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 5 was delivered on 02.05.2022</p>', '2022-06-03 16:27:41', '2022-07-03 11:40:19'),
(2396, '2022/06/03', '04:27 pm', '2', '5', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-03 16:27:46', '2022-06-03 16:58:16'),
(2399, '2022/06/03', '04:53 pm', '2', '4', 'Josh Zeeman', 'Academic Coaching', 'Independent Study', 'School Assigned Worksheet or Assignment', 'See Notes', 'Will Hughes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Internet was down so we could not refer to the video, however we did a crash course history lesson on religion as well as exploring the science behind disproving some religion. Started on Christianity, as well as discovered the links between hinduism and buddhism as well as christianitys link with Judaism.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-03 16:54:26', '2022-06-10 17:03:12'),
(2400, '2022/06/04', '10:12 am', '2', '5', 'Nell  Brooks', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we only had one topic, long divisions.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>I explained with many details to Nell how to do long divisions.&nbsp;</li><li>All problems were made up and without reminder.</li><li>At the same time, we had a review on our skip counting skills.&nbsp;</li><li>In the end, Nell was able to do long divisions by a one-digit number.</li><li>I have noticed that the time with Nell is starting to go so fast, even Rachel said that it\'s the quickest hour of her Thursday.&nbsp;</li><li>Nell started to talk about what he does in the school council and how much she loves dancing.&nbsp;</li></ul>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 5 was delivered on 02.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-04 10:12:53', '2022-07-03 07:41:21'),
(2401, '2022/06/04', '10:20 am', '2', '5', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics – Foundation', 'Shape and measurement', 'PLEASE SEE THE NOTES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<ul><li>solve practical problems involving the trigonometry of right-angled triangles, including angles of elevation and depression and using bearings in navigation.</li></ul><p>Continuing our work on the current program Finlay is doing at Hobart College, we moved to work on the topic listed above. The student did good work, however, Finlay needs explicit and direct instruction to solve these kinds of problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 5 was delivered on 02.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-04 10:29:57', '2022-07-02 19:07:09'),
(2402, '2022/06/04', '10:29 am', '2', '4', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics – Foundation', 'Shape and measurement', 'PLEASE SEE THE NOTES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<ul><li>review the use of the trigonometric ratios to find the length of an unknown side or the size of an unknown angle in a right-angled triangle</li><li>determine the area of a triangle either given the height and the base length or two sides and an included angle</li></ul><p>Due to work done last year on trigonometry, Finlay did amazing work with those topics. Despite we haven\'t worked yet on SIN or COS rules, he didn\'t have any big difficulties working out the practice problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lessons No 3 and 4 were delivered on Saturday. This was because I was on sick leave.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-04 10:32:16', '2022-07-02 18:50:12'),
