(2406, '2022/06/06', '12:52 pm', '2', '1', 'Ajay Sekar', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Standardised Spelling Assessment', 'South Australia Spelling - Part A', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Assessments – 40 min</strong></p><p>PAST&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Good skills with concept of spoken word, rhyme recognition and production, syllable blending, syllable deletion</li><li>Needs further instruction with syllable segmentation, isolation initial and final sounds.</li></ul><p>OPR</p><ul><li>Got first sounds for almost all, notes on page.</li></ul><p>WPR/ Alphabet Assessment</p><p>MM&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Not completed.</li></ul><p>South Australia</p><ul><li>Just above chronological</li></ul><p>Burt Word</p><p>Wad Reading + colour in </p><p>Write sentence in book.</p><ul><li>Not completed</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><p>&nbsp;</p><p>GAME (one of the following): DBG, CVC spelling, Sight Word Bingo, OzPhonics, Bunny, Jenga, Hide &amp; Seek</p><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Spiel – 40 min</strong></p><ul><li>How do we communicate?</li><li>Symbols. Symbols give instruction. Hide and seek with symbols. Letters give instruction.&nbsp;</li><li>OPR – 1-26 first sounds</li><li>Some letters are special</li><li>Clockface letters – race car game, make letters with counters, 2x2 boxes</li><li>Segment, count, sound and write words.</li><li>Use words in sentences.</li><li>Write sentence &amp; illustrate.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Letter writing – homework activity</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Reading – Nessy on Ajay’s iPad</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-06 12:53:24', '2022-06-06 12:54:34'),
