(2408, '2022/06/06', '02:28 pm', '2', '6', 'Matthew Heard', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving multiplication and division', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<ul><li>Apply the four operations to simple algebraic fractions with numerical denominators.</li><li>Expand binomial products and factorise monic quadratic expressions using a variety of strategies.</li><li>Sketch linear graphs using the coordinates of two points and solve linear equations.</li><li>Solve problems involving linear equations, including those derived from formulas.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Overall, Matt continues progressing and his ability to perform algebraic operations is getting better.&nbsp;</p><p>However, we haven\'t had enough time to work on geometrical reasoning and this gave us a setback in his schoolwork.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-06 14:28:03', '2022-06-11 17:37:47'),
(2409, '2022/06/06', '03:23 pm', '2', '6', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpattrick F. They both are ready for more challengable level</p><p>OPR: five er, u, i, s, c. Thomas is still a bit shaky at u, so does Mia.&nbsp;<br>WPR: &nbsp;five er, u, i, s, c. &nbsp; Thomas is not familiar with ir, ur, wor, and ear, and Mia is not familiar with ur, wor, and ear.&nbsp;</p><p>handwriting focus: clockface g<br>rule review RUle 4- analyze the word music and cut out syllables. Thomas has mastered rule 4 and Mia still needs a bit help with rule 4.&nbsp;<br>Morphology activity 4. They both are excellent at this when it is a competition.&nbsp;<br>SD:five er words marking. This was very helpful for them to rememebr the formation for five different er.&nbsp;</p><p>compose written sentences using SD words. Their sentences were great, Mia could spell the word worked yet Thomas\'s spelling was workt.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>This pair has been working out very well and they two can get very competitive during tasks and they concentrate very well. Sometimes Thomas finishes his task way faster than Mia, he will need more tasks.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>