(2412, '2022/06/06', '03:34 pm', '2', '6', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Explore and describe number patterns resulting from performing multiplication', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<ul><li>Continue and create sequences involving whole numbers, fractions and decimals. Describe the rule used to create the sequence.</li><li>Explore the use of brackets and order of operations to write number sentences.</li><li>Introduce the concept of variables as a way of representing numbers using letters.&nbsp;</li></ul>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-06 15:34:27', '2022-06-11 19:02:19'),
(2413, '2022/06/06', '03:48 pm', '2', '5', 'Elsa Clennet', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'To Be Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 51-70</td></tr><tr><td>Errors/pauses: ey gn&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 2 4 6 11 14 24 28 29</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: celery-create</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence writing with Ayres words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Writing Process/text types: Narrative structure.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Good discussion with Elsa re: theme, emotional and eventful arcs. We also applied these concepts to various films/stores (e.g. identifying the A-plot of LOTR as being about Frodo getting the ring to Mordor, and the B-plot (or theme) being the power of friendship). Began a conversation applying these concepts to Elsa\'s story and using them to craft the emotions in the story. This is high concept stuff, but I think it\'s good to engage with text types like this for her -- she definitely doesn\'t need help with sentence structure or anything like that.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-06 15:49:11', '2022-06-23 17:40:36'),
(2414, '2022/06/06', '03:49 pm', '2', '6', 'Elsa Clennet', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: H1</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 50-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: See workbook</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 2 17 11</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: certainly-before</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence writing with Ayres words.</td></tr><tr><td>Narrative structure. Discuss beginning, climax, denouement -- draw map. Map out Lamb to the Slaughter in 4 key plot points and draw map. Discuss. Discuss why we root for the protagonist and in what situation we might not want her to get away with the murder (e.g., what if we were watching an episode of Miss Fisher?)&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-06 15:50:06', '2022-09-12 16:28:59'),
