(2420, '2022/06/06', '04:32 pm', '2', '6', 'Arlo Clark', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We focused on Spiel folder part 4, 5, and 6. Arlo understands individual sounds in words, yet understanding symbols as a represent of sounds can be chanllege. He can precisely count letters, sounds, and phonograms in words, yet he does not understand phonograms. We will have to review this bit before we introduce phonograms next week.</p><p>Arlo is a hard working kid and he is a perfectionist, so sometimes it can take a longer time for him to learn things yets he is usually right on his answers.&nbsp;</p><p>He likes to think out loud for knowledge that he is shaky at.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-06 16:32:48', '2022-06-07 14:05:30'),
(2421, '2022/06/06', '04:32 pm', '2', '1', 'Amelia Sekar', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Spelling Assessment for Ayres Placement', 'Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment - List 1', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>LESSON ONE 6/6/22</p><p>Assessments</p><ul><li>PAST</li><li>OPR 1-30</li><li>WPR 1-30</li><li>Morrison McCall</li><li>Holborn</li><li>SA Spelling</li><li>Burt word</li><li>Wadd reading (colour in)</li></ul><p>Game together (non-educational)</p><p>Teach spiel (together)</p><p>1-26 OPR (first sounds)</p><p>OPR consonants first sounds (intro second sounds of c and g)</p><p>Assessments (PAST, OPR, WPR, Morrison, SA, Holborn, Burt, Wadd reading). Amelia did well but was very restless and keen to move onto writing activities, although did settle and focus when I asked her to. Had a break at 11am for the kids to have a snack, then came back at around 11:10am to play a game. Neve went through spiel about symbols and sounds (communication), then Ajay and Amelia went to go find symbols around the office. Came back together and chatted about the word ‘phonogram’, OPR with 1-26, then focused on cons with &gt;1 sound i.e. s c g qu. Finished with Amelia checking the mailbox and reading her letter.</p>', '<p>Week 6 Lesson 1 (Mon)</p>', '2022-06-06 16:33:08', '2022-06-10 11:46:14'),
(2422, '2022/06/06', '04:33 pm', '2', '6', 'Zac Pharaoh ', 'Mathematics', 'OTHER', 'OTHER', 'Please read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Unfortunately, Zac had some difficulties accurately completing his homework. Also, when I asked him some questions to check his understanding, I could notice a level of hesitation that required us to work one more time on what we did last week.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Investigate and calculate percentage discounts of 10%, 25% and 50% on sale items, with and without digital technologies.</li><li>Create simple financial plans.</li><li>Find percentages of quantities and express one quantity as a percentage of another, with and without digital technologies.</li><li>Review, multiplications and divisions with decimals by 10, 100 and 1000 base numbers.</li></ul>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-06 16:33:35', '2022-06-11 19:31:57'),
