(2430, '2022/06/06', '05:33 pm', '2', '4', 'Jett  Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Solve problems involving simple interest', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<ol><li>Solve problems involving simple interest.</li><li>Connect the compound interest formula to repeated applications of simple interest using appropriate digital technologies.</li></ol><p>Today we started to solve problems in the way above the standard level. And did a review of Logs</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-06 17:33:53', '2022-06-11 20:04:21'),
(2432, '2022/06/07', '09:04 am', '2', '6', 'Henry  Badock', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Represent and solve simple addition and subtraction problems using a range of strategies', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W6</p><p>Focus: Mental computation</p><p>Timed activities: to/from 20</p><p>Written and verbal</p><p>Focus: Addition retaining place value. Henry tends to add from right to left. Complete the addition to 100 worksheet&nbsp;</p><p>Use number line to count up with addition to check answers</p><p>Focus: Addition with regrouping</p><p>Although Henry likes to work from right to left when adding, today he was cooperative and worked through the process from left to right. He occasionally went R-L and made errors. He was able to recognise this and articulate that he had forgotten to carry over the 10 or 100. &nbsp;</p><p>Dice Game/Pirate Pete</p><p>Focus: Addition of more than 2 numbers no regrouping. Highest number stabs. Also required some estimation as to which problem to choose to ensure the lowest number.&nbsp;</p><p>Repeat with subtraction.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Focus: Multiplication introduction to the 20x20 chart.&nbsp;</p><p>Henry has a block around multiplication. We used the chart to play battle ships by finding coordinates. NW use it as an aside to the multiplication in workbook</p>', NULL, '2022-06-07 09:04:59', '2022-06-07 09:07:42'),
(2433, '2022/06/07', '02:34 pm', '2', '6', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>OPR u, s, i, c. sh, ee, th, ow, ou. Stella knows one sound of u. She is confused with sounds between s and c. Surprisingly, she knows all four sounds of ou with a bit shaky sometimes. &nbsp;</li><li>WPR u, s, i, c, sh, ee, th. ow, ou. She needs help with the formation of ee, sh, ow, ou.</li><li>handwriting focus: clockface s</li><li>rule review RUle 4- analyze the word music and cut out syllables. She has grasped rule 4 now.&nbsp;</li><li>SD: ou/ow acrivity. color code all ou and ow.<br>&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-06-07 14:34:41', '2022-06-08 08:57:12'),
(2434, '2022/06/07', '03:34 pm', '2', '6', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Paragraphs - Two or more sentences about a topic presented in a logical order of ideas with appropriate indentations and margins', 'Think aloud when identifying the topic in two or more given sentences and whether they are related', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>Kilpatrick H</li><li>work class sorting activity. Brock has a steady understanding in word class yet he needs to think out loud about what verb or adjectives are.&nbsp;</li><li>OPR s, er, e, ch, ur, ow, o. Brock is quite solid on his first 50 phonograms now, might due for an assessment.&nbsp;</li><li>Sentence structure recap. Find 3 compound and 3 complex sentences in the given sentences. And articulate parts of speech in each sentence.&nbsp;</li><li>related sentences--paragragh flowchart-planning a related paragraph- My favoriooate pet. We finished planning and working on first draft. Sent to home.&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-06-07 15:34:06', '2022-06-07 16:32:26'),
