(2438, '2022/06/07', '04:28 pm', '2', '6', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>kilpatrick F1</li><li>challenge word: word class sorting activity. Callum does not have a solid understanding for nouns, verbs and adjectives.&nbsp;</li><li>OPR/WPR: ar, y, e, s, o, , c, ai, ay. He is struggling with ar, o.</li><li>new phonogram: ough with an activity. Homework sent for coloring code all six sounds of ough.&nbsp;</li><li>rule review 6 city, 29little, sfe 5, 18 play. Callum is still shaky at this as we did not have enough time to practice each week. He is a slow learner yet very hard working.&nbsp;</li><li>Sentence structures-simple sentence. We used sentence blocks to build simple sentence and articulated the elements.&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-06-07 16:28:31', '2022-06-08 08:52:37'),
(2439, '2022/06/07', '05:23 pm', '2', '4', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving multiplication and division', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<ul><li>Solve linear simultaneous equations, using algebraic and graphical techniques, including using digital technology.</li></ul><p>Isaac has significantly improved with linear equations. Although, simultaneous equations sometimes might be a little difficult for him, particularly, when solving the problem needs to rearrange the equations. For example 2X - 3Y = -⅔ and X = -5(Y - 3X) + 4</p>', NULL, '<p>Isaac\'s 4th lesson was delivered on 24.05.2022</p>', '2022-06-07 17:23:57', '2022-06-13 10:07:23'),
(2440, '2022/06/07', '05:31 pm', '2', '2', 'Lucy Crosswell', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>The Spiel.</td></tr><tr><td>When we speak we use sounds to talk to each other [show sound card]</td></tr><tr><td>Segment and blend:&nbsp;cat dog sheep</td></tr><tr><td>Vowels and consonant sounds. Explain. Model. Lucy identify vowel/consonant sounds.</td></tr><tr><td>Explain we use letters to show sounds when we want to communicate without speaking. Letters go in words go in sentences.</td></tr><tr><td>Begin Vowels and Consonants reference page in workbook -- cat and parrot drawings.</td></tr><tr><td>OPR 1-8 + i e u, introduce 2nd sounds.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Promising lesson with Lucy today, she was pretty chatty but picked concepts up well. Got a little muddled with listening for sounds in words. Started struggling at F1 for Kilpatrick. For next week: important to get a look at her letter formation and address pencil grip. Spoke to Mel and she said Lucy used to use a pencil grip to help. Also said Lucy\'s just been put in a handwriting class that she\'s a bit miffed about, because she feels her writing is very neat (which it is -- must be a formation issue?)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-07 17:31:47', '2022-07-05 17:15:12'),
(2441, '2022/06/07', '05:37 pm', '2', '6', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Adjectives - describe nouns', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W6</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR&nbsp;</p><p>Ough sh ti si ci igh eigh I o u a y e ea x ei ie ey</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD Sect H</p><p>Ball ask just way weigh reed reading</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Pos Worksheet choosing adjectives so the sentence makes sense.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing – The Land Of OZ Chapter 2. Focus on Sentence beginning with a capital letter, names beginning with a capital, and punctuation to end.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading – Fitzroy 41. Upto page 7&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-07 17:38:04', '2022-06-07 17:40:04'),
(2442, '2022/06/07', '06:14 pm', '2', '6', 'Shay Douglas', 'Academic Coaching', 'Independent Study', 'School Assigned Worksheet or Assignment', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>On Zoom as Shay unwell.</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Shay\'s geography assignment.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Shay had a group project on how to make the Bay of Fires more of a successful tourist attraction. We went through the assignment and brainstormed some ideas, and also talked about the merits of each idea and how we might justify them (particularly for an idea the group had already come up with, which was not a very \'serious\' idea at all).</td></tr><tr><td>Boat tour, hotel/accomodation (like Frecinet) - bungalows, camping, natur walks (start at Eddie stone, walk down to the second penisula, walk down to the gardens, walk down to Binalong bay, catch the train back up).&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>https://trackslesstravelled.com/bay-of-fires-tasmania/</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-07 18:14:33', '2022-06-21 16:49:13'),
(2443, '2022/06/08', '08:24 am', '2', '6', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Related sentences - Two or more sentences about one topic', 'Compose two or three related sentences that include previously introduced language skills (see notes)', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>Kilpatrick i</li><li>OPR: 50-60. &nbsp;Luke needed help for multi sounds of ey and gu.&nbsp;</li><li>multi sound phonogram ey-ball throwing</li><li>WPR: 50-60. He is not familiar with the formation of oe, ew, ui, gu</li><li>Sentence Types: complex sentence- independent sentence abd dependent sentence matching</li><li>Paragraph writing: an interesting place to visit-using paragragh flowchart. Luke is quite resistant to this topic today. I had to go through all the supporting sentences with him and come up with ideas. I will need to find some fun topics for him to write. &nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-06-08 08:25:08', '2022-06-08 08:46:24'),
(2444, '2022/06/08', '11:12 am', '2', '2', 'Ajay Sekar', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Spiel&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>OPR 1-26</li><li>Some letters are special</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Clockface letters – race car game, make letters with counters, 2x2 boxes</li><li>Ajay’s formation okay except for d/g</li><li>WPR 1-8</li><li>Ajay needed reminding to follow clockface formation for d/g</li><li>Segment, count, sound and write words.</li><li>Ajay needed reminding to follow clockface formation for d/g</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>GAME</strong> (one of the following): DBG, CVC spelling, Sight Word Bingo, OzPhonics, Bunny, Jenga, Hide &amp; Seek</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Use words in sentences.</li><li>Once a dog was stuck in a fog.</li><li>Ajay knew about full stops and finger spaces.</li><li>Illustrate sentence</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Reading</strong></p><ul><li>SCORE page 1 – no difficulty</li></ul><p>Ajay’s epic readers on iPad + comprehension activities</p>', NULL, '2022-06-08 11:12:45', '2022-06-08 12:03:51'),
