(2449, '2022/06/08', '03:32 pm', '2', '6', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>OPR. u, s, i, c, five er. Phoebe is confused with sounds for c and s. She cannot say all 3 sounds for u. She has not graspped five er.&nbsp;</li><li>a multi sound game-hide and seek. She was using this game to kill time. we might have to come up with something different for next time.</li><li>WPR:u, s, i, c, five er. &nbsp;She could only write er.&nbsp;</li><li>Handwriting focus: clcockface letetr g</li><li>rule review RUle 4- analyze the word music and cut out syllables. Phoebe has mastered this as she did her homework from last week.</li><li>SD:five er words marking</li><li>Written sentence using er words. (I pat my dogs fur.</li><li>Phoebe did not want to do any tasks today. She wanted to clean up the table at the end of the lesson instead of playing a game. It feels like that she is anxious the whole time. She had a hard time to focus on five er &nbsp;too.&nbsp;<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-06-08 15:32:11', '2022-06-08 21:06:13'),
(2450, '2022/06/08', '03:33 pm', '2', '5', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'BODMAS - Brackets of division, multiplication, addition, subtraction', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Using the Singapore education textbook No 4 and 5, made-up problems and Waddington mathematics modules Connor and I were working on:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Calculate perimeter and area of rectangles using familiar metric units.</li><li>Multiply and divide decimals by powers of 10.</li><li>Introduction to proportions, rates and ratios using BODMAS and decimals.&nbsp;</li></ul>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 5 was delivered on 01.05.2022</p>', '2022-06-08 15:33:18', '2022-06-13 12:02:30'),
(2451, '2022/06/08', '03:34 pm', '2', '5', 'Toby Webb', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-08 15:34:01', '2022-06-08 15:34:01'),
(2453, '2022/06/08', '04:30 pm', '2', '6', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Xave had no work to complete this week due to a broken computer.</p><p>We used the opportunity to focus on syllabification and morphology to assist xav with spelling.&nbsp;</p><p>Using words from his recent English writing piece and common words such as&nbsp;</p><p>unavailable, misadventure, disrespectful, etc X. identified base words, prefixes and suffixes, syllabifying where necessary, and applying his knowledge of phgs and rules.&nbsp;</p><p>Its laborious for X. but he is willing to give it a go and when he takes his time and is guided through the process he can usually produce a correct spelling.&nbsp;</p><p>X. tends to rush and not sound the words aloud when writing which often leads to illegibly written pieces. X. struggles to distinguish between e and i sounds still and this is very apparent in his writing as i is rarely used.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-08 16:30:06', '2022-06-17 10:05:45'),
(2454, '2022/06/08', '04:30 pm', '2', '4', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Ratios', 'Using Ratios to Find Amounts', 'Textbooks, practice papers, school work', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using currency conversions Jacob and I were working today with decimals.&nbsp;</p><p>Jacob is improving in confidence, he knows very well how to do multiplication and decimals by 10, 100 and 1000.&nbsp;</p><p>Also, we did a revision on skip counting and adding and subtracting with 5/6 digit numbers. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-08 16:30:24', '2022-07-01 22:02:56'),
(2455, '2022/06/08', '04:33 pm', '2', '6', 'Kaiden Reynolds', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-08 16:33:23', '2022-06-08 16:33:23'),
(2456, '2022/06/08', '05:27 pm', '2', '5', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Shape', '2D', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'To Be Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using the Singapore Education No 4 Luca and I were working on the area and perimeter of squares, rectangles and triangles.&nbsp;</p><p>Also solved worded problems where the perimeter was given and one side was missing.&nbsp;</p><p>In the majority of the problems we used decimals and sometimes fractions</p>', NULL, '<p>Lessons 5, and 6 last 1.5 to cover lesson No 4.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-08 17:27:59', '2022-06-13 15:23:52'),
(2457, '2022/06/08', '05:36 pm', '2', '1', 'Callan Bartlett', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Kieran Oates', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Started with Waddington test modules but after it became too difficult we switched to learning about decimals and fractions. Also rounding up numbers.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-08 17:36:22', '2022-06-08 18:42:23'),
(2458, '2022/06/09', '07:30 am', '2', '6', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving division by a one digit number including those that result in a remainder', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>In this lesson, we worked on:</p><ul><li>Review times tables.</li><li>Short divisions. 65 / 5</li><li>Introduction to units of measurement.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Nate was fully engaged with the lesson; most of the time his answers were correct.&nbsp;</p><p>We were looking into the main units of measurement for distance, time, weight, volume and temperature.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 07:30:29', '2022-07-03 11:50:49'),
(2459, '2022/06/09', '07:59 am', '2', '3', 'Chester  Vincent', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 07:59:24', '2022-06-09 07:59:24'),
(2460, '2022/06/09', '08:51 am', '2', '4', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Measurement', 'Measure and compare the lengths and capacities of pairs of objects using uniform informal units', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today a different strategy was implemented to avoid James\' tantrums.&nbsp;</p><p>The concept of the number will be revisited and the mathematical concept to support this will be the measurement.&nbsp;</p><p>We worked on perimeter of composite and irregular shapes, I help James to write down the lengths of what we were measuring.&nbsp;</p><p>We did some column addition and a few subtractions.&nbsp;</p><p>James\' behaviour wasn\'t the best. Although, he didn\'t hit himself and was less resistant than some weeks ago.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Lesson No 4 was delivered on 02.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-09 08:51:55', '2022-07-03 08:59:38'),
(2461, '2022/06/09', '02:25 pm', '2', '6', 'Mia Harvey', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 14:25:02', '2022-06-09 14:25:02'),
(2462, '2022/06/09', '02:35 pm', '2', '6', 'Nell  Brooks', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>In today\'s lesson we worked on:</p><ul><li>Number and place value, comparing numbers up to 6 digits.&nbsp;</li><li>Short multiplications and divisions</li><li>Short divisions with reminders</li><li>Check on word problems with + and -</li></ul><p>Nell continues improving in selecting the right method to solve a problem. It\'s necessary to encourage her to do more work on paper rather than mental computation. This is because she confuses herself with the operations. However, soon she will be ready to do most of the operations without paper.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 14:35:25', '2022-07-03 07:48:15'),
(2463, '2022/06/09', '03:28 pm', '2', '4', 'James  Coleman', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ellie Connor', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 15:28:41', '2022-06-09 15:28:41'),
(2464, '2022/06/09', '03:32 pm', '2', '6', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 15:32:34', '2022-06-09 15:32:34'),
(2465, '2022/06/09', '03:40 pm', '2', '6', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Writing - Capitalisation & Punctuation', 'Quotation/Speech marks are used for direct quotations', 'See notes...', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus: Use of speech in written text - Informative Narrative writing</p><p>Activity - read some facts about slinkies and use this to compose an IN text, including dialogue between two characters.</p><p>Format chosen was comic strip. Cara produced a short but effective dialogue between two people, which informed the reader of some basic facts. The format &nbsp;(comic strip) increased the reader\'s interest however there was little use of engaging language, humour or story line.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-09 15:40:35', '2022-06-17 09:44:28'),
(2466, '2022/06/09', '03:44 pm', '2', '4', 'Stella Bowerman', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 15:44:04', '2022-06-09 15:44:04'),
(2467, '2022/06/09', '04:26 pm', '2', '6', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose third-person informative-narrative paragraph', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus - The Writing Process - speech in writing</p><ol><li>complete the composition of &nbsp;an informative - Narrative passage</li></ol><p>Include speech.</p><p>2. Reviewthe guidelines for presenting speech in text.</p><p>3. &nbsp; Continue with the &nbsp; commentary &nbsp;writing task. Add another person/s to the dialogue. Finn chose to add another commentator. He dictated a funny and engaging script for the dialogue between the two commentators. We then used the comic strip format to formailise this. Finn is super motivated by this and is looking forward to completing both the drawings (at home) and the dialogue. Supplied him with several options for formatting. It will continue to be homework with revision in class each week. Goalto complete by Week 10 for publication.&nbsp;</p><p>Focus- spell check of words used in the written texts.</p><p>Finn used his knowledge of phonograms, syllabification and rules to go through the options for the long vowel sounds in words. He systematically tries each, but often lands on the correct spelling quickly as his brain “tells” him the correct one.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-09 16:26:26', '2022-06-17 09:57:29'),
(2468, '2022/06/09', '04:27 pm', '2', '6', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics – Foundation', 'Shape and measurement', 'PLEASE SEE THE NOTES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>The lesson was focused on COS rule and their use in real-life situations.&nbsp;</p><p>Sometimes Finlay gets confused between the SIN and COS rules. To help Finlay with that, we were doing several examples on the whiteboard.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Finlay had a stomach ache, we continued our lesson through zoom on Wednesday evening 15.06.2022.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-09 16:27:37', '2022-07-02 19:15:32'),
(2469, '2022/06/09', '04:50 pm', '2', '6', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Trigonometry', 'Trig Equations', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Callisto has a Trigonometry test tomorrow and so we covered as much of the work for which she has been absent from school as we could in preparation for this test. We were particularly looking at World Geometry. We covered - calculating distances North and South (great circles) in kilometres and nautical miles and then distances East and West (small circles) in kilometres and nautical miles. We note that the North-South journeys are easier to calculate!</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 16:50:20', '2022-06-09 18:09:39'),
(2470, '2022/06/09', '05:23 pm', '2', '6', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Practice on board/in book', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Lucy shared that she achieved a ‘High’ standard score on a recent maths test at school. &nbsp;This is a really wonderful outcome for Lucy. &nbsp;I\'m so proud of her!</p><p>Today, Lucy demonstrated some very reasoned approaches to problem solving as she worked out the value of unknown quantities. &nbsp;Lucy beginning to make articulate connections as she recognises that her 1:1 correspondence strategy could have easily been replaced by a simple short division equation. &nbsp;She also stated, “What if I did [the reverse operation]?” It was wonderful to see Lucy independently recognising the value of drawing on recently practiced strategies for problem solving.</p><p>Further practice bridging tens will be helpful - the more Lucy is articulating her workings with these problems, the more fluent she is becoming. &nbsp;She is not yet applying the most efficient strategy each time, but she is increasingly recognising how to do so when asked to explain her thinking.</p>', NULL, '<p>This was a Zoom lesson as Naomi had a cold.</p>', '2022-06-09 17:24:30', '2022-06-09 18:03:15'),
(2471, '2022/06/09', '05:31 pm', '2', '5', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Quadratics', 'Expand binomial products and factorise monic quadratic expressions using a variety of strategies', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', '<p>Continuing our work on factorisation. Today we looked at Differences of Perfect Squares.&nbsp;</p><p>In the first 20 minutes of the lesson, it was necessary to check on some problems from Nicholas\' homework as those were not quite good. In some of them, Nicholas forgot the multiplication and division rule (index law) and the sign law.&nbsp;</p><p>Then we moved to DOPS; it was necessary to do a quick revision on square roots.&nbsp;</p><p>Overall, Nicholas did well with DOPS; I\'m happy to see that number of mistakes is reducing time after time.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-09 17:31:34', '2022-07-02 17:24:21'),
(2472, '2022/06/10', '07:49 am', '2', '5', 'Gus  Pettit', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today the lesson was planned to last 1.5 hours. However, Gus didn\'t show up. I call Nat and she didn\'t pick up the phone.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-10 07:49:36', '2022-07-02 14:31:38'),
(2473, '2022/06/10', '11:46 am', '2', '2', 'Amelia Sekar', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><ul><li>Recap spiel (communicate using sound, phonograms are symbols telling us to make a sound – connection between symbol/sign and phono)</li><li>Vowels &amp; consonants differences</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><ul><li>OPR recap s c g qu</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><ul><li>WPR consonants rule page 1<ul><li>Handwriting intro<strong>&nbsp;</strong></li></ul></li></ul><p><strong>BREAK</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><ul><li>Finish Wadd reading</li><li>Amelia – ORF/SCORE? OR read a story together</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><ul><li>Amelia to create a postcard for her teacher<ul><li>Draw picture of Hobart (what was your highlight?)</li><li>Write letter</li></ul></li></ul><p><strong>BREAK</strong> - Nessy</p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Amelia was a little calmer than Monday, and I feel like she worked really well today. She was able to clearly articulate that letters/phonograms are symbols that tell us to make a sound. We recapped about how we communicate through pictures, sounds and symbols, then did a hide and seek activity with the symbol cards. We spoke about vowels and consonants, and Amelia was quick to pick up this concept, articulating it nicely. She already was able to identify what the vowels are, and had a bit of an understanding (mentioned short and long sounds). Intro to handwriting – Amelia did well, and her handwriting is heaps better when she slows down and focuses. After OPR, WPR, we had a quick break and Amelia did some playdough with Ajay. Got back into it after 10mins, and finished the Wadd reading. Amelia very chatty and distracted when doing her Wadd reading independently – needed a bit of prompting to return to the task. Started on a postcard for her teacher in HK with Amelia tracing a kangaroo (the highlight of her Hobart trip). Convo about a postcard having a picture on the front and writing on the back.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<p>Week 6 Lesson 2 (Fri)</p>', '2022-06-10 11:47:33', '2022-06-10 11:54:16'),
(2474, '2022/06/10', '02:29 pm', '2', '6', 'Molly  Jackson', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) second phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level K', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick K1</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-57</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: th ow ou oo ch oi ir ea au ed ui gu&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: ever-before</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Complex sentences. IC-DC and DC-IC structure. Molly really wasn\'t engaging with this the way I would\'ve liked her to -- it was like she had no idea what she was doing, which was fine, but she wouldn\'t take the time to listen to me explain or help her.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Even though she hadn\'t had a hot chocolate, Molly was super silly. She was also having pretend/exaggerated sulks and tantrums when I told her to get back on track. I thought I was fairly kind in telling her to pull her socks up, but I did want her to know that it wasn\'t on. M: \"Are you mad at me?\" N: I\'m not mad, but I\'m not impressed.</td></tr><tr><td>We had a really weird moment where, after I told Molly she could only have one sticker, she got really genuinely upset (I couldn\'t tell at first) and after I asked her about it she burst into a massive bought of tears. I asked if it was something I\'d done or if it was unrelated (she said it was unrelated) and if she would like me to stay and go (she asked me to go). I left her alone for 5 minutes. When I came back she wanted to breeze past it and not talk about it and was very, very insistent. She had opened up my WRTR and done some of her words herself. Completed sentence structure.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-10 14:29:41', '2022-06-10 16:25:06'),
(2475, '2022/06/10', '02:29 pm', '2', '2', 'Finn McKenzie', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>The Spiel -- sounds/words/sentences.Phonogram (phone = sound, gram = symbol) .</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8, 27-38</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: a, c, g, s, sh, ee, th, ow, ou, oo, ch</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: N/A, intro to markings (underline phonogram, syllable break)</td></tr><tr><td>Explain finger scaffolding.</td></tr><tr><td>SD: trust, extra, dress, beside, teach happen, begun, collect</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>POS: Introduce to nouns and verbs. Sort given spelling word into part of speech. Finn knew all about nouns and verbs and needed no instruction.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Sentences have structure. Made up of nouns and verbs, capitals, full stop. Introduce to sentence builder blocks. Again, Finn very okay with this. Introduced to&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Sentence structure: Write sentences using spelling words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: Fitzroy 32</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Finn knows compound and complex sentences from school, so we might touch on them next lesson so we can utilise them during the writing portion.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Reading Fitzroy 32 was okay in terms of decoding/encoding/fluency, but very stilted in terms of expression.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-10 14:34:35', '2022-06-10 16:21:16'),
(2476, '2022/06/10', '03:28 pm', '2', '6', 'Connor Thompson ', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rewording activity. Read ORF #419, highlight key words. Connor needed lots of instruction and modelling to highlight just key words and not whole sentences. Transform into a list. Modelled for Connor by drawing a diagram on the door how we were whittling down the information as much as possible so that when we build back around it, we use our own words. To complete next week by turning into a paragraph and actually doing the re-wording.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-10 15:28:17', '2022-06-10 16:29:49'),
(2477, '2022/06/10', '03:29 pm', '2', '5', 'Harlow Booy', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Recognise and represent multiplication as repeated addition, groups and arrays', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>HANDS UP!</p><p>Today we were working on skip counting, using the even times\' tables. We did this activity in the rolled canvas that is in T1.&nbsp;</p><p>The idea of this activity was to work not only on skip counting but also, to work in arrays. And see how multiplications can be additions and subtractions along with divisions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-10 15:29:30', '2022-07-02 12:13:47'),
(2478, '2022/06/10', '04:01 pm', '2', '3', 'Josh Zeeman', 'Academic Coaching', 'Independent Study', 'School Assigned Worksheet or Assignment', 'See Notes', 'Will Hughes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Internet was down this week so I could not fill out Josh\'s comments. Had to divert from the original plan and rely on my own knowledge for the religion lesson. Josh was very understanding of the situation</p>', NULL, '2022-06-10 16:01:45', '2022-06-10 17:02:20'),
(2479, '2022/06/10', '05:41 pm', '2', '3', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 100', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>To get ready Ava for the test, in the last part of the lesson we were practising problems like:</p><p>If 30 is 10% of a number, what is that number?&nbsp;</p><p>What percentage is 2/7 of 120?&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Due to illness, Shannon and I agreed to do 2x1.5 hours of lessons to catch up. This lesson was delivered on 3.06.2022 and 10.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-10 17:41:51', '2022-07-02 08:23:07'),
(2480, '2022/06/10', '06:07 pm', '2', '6', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-57</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ew ou ea oo ey eigh ch ee ai ay ar&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 4 6 18</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: money-chance</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ayres words in sentences. Discuss meaning of word omit, and omit/admit. Discuss eat/ate (common error for Nate).</td></tr><tr><td>Dialolgue punctuation discussion - draw picture, discuss, use in sentences.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-10 18:08:18', '2022-06-10 18:12:07'),
(2481, '2022/06/11', '05:04 pm', '2', '7', 'Matthew Heard', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving multiplication and division', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p><strong>Algebra Skills</strong><br>• Index Laws: know and apply<br>• Expansion/distribution (brackets)<br>• simplification and<br>• Factorisation<br>• Algebraic Fractions<br>• Substitution - values in formula to find the unknown.</p><p><br><strong>Linear Equations</strong><br>• Graphing Straight Lines<br>• Finding the equation of a line<br>• Finding the gradient of a straight line and the intercepts<br>• Simultaneous equations.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Matt did an excellent job today; I sincerely hope Matt can remember all what we did today on his exam.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Matt has the mid-year exam on Friday 17.06.22 and as Monday 13th of June is a public holiday, we had to do the lesson today, Saturday 11/06/22.</p><p>Initially, the lesson was going to be for 1.5 hours but it lasted for 2 hours.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-11 17:05:27', '2022-06-11 17:47:51'),
(2482, '2022/06/11', '07:33 pm', '2', '6', 'Jett  Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Pythagoras and Trigonometry', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'See notes', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using bearings and<i> above standard </i>problems, Jett and I were working on:&nbsp;</p><p>Today Jett and I were reviewing the following topics:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Investigate Pythagoras’ Theorem and its application to solving simple problems involving right-angled triangles.</li><li>se similarity to investigate the constancy of the sine, cosine and tangent ratios for a given angle in right-angled triangles.</li><li>Establish the sine, cosine and area rules for any triangle and solve related problems.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-11 19:34:55', '2022-06-11 20:13:57'),
(2483, '2022/06/11', '07:34 pm', '2', '5', 'Jett  Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Pythagoras and Trigonometry', 'Trig ratios SOH CAH TOA', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today Jett and I were reviewing the following topics:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Investigate Pythagoras’ Theorem and its application to solving simple problems involving right-angled triangles.</li><li>se similarity to investigate the constancy of the sine, cosine and tangent ratios for a given angle in right-angled triangles.</li><li>Establish the sine, cosine and area rules for any triangle and solve related problems.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>As I could notice that Jett was having some hesitation with some problems, I decided to only solve problems<i> to at the standard level.&nbsp;</i></p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-11 19:35:32', '2022-06-11 20:11:37'),
(2486, '2022/06/13', '07:00 am', '2', '6', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving multiplication and division', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', '<p>Isaac will have the mid-year exam on Friday, 10.06.2022. Hence, we did a review of all topics we have looked at so far during the term.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Factorise algebraic expressions by taking out a common algebraic factor.</li><li>Simplify algebraic products and quotients using index laws.</li><li>Expand binomial products and factorise monic quadratic expressions using a variety of strategies.&nbsp;</li><li>Solve problems involving linear equations, including those derived from formulas.</li><li>Solve linear inequalities and graph their solutions on a number line.</li><li>Solve linear simultaneous equations, using algebraic and graphical techniques, including using digital technology.</li></ul>', NULL, '<p>Isaac\'s 6th lesson was delivered on 07.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-13 07:00:33', '2022-06-13 10:28:24'),
(2487, '2022/06/13', '07:01 am', '2', '5', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving the four operations', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Review on:</p><ul><li>Find the distance between two points located on the Cartesian plane using a range of strategies.</li><li>Solve problems involving linear equations, including those derived from formulas.</li><li>Sketch linear graphs using the coordinates of two points and solve linear equations.</li></ul><p>We looked at the 3 methods to solve simultaneous equations, substitution, elimination and graphs. Also, we review inequalities.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Isaac\'s 5th lesson was delivered on 31.05.2022</p>', '2022-06-13 07:01:37', '2022-06-13 10:13:18'),
(2489, '2022/06/13', '10:29 am', '2', '5', 'Joseph Martín', 'Mathematics', 'OTHER', 'OTHER', 'Please read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Joseph brought a college assignment to be completed, the topics included;&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Using the concepts of average and instantaneous rates of change in a variety of practical contexts.</li><li>Using the gradient as a measure of the rate of change of a linear function.</li><li>Using the gradient of a tangent at a point on the graph of a function to describe and measure the instantaneous rate of change of the function, including consideration of where the rate of change is positive, negative or zero and the relationship of the gradient function to features of the original function.</li><li>Using the gradient of a chord of a graph to describe the average rate of change of&nbsp;<br>y = f(x) with respect to x over a given interval.</li></ul>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 5 was delivered on 07.06.22</p>', '2022-06-13 10:29:51', '2022-06-13 10:37:21'),
(2490, '2022/06/13', '10:30 am', '2', '4', 'Joseph Martín', 'Mathematics', 'OTHER', 'OTHER', 'Please read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Joseph brought a college assignment about exponential functions, the main topics were:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Establishing and using the algebraic properties of exponential functions</li><li>Recognising the qualitative features of the graph of&nbsp;<br>y = bx (a &gt;0) including asymptotes, intercepts and simple translations:&nbsp;<br>y = a × bx + k</li><li>Solving equations involving exponential functions using technology and algebraically in simple cases.</li><li>Using function notation, domain, range, independent and dependent variables<br>examining simple applications of exponential functions such as growth and decay, compound interest, inflation and depreciation.</li></ul>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 4 was delivered on 31.05.22</p>', '2022-06-13 10:30:04', '2022-06-13 10:42:01'),
(2491, '2022/06/13', '10:30 am', '2', '3', 'Joseph Martín', 'Mathematics', 'OTHER', 'OTHER', 'Please read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Joseph had an assignment to complete on quadratics and cubics.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>recognising examples of quadratically related variables</li><li>recognising features of the graphs &nbsp;y=x2y=x2, &nbsp;y=a(x−b)2+cy=a(x-b)2+c, &nbsp;and &nbsp;y=a(x−b)(x−c)y=a(x-b)(x-c)&nbsp; (zeros, y-intercepts and turning points as applicable)</li><li>solving quadratic equations using the quadratic formula and by completing the square.</li><li>identifying the coefficients and the degree of a polynomial</li><li>expanding cubic polynomials from factors</li><li>factorising cubic polynomials in cases where a linear factor is easily obtained</li><li>recognising features of the graphs of &nbsp;y=x3y=x3, &nbsp;y=a(x−h)3+ky=a(x-h)3+k &nbsp;and &nbsp;y=k(x−a)(x−b)(x−c)y=k(x-a)(x-b)(x-c)&nbsp; including shape, intercepts and behaviour as &nbsp;x→∞x→∞&nbsp; and &nbsp;x→−∞x→-∞&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 3 was delivered 24.05.2022</p>', '2022-06-13 10:30:22', '2022-06-13 11:05:18'),
(2492, '2022/06/13', '11:10 am', '2', '6', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions, Decimals & Percentages', 'Comparing & ordering fractions, decimals & percentages', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Using the Singapore education textbook No 4 and 5, made-up problems and ET maths resources, Connor and I were working on:&nbsp;</p><p>Converting units of measurement, using length (meters, cm, mm, km, feet, inches, yards, currencies and grams).&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 6 was delivered on 08.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-13 11:10:59', '2022-06-13 12:46:38'),
(2493, '2022/06/13', '01:10 pm', '2', '6', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions, Decimals & Percentages', 'Fraction, decimal & percentage conversions (including simplification & expansion)', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>We started the lesson by doing a revision on long division with and without reminders. Then, we moved to look at the connections between fractions, decimals and percentages and how to convert between each of them.&nbsp;</p><p>Luca did a great job, he understands very well the connection between each, F % and D also he didn\'t take too long to solve each question.&nbsp;</p><p>All the problems I used today were made-up even the ones sent for homework.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lessons 5, and 6 last 1.5 to cover lesson No 4.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-13 13:10:21', '2022-06-13 15:29:19'),
(2494, '2022/06/14', '09:03 am', '2', '7', 'Henry  Badock', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 20', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W7</p><p>Focus: Mental computation</p><p>Timed activities: to/from 20</p><p>Written and verbal</p><p>Focus: Addition retaining place value. Henry tends to add from right to left. Complete the addition to 10000 worksheet&nbsp;</p><p>Use number line to count up with addition to check answers</p><p>Focus: Addition with regrouping to 10000</p><p>Dice Game/Pirate Pete</p><p>Focus: Multiplication 2 x table. Using number line to reinforce the concept of related to addition.&nbsp;</p><p>Lowest &nbsp;number stabs. Also required some estimation as to which problem to choose to ensure the lowest number.&nbsp;</p><p>Focus: Multiplication &nbsp;x 2</p><p>Modelling using swords in groups/sets of two. Explore the language that works for Henry. Lots of seems to work atm. Use number line to check answers, also count on in twos. When the model was covered Henry was able to articulate the process of counting in 2s. He often rushes and doesn’t check his answers make sense.&nbsp;</p><p>Use the 20x20 chart to articulate the x2 table upto 20.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-14 09:03:47', '2022-06-14 09:04:53'),
(2495, '2022/06/14', '02:51 pm', '2', '7', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR s, c. sh, ee, ow, ou. Stella was supringly good today and she has grasped all four sounds for ou and two sounds for ow. She is confused with ee and e sounds.&nbsp;</p><p>Loud Cow sorting activity for ow and ou, which helped her understand when to use ou and when to use ow.&nbsp;</p><p><br>WPR s, i, sh, ee, ow, ou. Stella was great at all phonograms other than ow(She wrote wo, same as her other words or numbers formation, she shows signs of dyslexia).</p><p>handwriting line letter u</p><p><br>pink book page 2 for marking system: She understands we need to underline vowels at the end of a syllable for rule 4. Need to recap unlerlining multi letter phonogram and write numbers on top of a multi sound phonogram that does not say it\'s first sound.</p><p><br>SD: do, and, go, is, she. Stella did a great handwriting today on her notebook. Her writing was more natural this time and the word size was natural too. She wrote si as she was sounding out is.&nbsp;</p><p><br>oral sentence using SD words: She is at the pool!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbs