(2496, '2022/06/14', '03:43 pm', '2', '7', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) second phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level K', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick H1</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-46</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ow ou wor aw</td></tr><tr><td>HF: Dip off w</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 21, 20</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: always-thus</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Writing Process: Discuss and plan for Sophie\'s 3 sentence story; place beginning, middle, end on whiteboard, identifying where Sophie\'s sandwich is during these parts of the story (she has it, its stolen by the crow, she doesn\'t have the sandwich).&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Write three sentence story.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Not completed:</td></tr><tr><td>Oral Fluency: 220</td></tr><tr><td>Comp: Answer MA questions about the passage.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>It was Sophie\'s birthday yesterday so today she brought in cupcakes, which was very sweet of her. She was super duper chatty as per usual today. Spoke to Alex at the end of lesson and they\'ve decided to opt out of the progress report this term.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-14 15:44:02', '2022-06-14 17:27:52'),
(2497, '2022/06/14', '03:55 pm', '2', '7', 'Brock Smith', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-14 15:56:20', '2022-06-14 15:56:20'),
(2498, '2022/06/14', '04:35 pm', '2', '1', 'Owen Fitzgerald', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics', 'Networks and decision mathematics.', 'Paths and cycles', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Owen brought a college assignment to be completed on Networks, it was about:</p><ul><li>investigate and solve practical problems to determine the shortest path between two vertices in a weighted graph</li><li>explain the meaning of the terms; Eulerian path, Eulerian circuit, and the conditions for their existence and use these concepts to investigate and solve practical problems; for example, the Konigsberg Bridge problem, planning a garbage collection route.</li></ul><p>Owen told me he tried to use Youtube to understand the problems but it was slightly hard for him. After I explained those topics to him, Owen felt more confident and was able to solve the practice question correctly.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-14 16:35:28', '2022-07-03 19:37:09');
