(2501, '2022/06/14', '04:43 pm', '2', '7', 'Esther Mclver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 26: Capitalise proper nouns (names and titles)', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W7</p><p>OPR &nbsp;ea or y ch er ough th &nbsp;ow ou j a e I o u ck er x5</p><p>WPR ea th ch er or a e o u I y&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule Review:&nbsp;</p><p>26 June J1</p><p>4/6 gra vy</p><p>29 splat ter</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sect N teacher-thought</p><p>Identify POS.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>My teacher thought I should study another subject, so he chose Tasmanian History.&nbsp;</p><p>In April and November the weather is chilly, so we use heaters to warm us.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Analyse the sentences above?</p><p>&nbsp;Compound</p><p>POS?</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Of 112</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Hw sheet given + 112</p>', NULL, '2022-06-14 16:43:43', '2022-06-14 16:45:50'),
(2502, '2022/06/14', '05:23 pm', '2', '7', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Solve linear simultaneous equations, using algebraic and graphical techniques, including using digital technology', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Isaac told me that at school he\'s looking at simultaneous equations.&nbsp;</p><p>I did a review of the 3 techniques to solve simultaneous equations. Since last term we did a lot of practice on linear equations, he was feeling confident with this topic.&nbsp;</p><p>Overall, Isaac did a great job with substitution. I did help him a lot when the question required re-arranging.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-14 17:23:08', '2022-07-03 19:17:49'),
(2503, '2022/06/14', '05:32 pm', '2', '3', 'Lucy Crosswell', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 1-8, e I, u with 2nd and 3rd sounds for vowels</td></tr><tr><td>Immediate feedback.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PROMPT CARDS ON BOARD</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: A-G</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Lucy was great today - she struggled a little with the language around rule 4, but we spoke about it and explaining it as \"when the vowel is the last letter in a syllable\" worked better than \"when a vowel is at the end of a syllable\". She\'s okay with the word syllable. Her spelling words and markings were also neat and lovely.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>She needs more practice (obviously) with the phonograms, and I think lots of support around the sound/symbol connection. Hopefully as she makes that connection other things will fall into place for her.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-14 17:32:46', '2022-06-14 18:41:06'),
(2504, '2022/06/14', '05:34 pm', '2', '7', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Tardy', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W7</p><p>Andrew was cooperative, listened well and was engaged for the full 45 mins.&nbsp;</p><p>WPR</p><p>Opr</p><p>A e I o u y e a ch th ee ou ow ough or&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD Sect H – get home much call long (rode road good ground)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Activity – Connect 4 Rule 4</p><p>Andrew articulated the rule every time for the first time.&nbsp;</p><p>He modelled covering up the second syllable and said “a says a2 at end of a syllable” etc.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>Focus on Capital letters for Proper Nouns, beginning of sentences, punctuation.&nbsp;</p><p>Story continued.</p><p>NW have more sentences for him to complete with nouns verbs and adjectives.&nbsp;</p><p>Reading – Fitzroy 41 – A. read fluently the first 2 paragraphs. Able to sound out unfamiliar words, and self-correct if he misread and it didn’t make sense.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW</p><p>Syllabify and Proper Nouns.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-14 17:35:30', '2022-06-14 17:44:30'),
