(2506, '2022/06/14', '07:39 pm', '2', '6', 'Joseph Martín', 'Mathematics', 'Maths methods 3', 'Other', 'Read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Getting Joseph ready for the test, today he brought a school assignment to cover the following:</p><p><strong>Language of functions:</strong></p><ul><li>understanding the concept of a function as a mapping between sets, and as a rule or a formula that defines one variable quantity in terms of another</li><li>recognising the distinction between functions and relations, using examples of relations such as the circle or &nbsp;x=y2x=y2&nbsp;</li><li>using function notation, domain, range, independent and dependent variables.</li></ul><p>Some questions were above standard however I could manage to solve them and explain those to Joseph.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-14 19:39:33', '2022-07-03 18:37:44'),
