(2509, '2022/06/15', '12:10 pm', '2', '3', 'Ajay Sekar', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR</p><p>WPR</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Vowels/Consonant&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Vowels/consonants spiel</li><li>Cat/parrot conversation &amp; illustration</li><li>Intro 2nd and 3rd sounds vowels</li><li>Spelling dictation A-G</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Ajay very difficult to keep focused today, he just kept asking about “game time”… He found the multiple sounds confusing, especially in WPR – same problem I have with Max Shaprio, writing something to represent each sound (“a a r”). Spelling dictation I only looked at underling digraphs &amp; marking 2/3 sounds. He was okay with SD and also with using words in sentence. Looked at d letter formation as lesson’s handwriting focus.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-15 12:10:16', '2022-06-15 12:11:02'),
