(2512, '2022/06/15', '03:31 pm', '2', '7', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 24: Turn the y into at the end of a word when adding a vowel ending', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T2W7</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR&nbsp; a e I o u y eigh ea ie ei ey ay oy ed ng ck dge</p><p>Rule review -9/10/11</p><p>Challenge Words</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Grate + er</p><p>Stun + ed</p><p>Reset + ing</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD: Rule page for 9/10/11</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>New Rule Intro: 24</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Read words on board and remind of Rule 5 by identifying the i/I sounds made by y</p><p>Reminder of Rule 6.</p><p>Identify all rule 6 words</p><p>Work sheet</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>Complex sentence using two words from Rule 24 sheet.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading OF&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW – complete worksheet</p><p>Reading.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-15 15:31:14', '2022-06-15 17:36:19'),
(2513, '2022/06/15', '03:33 pm', '2', '3', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-15 15:33:29', '2022-06-15 15:33:29'),
(2514, '2022/06/15', '03:37 pm', '2', '7', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving division by a one digit number including those that result in a remainder', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>In this lesson, Connor and I were working on long divisions and operations with fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>Connor was hesitant at the beginning, he was forgetting, <i>how many X can you fit in Y with a reminder of Z. </i>For that reason, I explained this in more detail and did a good number of examples on the board and in his notebook. After this, Connor was solving the sums with correct answers and was able to do it without my help.&nbsp;</p><p>Then we moved to work on operations with fractions; we did “butterfly wings\" to solve those fractions with different denominators. However, I didn\'t ask Connor to simplify the answers.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-15 15:37:52', '2022-07-03 17:51:11'),
