(2554, '2022/06/20', '03:35 pm', '2', '7', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Describe, continue, and create number patterns resulting from performing addition or subtraction', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we worked towards:</p><p>Create algebraic expressions and evaluate them by substituting a given value for each variable.</p><p>Inputs/outputs with both cases when the formula is given and when the formula needs to be created.</p><p>I could say that Archie mastered these concepts, even though sometimes he needed some extra help, he was able to solve all practice questions correctly.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-20 15:35:24', '2022-07-03 20:19:15'),
(2555, '2022/06/20', '03:38 pm', '2', '8', 'Elsa Clennet', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 27-50</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 2 4 6 29 11</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: pleasant- ceiling</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ayres words in sentence. Revise sentence and check for spelling, grammar and punctuation.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Continue conversation on narrative structure + map out a story of Elsa\'s choosing -- her Feradoor story, perhaps? A and B storylines (events vs emotions and the link between them).</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Elsa was tired today and quite \'loud\' about it with her body language, which we talked about. She got muddled a lot and frustrated at herself for getting muddled. She made a number of errors in her sentence but was able to self correct when prompted to engage in that behaviour. She really liked the beginnings of the A- and B-story conversation we started having.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-20 15:38:20', '2022-09-12 16:26:50'),
(2556, '2022/06/20', '04:28 pm', '2', '8', 'Arlo Clark', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick F1<br>Challenge: seed. To recognize letters, sounds and phonograms in the word seed. Arlo did a good job here.&nbsp;<br>Phonograms introduction:&nbsp;<br>1. some phonograms have more than one sounds;2. some phonograms have more than one letters; 3. some phonograms share the same sounds; 4. a phonogram only represents one sound in a word.</p><p>OPR: &nbsp;new phonograms : clockface letters 1-8<br>Arlo could say at least one sound for each phonograms.&nbsp;<br>WPR: 1-8&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;handwriting focus: clockface letters. Homework was sent home related to handwriting. Arlo forms a from the left bottom and he needed remindings for each formation as he writes.&nbsp;</p><p>SD: A-G words. and, run<br>make an oral sentence with SD words.He was good at this.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-20 16:28:43', '2022-06-22 08:56:30'),
(2557, '2022/06/20', '04:29 pm', '2', '8', 'Connor McLaren', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Eight</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 20 June 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick H2 S9</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #26</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: ew ow dge or ti wh th oa ai sh oi ee</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 4, 6, 2, 11</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. N - trophy, voices, voice, (Sec. O) eight, ate, afraid, uncle, rather</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>LS continue work on election passage (compose)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>CM ORF x2</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Uno</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>CM &amp; LS did well with PA and harder MA. Fine with OPR/WPR, did well with SD but both needed lots of prompting to do neat handwriting. LS continued compose of passage while CM did reading fluency with me, then we played a game of Uno to finish.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-20 16:29:34', '2022-06-20 18:07:23'),
