(2559, '2022/06/20', '04:31 pm', '2', '7', 'Zac Pharaoh ', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics – Foundation', 'Consumer arithmetic', 'Please see lesson notes', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>In today\'s lesson we did:</p><ul><li>calculate weekly or monthly wage from a salary and from an hourly rate, including situations involving overtime and other allowances, and earnings based on commission or piecework</li><li>calculate payments based on government allowances and pensions.</li></ul><p>With a lot of guidance, Zac was able to solve problems related to the topics listed above. Mainly, we use the textbook - Compendium of general Mathematics, Consumer - by John Shorten.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-20 16:31:17', '2022-07-03 21:12:54'),
(2560, '2022/06/20', '04:38 pm', '2', '8', 'Arki Young', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-20 16:38:45', '2022-06-20 16:49:16'),
(2561, '2022/06/20', '05:35 pm', '2', '7', 'Jett  Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Pythagoras and Trigonometry', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'See notes', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Jett and I were working on Bearings, Mainly we did problems like</p><p>A, B and C are three ships. The bearing of A from B is 045º. The bearing of C from A is 135º. If AB= 8km and AC= 6km, what is the bearing of B from C?</p><p><img src=\"https://revisionworld.com/sites/revisionworld.com/files/imce/bearings.gif\" alt=\"bearings\"></p><p>Jett needed a lot of guidance to solve problems like that; I strongly recommended Jett draw big diagrams to help him understand the problem and know what he would need to find the answer.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-20 17:35:35', '2022-07-03 21:26:17'),
(2562, '2022/06/21', '08:44 am', '2', '6', 'Max Shapiro', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-21 08:44:04', '2022-06-21 08:44:04'),
(2563, '2022/06/21', '03:33 pm', '2', '8', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Stella was really impressive on his tasks today because her mother sat in. She wanted to do her best in front of her mother and showed her potential for more challengable tasks than ever. She could say all multiple sounds for complicated phonograms such as ou and ow, and she could form them correctly in spelling dictation. The sSD words definetelly were some chanllege for her yet she did a great job and concentrated so well today!</p><p>OPR: th, ee, ow, ou. She needed help with ee sound. she has confusions between ee and e.&nbsp;</p><p>multi sound ball throwing activity for ou. She did a great job here,&nbsp;</p><p>new phonogram learning oo with the sorting activity. She can recognize the long and short sounds for oo.&nbsp;</p><p><br>WPR th, ee, ow, ou, oo. &nbsp;She tends to write lots of numbers and ou and ow backwards. for example, she wrote wo and uo, she wwrote 3 and 2 back to front.&nbsp;</p><p>handwriting focus: line letter w.&nbsp;<br>morphology activity 14: we used color code manipulatives aand she did a great job!</p><p>SD: this, see, now, you, good. She needed help with this(thes). These words were some challenge for her yet she did a great job because she focused very well during phonogram reviews. Marking in these words gave her some frustration.&nbsp;</p><p><br>oral sentence using SD words.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-21 15:33:57', '2022-06-22 09:36:28'),
(2565, '2022/06/21', '03:36 pm', '2', '8', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 55 > 70', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Brock did not show up last week without notification and this week he showed up late. He was upset as he had an argument with his mother about tutoring. He thinks that he has gotten enough progress at school and does not need tutoring any more, yet his mother wants him to continue doing tutoring. He was quite resistant during our lesson as he was upset from his mother.&nbsp;</p><p>We did some chat and a little bit of work. Brock would love more activities that have tasks combined with sport activities.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>OPR: 50-60. Brock needed help with ew and ui sounds.&nbsp;</li><li>WPR: he needed help with the formation of ew.&nbsp;</li><li>match dependent sentences with related independent sentences for complex sentences. Brock needed help to initiate the task and he then focused on it himself.&nbsp;</li><li>Write a letter. He wrote a letter to his mother, in which he obviously expressed his upset feelings and unhappiness about her.&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-06-21 16:13:53', '2022-06-22 09:04:18'),
(2566, '2022/06/21', '04:26 pm', '2', '2', 'Owen Fitzgerald', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics', 'Trigonometry', 'Applications of trigonometry', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Next week is Owen\'s test and he told me he\'s struggling with bearings and COS and SIN rule.&nbsp;</p><p>I showed him how drawing big diagrams are important; I could notice that Owen\'s spatial skills aren\'t up to the level they should be.&nbsp;</p><p>We covered:</p><ul><li>review of true and reduced bearings</li><li>review the use of the trigonometric ratios to find the length of an unknown side or the size of an unknown angle in a right-angled triangle</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-06-21 16:26:56', '2022-07-03 19:41:13'),
(2567, '2022/06/21', '04:27 pm', '2', '6', 'Lachlan Prior', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-21 16:27:36', '2022-06-21 16:27:36'),
(2568, '2022/06/21', '04:29 pm', '2', '8', 'Shay Douglas', 'Academic Coaching', 'Independent Study', 'School Assigned Worksheet or Assignment', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, 'Subject: Science\r\nFocus: Creating Shay\'s science poster (due Thursday).\r\n\r\nShay had already done some work on this poster which we looked over. We then identified what exactly he was being asked to do for a section of the assignment he was unsure about. Shay then had some independent time to work on his assignment and compose his first draft.', NULL, '2022-06-21 16:29:36', '2022-06-21 17:05:42'),
(2569, '2022/06/21', '04:32 pm', '2', '8', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>kilpatrick F1</p><p>challenge: &nbsp;noun, pronoun, verb, adjective sorting. Callum usually needs help to recognize verb and noun.&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR: 1-ear43. Callum has mastered all these phonograms</p><p><br>new phonogram: kn, gn, wr, ie, dge,<br>SD: high, they, goes, &nbsp;knock, sign, recieve, badge. Callum could not recall silent final e job 5 and needed help to recognize. We might need more practice on this. &nbsp;</p><p>new rules introduction: rule 23 and 25.&nbsp;</p><p>Sentence structures-Write a simple sentence with SD words. He needs remindings for capital letter at the start of a sentence, as well as punctuation at the end of his sentences.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-21 16:32:39', '2022-06-22 09:10:30'),
(2570, '2022/06/21', '04:45 pm', '2', '8', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'To Be Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-21 16:46:09', '2022-07-04 15:42:05'),
(2571, '2022/06/21', '05:27 pm', '2', '4', 'Lucy Crosswell', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete onset or rime - Kilpatrick Level F', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8 + e i u + 27-30</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: a c g o s e u sh ee th ee ow</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: it-in</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>POS: Introduce nouns as person, place or thing. Introduce action verbs. Sort list of words into nouns and verbs. Pair nouns and verbs together into complete toughts.&nbsp; Noun + Verb + Punctuation = Simple Sentence (show on SBB). Mark nouns and verbs in given (basic) sentences. Explain that a sentence needs a subject and action. Explain and discuss meaning of the word subject. Explain that the subject of a sentence is the person, place or thing (the who or what) that is completeing the action (doing something). Show Subject Nouns in each of given sentences (what is the verb? Who is [completing the action]?).</td></tr><tr><td>Simple sentence EP, read and highlight important infomation. Compose sentences using given noun/verb and colour code.</td></tr><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Simple sentence does not equal lacking detail.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule 4 -- concept of rules needs work. She couldn\'t answer the question \"what rule is being used in this word?\"</td></tr><tr><td>Keep working on nouns and verbs. She was okay but needs practice articulating them/understanding themas categories.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-21 17:27:52', '2022-06-21 18:41:54'),
(2572, '2022/06/22', '07:49 am', '2', '8', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 55 > 70', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Luke forgot to show up last week and he attended lesson 15 minutes late today, but he had a good mood today because I promised to play a ball game with him at the end. It is easier for him to focus when he gets to stand up and move around. He definetely benefits from that. It can be hard to manage him to get back to tasks when he is hooked with his ball games.&nbsp;</p><p>PA: Kilpatrick&nbsp;<br>i</p><p>OPR: 60-70. Luke needed help with the sounds for ie, ei, and eigh.&nbsp;</p><p>multi sound phonogram ball throwing game: he had a hard time with the 3 different sounds for ie.&nbsp;</p><p>WPR:60-70. He needed help to form dge and eigh.&nbsp;</p><p>Morphology: we need to redo affixes next week for this<br>Parts of speech: Luke knows nouns and verbs very well, yet he needs help to recognize other parts of speech.<br><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-22 07:49:37', '2022-06-22 09:17:57'),
