(2577, '2022/06/22', '01:52 pm', '2', '6', 'Eleanor  Stam', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-22 13:52:02', '2022-06-22 13:52:02'),
(2578, '2022/06/22', '03:28 pm', '2', '7', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: sh ow ng kn ck oo igh ed&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 18 5 &amp; 6</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: today-six</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: 100 -- mark all multiletter phonograms in words. ORF read through, stilted &amp; obviously decoding, then read through the first sentence again -- huge improvement.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>As promised, took some time at the beginning to make a hot chocolate with Max. This was effective in ensuring we didn\'t have to do any of the coaxing to get him up to the room. I think it gave him a sugar high, though -- he was pretty loud and excitable and easily distracted. The reading activity was a really good activity.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-22 15:28:08', '2022-06-22 16:46:24'),
(2579, '2022/06/22', '03:28 pm', '2', '8', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR&nbsp; a ai ay eigh e ee ie ei ey o ow ou ough oa oe I y igh u ew ui&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review -9/10/11/24</p><p>Challenge Words</p><p>Jump+er</p><p>Fly + ing</p><p>Spoke + en</p><p>Sunny + est</p><p>State +ment</p><p>Cry + ed</p><p>Reset + ing</p><p>Swim+ er</p><p>Digest + ed</p><p>Fun+y</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD: Q – president to dew rules 11/4 /12/29/j1&amp;2</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>Complex sentence using from SD.&nbsp;</p><p>Due to the dew…..</p><p>Either …….. or…………</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading OF&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW – complete worksheet</p><p>Reading.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-22 15:28:35', '2022-06-28 10:07:48'),
(2580, '2022/06/22', '03:30 pm', '2', '6', 'Toby Webb', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-22 15:30:39', '2022-06-22 15:30:39'),
(2581, '2022/06/22', '03:31 pm', '2', '8', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Find unknown quantities in number sentences involving multiplication and division', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today Connor was very distracted. Probably the medication to control his ADHD was clearing.&nbsp;</p><p>It was difficult to get him focused to solve simple equations.&nbsp;</p><p>All the problems we did today were done on the board. &nbsp;We did problems like:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>X + 4 = 2</li><li>3 - X = 1</li><li>12 x X = 36</li><li>54 / X = 9&nbsp;</li></ul><p>I was trying to explain to Connor how to solve these problems without “just knowing” instead, I wanted him to see the connection between additions, subtractions, multiplications and divisions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-22 15:31:45', '2022-07-03 17:56:56'),
(2582, '2022/06/22', '03:37 pm', '2', '2', 'Archie Smith', 'English Assessment', 'Reading Comprehension', 'Phonics, Single Word Decoding and Word Meaning in Context', 'Waddington Reading Test - #1', 'Will Hughes', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Archie finished assessments today, started on spiel and went through phonograms 30-38. Archie relatively comfortable with these phonograms, will put into a SD next week</p>', NULL, '2022-06-22 15:37:54', '2022-06-22 15:40:11'),
(2583, '2022/06/22', '04:24 pm', '2', '6', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Challenge: association. Find all rules and markings.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Spelling Words: examination particular supply reveal</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 24 12</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: course-further</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Integrating quotes. Read ORF #618 and discuss. Identify direct quote from Beachey. Discuss the four steps to integrating a quote. Write 3-4 sentences, following the given structure, using the quote from 619.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>The integrating quote activity was really good! He needed more coaching with the analysis portion, which I probably could have predicted. Might have to incorporate an analysis task with this next week -- I\'d like to do a repeate, with focus on analysis.</td></tr><tr><td>Uno: Angus - 1, Neve - 0</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-22 16:24:20', '2022-06-22 17:28:37'),
(2584, '2022/06/22', '04:28 pm', '2', '6', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>In this lesson, we worked with operations with fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>But before, we did a review on the concept of fractions by Make Fraction Teams and Fractions BINGO!</p><p>Then we moved to operations with fractions with/without the same denominator.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-22 16:28:33', '2022-07-03 12:30:14'),
(2585, '2022/06/22', '04:31 pm', '2', '8', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Xavier did not have any work with him today so we reviewed syllabification and associated spelling rules.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-22 16:31:55', '2022-06-28 10:05:08'),
(2586, '2022/06/22', '04:35 pm', '2', '3', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-22 16:35:28', '2022-06-22 16:35:28'),
(2587, '2022/06/22', '05:28 pm', '2', '8', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>In today\'s lesson we were working on long multiplications and divisions; percentages and fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>Last week I could notice some hesitation in Luca with long multiplications and divisions. I asked him to solve a good number of problems on the board and was guiding him with all questions.&nbsp;</p><p>Then we moved to work on percentages and their connection with fractions. This is part of the stock market game; Luca and I are participating in this game and hopefully, in some weeks we could enter and trade there.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-22 17:28:52', '2022-07-03 18:13:59'),
(2588, '2022/06/22', '05:52 pm', '2', '3', 'Callan Bartlett', 'Mathematics', 'Decimals', 'Operations with decimals', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Kieran Oates', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Callan was quite attentive although lost focus at times. We studied multiplication with large numbers as well as decimals which he began to comprehend quite well.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-22 17:52:41', '2022-06-22 18:40:14'),
(2589, '2022/06/23', '07:34 am', '2', '8', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'OTHER', 'OTHER', 'Please read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', '<p>Nate\'s school teacher, Rebecca, asked me to work with Nate on the topics listed below. So far, all of them have been covered and Nate understands the concepts.&nbsp;</p><p>I wanted to let you know that Nate and I have been going all through the topics you passed me some weeks ago,&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><p><i><strong>Number</strong></i></p><p><i>-Place Value (up to and beyond tens of thousands)&nbsp;</i></p><p><i>-Partitioning numbers</i></p><p><i>-Connections to real life examples (country populations, land size)&nbsp;</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i><strong>Mental Computation&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></i></p><p><i>Strategies for addition and subtraction (moving to multiplication later eg. Term 2?)</i></p><p><i><strong>&nbsp;</strong></i></p><p><i><strong>Problem Solving</strong></i></p></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><i>Drawing diagrams for worded problems</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>That information was so useful and relevant. On top of those topics, we have been working on skip counting, connections between additions/subtractions and multiplications/divisions, short and long divisions, and operations with decimals, but divisions. In this last part, we only have done divisions by 10, 100 and 1000 base numbers.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rebecca\'s recommendation for the upcoming weeks is to work on the following,&nbsp;</p><p>Future Maths Focus for our class is:</p><p>-Recall multiplication facts up to 10x10 and related division facts.</p><p>-Develop efficient mental and written strategies and use appropriate digital technologies for multiplication and division with no remainder.&nbsp;</p><p>-Recognise that the place value system can be extended to tenths and hundredths. Make connections between fractions and decimal notation.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-23 07:34:29', '2022-07-03 12:05:33'),
(2590, '2022/06/23', '07:51 am', '2', '4', 'Chester  Vincent', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-23 07:51:48', '2022-06-23 07:51:48'),
(2591, '2022/06/23', '08:50 am', '2', '6', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Ratios', 'Using Ratios to Find Amounts', 'Textbooks, practice papers, school work', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Using James\' homework on how currencies, we were working rates of change.&nbsp;</p><p>I explained to James how to convert between currencies and also did some work around other rates. For instance, if 1 litre of petrol is 220 cents, how much do I need to fill a 100 L tank?&nbsp;</p><p>In the last 15 minutes of the lesson, we moved to work (one more time) with integers. Started off by doing operations like -6-4 = ? and then we were doing multiplications and divisions with integers.&nbsp;</p><p>James\' behaviour and engagement were significantly better than some weeks ago. He was talking about what he did at school, telling me dad jokes and also looking at the main reasons why mine-craft is much better than animal crossing.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Lesson No 6 was delivered on 16.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-23 08:50:07', '2022-07-03 09:16:02'),
(2592, '2022/06/23', '02:24 pm', '2', '7', 'Nell  Brooks', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Aiming to progress with Nell\'s learning plan, today we covered two topics at the same time, decimals and fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>To explain decimals, it was used wooden blocks and decimals were explained as another way to do divisions. The same operation, divisions, was used to explain fractions.</p><p>It was shown to the student how the decimal system works and its use in measurement.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 7 was delivered on 16.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-23 14:24:48', '2022-07-03 07:57:01'),
(2593, '2022/06/23', '03:25 pm', '2', '7', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Today, Sofia and I were reviewing the timetables and perimeter.&nbsp;</p><p>Sofia showed great improvement with the 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 and 9 times tables. We need to work with the 7 and 8.</p><p>Also, we revisited the perimeter of triangles and Sofia did &nbsp;good work on it too.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-23 15:25:08', '2022-07-02 21:25:11'),
(2594, '2022/06/23', '03:32 pm', '2', '8', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Adjectives - describe nouns', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus is to increase and expand Cara\'s vocab, both verbal and written.&nbsp;</p><p>Royal order of Adjective focus gave her explicit categories to focus on and encouraged using single words or short phrases to produce quality descriptions.</p><p>1. modelling on board</p><p>2. worksheet</p><p>3. verbal</p><p>4. online activity</p><p>5. descriptive task.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-23 15:32:01', '2022-06-28 10:00:57'),
(2595, '2022/06/23', '03:38 pm', '2', '8', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 100', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Lucy began the lesson using inverse operations to solve, correct and explain workings of facts to 100 equations completed last week. &nbsp;She is developing confidence and speed when using these operations to problem solve.</p><p>Also worked through practice papers as provided by Key Maths Assessment covering weight and money. &nbsp;</p><p>Lucy has some difficulty visualising and calculating coin values but was increasingly confident by the end of the lesson. &nbsp;Some additional practise has been sent home for further consolidation. &nbsp;Ongoing review and increasing the complexity of these problems will be beneficial for Lucy to further develop the ability to manipulate various denominations.</p><p>A short time was spent recording labels for inverse equations used to justify a worked answer in NSPM Level 3a workbook. &nbsp;Prompts were needed to support Lucy label the values in this equation (making connections between the values and what they represent).</p><p>Lucy will continue with workings, labels and word problems in NSPM workbook at home.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-23 15:38:42', '2022-06-23 17:09:14'),
(2596, '2022/06/23', '03:41 pm', '2', '7', 'Elsa Clennet', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>NO LESSON DUE TO PUBLIC HOLIDAY</p>', '2022-06-23 15:42:46', '2022-09-12 16:29:46'),
(2597, '2022/06/23', '04:22 pm', '2', '8', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Writing - Parts of Speech & Vocabulary', 'Adjectives - describe nouns', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus - The Writing Process</p><ol><li>Building Finn\'s written descriptive language by</li><li>Royal Order of Adjectives</li><li>Verbal discussion, online activity, written task</li></ol><p>Finn has great verbal vocab but hesitates to write using the same language.</p><p>NW - Bring together this lesson to have finn write a short descriptive piece about an object - sight unseen by Kim.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-23 16:22:37', '2022-06-28 09:52:38'),
(2598, '2022/06/23', '04:30 pm', '2', '6', 'Samuel Lamont', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-23 16:30:24', '2022-06-23 16:30:24'),
(2599, '2022/06/23', '04:37 pm', '2', '7', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics – Foundation', 'Consumer arithmetic', 'Please see the notes', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>To help Finlay to get ready for the mid-year exam, in this lesson we started to re-visit the consumer maths unit from the beginning.&nbsp;</p><p>In some opportunities, Finlay gets stuck when he needs to re-arrange the equations to solve the problem. Apart from this, the student solves the problems correctly.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson 7 was delivered on 16.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-23 16:37:52', '2022-07-02 19:21:28'),
(2600, '2022/06/23', '04:50 pm', '2', '8', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Money & Financial Maths', 'Connect the compound interest formula to repeated applications of simple interest', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callisto has a Mid-Year Exam on Tuesday next week. The sections of the exam will deal with Finance and Trigonometry. We started work on the Finance section of the 2020 final exam as it is some time since Callisto did any work on this topic. We will do some work on Trig next time (Monday) which is the day before the exam. Callisto remembered quite a bit about how to do these problems on the graphics calculator once we got going.</p>', NULL, '2022-06-23 16:50:00', '2022-06-23 17:40:00');
INSERT INTO `attens` (`id`, `date_created`, `time`, `term`, `lesson`, `student_name`, `subject_name`, `concept_name`, `conceptDetail`, `learningActivity`, `tutor_name`, `tutor_evaluation`, `student_self`, `student_attendance`, `homework_completed`, `weekly_lesson`, `homework_assignment`, `email_school`, `comment`, `commentPrivate`, `notesAttendance`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2601, '2022/06/23', '05:31 pm', '2', '7', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Quadratics', 'Expand binomial products and factorise monic quadratic expressions using a variety of strategies', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Introductory', '<p>Factorising quadratics → Trinomials → aX^2 + bX + c with a = 1&nbsp;</p><p>I explained this to Nicholas like a cooking receipt; doing this was very productive as despite we have been working on factorisation in the last weeks, this is the first we worked on trinomials.&nbsp;</p><p>Nicholas needs a lot of practice to grasp the concept, and he\'s definitely on the right track towards this.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 7 was delivered on 16.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-23 17:31:25', '2022-07-02 18:06:07'),
(2602, '2022/06/24', '07:34 am', '2', '6', 'Gus  Pettit', 'Mathematics', 'Measurement', 'Describe duration using months, weeks, days and hours', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Work done based on Essential Assessments, soon, Gus will have a test on this platform and we need to get him ready for it.</p><p>Today\'s work was about scales of time, calculating elapsed time and time zones.&nbsp;</p><p>In the second part of the lesson, we\'re looking at volumen. Calculating the volume of assorted parallelograms and prisms.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 6 was delivered on 10.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-24 07:34:48', '2022-07-02 15:35:39'),
(2603, '2022/06/24', '07:40 am', '2', '8', 'Archie Lester', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete final sound in word or final blend - Kilpatrick Level I', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>During morphology lesson, Archie was able to explain that the first word in a compound word is the adjective and the second is the noun.</p><p>We reviewed last week\'s sentences identifying the meaning of and punctuation for nouns of direct address, appositives and speaker tags. &nbsp;Archie and Naomi jointly composed sentences for dictation and punctuation. &nbsp;</p><ul><li>Katherine, the girl with the maths tutor, failed maths.</li><li>Archie, the curious boy, stuck his hand in a firepit and burned it.</li><li>Mum screamed, “Archie, you\'re in big trouble.”</li></ul><p>Read passge #2 of Practicing and Assessing Reading Comprehension (Level 4). &nbsp;We will revisit this for fluency and reformatting next lesson.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-24 07:40:21', '2022-06-24 10:20:07'),
(2604, '2022/06/24', '10:20 am', '2', '8', 'Lottie Young', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>On arrival, Lottie and I spoke about what she had remembered from our lesson last week. Lottie was very clear about the idea that some brains take longer to think about things because they take the long way. &nbsp;We spoke about the fact that this is not a bad thing - it\'s just that some brains need a bit more time, and that\'s okay.</p><p>I gave Lottie the option to continue strengthening the concepts we\'ve been working on the last couple of weeks or doing something new/different. &nbsp;Lottie was quick to say, “Well, I think we should keep going and finish what we\'re doing by the end of term and start something new next term.”</p><p>Further focus on partner phonograms, beginning with word decoding cards both at the table and stepping out, both reading for spelling and reading for reading. &nbsp;Also reading multi-letter phonograms only.</p><p>Lottie was notably more confident today. &nbsp;continues to struggle with the ‘ui’ and ‘au’ phonograms. &nbsp;</p><p>Words dictated: straw, threw, fault, cruise, bruise, haul, shrewd.</p><p>Sentence dictated: On the cruise I fell and now I have a bruise. &nbsp;It was all Arki\'s fault.</p><p>In morphology, introduced the concept of compound words - first word = adjective and second word = noun. &nbsp;ID noun and verb in each word of Sandra Donah #13.</p><p>Played Code Quest with partner phonograms minus ew and ui.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-24 10:21:30', '2022-06-24 10:51:03'),
(2605, '2022/06/24', '02:24 pm', '2', '8', 'Molly  Jackson', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) second phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level K', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR:27-58</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ee th ow ou oo ch ar ai oi ir&nbsp; ur ng ck ed ew ui igh&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 4 6</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: know-early</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use words in sentences to use words in context. Discussion about where, there, here, were.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: ORF #222 -- Molly did well reading with fluency/expression/adhereing to punctuation (particularly with questions).</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Molly was very frustrating today -- she was giving me a bit of attitude and did not want to listen to me when I was talking about sound/symbol. She was so quick to give up on herself and proclaim she couldn\'t do it and \"just help me, please?\" but she wasn\'t actually attempting the task in the first place. It all cam down to the sound/symbol connection in spelling -- with leave, she was saying \"I don\'t know how to spell that\", and I was explaining that I AM helping her/providing scaffolding but she didn\'t want to hear it. She just wanted to spell it out using letter names until I told her she had the right letter combination and order, which is obviously not something I\'m going to engage in.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>We fared slightly better with this type of discussion during sentence writing &amp; in her ORF reading. Again, she was quick to hurry me along when I got her to break words up into syllables and started talking about how her brain was interpeting words -- I thought it would interest her, but obviously not. She was clearly looking at the whole word, identifying a couple of letters, and then trying words she knew also had those letters. She really struggled decoding \"dormant\". Dor was okay, as was segmenting into m/a/n/t, but blending into mant she lost one of the consonant sounds and got upset (matn, mat). However, when I got her to blend to man and then add t, she got mant and blended the syllables to get dormant (a new word for her)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-24 14:24:51', '2022-06-24 15:57:59'),
(2606, '2022/06/24', '03:28 pm', '2', '7', 'Harlow Booy', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Represent and solve simple addition and subtraction problems using a range of strategies', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we did a review of all the work we have done so far. I wanted to do this to check on Harlow\'s progress. She has improved well in counting and regrouping, her skip counting with even times tables is much better than some weeks ago.&nbsp;</p><p>In the upcoming weeks, the work will focus on removing the counters and helping Harlow to solve divisions and multiplications without those.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-24 15:28:19', '2022-07-02 12:26:32'),
(2607, '2022/06/24', '03:42 pm', '2', '8', 'Connor Thompson ', 'English', 'Reading - Comprehension > Text Type & Mental Actions', 'Mental Actions of Reading', 'Reformat/categorise information to identify essential and additional information', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Continue reformatting activity from Week 6, reformat into a paragraph. Connor did this adequately, although too many sentences were lists with key words connected by \"and\". We then started revising and editing, first by editing punctuation (Connor had put in full stops before carrying on with \"and\" in many cases). In doing this, we started grouping key words based on commonalities to decide how we should break up his long sentences. Connor struggled with this concept. We played my grouping activity with objects/concepts on sticky notes, finishing with his key words. By the end Connor could group the key words. He also composed a sentence grouping these two key words.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-24 15:43:22', '2022-06-24 17:22:27'),
(2608, '2022/06/24', '04:26 pm', '2', '7', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write additional phonograms  (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review - Cards 71 - 87', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Game/connections activity: grouping objects game that I played with Connor. Nate made some good connections and could easily identify ‘obvious\' or tangible connections, such as shape, colour, size, etc. Creating abstract connections (e.g. things I can write with, things belonging to Neve) was trickier for him.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: Additional phonograms</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure:Compose 3 related sentences again, again proving to Nate that he can compose paragraphs.</td></tr><tr><td>Nate did well -- he kicked up a little bit of fuss, but once he got going, he actually composed more sentences than I had asked him to, and ended up with a full paragraph about Minecraft and iron ore!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-24 16:26:33', '2022-06-24 17:27:16'),
