(2610, '2022/06/27', '08:52 am', '2', '2', 'Liam Wells', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-27 08:52:54', '2022-06-27 08:52:54'),
(2611, '2022/06/27', '02:29 pm', '2', '8', 'Matthew Heard', 'Mathematics', 'OTHER', 'OTHER', 'Please read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Lesson No 8 was meant to be delivered on 21.06.2022. However, Matt was sick and could come to tutoring. I offered catch-up times to Melissa, however, she said that the options weren\'t good for Matt and decided to miss the make-up session.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-06-27 14:29:05', '2022-07-03 19:51:10'),
(2612, '2022/06/27', '02:44 pm', '2', '7', 'Luna Shapiro', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA:Kilpatrick G1</td></tr><tr><td>Revist vowels/consonants (in book) and segment/represent (IDing V/C sounds) using counters.</td></tr><tr><td>Luna did okay but struggled with remembering which were vowels and which were consonants. She was 90% accurate identifying which were closed/open sounds.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8 e i u + 27-33</td></tr><tr><td>HF: Handwriting features - 2 o\'clock letters, base line, top line, explicit instruction&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 1-8 using 2 o\'clock scaffold</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Drawing with letters activity</td></tr><tr><td>Phonemic awareness:</td></tr><tr><td>See \"dog\" written on board. Segment, count, blend.</td></tr><tr><td>Repeat for sheep, explicitly distinguishing between sounds, phonograms, and letters.</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Review: Rule 1</td></tr><tr><td>SD: queen, quit, quiz, quack</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Handwriting sheet - write and decode sentences.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SCORE: 1.1</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luna wasn\'t feeling well today so was subdued. She was a little worse off than last week -- she reeeeally didn\'t want to do any handwriting. I got a little bit in there but mainly focused on theory/revisting concepts such as vowels/consonants and handwriting. Also sent home tracing for decoding/practice and SCORE page.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-27 14:44:33', '2022-06-27 16:30:26'),
(2613, '2022/06/27', '03:28 pm', '2', '9', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer. Mia is usually more accurate on this activity yet Thomas is faster.&nbsp;</p><p><br>OPR/WPR: 1-45 try not to moo game. Mia and Thomas can say at least one sound for each phonogram up to 45. They still need help for multi sounds for some phonograms. Mia needs help with ch, th, o, u, y, ea, ay. Thomas needs help with &nbsp;u, ea, y. For WPR, they both still need help with the five er. Thomas writes z backwards and he normally cannot notice the difference without help.&nbsp;</p><p><br>SD: now the. Mia and Thomas needed help to analyze and mark the word the because of the pronunciation of it.&nbsp;</p><p><br>online spelling game. They both did a great job at finding the right words for the right pictures!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I find Thomas &nbsp;and Mia can concentrate so much better since we started our paired lessons, They have more motivation and they get to learn from each other by repeating and articulating together.&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-27 15:28:24', '2022-06-29 21:55:28'),
(2614, '2022/06/27', '03:29 pm', '2', '9', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer. Mia is usually more accurate on this activity yet Thomas is faster.&nbsp;</p><p><br>OPR/WPR: 1-45 try not to moo game. Mia and Thomas can say at least one sound for each phonogram up to 45. They still need help for multi sounds for some phonograms. Mia needs help with ch, th, o, u, y, ea, ay. Thomas needs help with &nbsp;u, ea, y. For WPR, they both still need help with the five er. Thomas writes z backwards and he normally cannot notice the difference without help.&nbsp;</p><p><br>SD: now the. Mia and Thomas needed help to analyze and mark the word the because of the pronunciation of it.&nbsp;</p><p><br>online spelling game. They both did a great job at finding the right words for the right pictures!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>I find Thomas &nbsp;and Mia can concentrate so much better since we started our paired lessons, They have more motivation and they get to learn from each other by repeating and articulating together.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-27 15:29:02', '2022-06-29 21:56:38'),
(2615, '2022/06/27', '03:32 pm', '2', '5', 'Seth Vanderlaan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-27 15:32:47', '2022-06-27 15:32:47'),
(2616, '2022/06/27', '03:34 pm', '2', '8', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Simplify algebraic expressions involving the four operations', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>The lesson was about the language of algebra, we did:</p><ul><li>Definition of algebraic term.</li><li>Alike terms.</li><li>Adding and taking away alike terms</li><li>review on sign law.</li></ul><p>Archie did great work today; he had no issues or problems with the practice questions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-27 15:34:50', '2022-07-03 20:33:37'),
(2617, '2022/06/27', '03:37 pm', '2', '9', 'Elsa Clennet', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ey gn kn</td></tr><tr><td>Bonus: write the following words - sign, gnat, gnome, design</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>South Australia Spelling Test</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Writing Process: Plan out the emotional arc of Elsa\'s story, utilising what we\'ve learned so far about beginning/climax/denounment and theme.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Elsa went up 18 months in 14 months for her SA. She showed some good thinking when faced with unfamiliar words, including some rule application (rule 29, 21) but not always correctly.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-27 15:37:59', '2022-06-27 17:44:33'),
(2618, '2022/06/27', '04:30 pm', '2', '6', 'Angus Singleton', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-27 16:30:58', '2022-06-27 16:30:58'),
(2619, '2022/06/27', '04:33 pm', '2', '9', 'Arlo Clark', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick F1<br>OPR/WPR: &nbsp;1-8. Arlo needs some remindings of the multi sounds of &nbsp;a, c, o. He has made the progress of forming the letter a from 2\'oclock, which means he definetely practiced at home.&nbsp;<br>multi sound phonogram game for ‘a’<br>new phonograms, 9-26 with line letter handwriting focus.<br>SD: A-G words. do, on. at, is, it. Arlo cannot say the second sound for ‘s’ in the words is.&nbsp;<br>Spelling online game.</p><p>Arlo can usually concentrate for 10 minutes the least on his tasks. He usually tries his best to concentrate, yet he needs game break in between a one-hour lesson.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-27 16:33:14', '2022-06-29 11:17:23'),
(2620, '2022/06/27', '04:33 pm', '2', '8', 'Zac Pharaoh ', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics – Foundation', 'Consumer arithmetic', 'Please see lesson notes', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Using the textbook - The Compendium of General Mathematics - Consumer Mathematics, we were working on:</p><ul><li>prepare a personal budget taking into account fixed and discretionary spending</li><li>compare prices and values using the unit cost method</li><li>apply percentage increase or decrease in various contexts; for example, determining the impact of inflation on costs and wages over time, calculating percentage mark-ups and discounts, calculating GST, calculating profit or loss in absolute and percentage terms</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-06-27 16:33:54', '2022-07-03 21:15:26'),
(2621, '2022/06/27', '04:34 pm', '2', '9', 'Arki Young', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read through Arki\'s assignment -- identifying what was being asked/what needed to be achieved. Planning on board using given school scaffold, arranging arguments into a logical order, creating topic sentences to use as scaffold for speech. Arki wanted some time to practice his typing skills but also requested he dictate some of it. He requested that I leave out grammar so that he could go back through and edit it himself. We also did some research and interpreted statistics. Arki did well with composing, however, as I\'ve noted in the past, with topics he\'s less familiar with, his words fail him a little. We could include more research in the planning stage, perhaps.</td></tr><tr><td>When Arki knows a lot about a topic, the words just seem to fly onto the page, in very \'academic\' speech. One other struggle was that Arki would say a sentence out loud, and then when he went to write it down, would forget what he wanted to say. I was taking note of his sentences, so could read them back to him, but without this support some of his great wording choices would have been lost.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-27 16:34:20', '2022-06-27 17:49:52'),
(2622, '2022/06/27', '05:36 pm', '2', '8', 'Jett  Knighton', 'Mathematics', 'Pythagoras and Trigonometry', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'See notes', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Jett didn\'t return his homework, he said that he totally forgot how to work out Bearings and got confused with when to apply Pythagoras or trig ratios.&nbsp;</p><p>We went through all the problems I gave him for homework and did those on the board. With the last problems, Jett needed minimum guidance to solve the problems.&nbsp;</p><p>Jett wanted to solve more problems related to bearings and trig ratios. Therefore, we moved to use these concepts on 3D shapes and again, he needed minimal guidance to solve the proposed problems.&nbsp;</p><p>I think Jett needs to do a lot of practice at home to grasp the concept, he is on right track in terms of clearly knowing which trig ratio is needed to solve a problem and the appropriate angle to be used in the same problem.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-27 17:36:02', '2022-07-03 21:33:22'),
(2623, '2022/06/28', '08:45 am', '2', '7', 'Max Shapiro', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-28 08:45:41', '2022-06-28 08:45:41'),
(2624, '2022/06/28', '08:55 am', '2', '9', 'Henry  Badock', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Recognise and represent multiplication as repeated addition, groups and arrays', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus: Mental computation using Friends of strategies, counting on counting back, counting up, checking answers by reversing the process (addition into subtraction and vice versa)</p><p>Henry uses all the above strategies including use of manipulatives, number lines and fingers. Frequently does not check whether he is doing addition or subtraction unless reminded.&nbsp;</p><p>Focus: Addition with regrouping</p><p>H demonstrates understanding of the concept and articulates using the appropriate PV language.&nbsp;</p><p>Focus: Subtraction with PV reinforced in preparation for regrouping.&nbsp;</p><p>Focus Multiplication &nbsp;- relationship to addition. 2,5,10 x explored using text book examples, manipulatives and articulation of examples.&nbsp;</p><p>Henry was oppositional initially as he did not want to do work! However once he expereinced success, especially with multiplication he was enthused and engaged!!</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-28 08:56:26', '2022-06-28 09:07:17'),
(2625, '2022/06/28', '03:25 pm', '2', '2', 'Sebastian Bowerman', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-28 15:25:34', '2022-06-28 15:25:34'),
(2626, '2022/06/28', '03:26 pm', '2', '9', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'GEOMETRY', 'Location & Transformation', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'To Be Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>We worked towards, Comparing angles and classifying them as equal to, greater than, or less than, a right angle. Along with the definition of supplementary and complementary angles.&nbsp;</p><p>Luca did great work! He hadn\'t used the protractor in a quite long time, this allowed me to explain to him the difference between positive and negative angles.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;Then we were implementing all the concepts we looked at today to work on-location sketches. Luca\'s location skills are very good, he could solve the problems with little guidance and the majority of his answers were correct.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-28 15:26:59', '2022-07-03 18:21:39'),
(2627, '2022/06/28', '03:34 pm', '2', '8', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick H1 -- Still needs practice/scaffolding</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-50</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 27-41</td></tr><tr><td>Some trouble with \"ur\" (both IDIng correct phonogram vs writing as ru)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 29</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: woman-plan</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ayres words in sentence to show difference between woman/women.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Not Completed:</td></tr><tr><td>Oral Fluency: 220</td></tr><tr><td>Comp: Answer MA questions about the passage.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sophie was really struggling with sounds today, particularly ou. She struggled especially with \'young\' in SD, sounding it out correctly when segmenting, but sounding out as y/o/ng as soon as she started considering the symbols involved (despite me telling her to use ou phonogram). She also struggled to identify the sound it was making,&nbsp; &nbsp;following a process of:</td></tr><tr><td><p>NM: Which sound is it making in young?&nbsp;</p><p>SM: \'u\'.&nbsp;</p><p>NM: Great. The 4 sounds this phonogram makes are ow/O/oo/u. Which sound is it making in this word?&nbsp;</p><p>SM: o?&nbsp;</p><p>NM: Not quite. Which sound can you hear in the word young?&nbsp;</p><p>SM: o? oo! u?&nbsp;</p><p>NM: u, yes. That\'s one of the sounds that this phonogram makes. I want you to tell me if it is the phonogram\'s first, second, third, or fourth sound. The sounds are ow/O/oo/u.&nbsp;</p><p>SM: u.&nbsp;</p><p>NM: That is the sound its making! Is that it\'s first, second, third, or fourth sound?</p><p>SM: I\'m not sure.</p><p>NM: Okay! No worries. Let\'s go through the sounds of this phonogram and work out which one is the u sound. Is it making it\'s first sound, ow?&nbsp;</p><p>SM: Yes!&nbsp;</p><p>NM: Not quite. We already worked out that it\'s making an u sound. It\'s not making an ow sound in this word. Is it making the second sound, O?&nbsp;</p><p>SM: Yes! o!</p><p>&nbsp;NM: Not quite. Again, we worked out that it\'s making a \'u\' sound. We\'re now just finding out which sound of the phonogram that u sound is, so that we know which number to place on top for the marking.&nbsp;</p><p>SM: Oh.&nbsp;</p><p>NM: Is it making it\'s third sound, oo?</p><p>SM: No.</p><p>NM: Is it making its fourth sound, u?&nbsp;</p><p>SM: Yes!</p></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-28 15:34:47', '2022-06-28 17:32:23'),
(2628, '2022/06/28', '04:10 pm', '2', '7', 'Lachlan Prior', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-28 16:10:47', '2022-06-28 16:10:47'),
(2629, '2022/06/28', '04:09 pm', '2', '9', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 55 > 70', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick H1<br>OPR/WPR 61-70. Brock is confused with the multi sounds for phonograms ‘ie’ and ‘ei’.&nbsp;<br>So we did the multi sound ball throwing game for ‘ie’ and he enjoyed it.&nbsp;</p><p>SD: Brock is still upset about the argument he had with his mother. He does not think he needs help any more yet his mother thinks tutoring is helpful for him, so he feels he is forced and he does not like writing. When it came to word dictation, Brock went very resistant and he went quiet and did not want to do this, so we skipped it.&nbsp;<br>writing assessment: Brock has a good awarness about sentence types and structures, yet he needs examples for writing a proper sentence for certain sentence structures. He needed remindings of his capital letter at the beginng and punctuation at the end of a sentence. He mstered simple sentence and compound sentence yet a bit shaky about complex sentence.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-28 16:11:07', '2022-06-29 11:24:42'),
(2630, '2022/06/28', '04:11 pm', '2', '9', 'Stella Lorkin', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Assessement: Please see results in term progress report.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>OPR/WPR 1-30.&nbsp;</li><li>Morrison list 2 .&nbsp;</li><li>Reading: burt word&nbsp;</li></ol><p><br>new phonograms learning: ar, ch, ay, ai, oy, oi.</p><p>From Stella\'s assessment, we can tell that she definetely gained so much in the last 3 terms at Educate Tutring. She has learned 38 phonograms in total and can say almost all sounds for the first 30. Her handwriting has improved a lot this term when we put it into an competition. We have been focusing on her haaand writing formation and she now can write letters in a more natural size and formation.&nbsp;</p><p>Stella was a bit handful to haandle today as her father was sitting in and she acted a bit opposite to how she acted last week when her mother sat in. She was eager to do her best to show her mother her best by concentrating, yet she was a bit hard to handle today when her father was there. SHe resisted to learn and talked with less manners. We almost had to have her father to leave the room until she promised to behave herself.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-28 16:15:40', '2022-06-29 22:16:37'),
(2631, '2022/06/28', '04:26 pm', '2', '3', 'Owen Fitzgerald', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics', 'Trigonometry', 'Applications of trigonometry', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Owen asked me to work one more time on bearings, SOH CAH TOA, Cos and Sin rules and today he was a bit hesitant with his responses on the exam.&nbsp;</p><p>Using the John Shorten textbook we worked on:</p><ul><li>review Pythagoras’ theorem</li><li>angle measure in decimal degrees and in degrees and minutes</li><li>review of true and reduced bearings</li><li>review the use of the trigonometric ratios to find the length of an unknown side or the size of an unknown angle in a right-angled triangle.</li><li>solve problems involving non-right angled triangles using the sine rule (ambiguous case excluded) and the cosine rule</li><li>solve practical problems involving the trigonometry of right-angled and non-right angled triangles, including problems involving angles of elevation and depression and the use of bearings in navigation.</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-06-28 16:26:56', '2022-07-03 19:47:48'),
(2633, '2022/06/28', '04:37 pm', '2', '9', 'Shay Douglas', 'Essay Writing', 'Elements', 'Essay Structure', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Essay skils</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Neve\'s intergrating quotes task.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Go through the worksheet and discuss, with reference to the given example.</td></tr><tr><td>Integrating quotes: Introduce the author, state the quote, explain the quote, analyse the quote, explain the quote\'s relevance to the argument.</td></tr><tr><td>Read through given stimulus (Leonardo da Vinci) and highlight possible quotes. Integrate quote into five sentences that follow the above structure.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-28 16:37:24', '2022-07-05 17:10:49'),
(2634, '2022/06/28', '05:28 pm', '2', '8', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Trig Identities', 'SOH CAH TOA', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we were working on trigonometrical ratios.&nbsp;</p><p>Kieran and I explained to Isaac how to use similarity to investigate the constancy of the sine, cosine and tangent ratios for a given angle in right-angled triangles. This was to help Isaac to develop an understanding of the relationship between the corresponding sides of similar right-angled triangles.&nbsp;</p><p>Isaac understood which ratio he had to use to find an unknown length of a right triangle.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-28 17:28:08', '2022-07-03 19:24:18'),
(2635, '2022/06/28', '06:31 pm', '2', '7', 'Joseph Martín', 'Mathematics', 'Maths methods 3', 'Other', 'Read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>As the exam is approaching today we were looking at some algebraic concepts which will be helpful to have them fresh for the exam, we covered.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>solving quadratic equations: obtaining rational solutions by simple iteration, graphing or obtaining rational and irrational solutions by ‘completion of the square’ and by the quadratic formula</li><li>using the ‘completion of the square’ method for finding maximum or minimum values of quadratic functions.</li><li>solving equations using indices.</li><li>solving linear equations.</li></ul><p>Also, Joseph brought a school assignment to be completed on:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>applying the derivative to:<ul><li>finding instantaneous rates of change</li><li>finding the slope of a tangent and the equations of a tangent and a normal to a curve at a point</li><li>sketching graphs of and analysing graphs associated with quadratic and cubic functions, finding stationary points, and the local maxima and minima and examining behaviour as x→∞x→∞ &nbsp;and &nbsp;x→−∞x→-∞</li><li>sketching graphs of the derivative function when turning points are given</li><li>constructing and interpreting position/displacement-time graphs, with velocity as the slope of the tangent</li></ul></li></ul>', NULL, '2022-06-28 18:31:17', '2022-07-03 18:42:29'),
(2636, '2022/06/29', '07:47 am', '2', '9', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics & Morphology - The Vocabulary of Word Structure', 'Prefix - letters added to the start of base words or word roots to create new words > they have their own meaning & they change the meaning of the base or root - Prefixes cannot stand/be used alone', 'Articulate/explain the meaning of prefix', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>recap morphology-prefixes and suffixes. Luke could quickly find prefix and suffix for the word discovery. He is aware of word roots and affixes.&nbsp;</li><li>recap parts of speech--focused on nound, verb and adjective. Luke has problem to recognize the specific categories for words. He gets frustrated about them and did not want to do any work on this. We played a ball throwing game for parts of speech and he could not recognize words. He knows about prepositions, articles and counjunctions yet he usually needs help.&nbsp;</li><li>recap sentence types and sentence structures. He has mastered sentence types yet he is very shaky at recognizing sentence structures.&nbsp;</li><li>We also did an online spelling game and he struggles with word spelling for his grade.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>Luke got frustrated and upset today because he lost one point in the game, then he went very quiet for nearly five minutes and we got back to the lesson again. He is a perfectionist.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-29 07:48:09', '2022-06-29 20:52:20'),
(2637, '2022/06/29', '07:51 am', '2', '9', 'Darcy Callaghan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-29 07:51:19', '2022-06-29 07:51:19'),
(2638, '2022/06/29', '08:47 am', '2', '3', 'Archie Smith', 'English', 'Writing - Morphology & Vocabulary', 'Accurate use of analysed words containing more than one morpheme', 'Compose sentences that demonstrate the meaning of given morphemes (word parts)', 'Will Hughes', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Started working on expanding Archie\'s vocabulary through spelling, exploring words like voyage, cellar, department etc. Archie picks the words up quite quickly, once he has been given synonyms that he does know, he can contrast them</p>', NULL, '2022-06-29 08:47:44', '2022-06-29 08:50:28'),
(2639, '2022/06/29', '11:24 am', '2', '9', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Cards 55 - 70', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>kilpatrick F1<br>OPR/WPR: 44-65. Callum is quite shaky for phonograms from 44. we will need to to focus on our spelling dictation that use these phonograms more. He is especially shaky at ew, ui, ough, and si. He cannot say certain sounds individually yet he can pronounce the words very well. He cannot say first and second sounds for ough, and he has a hard time to say the second sound of si.&nbsp;</p><p><br>new phonogram: 66-70. Callum does not know the phonograms ti.&nbsp;<br>rule review r. 29.&nbsp;</p><p>new rule； rule 14</p><p><br>SD: conceit, veil, na tion, ses sion, vi sion, spe cial. Callum is good at breaking syllables.&nbsp;</p><p><br>Sentence structures-simple sentence with SD words</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>We speed up on spelling and phonograms as Callum is about to go to college and we need to move up to academic writing coaching next term. He still need to learn all the foundations and he struggles at memorizing them.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-29 11:25:42', '2022-06-29 20:41:20'),
(2640, '2022/06/29', '03:32 pm', '2', '8', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ow ou ch ar er ir ur</td></tr><tr><td>Max was a bit silly and refused to say the sounds.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 5 6</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: boy-have</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use words in sentences. NM dictate a sentence.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Max incredibly silly today. Although he was much happier to come to tutoring and did not put on a sulk, he was distracted and actively working against his learning. During his WPR he refused to say the sounds of the phonograms, and I refused to move on before he had. In SD, he would purposefully write with silly letters (too big, too small, or with too many loops).&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-29 15:32:09', '2022-06-29 17:31:28'),
(2641, '2022/06/29', '04:25 pm', '2', '7', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-29 16:25:46', '2022-06-29 16:58:39'),
(2642, '2022/06/29', '04:33 pm', '2', '7', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Operations with fractions with different denominators.</p><ul><li>Equivalent fractions.</li><li>Mixed numbers</li><li>Improper fractions.</li><li>Graphic representation of improper fractions and mixed numbers.</li></ul><p>Kieran was present today and he explained the last concept to Jacob.&nbsp;</p><p>It\'s necessary to reinforce this one next week before starting with word problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-29 16:33:50', '2022-07-03 13:09:10'),
(2643, '2022/06/29', '05:39 pm', '2', '4', 'Callan Bartlett', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Kieran Oates', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callan had moments of inattentiveness during our lesson today. Overall, I think he learnt a lot and paid attention. I would really like him to complete the HW I have set him as I am sure he would benefit a lot from doing them.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-29 17:39:09', '2022-06-29 18:25:34'),
(2644, '2022/06/30', '07:16 am', '2', '9', 'Phoebe Webb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Will Hughes', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Not Returned', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-30 07:16:37', '2022-06-30 07:16:37'),
(2645, '2022/06/30', '07:30 am', '2', '9', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', 'Measurement', 'Choose appropriate units of measurement for length, area, volume, capacity and mass', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>In today\'s lesson, we finished our work on units of measurement.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Distance, metric system and US system.</li><li>Weight.</li><li>Volume.</li><li>Time</li><li>Temperature. Celsius, Fahrenheit and Kelvin.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Since Nate is a very curious learner, we were working not only with the International Measurement System but also with the American. Nate drew pictures of objects that can be used on each unit among, mm, cm, m, Km, inches, yards, grams, pounds, seconds, etc.</p><p>With temperature, we watch a short video clip about absolute zero and how this is relevant in measurement and also allowed us to discuss kinetic energy. Nate found that absolutely interesting. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-30 07:30:18', '2022-07-03 12:17:04'),
(2646, '2022/06/30', '08:45 am', '2', '8', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Investigate everyday situations that use integers. Locate and represent these numbers on a number line', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Using temperature James and I were looking into operations with integers.&nbsp;</p><p>We watch two video clips of the coldest place on earth and the universe. This helped us to correctly place numbers into the number line.&nbsp;</p><p>Did a short practice round of multiplications and divisions with integers.&nbsp;</p><p>Looked at rounding with decimals and taking a quiz on maths is fun. Even though the result was terrible, James and I were laughing!&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-30 08:45:39', '2022-07-03 09:33:45'),
(2647, '2022/06/30', '08:45 am', '2', '7', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Investigate everyday situations that use integers. Locate and represent these numbers on a number line', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Fiona let me know that James\' grandmother is very ill and this situation is passively impacting James. She also mentioned that this could trigger some changes in James\' tutoring.&nbsp;</p><p>I didn\'t want to give an extra concern to James, we moved to T1 and on the rolled canvas we were doing maths art. This involved letting James draw on it and perform short divisions and multiplications with integers.&nbsp;</p><p>Once he was confident using integers, we moved back to adding and subtracting by re-grouping with integers. For instance, &nbsp;-10+14+21-2-17+23 = ?&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Lesson No 7 was delivered on 23.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-30 08:45:40', '2022-07-03 09:27:53'),
(2648, '2022/06/30', '09:06 am', '2', '9', 'Connor McLaren', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today\'s lesson was about operations with fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>We were revisiting this concept as part of the learning journey. In the first part of the lesson, Connor couldn\'t remember very well how to do operations with fractions. I explained to him the “butterfly” method and then he was able to do the operations on his own.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-06-30 09:06:36', '2022-07-03 18:00:29');
INSERT INTO `attens` (`id`, `date_created`, `time`, `term`, `lesson`, `student_name`, `subject_name`, `concept_name`, `conceptDetail`, `learningActivity`, `tutor_name`, `tutor_evaluation`, `student_self`, `student_attendance`, `homework_completed`, `weekly_lesson`, `homework_assignment`, `email_school`, `comment`, `commentPrivate`, `notesAttendance`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2649, '2022/06/30', '09:43 am', '2', '8', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Rescheduled', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Eight CATCH UP (W9)</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 30 June 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #17</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>OPR: ch gu ey oo wr dge</td></tr><tr><td>Prompting with wr ey&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ey</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: run<br>2 top<br>3 red<br>4 book<br>5 sea<br>6 play</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Pip &amp; Tim \"The Shed Shop\"</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Drawing time</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>LP was a little silly when he came in (possibly because I hadn\'t seen him in so long!). Convo about his new medication and dyslexia diagnosis - \"it means I can\'t read\". EC corrected - \"your brain reads differently\". Good with PA and MA, some prompting to stay on task. Did well with phonos, only prompting on ey and wr (LP said \'ar\'). Only wrote one phono because LP rolled a dice. Was a little resistant \"I\'m bored\". Wrote a few MM words, LP was doing his \'creative\' handwriting. Only got the first couple correct. Excited to show me his reading at level 5 (!!!), so we did a Pip and Tim - \"The Shed Shop\". LP was persistent even with tricky words, and did the entire thing without my help. I was super super impressed. Finished with 5 mins drawing time.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<p>W8 lesson completed 30/6/22 - EC unwell in W8</p>', '2022-06-30 09:50:05', '2022-06-30 09:51:23'),
(2650, '2022/06/30', '03:25 pm', '2', '8', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we worked on the area and perimeter of triangles, squares and rectangles.</p><p>Sofia was more confident with the operations. However, it seems to be hard for her to understand the difference between the two ideas.&nbsp;</p><p>I explained the two concepts with a high level of detail, at the end of the lesson Sofia was able to do with more confidence the problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 8 was delivered on 23.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-30 15:25:56', '2022-07-02 21:38:33'),
