(2655, '2022/06/30', '04:21 pm', '2', '9', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-06-30 16:21:10', '2022-06-30 16:21:10'),
(2656, '2022/06/30', '04:26 pm', '2', '9', 'Chelsea Cooper', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Pathways', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Nine</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 30 June 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>CC brought in some maths homework today that\'s due tomorrow, so we spent the lesson working on this. She did an online maths program about place value, and we stopped and had some convos when she got stuck. Then we did some times tables work with CC doing a drill sheet from school. Talked through squared numbers i.e. 8x8 7x7.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-06-30 16:26:22', '2022-07-08 15:31:48'),
(2657, '2022/06/30', '04:38 pm', '2', '8', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'General Mathematics – Foundation', 'Shape and measurement', 'PLEASE SEE THE NOTES', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Since next week is the mid-year exam, today we worked on Trigonometry, particularly on Pythagoras, Trig Ratios, Cos and Sin laws.&nbsp;</p><p>I gave Finlay some work to be done during the weekend to help him to get ready for the exam.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 8 was delivered on 23.06.2022</p>', '2022-06-30 16:38:25', '2022-07-02 19:33:44'),
(2658, '2022/06/30', '04:52 pm', '2', '9', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Create algebraic expressions and evaluate them by substituting a given value for each variable', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>We got back to Sequences and Series today with Callisto and picked up where we left off with arithmetic series. We worked on finding the common difference and first term given 2 terms and also on finding which term in a sequence a given number was.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-06-30 16:52:03', '2022-06-30 18:11:57'),
(2659, '2022/06/30', '05:34 pm', '2', '8', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Quadratics', 'Expand binomial products and factorise monic quadratic expressions using a variety of strategies', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>We continued with our work on trinomials aX^2 + bX + c with a = 1</p><p>My expectations of Nicholas\' homework were higher. I thought he was doing to do better. For this reason, today we didn\'t move to the next topic as it\'s paramount the student clearly knows how to factorise quadratic trinomials.&nbsp;</p><p>In year 10 knowing this particular topic will be a huge advantage for him and as always in Educate Tutoring we want our students to achieve high goals.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 8 was delivered on 23.06.2021</p>', '2022-06-30 17:34:37', '2022-07-02 18:13:27'),
(2660, '2022/07/01', '02:35 pm', '2', '6', 'Molly  Jackson', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-01 14:35:12', '2022-07-01 14:35:12'),
(2661, '2022/07/01', '04:25 pm', '2', '9', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Challenge: fuzziness (Base word: fuzzy. Rules: 29, 17, 24). Nate won\'t know rule 24 (I don\'t think!) so instead you can get him to write the base word, fuzzy, underneath fuzziness and then ask what letter we changed the y to before adding \'ness\'. He can check his rules cheat sheet if he wants, or just tell you the rule (rather than the number)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 50-70, + additional phonograms if he asks to see them.</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: About 10 from 50-70, your pick</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Section M, page 303</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 2 5 6 17 (can ignore 12 in pie)</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: monkey-so</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Section M, page 303</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 2 5 6 17 (can ignore 12 in pie)</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: monkey-so</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>TEXT TYPES/SHORT STORY WRITING&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Review Nate\'s paragraph from last week (he is still in progress with paragraph writing -- he\'s super resistant to the idea, but getting better, so your only goal is to get him to write one. Grammar and editing can come later). Identify that it\'s a great paragraph because it is several sentences about one idea, iron ore/Minecraft.</td></tr><tr><td>Introduce to informative and narrative text types using whiteboard sorters (Nate may be able/want to do this). Maybe only put up a couple of elements for informative (main idea, topic sentence… I can\'t think of what they are off the top of my head. Just enough so that he can identify last week\'s as an informative text), and for narrative just character, setting, plot. ID text type of last week\'s paragraph.</td></tr><tr><td>Explain that this week we\'re looking at Narratives. Narratives are fictional stories -- they\'re made up &amp; they need three elements. Read Fitzroy 24 and ID the characters, setting, story, and plot. 24 might be too easy for him, I can\'t think off the top of my head where he\'d be up to! If it is too easy, you can tell him that \"yes, this one\'s quite easy, but that\'s because we\'re trying to spot the elements, not practice your reading\" or something similar.</td></tr><tr><td>Explain to Nate that now we\'re going to write his own story. Brainstorm a character, a setting, and what the character is going to do. You might do this on the whiteboard.</td></tr><tr><td>Nate needs help with story writing. He\'s refusing to do it at school. My plan was to really heavily coach him in the creation of this story. You can refer back to 24 to demonstrate structure E.g.: First, we\'re going to write a sentence that introduces our character (highlight/point to first sentence of 24, telling us the character\'s name and that he\'s a cat). Second, tell me where the character is (point to \'Hawker went to the park\'). Third, introduce the plot by having something happen (point to \'he saw a dog\').</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Took us a while to get through phonos and SD, as Nate was very chatty and EC not good at redirecting!! Nate asked if we could do phonos 26-70, and was really good with all of them. Prompting needed with ey, ch sound order, gu, igh. Fine with WPR, pretty good with SD - some confusion between rules 5 and 6, did a few less words than planned. Looked at last week\'s paragraph - NB did a good job of editing his paragraph as he read (mostly in terms of Minecraft inaccuracies!). Able to articulate that \"a paragraph is a group of sentences about the same topic that are related and which go together\". Convo about INF/NAR text types, NB wasn\'t able to tell me anything about these and kept going off on tangents, so EC redirected and prompted responses. Used the three little pigs as a model for narrative text and orally talked through elements alongisde informative. NB able to ID his paragraph as an informative and tell me why (using elements). Planned a narrative text together, and Nate quickly wrote it up as a story with EC prompting. Just told Nate that we were writing a couple of sentences - asked him to write 1 introducing characters, 2 introducing setting, then a couple more giving the beginning, middle and end of the plot. Ended up being a story without him realising! Can use this as a springboard to do more advanced work later - we very much rushed through it. We ended up going 10mins over time because Nate just kept writing! He seemed very absorbed and I didn\'t want to stop him.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-07-01 16:25:17', '2022-07-08 17:49:22'),
(2662, '2022/07/01', '05:52 pm', '2', '9', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Simplify algebraic expressions involving the four operations', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using Essential Mathematics 7, Cambridge, we worked on the language of algebra.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Quick review on the 4 parts of an algebraic term.</li><li>Definition of alike terms.</li><li>Expanding brackets 2(x-4y)</li><li>BODMAS</li><li>Simplifying algebraic expression by collecting alike terms.&nbsp;</li><li>Word problems related to the perimeter. For instance, if the perimeter of a square is 12 what is the length of each side.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Ava is progressing in his algebraic skills, she told me that in the classroom sometimes she\'s the only one who knows how to do algebraic expressions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Today\'s lesson lasted 1.5 hours.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-07-01 17:52:40', '2022-07-02 07:23:34'),
(2663, '2022/07/01', '08:59 pm', '2', '9', 'Matthew Heard', 'Mathematics', 'Chance & Data', 'Everyday chance', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Matt has moved to work on Statistics and Probability.</p><ul><li>We started the lesson by doing a review on how to calculate experimental probability.&nbsp;</li><li>Unions and intersections.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Matt and I looked at those topics aiming to understand how to describe the results of two- and three-step chance experiments, both with and without replacements, assigning probabilities to outcomes and determining probabilities of events. Investigate the concept of independence</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-01 21:00:54', '2022-07-03 19:56:12'),
(2664, '2022/07/01', '09:52 pm', '2', '8', 'Joseph Martín', 'Mathematics', 'Maths methods 3', 'Other', 'Read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Joseph told me the exam wasn\'t as hard as he thought it could be.&nbsp;</p><p>I would like to have a conservative expectation as sometimes Hobart college provides very tricky questions on those exams.&nbsp;</p><p>Today we were working with logs and exponentials; Joseph wanted to work on:</p><ul><li>solving simple equations involving logarithmic functions algebraically and graphically</li><li>using function notation, domain, range, independent and dependent variables</li><li>examining simple applications of logarithmic functions.</li></ul>', NULL, '2022-07-01 21:54:24', '2022-07-03 18:46:04'),
(2665, '2022/07/01', '10:40 pm', '2', '8', 'Nell  Brooks', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Continuing our work from last week, today\'s focus was on fractions.</p><ul><li>What is a fraction</li><li>Fractions as divisions.</li><li>Equivalent fractions using the magnets.</li><li>Adding and subtracting fractions with the same denominator.</li></ul><p>Overall, Nell did a great job today, she was fully engaged with the lesson. I could say she mastered equivalent fractions and operations with the same denominator were also easy for her.</p><p>We took 5 minutes to watch the video clip, <i>measuring the world</i> from F. Gauss. Rachel and Nell enjoyed a lot knowing his history. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 8 was delivered on 23.06.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 22:41:18', '2022-07-03 08:04:07'),
(2666, '2022/07/01', '10:41 pm', '2', '9', 'Nell  Brooks', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we worked on:</p><ul><li>Definition of factors and multiples.</li><li>Common factors.</li><li>Check on equivalent fractions.</li><li>Prime numbers.</li><li>Adding and subtracting fractions with different denominators.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Nell passed her challenge and in the spinning wheel she got, “No Homework”.</p><p>Kindly, I asked Nell to continue practising with the skip counting strategies I gave her some weeks ago. Following those will help her to perform multiplications and divisions in a short time.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 9 was delivered on 30.06.2022 - Zoom.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-07-01 22:42:05', '2022-07-03 08:14:21'),
(2667, '2022/07/01', '10:43 pm', '2', '9', 'Harlow Booy', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-01 22:44:06', '2022-07-01 22:46:50'),
(2668, '2022/07/01', '10:44 pm', '2', '8', 'Harlow Booy', 'Mathematics', 'Measurement', 'Tell time to the half-hour', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using Syllabus 3B pages 63 - 64, we worked on clockfaces. Working on this will help Harlow to create connections between additions and subtractions.&nbsp;</p><p>Also using the clock, we reviewed the times\' tables and worked a little on arrays to solve divisions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>The lesson was delivered on 24.06.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 22:45:02', '2022-07-02 12:31:24'),
(2669, '2022/07/01', '10:47 pm', '2', '9', 'Gus  Pettit', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Create algebraic expressions and evaluate them by substituting a given value for each variable', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>In the first 15 minutes of the lesson, we did some work on Essential Assessments. This was about units of measurement. This helped me to do a review on decimals, particularly on multiplications and divisions.</p><p>For the rest of the lesson, we worked on algebra;</p><ul><li>Language of algebra.</li><li>Algebraic terms.</li><li>Alike terms.</li><li>Collecting alike terms (plus and take away)</li><li>Substituting, if a=2 and b=-3 find the value of 2a+3b&nbsp;</li><li>Review on sign law and BODMAS.</li><li>Review on powers with whole numbers.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>We did an extensive round of practice problems, the majority on the whiteboard and Gus got the majority of them correctly.&nbsp;</p><p>In the last 5 minutes, I did a short quiz and played with a spinning wheel. The price was no homework and the student just hit the right place. &nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 9 lasted 1.5 hours. It was delivered on 01.07.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 22:48:24', '2022-07-02 15:58:29'),
(2670, '2022/07/01', '10:48 pm', '2', '8', 'Gus  Pettit', 'Mathematics', 'Measurement', 'Choose appropriate units of measurement for length, area, volume, capacity and mass', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Gus was way behind with his work on Essential Assessments; I communicated this with the parent and she told me that it was okay for me to help Gus with this school work. However, she will talk with the student about this and ask Gus to do this job at home. We complete 3 modules, all of them with more than 80% of correct answers.&nbsp;</p><p>Along with the work on Essential Assessments, we looked at the area and perimeter of some composite shapes. Once I provided a short explanation, Gus was able to remember most of the formulas and used them properly.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 8 lasted 1.5 hours and was delivered on 24.06.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 22:49:26', '2022-07-02 15:46:45'),
(2671, '2022/07/01', '10:48 pm', '2', '9', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>The concept of the perimeter of a square and rectangle is now easy for Sofia. She did the problems with ease and could regroup perfectly.&nbsp;</p><p>On the other hand, the concept of area is still to be covered. For 15 minutes, Sofia and I were looking at the concept of formulas. Replace letters with numbers to find the area.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 9 was delivered on 30.06.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 22:50:03', '2022-07-02 21:47:28'),
(2672, '2022/07/01', '10:49 pm', '2', '7', 'Gus  Pettit', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Nat Hankin re-scheduled the lesson to do 1.5 hours on 24.06 and 01.07.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-07-01 22:50:33', '2022-07-02 15:38:34'),
(2673, '2022/07/01', '10:54 pm', '2', '9', 'Finlay Tueno', 'Mathematics', 'OTHER', 'OTHER', 'Please read comments', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Finlay let me know that since he\'s doing level 2 and not 3 General Maths, he didn\'t have an exam. I was pushing him hard to get ready for the exam. However, doing this intensive preparation for the exam was very beneficial as Finlay could grasp some concepts which will be helpful in the short future.&nbsp;</p><p>Lesson No 9 was more relaxed, we were working on mathematical logic, solving some riddles and also working on sensory activities like doing long additions and subtraction with the left hand.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-01 22:55:54', '2022-07-02 19:40:33'),
(2674, '2022/07/01', '10:54 pm', '2', '6', 'Thomas Anderson', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Quadratics', 'Solve simple quadratic equations using a range of strategies', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>We looked at:</p><p>Factorization of quadratics.</p><ul><li>aX^2 + bX + c with a = 1</li><li>aX^2 + bX + c with a different than 1.</li><li>Difference of Perfect Squares (DOPS)</li><li>Completing the square.</li><li>Check on prime decomposition.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Overall Thomas did good work, he was able to solve DOPS almost without a problem. Once I helped him to use decomposition using prime numbers, he was able to factorise the trinomials. In the end, we worked on completing the square and despite the fact, that Tom hadn\'t worked with this, he was able to follow the process smoothly.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson number 6 was delivered on 01.07.2022</p><p>Thomas is missing 3 lessons which will be held during the winter holidays.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-07-01 22:56:08', '2022-07-02 13:42:57'),
(2675, '2022/07/01', '10:56 pm', '2', '5', 'Thomas Anderson', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Sketch linear graphs using the coordinates of two points and solve linear equations', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using Essential Mathematics Y 10-10A, pages, 26, 36, 48 and homework given on page 46.&nbsp;</p><p>We were working on:</p><ul><li>Graphing straight lines.</li><li>Finding equations of a line.</li><li>Perpendicular and parallel lines.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Overall, Thomas did a great job! He could recall easily the gradient of a line, the general equation of a line and how to re-arrange the equations. I helped him to use the intercepts to sketch the graph and also showed him visual examples how to find the perpendicular and parallel lines/equations of a linear equation.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 5 was delivered on 24.06.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 22:57:20', '2022-07-02 13:28:04'),
(2676, '2022/07/01', '10:57 pm', '2', '4', 'Thomas Anderson', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Solve linear simultaneous equations, using algebraic and graphical techniques, including using digital technology', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using Essential Mathematics Y 10-10A.</p><p>Thomas and I were working on simultaneous equations. We looked at the 3 methods to solve them, Substitution, Elimination and Graphing.&nbsp;</p><p>Overall, Tom did a great job. Even though in the beginning, he was a bit lost, with a little guidance and explicit instruction he was able to solve “At standard to Above standard” level questions on the practice round.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 4 was delivered on 17.06.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 22:58:03', '2022-07-02 13:19:34'),
(2677, '2022/07/01', '10:58 pm', '2', '3', 'Thomas Anderson', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'INEQUALITIES', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Thomas asked me to go through some inequalities I gave him for homework.&nbsp;</p><p>Some of his doubts were more about how to solve the inequation when we have brackets on both sides of the inequalities and fractions with pronumerals also, on both sides of the inequation.&nbsp;</p><p>I showed Tom how to solve that kind of problem and then he was able to solve the practice ones almost without my help.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>This was delivered through zoom on &nbsp;14.06.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 22:58:38', '2022-07-02 13:03:57'),
(2678, '2022/07/01', '11:01 pm', '2', '9', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Expand binomial products and factorise monic quadratic expressions using a variety of strategies', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Next week, I have planned to do a progress quiz with Nicholas. This activity will allow us to know how much Nicholas has improved with factorisation.&nbsp;</p><p>Today we looked at the main concepts that he would need to factorise, using common group, grouping by families, and trinomials.&nbsp;</p><p>Overall, Nicholas did good work, however, I am concerned about Nicholas mixing the techniques. when Nicholas is next to me solving the problems, he does it correctly. But, when I ask him to work independently, he makes some mistakes related to understanding and conceptualization.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson No 9 was delivered on 30.06.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 23:02:22', '2022-07-02 18:21:14'),
(2679, '2022/07/01', '11:05 pm', '2', '8', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Extend and apply the laws and properties of arithmetic to algebraic terms and expressions', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<ul><li>We worked only on expanding brackets using the multiplication and division sign law.&nbsp;</li><li>Most of the problems were made up and some were from Essential Mathematics Y 7.&nbsp;</li><li>4X( 2X/Y + 1)&nbsp;</li><li>-4( X - 2X^2)&nbsp;</li><li>Ava was getting confused sometimes with adding and subtracting integers and the sign law.&nbsp;</li><li>In the end, she understood and was doing the problems almost without my help.&nbsp;</li><li>Ava completed the challenges and no homework was given.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson delivered on 24.06.2022 through Zoom</p>', '2022-07-01 23:06:42', '2022-07-02 07:30:48'),
(2680, '2022/07/01', '11:06 pm', '2', '7', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Introduce the concept of variables as a way of representing numbers using letters', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we worked on:</p><ul><li>Introduction to algebraic terms.</li><li>Check on the sign and index law (1, 2 and 3)</li><li>Definition of alike terms.</li><li>Add and take away algebraic terms.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Overall Ava did a great job, we need to continue working on all the topics listed above. When she applies the first index law, she forgets the sign one. Having the skill to see that multiple concepts apply at a single time and also exclude others is something that we were working on in the upcoming lessons.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>Lesson delivered on 17.06.2022. The lesson lasted 1.5 hours</p>', '2022-07-01 23:07:11', '2022-07-02 07:53:45'),
(2681, '2022/07/01', '11:07 pm', '2', '6', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Extend and apply the laws and properties of arithmetic to algebraic terms and expressions', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we were working on algebraic terms.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>How we can use letters to represent numbers.</li><li>Adding and taking away algebraic terms.</li><li>Sign law.</li><li>Operations with integers.</li></ul><p>All the problems were made up and a few from Essential Mathematics Y 7.&nbsp;</p><p>It was a good lesson, despite the fact that most of the time it was only me speaking, Ava was fully engaged and her participation was amazing. During the practice problems round, she had a good level of correct answers. However, lots of practice is needed to grasp the concepts.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>This lesson was delivered on the 10.06.2022</p>', '2022-07-01 23:07:43', '2022-07-02 08:03:43'),
(2682, '2022/07/01', '11:07 pm', '2', '5', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Percentages', 'Connection between percentages, fractions and divisions', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Ava and Shannon mentioned the student is having a maths test next week and wanted to practice percentages, fractions and decimals.&nbsp;</p><p>Ava did a great job, we were solving problems with and without a calculator. Most of the time, Ava had correct answers to the word problems and when it was about only operations she did it very well.&nbsp;</p><p>We also did a quick review on operations with fractions and decimals just in case it was needed.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '<p>This lesson was delivered on 03.06.2022. Today\'s lesson lasted 1.5 hours</p>', '2022-07-01 23:08:30', '2022-07-02 08:11:06'),
