(2688, '2022/07/04', '08:45 am', '2', '9', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Nine CATCH UP (W10)</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 4 July 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #18</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>OPR: ey ew aw ea wr igh</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ey wr igh</td></tr><tr><td>Help with all phonos in WPR</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: MM: 7 lay<br>8 led<br>9 add<br>10 alike</td></tr><tr><td>SA: up to 12</td></tr><tr><td>Great sounding as he was writing. Some confusion with m/n but fixed after my prompting to take another look. Sometimes was able to ID sounds but not phono - e.g. sounded \'for\' but said \"I don\'t remember what \'or\' looks like!\"</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Wadd reading - \"colouring in\"</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Homework: holiday practice pages</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>LP \"wired\" today (mum\'s words). Seemed dysregulated. Wanted to play with paperclips and then fix them to the end of his pencil, despite me asking him to put them to the side/out of his hands as they were distracting him. So much more focused without anything in his hands to fiddle with. Got really upset when sticky tape stuck to his hand and he couldn\'t get it off - made squawking/hissing/growling noises as he flapped his hand to get the tape off. Needed prompting with almost all phonos in OPR and WPR. Very resistant to do writing, but finally agreed when I said that the rest of the lesson would be drawing time. Did sneaky SA and MM in Lewis\' workbook, and he did an awesome job, getting through heaps of words. Gave LP the last 10mins to do \'colouring in\' - i.e. Wadd reading.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<p>Lesson held in W10 - catch-up for W9 (EC unwell)</p>', '2022-07-04 08:45:07', '2022-07-04 10:06:14'),
