(2692, '2022/07/04', '03:28 pm', '2', '10', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer. Mia usually needs 30 seconds for this actitivity. She did a great job today and concentrated very well even if Thomas was not there to compete.&nbsp;</p><p><br>OPR/WPR:sh, e, s, o, n, h, th. Mia has graspped all sounds for these phonogram except th, so we &nbsp;did a multi sound ball throwing game for th.&nbsp;</p><p><br>rule review: rule 4. Mia needed help to recall rule 4 and she needed remindings for the concept of syllable. She mastered the marking for rule 4 pretty fast though.&nbsp;</p><p><br>SD: she, so, no, he, the. Mia was a little bit confused with the pronunciation for ‘the’.&nbsp;</p><p><br>online spelling game: Mia\'s spelling skill is quite good and she can recognize all the short words and needed me to read out loud for the longer words.&nbsp;</p><p><br>compose sentences using SD words.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-07-04 15:28:34', '2022-07-05 10:06:18'),
(2693, '2022/07/04', '03:31 pm', '2', '9', 'Freya McIver', 'Academic Coaching', 'Independent Study', 'School Assigned Worksheet or Assignment', 'See Notes', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>FM brought along schoolwork again today which was great. We looked at her English assignment - 3 x TEEL paragraphs, and did a bit of a revise and edit. FM structured them nicely and was able to articulate her TEEL structure. Also looked at her HASS assignment - a day in the life of an Ancient Roman patrician girl. Similar conversations about punctuation (especially commas) and revising to utilise most appropriate words for the job. Freya does really well with tasks like these - she has a great imagination!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<p>W10 catch up for missed W9 lesson due to EC illness</p>', '2022-07-04 15:31:46', '2022-07-04 17:59:00'),
(2694, '2022/07/04', '04:29 pm', '2', '10', 'Arlo Clark', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick F1<br>OPR: a, e, o, m, g, s, n, h. &nbsp;Arlo picked up all multi sounds pretty fast, except for a, e, o, s. He needed some remindings.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><p>multi sound phonogram game for a.&nbsp;</p><p>WPR: a, e, o, m, g, s, n, h. &nbsp;Arlo is a perfectionist for his handwriting and he shows lots of interest in handwriting.&nbsp;</p><p>Handwriting focus: clockface letter g.<br>&nbsp;</p><p>new rule: rue 4<br>SD: A-G words: me, go, a, so, no, he. Arlo picked this bit up quite fast yet I think we will need more practice in the future. I sent homework about rule 4 for him to practice.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><p>Spelling online game. Arlo sometimes sounds out and decode words yet he is not aware of mult letter phonograms which we will learn in the future.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-07-04 16:29:28', '2022-07-05 09:54:21'),
