(2702, '2022/07/05', '04:31 pm', '2', '10', 'Shay Douglas', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose informative paragraph', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Essay skills</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Neve\'s integrating quotes task/write a short informative paragraph (in the style of an article) using the resource(s) provided</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Read through the provided resource &amp; discuss.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Plan out an informative paragraph in response. Gave Shay some independence in terms of what aspect of the concept he wanted to write about.</td></tr><tr><td>Compose a response that includes a quote and makes use of the structure we introduced last week.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-07-05 16:31:19', '2022-07-05 17:11:26'),
(2703, '2022/07/05', '04:35 pm', '2', '10', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 70', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>We did not recieve Brock\'s mother\'s confirmation for week 10 lesson so I was not expecting Brock today yet he showed up so we had a short and review lesson today. He was in a good mood today and asked for something fun to do, so we did some assessment and reviews as well as an online spelling game.&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Morrison Macall spelling scale.Brock has moved up to section N for his spelling. His raw score was 20 and is equivalent to year 2.9, which he did in October 2021 was 2.1 and 8 years and 2 months old. From his spelling, it reflects that he needs more recap for his phonogram application in specific words which should be our focus next term.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;burt word assessment. Brock\'s reading age is between 9.11 and 10.05 which has shown a great gain.&nbsp;</li><li>spelling game: Brock needed help with spelling for words that he does not use very often even if he knows the phonograms, &nbsp;and we will need to recap this in his spelling dictation.&nbsp;</li><li>OPR 1-70. He is a bit shaky on the sounds for ei, ie, ea, ey. ew, ui.&nbsp;</li></ol>', NULL, '2022-07-05 16:35:45', '2022-07-05 17:10:24'),
(2704, '2022/07/05', '05:20 pm', '2', '6', 'Lucy Crosswell', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Kilpatrick G1</td></tr><tr><td>10/10 From Lucy -- may go up another level next lesson.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8 + e i u, 27-30 + 38</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: a g I c sh ow ou oo ch ar&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule intro: 2 &amp; 3</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Rule Page 1 -- consonants + rule 2 &amp; 3</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Cyclops and Giants with discussion and articulation</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Lucy did well at articulating Rules 2 &amp; 3 in Cyclops and Giants. She got a liiiittle shaky with her articulation as we progressed and it became more automatic for her. I think she\'s going to be a student that requires very dedicated and consistent revision of concepts in order to maintain her understanding.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-07-05 17:20:15', '2022-07-05 18:36:12'),
(2705, '2022/07/06', '08:05 am', '2', '11', 'Darcy Callaghan', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-06 08:05:08', '2022-07-06 08:05:08');
INSERT INTO `attens` (`id`, `date_created`, `time`, `term`, `lesson`, `student_name`, `subject_name`, `concept_name`, `conceptDetail`, `learningActivity`, `tutor_name`, `tutor_evaluation`, `student_self`, `student_attendance`, `homework_completed`, `weekly_lesson`, `homework_assignment`, `email_school`, `comment`, `commentPrivate`, `notesAttendance`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2706, '2022/07/06', '03:32 pm', '2', '8', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Using the Singapore Asia Education textbook 3; Jacob and I started to work on word problems with fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>Before we jumped into that topic, we did a revision on operations with fractions, the 4 of them and also equivalent fractions.&nbsp;</p><p>Jacob let me know that the questions were very confusing for him; hence, I decided to not do the problems and instead we worked with modelling. We did many pictures on the board of the same problems a couple of times to allow Jacob to understand the questions.&nbsp;</p><p>I change the situation, from examples with food, we moved to money, time etc..</p><p>In end we played the lottery a little bit, this was just to reduce the stress from fractions.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-06 15:32:41', '2022-07-08 14:16:08'),
(2707, '2022/07/06', '03:34 pm', '2', '4', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-06 15:34:07', '2022-07-06 15:34:07'),
(2708, '2022/07/06', '03:36 pm', '2', '10', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: sh th ow ou oo ch ar ay ai&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Mark these words and read R&amp;S: show touch car shark round</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: NA</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: show touch car shark round&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use above words in sentences given to MB by NM. Oral work with sentence prior to writing and ID any words we are uncertain of the spelling for. NM provide spelling on whiteboard.</td></tr><tr><td>MB read out his sentences to me. We watched a show instead of we saw a show, touched instead of touch</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency:Fitzroy 1. 63 WPM, reading a little stilted but no errors or difficulty decoding. Sent home with Fitzroys 1-5 plus a reading record.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-07-06 15:37:03', '2022-07-06 17:14:07'),
(2709, '2022/07/06', '04:28 pm', '2', '8', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-06 16:28:18', '2022-07-06 16:28:18'),
(2710, '2022/07/06', '04:42 pm', '2', '10', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Cards 31 - 45', 'Will Hughes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Phoebe did not want to work today. We managed to quickly get through her phonograms and used magnetic letters for spelling. She used three spelling words in one sentence which was good, but her ORF was not as good as last week, we will continue to work on reading as we continue through into term 3</p>', NULL, '2022-07-06 16:44:22', '2022-07-06 17:10:36'),
(2711, '2022/07/06', '05:11 pm', '2', '5', 'Archie Smith', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Will Hughes', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Archie was very switched on with his phonograms today. Had a few spelling mistakes, but also recognised where he went wrong and endeavoured to fix them up. He put together some strong complex sentences for his spelling words, and flew through ORF510 in 1.37. We will move onto ORF511 next lesson, as well as continue with our phonogram mission.</p>', NULL, '2022-07-06 17:11:42', '2022-07-06 17:13:23'),
(2712, '2022/07/07', '07:25 am', '2', '10', 'Nate Betros', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-07 07:25:55', '2022-07-07 07:25:55'),
(2713, '2022/07/07', '08:51 am', '2', '9', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Counting in groups of 3, 6, 10, 30 and 40.</p><p>Check on operations with integers -5 - 6 // -12 + 3 // -7 x 2//&nbsp;</p><p>James was very tired today and wanted to have a relaxing lesson. He has a family member very ill and Adrian told me that his mum is in Canberra because of this.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-07-07 08:51:39', '2022-07-15 11:14:47'),
(2714, '2022/07/07', '02:11 pm', '2', '7', 'Mia Harvey', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-07 14:11:12', '2022-07-07 14:11:12'),
(2715, '2022/07/07', '02:29 pm', '2', '10', 'Nell  Brooks', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'To Be Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>It was a short video about black holes, this was to engage Nell with today\'s lesson and to create an academic stimulus for the work we did.&nbsp;</p><p>We worked with operations with fractions with the same/multiple/different denominators; there is much work to be done on this as Nell forgot from a couple of weeks ago about operations with the same denominator. I\'d say that this is totally related to her low working memory; for this reason, more concrete material needs to be brought to the lessons and let her work with this as same as more visual aids.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-07-07 14:29:44', '2022-07-08 14:21:15'),
(2716, '2022/07/07', '03:24 pm', '2', '9', 'Sofia Creek', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Today we continued our work on measurement and area. This helps to see the use of maths in real-life situations.&nbsp;</p><p>At times the student struggles with multiplications and short divisions. A review of geometric techniques to solve multiplication by 2-digit numbers was shown. The aim of this is to help the student to follow a more detailed process to do multiplications.&nbsp;</p><p>We did all the problems on the whiteboard to make the lesson more dynamic, Sophia enjoys working on this a lot!&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-07 15:24:20', '2022-07-08 14:00:39'),
(2717, '2022/07/07', '03:26 pm', '2', '7', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-07 15:26:15', '2022-07-07 15:26:15'),
(2718, '2022/07/07', '03:33 pm', '2', '8', 'James  Coleman', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ellie Connor', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-07 15:33:48', '2022-07-07 15:33:48'),
(2719, '2022/07/07', '04:31 pm', '2', '8', 'Chelsea Cooper', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Ten (W8 catch up)</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 30 June 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Suffix practice page</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #20</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>OPR/WPR: kn ow or ea ear ou aw ar oo ng</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 9</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SD: Sec. K p.287 - bone, cloud, draw, drink, garden, goose, hopping, hop, knife</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>3x spelling words in sentences</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Greek Mythology book</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>EC struggling with voice/sore throat today. Chels started with a suffix morphology activity (instead of challenge word), then we did PA and MA. CC seemed to struggle a bit with the concept of \"\'did\': instead of \'id\' say \'un\'\" at first, but I rephrased and prompted, and we got there in the end.&nbsp; Powered through phonos (prompting with ow/ou, aw/ow) then CC did SD as a word analysis task. Used 3x spelling words in sentences, did 2x ORF and then played a game to finish.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<p>W8 lesson delivered in W10 as a catch up</p>', '2022-07-07 16:31:51', '2022-07-08 15:40:20'),
(2720, '2022/07/07', '04:36 pm', '2', '10', 'Nicholas Geeves', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Quadratics', 'Factorise monic and non-monic quadratic expressions and solve a wide range of quadratic equations derived from a variety of contexts', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Using problems from Essential Mathematics and the internet, Nicholas was solving a progress quiz today.&nbsp;</p><p>Topics:</p><p>Factorising common factor = 1 / 3</p><p>Factorising by grouping/common factor = 0 / 3</p><p>Factorising quadratics with 2 brackets with a=1 → 3 / 3</p><p>General operations; fractions 0/2 and percentages 2/2&nbsp;</p><p>Overall, Nicholas didn\'t have a good score. There is significant work with the index law that needs to be done one more time. Reviewing this will be helpful with common factors.&nbsp;</p><p>On the other hand, quadratics with a= 1 (aX^2 + bx + c) were not a problem; Nicholas did this part very well and my help was very little.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-07 16:36:23', '2022-07-08 14:08:52'),
(2721, '2022/07/07', '04:43 pm', '2', '10', 'Callisto Pratten', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Describe, continue, and create number patterns resulting from performing addition or subtraction', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Rosemary Beswick', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Callisto has been unwell this week and has thus been absent from school. We therefore picked up where we left off with the sequences and series work last week. We looked at arithmetic series and worked on numeric and worded problems. Callisto made a few calculation mistakes but mostly got correct answers.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-07 16:43:12', '2022-07-07 18:11:56'),
(2722, '2022/07/07', '05:12 pm', '2', '10', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Represent and solve simple addition and subtraction problems using a range of strategies', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Calculation of given monetary values, calculation of totals based on changes to place value digits. &nbsp;For example: &nbsp;What is the total monetary value of 1x 50c, 2x 20c and 4x 5c, What is the value of 700 less than 4753. &nbsp;Key Maths Measurement and Numeration tasks.</p><p>Algebra - solving for the unknown by adding or subtracting the number value from the pro-numeral. &nbsp;Eg: n+20=32 &gt; n + 20-20 = 32 - 20 = 12. &nbsp;Check with substitution: &nbsp;12 + 20 = 32.</p><p>Further practice needed with the arithmetic element of this process.</p>', NULL, '<p>Today\'s lesson was held via Zoom at family\'s request.</p>', '2022-07-07 17:12:44', '2022-07-07 17:19:20'),
(2723, '2022/07/08', '10:27 am', '2', '10', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today James and I were working on long additions and subtractions; elapsed time and 24-hour format.&nbsp;</p><p>James was having some difficulties with borrowing, we went back to some foundation bits of this process and did foundation-level problems.</p><p>We played bingo along with Adrian and Fiona, the parents were in the classroom for this activity. We had the chance to talk about the pros and cons of the lessons, the comments were this:</p><p><strong>Positive:</strong></p><p>James has improved on his maths and even though maths still being a hurdle for James, he knows how to navigate some problems.&nbsp;</p><p>Being flexible and the patient has helped James on his maths journey.&nbsp;</p><p>Allowing James to move is important, in that way he can concentrate.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Negative</strong></p><p>Don\'t do math minute maths.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-07-08 10:27:36', '2022-07-15 10:55:41'),
(2724, '2022/07/08', '10:52 am', '2', '6', 'Lottie Young', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Lottie was able to accurately complete all Mixed Level phonemic manipulations except cub to cat. &nbsp;She was quite unable to accurately substitute the sounds of the new word even with finger scaffolding.</p><p>Lottie was able to recall the partner phonograms with a high level of accuracy and automaticity, self correcting a couple of errors but recalling all ten accurately after the third review. &nbsp;She was unable to recall ew, ou, aw &nbsp;for the written review.</p><p>When recording the reference words for silent final ‘e’ on Rule Page 1, Lottie was able to articulate the jobs of silent final \'e accurately even though these concepts have not been reviewed in some time. &nbsp;</p><p>During the spelling assessments, Naomi prompted Lottie several times to sound as she wrote each word. &nbsp;Lottie was also prompted to sound out some words she had written in order to connect the sounds represented with the sounds in the given words. &nbsp;She was able to recognise her errors and self correct. For example: Lottie wrote alarve for alive. &nbsp;When she sounded out this word, she could hear the difference between what she had written and what she had been asked to write. &nbsp;She subsequently wrote the correct spelling for alive. &nbsp;</p><p>Whilst Lottie\'s accuracy score only improved five months in the past twelve, today demonstrated a significant improvement in size and legibility in her handwriting and in the quality and quantity of her attempts. &nbsp; When she last completed this assessment, Lottie recorded 36 words in total, but today she attempted 61 words. &nbsp;Errors include accurate sound but wrong phonogram, missing a double consonant, missing a silent final ‘e’ or using a silent final ‘e’ instead of a partner phonogram, or recording an accurately spelled word but the wrong homophone.</p><p>Lottie also made several reversal errors today - s x2 and b (self corrected x1 and x1 not)</p>', NULL, '<p>Last week\'s lesson was cancelled by Naomi due to covid.</p>', '2022-07-08 10:52:42', '2022-07-08 11:40:35'),
(2725, '2022/07/08', '10:53 am', '2', '6', 'Archie Lester', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete final sound in word or final blend - Kilpatrick Level I', 'Naomi Wright', 'Achieved', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Rule Page 3 - discussed single syllable for shipped and stopped due to one vowel sound only.</p><p>OPR - list as per last week. &nbsp;No WPR today.</p><p>Review nouns of direct address, appositives and speaker tag elements in sentences previously recorded x6. &nbsp;</p><p>Use firm as a noun in a compound sentence, and use burn as a noun in a complex sentence. &nbsp;Identify elements of each structure and the parts of speech different words represented in each. &nbsp;Conversation needed re firm as a noun (a business, company or large organisation). &nbsp;Identify a noun by placing the/a/an in front.</p><p>Begin highlighting key words in practicing and assessing comprehension passage. &nbsp;After each sentence, take key words and reformat text into own words - first four sentences so far. &nbsp;Complete this passage next lesson.</p>', NULL, '<p>Last week\'s lesson was cancelled by Naomi due to covid.</p>', '2022-07-08 10:53:08', '2022-07-08 12:07:40'),
(2726, '2022/07/08', '01:38 pm', '2', '10', 'Gus  Pettit', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Game', 'Ivan Botero', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>As per the parent\'s request; today\'s lesson had an extra component of games.&nbsp;</p><p>After doing 2 modules on Essential Assessments on Measurement and Introduction to Algebra; Gus and I were playing Mario Kart.&nbsp;</p><p>Gus scored 75% and 80% in each module and questions around operations with algebraic terms were solved.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-08 13:38:49', '2022-07-08 13:43:15'),
(2727, '2022/07/08', '03:24 pm', '2', '9', 'Harlow Booy', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-08 15:24:17', '2022-07-08 15:24:17'),
(2728, '2022/07/08', '03:38 pm', '2', '8', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-08 15:38:10', '2022-07-08 15:38:10'),
(2729, '2022/07/08', '03:38 pm', '2', '9', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-07-08 15:38:10', '2022-07-08 15:38:10'),
(2730, '2022/07/08', '03:41 pm', '2', '6', 'Chelsea Cooper', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Spelling Assessment for Ayres Placement', 'Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment - List 5', 'Ellie Connor', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Six</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 9 June 2022</td></tr><tr><td>ASSESSMENTS (WH relief)</td></tr><tr><td>PA (F1 exercise 8), MA (18) attached. OPR &amp; WPR assessments (all 70), SA spelling, Wadd reading. Finish with a game (and feel free to have a game break between assessments).</td></tr><tr><td>CC SASA is the same. WPR gone backwards by 1. WD Reading has improved 18 months in 6 months.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<p>Lesson delivered 9 June 2022 by WH (EC on leave)</p>', '2022-07-08 15:41:48', '2022-07-08 15:43:06'),
(2731, '2022/07/08', '04:50 pm', '2', '10', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR:45-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ea aw au ed z ew ui igh oa gu ey ei ie dge si</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Prompted Nate to take a second look at: told (wanted to use oo, ou, prompted him to think about his vowels), hope (again, prompted him to think about single letter phonograms), push (again, vowels), few (Nate wrote fue, prompted for phonograms), wire (kinda) truly&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Broke into syllables: consider, complete. Gave Nate some time to think about complete (not notably, I just didn\'t move onto the next word) and with that&nbsp; extra thinking time he realised independently that he needed to add the SFe.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Receipt: \"I\'m gonna give it a c because the c can make the s sound.\"</td></tr><tr><td>Raw score 19 = 8.10, +5 that I assisted with or prompted Nate for (see above) bumps him up to 24 = 9.8. Nate\'s CA is 9.8.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-07-08 16:52:07', '2022-07-08 17:43:26'),
(2734, '2022/07/11', '09:31 am', '2', '10', 'Ava Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Extend and apply the laws and properties of arithmetic to algebraic terms and expressions', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Progress Quiz.</p><p>The four operations with algebra. Year 8 Mathematics Practice Tests, Excel.&nbsp;</p><p>Overall, Ava needs to keep working on additions and subtractions with algebraic terms. She constantly gets confused with multiplications/divisions and additions/subtractions of alike terms. If the terms are different, she doesn\'t struggle to complete the questions.&nbsp;</p><p>It is important to mention that Ava and I are using the year 8 textbook, this is to get her ahead in terms of understanding and also to keep class participation. Even though she sometimes complains about the level is too difficult, with the right prompts she can solve the problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-11 09:33:00', '2022-07-11 09:41:32'),
(2735, '2022/07/11', '09:42 am', '2', '10', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', 'Assessment', 'Waddington module', 'Module 15 - 29', 'Ivan Botero', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Waddington Module 27 = 94%</p><p>Mental Computation = Facts to 144, Additions 70% - Subtraction 55% - Multiplications 45% - Divisions 100%</p><p>Archie did a terrific job on his assessment; in the upcoming weeks, a review on volume would need to be done.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-11 09:42:46', '2022-07-11 10:06:27'),
(2736, '2022/07/11', '10:56 am', '2', '10', 'Luca Mignanelli', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Solve problems involving all four operations with whole numbers', 'Text Book - Exercises, Questions and Activities', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Today we did a revision, we used Singapore Asia Education 4. Revision 1.</p><p>Luca understands well the concepts and knows the concepts related to factors, multiples, common factors and multiples, along with supplementary and complementary angles.</p><p>However, at times, Luca struggles with word problems related to the concepts listed above; he tends to use a long way to solve the word problems.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-11 10:56:52', '2022-07-11 14:22:05'),
(2737, '2022/07/11', '02:22 pm', '2', '9', 'Jett  Knighton', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>The student didn\'t show up. I called Kyra and she texted back informing me that Jett knew about the lesson and didn\'t pick the phone up.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-07-11 14:22:55', '2022-07-11 14:25:53'),
(2738, '2022/07/11', '02:37 pm', '2', '9', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', 'Pythagoras and Trigonometry', 'Trig ratios SOH CAH TOA', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Today we worked on:</p><p>Solve right-angled triangle problems including those involving direction and angles of elevation and depression.&nbsp;</p><p>Isaac and I solved about 10 problems on the whiteboard. The student created the questions to be solved and I asked him to use the information to find a particular triangle length, Adj, Opp or Hyp. Also, we did problems where we needed to find the angle and others to review the application of Pythagoras.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-11 14:37:12', '2022-07-14 13:59:12'),
(2739, '2022/07/12', '12:57 pm', '2', '9', 'Cara Lashmar', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'To Be Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Cara has covid. Lesson scheduled for Week 10. Laree Ill rescheduled for Term 3</p>', NULL, '2022-07-12 12:57:38', '2022-07-12 12:59:20'),
(2740, '2022/07/14', '01:43 pm', '2', '8', 'Thomas Anderson', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Quadratics', 'Solve simple quadratic equations using a range of strategies', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'Not Yet', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<ul><li>Solve simple quadratic equations using a range of strategies.</li><li>Expand binomial products and factorise monic quadratic expressions using a variety of strategies.</li></ul><p>Thomas and I did a review on quadratics, factorisation, DOPS, Complete the square, and common factors.&nbsp;</p><p>The student did a great job and is improving. However, Thomas sometimes takes a long time to solve quadratic equations. He needs to practice more on this.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-07-14 13:44:38', '2022-07-14 13:51:23'),
(2741, '2022/07/14', '01:44 pm', '2', '7', 'Thomas Anderson', 'Mathematics', 'Patterns & Algebra', 'Quadratics', 'Solve simple quadratic equations using a range of strategies', 'Ivan Botero', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Please see notes on lesson 8. Today we had a 2 hours lesson.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-07-14 13:45:11', '2022-07-14 13:46:47'),
(2743, '2022/07/15', '10:01 am', '2', '2', 'Harriet Van Der Laan', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Will Hughes', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Harriet Van Der Laan Lesson Plan 15/07/22</strong></p><p>Morrison McCall Spelling</p><p>PAST</p><p>OPR/WPR: a, e, i, o, u</p><p>Handwriting: Aa</p><p>Donah #1</p><p>ORF Kindergarten Fluency Book 8, Week 17, Day 1</p><p>Harriet struggled with the third sound of ‘u’, but once it was put into words she started to get it. Harriet is very eager to learn, but is behind in both spelling and reading. I have told her mum what levels she is at, and am happy to work with her. Harriet enjoys spelling and handwriting, and is always well behaved.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-07-15 10:01:42', '2022-07-15 10:03:53'),
(2744, '2022/07/21', '09:55 am', '2', '8', 'Jacob Tipping', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Operations with fractions', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Ivan Botero', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Jacob and I were working on:</p><ul><li>Extended review of fractions, including operations with the same and different denominators.</li><li>Concept of improper fractions.</li><li>Multiplications with decimals.&nbsp;</li><li>Briefly worked on word problems with fractions.</li><li>Mentioned integers.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>The student wasn\'t showing confidence in his answers, Jacob struggled to recall how to perform operations with fractions, and to understand the concept of improper fractions and mixed numbers.&nbsp;</p><p>Jacobs needs a lot of practice on fractions before going ahead with percentages and decimals.&nbsp;</p>', '<p>Lesson lasted 1.5 hours.&nbsp;</p>', '2022-07-21 09:55:14', '2022-07-21 11:59:30'),
(2746, '2022/07/25', '09:55 am', '3', '1', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week One</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 25 July 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Continue PAST</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: i o ey ed ck th ch</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: o</td></tr><tr><td>Intro rule 19</td></tr><tr><td>Recap vowels vs. consonants again before covering r.19. Rocketdog roll &amp; cover game</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>CVC game</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Cont. with hol bundle (+ EC prep resource pack)</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>LP did a great job today. A little wobbly perhaps to start, especially as he was struggling with some of the PAST activities (dropping a consonant from a consonant blend). Needed prompting with first sound of ey, and with o in OPR. Intro of rule 19, LP did well but was a little disengaged - typically struggles with just sitting and listening while I use the board to explain something. He picked up what I was saying, though, and we had a good convo about vowels and consonants. Did Rocketdog roll &amp; cover game, Lewis did an amazing job of sounding out words and persevering even when they were difficult. Only needed some prompting/a reminder of i/o saying their name and help with b/d in some words. Finished with CVC game at Lewis\' request. Convo with Alysia about two sessions a week and EC observing some of Lewis\' school literacy sessions.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week One</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 25 July 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-07-25 09:56:14', '2022-09-17 16:21:40'),
