(2767, '2022/07/27', '10:56 am', '3', '1', 'Esther Mclver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3 W1&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR&nbsp; ng th ai ay I o e a u y er ir ur wor ear or&nbsp; &nbsp;our qu ti ci si s z c g&nbsp;</p><p>WPR ng th ay a y s z er or qu ti e c</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Next week formally add 4th sound to O</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule Review:&nbsp;</p><p>Re play 4 18</p><p>Na tion 4 14&nbsp;</p><p>Cecil 26 2 &nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Next week establish Rule 14 and do rule page.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sect N yesterday among quest question doctor size December dozen there tax number&nbsp;</p><p>Identify POS.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Complex sentences model with blocks –&nbsp;</p><p>Practice verbal sentences using Card 20 with examples of independent and dependent clauses.&nbsp;</p><p>Practice verbally IC + DC</p><p>Practice reversing.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Essie picked this up very quickly.</p><p>Focus – language: subbie, IC, DC, POS.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading – OF 112 N 1 min 0 errors, 2 sc, 97/97 words</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW&nbsp; worksheet 1 Complex sentences plus Word analysis for Rules 4/26</p>', NULL, '2022-07-27 10:57:49', '2022-07-27 11:00:41'),
(2768, '2022/07/27', '11:01 am', '3', '1', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 70', 'Laree Thorsby', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3 W1&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR&nbsp; 1-70 in random order + gh&nbsp;</p><p>NW focus au aw ti ci si ough gn gu o ew ui&nbsp;</p><p>WPR o ar th ough ou aw au ee ng r&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>NW Add 4th sound to O</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sect H &nbsp;has some (sum) …………</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Simple sentences model with blocks –&nbsp;</p><p>Practice verbal sentences using manipulatives as cues.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Focus – language: subject noun, verb, object noun plus adjectives, capital. Full stop.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Write one sentence in workbook following the model.&nbsp;</p><p>Andrew enjoyed using the blocks although slightly distracted by wanting to build with them.&nbsp;</p><p>Was able to verbally produce correct simple sentences following the model.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule practice: GAME&nbsp;</p><p>Rule 4 connect 4 – Andrew can consistently articulate this rule.&nbsp;</p><p>Next week Rule 5 intro to our game board&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW&nbsp; construct three simple sentences following the model in his book.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-07-27 11:02:26', '2022-07-27 11:29:26'),
