(2774, '2022/07/27', '03:31 pm', '3', '1', 'Jimmy Fitzgerald', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<ul><li>Romeo &amp; Juliet<br><br><ul><li>Summary<br>Preliminary Analysis<br>Cinematic Techniques<br>Baz Luhrmann - Scene Summary &amp; Analysis</li></ul></li></ul>', '2022-07-27 15:31:57', '2022-09-30 15:21:04'),
(2775, '2022/07/27', '03:32 pm', '3', '1', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3 W1</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR</p><p>Vowels + ng ed sh ti ci si ck k j dge c g&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review sort Rule 9/10/11/24 words</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD: Sect Q from Dew&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>In class – Mind map on board.</p><p>FIFA World Cup 2022</p><p>What is it?</p><p>When is it?</p><p>Where is it?</p><p>Which countries are involved?</p><p>How many teams?</p><p>Can any team join?</p><p>How does qualifying work?</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Choose your favourite &nbsp;team -?????</p><p>How many matches does ??????? play to qualify?</p><p>Who are their opponents?</p><p>Where are their games played?</p><p>How many games do they need to win to play in the WC?</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW Worksheet&nbsp;</p><p>Choose your favourite player?</p><p>Use the WWWWWWH questions to write a paragraph about your player.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Plan</strong> your writing.</p><p><strong>Compose</strong> a draft.</p><p><strong>Revise&nbsp;</strong>your draft.</p><p><strong>Edit</strong> your draft.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading OF&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW – complete worksheet</p><p>Reading.</p>', NULL, '2022-07-27 15:32:22', '2022-08-02 10:17:44'),
(2776, '2022/07/27', '03:32 pm', '3', '1', 'Phoebe Webb', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Will Hughes', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Phoebe Webb Lesson Plan 27/7/22</strong></p><p>Kilpatrick level i1 no.3 and 4</p><p>Handwriting: Gg</p><p>OPR/WPR: ai, oo, ee, ch, ay, oi.&nbsp;</p><p>Review rule 7 job 4 every syllable must have a vowel&nbsp;</p><p>Became, by, be, today</p><p>SD: paint, pool, three, child, play, oil, tooth, teeth, day, yes</p><p>3 Sentences</p><p>Donah #4</p><p>ORF-201 (folder)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Phoebe needs to work on K, m, n, q, g, l, r handwriting. Phoebe enjoyed doing phonograms and spelling words to a song. Wrote a good sentence using SD words. Phoebe got a bit carried away on the singing part, but nonetheless she got the job that she needed to get done, done. Phoebe very confident with Kilpatrick. Didn’t get around to Donah, but Phoebe read Billie B Brown and seemed to enjoy it.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-07-27 15:32:45', '2022-07-29 15:41:55'),
(2777, '2022/07/27', '04:26 pm', '3', '1', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: igh dge ow ou ea au ew ui aw ed si ti ough ie ei</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 14 2 11</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: circular-office</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ayres words in variety sentence type and&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ORF conversation -- read at reading level (600s) even though it\'s difficult? Will require Angus to slow down and take time. Also explain why I want him reading these: so he sees the words from his test in his reading, and so his brain can then match up what it creates based on phonics with \'that doesn\'t quite look right\'.</td></tr><tr><td>Comp: Key into inference shorter paragraph activities. Successful, especially when contrasted with the longer texts we have tried to look at. Mihgt go up to working with slightly longer ones and try to identify at what level Angus starts havign difficulty.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-07-27 16:26:21', '2022-08-03 17:18:12'),
