(2808, '2022/08/01', '03:35 pm', '3', '1', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Madeleine Foster', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-01 15:35:30', '2022-08-01 15:35:30'),
(2809, '2022/08/01', '03:37 pm', '3', '2', 'Elsa Clennet', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: H1</td></tr><tr><td>10/10!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR:27-50</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ea igh ed ou er th ck or ear au sh</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 28 4 6 12 25</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: frightened-niece</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ayres words in sentences and identify sentence structure. Also had Elsa go back through and revise/edit her spelling.</td></tr><tr><td>Writing Process: Go through plan and arrange/number points in a logical order. Compose first draft of informative text, using plan from last week.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Elsa proclaimed herself extremely tired today, but she did just as well as usual despite getting a little muddled in some places.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Elsa needed very little help with her informative text.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-01 15:37:53', '2022-08-01 16:30:39'),
(2810, '2022/08/01', '04:02 pm', '3', '2', 'Luna Shapiro', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick G2</td></tr><tr><td>Luna found these activities really difficult and needed to break them into onset and rime</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Handwriting features -- recap</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>OPR: 1-8 + 27-38</td></tr><tr><td>WPR:&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>HF: 2 o\'clock letters</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SD: A-G</td></tr><tr><td>With focus on handwriting and sound symbol connection rather than rules.</td></tr><tr><td>If Luna wants: make words/sentence with magnet letters</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr><tr><td>Luna had trouble remembering the&nbsp; sound a letter was making (do(1) for do, go(1) for go) but otherwise I was very impressed with her behaviour throughout.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luna and I did really well today! She was eager for games (as always) but she responded really well when I removed a game and told her she could have it back if she stayed focused for her next job.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>She did extremely well with the promise of a game, and we actually got through WPR and SD without difficulty or resistance from her. She did an amazing job! She listened well and applied all her handwriting knowledge.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-01 16:03:22', '2022-08-01 16:24:12'),
(2811, '2022/08/01', '04:32 pm', '3', '1', 'Angus Singleton', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-01 16:32:29', '2022-08-01 16:32:29'),
(2812, '2022/08/01', '04:35 pm', '3', '2', 'Arlo Clark', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Arlo usually can focus on our session very well as long as we have a small break in between the session. Kilpatrick F. Arlo sometimes has problems to catch the final sounds.&nbsp;</p><p>OPR: 1-31. Arlo is a bit shaky for multiple sounds phonograms such as o, u, a, e, i, y, ou, ow, th. He struggles with the sound th which usually sounds like f when he says it.&nbsp;<br>WPR: rule 1. We learned a new rule today and Arlo grasped it very well. He still gets confused with the formation of z and p, but he usually can self correct.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><p>morphology activity 1. Arlo is quite good at recognizing words in compound words and he can manipulate compound words very well.</p><p>SD: &nbsp;man, ten tan tin ton bed top<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-01 16:35:52', '2022-08-01 17:43:53'),
(2813, '2022/08/01', '04:35 pm', '3', '2', 'Arki Young', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 50-70 (shuffled)</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ti ea dge gu ough oe igh kn si ui&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 20 4 14</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: mixture-steal</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Great questions from Arki. We ran into trouble with \"ture\" with Arki wanting to mark it with the silent final e as job five and underline ur. Arki thought I had marked it like that with him before, but I don\'t remember and can\'t find any evidence in his book. However, Arki obviously retained that information (whether given to him by me or a connection he made himself), which is the goal, so I\'m in two minds about it. We marked it Arki\'s way today but I may fix it up.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Compose a complex sentence using Ayres words.Had to recap complex sentences at Arki\'s request. Talked about conjunctions and the words subordinating vs co-ordinating (subordinate = lower/lesser = I/D, co-ordinating = equal = I/I).</td></tr><tr><td>Writing Process: Plan Arki\'s informative paragraph in the way he prefers.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-01 16:36:12', '2022-08-01 17:31:16'),
(2814, '2022/08/02', '10:20 am', '3', '1', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Syllables', 'Syllable Types - Open and Closed', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'Followup', NULL, '<p>Spelling lesson</p><ol><li>Focus on syllabifying words and recognising open and closed syllables and therefore long and short vowel sounds.&nbsp;</li><li>when to use c/k/ck; j/dge/g; tch/ch</li><li>Review rules 9/10/11 /24 when adding suffixes. sorting/connect 4</li></ol><p>Xavier was able to choose the correct end sounds when working in isolation. during sentence dictation activity he made 2 errors with j/dge and ck/k. &nbsp;</p><p>NW 5 spelling words &amp; short &nbsp;sentence dictation for sounds of ck &amp; dge + rules 9/10/11 /24</p><p>This will encourage Xavier to think quickly within the framework of each skill.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-02 10:21:33', '2022-08-02 10:31:34'),
(2815, '2022/08/02', '10:31 am', '3', '1', 'Matthew Heard', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-02 10:31:08', '2022-08-02 10:31:08');
INSERT INTO `attens` (`id`, `date_created`, `time`, `term`, `lesson`, `student_name`, `subject_name`, `concept_name`, `conceptDetail`, `learningActivity`, `tutor_name`, `tutor_evaluation`, `student_self`, `student_attendance`, `homework_completed`, `weekly_lesson`, `homework_assignment`, `email_school`, `comment`, `commentPrivate`, `notesAttendance`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(2816, '2022/08/02', '10:51 am', '3', '2', 'Henry  Badock', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Recognise and represent multiplication as repeated addition, groups and arrays', 'Game', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3W2</p><ol><li>Mental Computation - Addition facts to 30. Henry improving with accuracy although reluctant to check his work.&nbsp;</li><li>Multiplication - use dot frames&nbsp;</li></ol><p>a) estimate</p><p>b) count the dots in a row &nbsp;eg 5</p><p>c) count the dots in a column eg 3</p><p>d) record as addition 5+5+5 = 15</p><p>e) record as groups of or lots of 3 x 5 = 15</p><p>f) turn dot frame 90 degrees and repeat 3+3+3+3+3 = 15 and 5 x 3 = 15</p><p>3. Create a 100 frame using dice &nbsp;(1-10 also using friends of 10 and mental computation as part of the game.&nbsp;</p><p>Take turns rolling dice, place dots in boxes eg 6. Score a point when complete a row or column of 10.&nbsp;</p><p>Henry loved this activity so we repeated with 8 x 10 and 6 x10 using language associated with multiplication</p><p>4. Pirate Pete using 10 x&nbsp;</p><p>roll 1-10 dice write answer on worksheet. Highest/lowest stabs pete.&nbsp;</p><p>Henry able to multiply by 10 as he recognises the pattern - add a zero.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-02 10:51:51', '2022-08-02 11:19:06'),
(2817, '2022/08/02', '03:28 pm', '3', '1', 'Sebastian Bowerman', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-02 15:28:55', '2022-08-02 15:28:55'),
(2818, '2022/08/02', '03:32 pm', '3', '2', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - Precisely say, write and read words in Section N', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Today\'s session was great with Brock as we made it easier and more relaxing during our learning session. Brock really liked the online Noun Game on my laptop and it was a great way for him to focus on parts of speech and absorb the concept.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;Kilpatrick H1</p><p>OPR/WPR: e, x, c, au, a, u, s, i, dge. He has mastered all these phonograms.&nbsp;<br><br><br>Rule review rule2, 20, 23. It was easier to print out the rule overview sheet for Brock\'s reference as we discussed and recapped rules. He usually can understand the rules but not the numbers.&nbsp;</p><p>SD: ex cept, aunt, ant, capture, else, bridge &nbsp; &nbsp; Brock wrote exsept which shows that he has not graspped rule 20.&nbsp;<br>read for spelling<br>read for reading&nbsp;</p><p>online noun game. He loved this and we will continue this routine for all parts of speech.&nbsp;<br>Writing: All About My Monster-Planning and first drafting.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-02 15:32:08', '2022-08-02 16:36:51'),
(2819, '2022/08/02', '03:33 pm', '3', '2', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-50</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ou ea ch er ay ow&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 26 4 6</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: God-study</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: ORF 410. Sent home for homework.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Talked to Sophie about precise pronunciation (demonstrated with a video of the Queen) and touched on some common errors she makes (namely, sounding out but incorrectly writing the symbols). She ducked out of cursive writing during spelling but I chose not to point it out to her just to see how she went. I didn\'t notice too much of a difference.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-02 15:33:52', '2022-08-09 17:01:50'),
(2820, '2022/08/02', '04:27 pm', '3', '2', 'Lachlan Prior', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-02 16:27:09', '2022-08-02 16:27:09'),
(2821, '2022/08/02', '04:32 pm', '3', '2', 'Shay Douglas', 'Mathematics', 'Linear & Non-Linear Relationships', 'Linear & Non-linear equations', 'School-assigned worksheet/task', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Maths</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Maths Exam Revision</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Area of focus: linear relations, since this is an area that Shay didn\'t score so well in on his last test.</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Work through provided practice test.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-02 16:32:36', '2022-08-09 17:06:02'),
(2822, '2022/08/02', '04:34 pm', '3', '2', 'Andrew Allan', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR&nbsp; vowels er x5 s ough oo ow ou ed ng ti si ci sh th or</p><p>WPR vowels er x5 s ough oo ow ou ed ng ti si ci sh th or</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>NW focus au aw ti ci si ough gn gu o ew ui</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sect H&nbsp; them other fell baby rules 4/6/17 intro&nbsp;</p><p>Oppositional today. Refusing to annotate correctly.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Simple sentences model with blocks –&nbsp;</p><p>Practice verbal sentences using manipulatives as cues.&nbsp;</p><p>Compound sentences model with blocks</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Focus – language: subject noun, verb, object noun plus adjectives, capital. Full stop. FANBOYS – Andrew familiar with these.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Write one sentence in workbook following the model.&nbsp;</p><p>Andrew enjoyed using the blocks although slightly distracted by wanting to build with them.&nbsp;</p><p>Was able to verbally produce correct simple sentences following the model, and could complete a compound sentence when given the first simple sentence and FANBOYS</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading OF 101 as practice Assess 102 next week.&nbsp;</p><p>Rule practice: GAME&nbsp;</p><p>Rule 4 connect 4/5 &nbsp;– Andrew can consistently articulate this rule.&nbsp;</p><p>Rule 5 intro to our game board caused Andrew much distress. Verbalised he did not like change and wanted to return to the original version.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW&nbsp; construct 2 compound sentences following the model in his book.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-02 16:34:29', '2022-08-02 17:58:46'),
(2823, '2022/08/02', '04:36 pm', '3', '2', 'Callum Coulson', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Yina Peng', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-02 16:37:30', '2022-08-02 16:37:30'),
(2824, '2022/08/02', '05:24 pm', '3', '2', 'Lucy Crosswell', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Write sentences.</td></tr><tr><td>I\'m really excited for Monty\'s birthday. I like flowers.</td></tr><tr><td>excited as itsitin</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8 + 27-43</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ow ar a c g ou oo ch sh th&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Difficulty with: oo ow a ch&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule intro: 17</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Review: 4</td></tr><tr><td>SD: bed-will</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Compose sentences with Ayres words.</td></tr><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Show SBB. Recap that every sentence needs a subject and action (point to respective SBB in box). NM: \"Here is the block that represents th subject noun. Here the block that represents the word. Here are the blocks that represent the capital letter and full stop\". Compose written sentences, modelling and coaching, and point to the block when saying the relevant word.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Really struggled with teaching Lucy the rules. She seemed to get Rule 17, but then as we looked back at Rule 4, she said \"so now we have to cross these out and put rule 17\".&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>\"The rules are annoying because there\'s so many of them.\" Lots of rules = a bit hard to remember them.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-02 17:24:07', '2022-08-09 18:11:17'),
(2825, '2022/08/02', '05:25 pm', '3', '1', 'Isaac Ellis', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-02 17:25:33', '2022-08-02 17:25:33'),
(2826, '2022/08/02', '05:45 pm', '3', '2', 'Esther Mclver', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 11: Drop the silent final \'e\' when adding a vowel ending/suffix', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3 W2&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR&nbsp; vowels + ee ou ow ck ed ng ch er th si ti ci ea&nbsp;</p><p>WPR ea ee th ck ch o er ow ou &nbsp;o(4)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>formally added 4th sound to O</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule Review:&nbsp;</p><p>No vember 26/4</p><p>Wake</p><p>Waking 11</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Sect N October reason fifth baking bake bowl cheap cheerful chicken&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Next week establish Rule 11 and do rule page.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Complex sentences model with blocks –&nbsp;</p><p>Practice verbal sentences when given a DC</p><p>Practice verbally IC + DC</p><p>Practice reversing.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Essie picked this up very quickly.</p><p>Focus – language: subbie, IC, DC, POS.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading – OF 112 N 1 min 0 errors, 0 sc, 97/97 words</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW&nbsp; Sentences Complex &nbsp;- language of and examples.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-02 17:46:11', '2022-08-02 17:47:59'),
(2827, '2022/08/03', '07:49 am', '3', '2', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Cards 55 - 70', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Luke was in a great modd this morning. It could be because we had a lot of fun in our last learning session and he was excited for his session today as he can then play the ball game with me.. He still showed some anxiety and had an uneasy time to sit down and focus on tasks. That\'s why he spelt words wrong(decteter &amp; eny &amp; havent).</p><p>PA: Kilpatrick&nbsp;<br>i</p><p>OPR/WPR: s, e, j, oy, aw f, u, l. Luke has mastered these other than a bit shaky on u.&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review: 22 &nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p>SD: spend, en joy, awful, awe. Luke needed confirmation about aw in the words awful and awe.&nbsp;<br>Read R&amp;S<br>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.<br>finish world map puzzle<br>writing: reply callum and find a noun and a coumpound sentence.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-03 07:50:08', '2022-08-03 09:02:09'),
