(2846, '2022/08/04', '03:37 pm', '3', '2', 'James  Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 4 August 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #28</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: x c dge ie gn wr ti eigh ci kn si</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 20, 2, 23, 29</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Start Sec. N - except, aunt, ant, capture, else, bridge, offer, suffer</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Start \"The Midnight Gang\"</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Really tired - did a phono treasure hunt after OPR as James was looking very floppy and sleepy. Not at all stoked, had to prompt him throughout the lesson to keep him engaged. Struggled with most phonos, especially prompts. Need to come back to sounds of ie, wr, ti/ci/si, eigh. Pretty good with rules, fine with SD but reluctant to offer markings/rules/thoughts today. James was obviously a little disengaged and tired, and didn\'t have a lot to contribute - lots of prompting/scaffolding needed. Finished with a chapter of \"The Midnight Gang\", which James seemed to enjoy.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 4 August 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-08-04 15:37:14', '2022-09-17 12:37:14'),
(2847, '2022/08/04', '03:47 pm', '3', '2', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 100', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Tardy', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Lucy displayed a strong performance on the subtraction component of the Mad Minute Maths (Facts to 100) task today - evidence of the skills she has gained throughout her tutorial program. &nbsp;Focus going forward will be to develop addition strategies particularly for bridging tens.</p><p>Lucy was asked to articulate her thinking around the values she selected for placement on the given number line last lesson as a means of consolidating her thinking around this skill and to recognise a couple of errors that were made. &nbsp;This was initially challenging for Lucy, yet a visibly beneficial process as she was able to clearly communicate her thinking after a model and several practices.</p><p>Lucy feels uncomfortable with the conversion of cm &gt; m and requires some practice to consolidate this learning and to routinely check the units required of given tasks. &nbsp;Again, Lucy made notable gains during this lesson and was able to complete the final task independently. &nbsp;I have encouraged her to continue with this practice at home as soon as possible and do to so for short periods of time and often in order to consolidate today\'s gains. &nbsp;This is turn will build her confidence.</p>', NULL, '<p>Traffic on Outlet slow - lesson began 3:45+ and ended 4:55.</p>', '2022-08-04 15:47:46', '2022-08-04 17:47:19'),
(2848, '2022/08/04', '04:25 pm', '3', '2', 'Finn Mackey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<ol><li>Quick spell check of suffix rules from last week</li><li>REview of rules via game</li><li>Narrative Writing Task - focus on planning in a different manner so the story builds itself.</li></ol><p>1.Sizzling sentence starter using a spelling word.</p><p>2. Concluding sentence using a spelling word</p><p>These give Finn the framework to build a story around without the need for a lot of unproductive thinking time.</p><p>3. Two characters names and one adjective to describe their characteristics or personaility.</p><p>4. A setting.</p><p>Homework - write the middle.</p><p>Next week do similar but have prepped the above and pick at random from a hat!!!</p>', NULL, '2022-08-04 16:25:41', '2022-08-05 09:40:25'),
(2849, '2022/08/04', '04:29 pm', '3', '2', 'Chelsea Cooper', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 4 August 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #27</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: x c dge ie gn wr ti eigh ci kn si</td></tr><tr><td>Struggled with all, but primarily dge, ie, eigh, ti/ci/si, wr cues for gn/kn</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 20, 2, 23, 29</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Start Sec. N - except, aunt, ant, capture, else, bridge, offer, suffer</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Convo to start about why we need to do PA - talked about hearing sounds and connecting sounds with symbols. Chels really struggled with PA again today, but did well with MA - understanding morphemes and associated language well. Struggled and needed prompting with almost all phonograms. Pretty good with rules in review, but working a little slower today than normal. Need to come back and review rule 23, CC not retaining \'dge\' sound and associated rule. Chels used four words in sentences then we finished by reading part of a Horrible Histories book. Sent home a ti/ci/si drill page for homework, will develop home support pack.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 4 August 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-08-04 16:29:05', '2022-09-17 12:54:45'),
