(2868, '2022/08/08', '10:18 am', '3', '3', 'Harriet Van Der Laan', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Will Hughes', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>HVDL 8/8/22</strong></p><p>Kilpatrick D1 in folder</p><p>OPR/WPR: g, qu, s, c, r, t, v, w, x, z</p><p>Handwriting: Ee</p><p>Review rule 2 ‘c’ says ‘s’ when followed by an e, y, i</p><p>Review Rule 7 job 1</p><p>Introduce Rule 3: ‘g’ may say ‘j’ when followed by ‘e’, ‘I’ or ‘y’, but not always</p><p>Germ, ginger, gym</p><p>Get, girl, give</p><p>SD: man, charge, child, play, bird, cool, now, top, ten, tan, tin</p><p>Kindergarten Fluency Book 8, week 17, days 3 and 4 (in folder).</p><p>Donah #2</p><p>Game</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Do phonogram y next week, might be worth revisiting other vowels as well. Harriet was very good with reading, and picked up rule 3 quickly as it is similar to rule 2. She was very good with both donah and Kilpatrick as well. Harriet’s reading is improving very quickly as she learns new rules.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-08 10:18:36', '2022-08-08 10:19:00'),
