(2870, '2022/08/08', '02:45 pm', '3', '3', 'Luna Shapiro', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick G2</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Recap handwriting features and have Luna ID.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8 + 27-38</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 1-8</td></tr><tr><td>HF: 2 o\'clock letters</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Handwriting activity -- guess the letter! Luna did SO well describing her letters, using tangible reference points such as 2 o\'clock</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Last week\'s Ayres words</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: NA</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: on it she fish wish&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>With focus on handwriting and sound symbol connection rather than rules.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use Ayres words in oral sentences.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: SCORE + Fitzroy 1</td></tr><tr><td>SCORE - Luna very resistant to the job, had to ocnvince her by promising we only had to do the top row. She had to sound out each word.</td></tr><tr><td>Fitzroy 1 -- all familiar words for Luna except \'fat\'. Very stilted reading but more agreeable with this task than SCORE.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes:</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>I feel really good about Luna\'s clockface formation! Finally! I want to start impressing \"jumping letters\" on her next week so she can talk to her pencil for those as well.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-08 14:45:23', '2022-08-08 15:44:52'),
(2871, '2022/08/08', '02:53 pm', '3', '3', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Mia was a bit distracted by Thomas today. She has a good concentration and great motivation in our paired lesson. She came for a 1.5 hour extended lesson today yet she did a great job even if at the end of it, she started to vague out a bit.&nbsp;</p><p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer<br>OPR/WPR o, u, s, a, g, oo, l, b, d. &nbsp; Mia is a bit shaky at o and &nbsp;oo. She has mastered the written form of these phonograms.&nbsp;<br><br>rule review: rule 4. new rule r. 19 with activity. Mia benefited a lot from today\'s lesson as she can now explained rule 4 fully.&nbsp;<br>SD: not, us, am, good, a go, old, bad, kind. Mia wrote cind for kind.<br>compose sentences using SD words. Mia\'s sentence starts with capital letter and finish with a full stop. She is ready for more challenge.&nbsp;</p><p>reading-M--wizkids stage 2 book1 3rd reading. Mia can read words naturally in a book and she did a good job at this activity.<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-08 14:53:39', '2022-08-09 15:19:46'),
(2872, '2022/08/08', '03:29 pm', '3', '3', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 30', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Thomas was a bit frustrated today at the begining as he couldn\'t win a task contest, then he was a bit out of control and made lots of noise. He needed encouragement and help to maintain his concentration today. Thomas will need to practice decodable reading at home as he cannot read naturally yet for some easy books.(wizkids series)</p><p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer<br>OPR/WPR o, u, s, a, g, oo, l, b, d. &nbsp; Thomas is a bit shaky at u and &nbsp;oo. He has mastered the written form of these phonograms.&nbsp;<br><br>rule review: rule 4. new rule r. 19. Thomas can explain rules we have learned as well new rules we have been learning. He has a good memory and can retain more knowledge now.&nbsp;<br>SD: not, us, am, good, a go, old, bad, kind.&nbsp;<br>compose sentences using SD words. Thoma\'s sentence usually doesn\'t have capital letter at the beginning, nor punctuations. His sentence is gramatically correct.&nbsp;</p><p>reading-M--wizkids stage 2 book 3 2nd reading. Thomas will need a lot of practice for his oral fluency as he cannot read 3-letter words naturally in books. He sometimes gets impatient about it, hence, he can mistake the words with other words.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-08 15:29:45', '2022-08-09 15:28:13'),
