(2906, '2022/08/10', '03:39 pm', '3', '3', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8, 27-43</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: a c g ow ou oo ch ar ay ai oi</td></tr><tr><td>Spell check: must over run look book</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>In lieu of a spelling lesson, create a story (hopefully using words from spelling). Refer back to spelling book. Although not concerned with the spelling of longer/unfamiliar words (e.g. created), encourage Max to sound out these words and write phonetically.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: Fitzroy 3: 46wpm Fitzroy 4: 39wpm</td></tr><tr><td>SCORE 2.1 - A couple of errors, and again sounding out. Might send home Book 1 for practice.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Max was very excitable today. He was jumping all about the place, standing on his chair in a funny way, suddenly going on tangents -- \"Imagine a pencil was so pointy and twisty it could go through things like a drill.\" \"Imagine a rubber so big it was bigger than house. And it can erase houses, that would be so useful, because then if there\'s too many houses it can jsut get rid of them.\"</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-10 15:40:51', '2022-08-10 16:47:50'),
