(2908, '2022/08/10', '04:16 pm', '3', '3', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-10 16:16:41', '2022-08-17 17:21:26'),
(2909, '2022/08/10', '04:36 pm', '3', '3', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'The Writing Process - Plan, Compose, Revise, Edit, Publish (by reading, speaking, media presentation)', 'Use the writing process to compose informative paragraph', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Xavier continued with his HASS assessment task on Vietnam.&nbsp;</p><p>HE began revision of his first question to ensure his sentences were clear and his information was in order. Xavier dislikes revision and editing and relies on the pc to pick up all his errors with punctuation and spelling. This week we will refine sentences and edit for spelling.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-10 16:36:06', '2022-08-15 21:25:22'),
(2910, '2022/08/10', '04:42 pm', '3', '3', 'Zac Pharaoh ', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-10 16:42:31', '2022-08-10 16:42:31'),
(2911, '2022/08/10', '05:02 pm', '3', '4', 'Phoebe Webb', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Will Hughes', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>Phoebe Webb 10/8/22</strong></p><p>Kilpatrick i1 no.7 and no. 8</p><p>Handwriting m</p><p>OPR/WPR: ea, ow, ou, oo, ar, wh, ew, ui,</p><p>Rule 7, job 4 every syllable must have a vowel.</p><p>Became, because, before</p><p>SD (A-G): be, book, must, make, street, eat, cool, paint</p><p>3 sentences</p><p>Donah #4</p><p>Reading</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Phoebe struggled with Donah #4, and we hid phonograms around the office for Phoebe to find and sound out when they were found. Kilpatrick was a bit of a challenge as well. Phoebe’s handwriting for ‘m’. Phoebe chose to read Bob Graham’s <i>Lets Get a Pup,&nbsp;</i>read through it with Phoebe. Phoebe was a bit all over the show today, and we didn’t manage to get any spelling done, sentences or review rule 7 job 4. Will repeat same lesson plan next week. Phoebe enjoyed listening to me read to her.</p>', NULL, '2022-08-10 17:02:55', '2022-08-10 17:03:33'),
