(2946, '2022/08/16', '08:46 am', '3', '4', 'Henry  Badock', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 30', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3 W4</p><ol><li>Mental Computation using number facts to 40. encouraging recognising friends of ten.</li></ol><p>Henry can do so up to 20 but does not recognise these beyond that. he does not consistently use chunking to 10 to assist.</p><p>2. Multiplication with manipulatives.&nbsp;</p><p>Same activity as last week. Blocks in various groups on table (using numbers he cannot mentally giv an answer to). Emphasis on no answers required.&nbsp;</p><p>Henry completely refused to engage initially. Threw himself around the room. Defiantly refused to sit or stand at the table. Removed the wobbly stool for inappropriate use.&nbsp;</p><p>After 15 mins Henry completed the task begrudgingly. Next week present differently. Henry was focused on getting the answer. He could not focus on one task with other tasks set up beside him. Present one at a time and use a different format.</p><p>The second part of the activity was for henry to create his own groups and I acted as scribe. He happily completed this task and was focused on the process and not the answer. Do the same but with different manipulatives next week.&nbsp;</p><p>3. Pirate pete to end using 3 dice -1000 100 10 and mental addition. Reinforcing place value, and greater than and smaller than.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-16 08:47:10', '2022-08-16 09:06:02'),
