(2962, '2022/08/17', '03:27 pm', '3', '4', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 14: Write ti/si/ci at the beginning of a second or subsequent syllable', 'See Notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3 W4</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR</p><p>Vowels c g ti si ci eigh ei ieoe oa ough s&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review&nbsp;</p><p>3 4 14</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SD: Sect Q from special present pre sent action act just justice gentle gentleman</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Spelling rule worksheet for plurals ending with f.&nbsp;</p><p>Calf knife wife life elf shelf&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Complete revision and edit of writing task from weeks 1-3. Published.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading OF 514</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW – complete worksheet</p><p>Reading.</p>', NULL, '2022-08-17 15:27:09', '2022-08-17 17:27:30'),
(2964, '2022/08/17', '03:29 pm', '3', '4', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8, 27-43</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: a ow oo ch oy s c er&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Fitzroy #5</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: \"Words We Know\" words</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: N/A</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD -- Word\'s We\'ve Used: hen pet net vet of fog had was let wet</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Asked Max to write a sentence. Max began by composing a story verbally that used the words: \"I had a pet hen. I let it out. It went crazy. I got a net. I caught the hen. It escaped. It flapped everywhere. It made me walk into a puddle. I got wet. I caught it again and took it to the vet.\"</td></tr><tr><td>Max was very agreeable today. He sounded many of his words as he was writing his sentences, including: spelling words, it, went, me</td></tr><tr><td>I coached for: out, made, flap</td></tr><tr><td>Max asked for help with: crazy, so (made him sound out), walk,&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: Fitzroy 5, untimed</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Max was able to apply the necessary spelling markings to the words, including adding a double underline on the a in was. He did this independently and explained his reasoning.</td></tr><tr><td>Max was generally very agreeable today, much more than usual.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-17 15:29:42', '2022-08-17 16:37:05'),
