(2973, '2022/08/17', '05:27 pm', '3', '4', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics & Morphology - The Vocabulary of Word Structure', 'Suffix - letters added to the end of base words or word roots to create new words > they have their own meaning & they change the meaning of the base or root - Suffixes cannot stand/be used alone', 'Spell words with suffixes indicating part of speech > y/er/en/ful/ion/ance/ence (tion)', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Xavier brought his Food studies assessment task to class today to complete. He researched staple.foods and food groups.&nbsp;</p><p>We also completed a review of adding suffixes to base words (rule 9/10) Xavier can do this with modelling but does not apply the rules when not reminded. Repetition is necessary on all rules and phonogram usage when writing.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-17 17:29:03', '2022-08-17 17:34:01');
