(2992, '2022/08/19', '04:28 pm', '3', '4', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 26-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ai ea ch ck ear ay th ng ou ee ey ei ie</td></tr><tr><td>Nate wanted to write all of his phonograms in a blocky, computer font, which I allowed so long as he also wrote them in his normal handwriting. I hoped being explicit about how during this task I was allowing \"fun\" handwriting would help drive home the need for \"proper\" writing in spelling, or make Nate more agreeable to the task.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 9&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Rule Page 3</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use words in oral sentences.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: 317 + 318 home for homework.</td></tr><tr><td>Reading -- Nate read \"The Amazing Adventures of Cat\". Funnily enough, this brought up a conversation about legible handwriting, because Nate couldn\'t read some of the words, and thought letters looked like others (e.g. L looked like a C)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Nate wasn\'t too obnoxious today with his spelling presentation, but definitely miffed about it. I had more patience this week, also. Nate was in a bit of a sook about it but surprisingly cheered up a bit when I called him out on it.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-19 16:28:16', '2022-08-19 17:26:29'),
(2993, '2022/08/19', '04:49 pm', '3', '4', 'Josh Zeeman', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Will Hughes', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Josh and I are working on research and persuasive writing skills. Josh is interested in conspiracy theories and wanted to research 9/11 conspiracy theories. I have tasked Josh with researching evidence into the 9/11 conspiracy theory that it was an inside job, putting points together into a persuasive essay. Josh seems to be really enjoying it, and really interested in it.</p>', NULL, '2022-08-19 16:50:18', '2022-08-19 16:55:03'),
