(2998, '2022/08/22', '03:27 pm', '3', '5', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Mia and Thomas have been working together for a while and lately, I noticed that the two can be disturbing to each other sometimes. Thomas tends to make lots of noises and Mia is a bit bothered. They two are still a good pair for the work and they share each other stories.&nbsp;</p><p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer. Both are doing great.<br>OPR/WPR 27-45 . &nbsp;They both are not good at ea, wor and ear. They are struggling with the written form of wor and ear, as well as ur. &nbsp;Thomas cannot remeber the sounds of oo.<br>rule 7: sfe activity-clip the magic e. Marking sfe. Thomas understands the knowledge and concepts yet Mia seems a bit confused with the concepts. Thomas sometiems helps her to understand. They both need more practice to understand silent final es.&nbsp;<br>SD: sfe reviewing activity<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-22 15:27:22', '2022-08-24 09:21:50'),
(2999, '2022/08/22', '03:27 pm', '3', '6', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Thomas and Mia has been developing a competitive learnign atmosphere, however, this competition has gone too far that sometimes they are not very nice to each other. I will have to figure out what to do with this situation soon.&nbsp;</p><p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer<br>OPR/WPR i, a, v, ch, c, ar, g, They both need to work on g.&nbsp;<br>morphology activity 5 for Mia. Tom-written focus a. Thomas still writes a and g in the wrong way. we will have to emphasize this quite often.&nbsp;<br>rule 7: sfe activity-clip the magic e. Marking sfe. They have graspped the sfe awarness and function well during the activity.&nbsp;<br>SD: sfe words. They both still write s for c. eg. chanse</p><p>&nbsp;compose sentences using SD words.</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-22 15:27:24', '2022-08-31 09:53:36'),
(3000, '2022/08/22', '03:27 pm', '3', '7', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - Precisely say, write and read words in Section A-G', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Mia and Thomas got along very well this lesson and it can be beneficial for both of them to work on one project. They learn about team work.</p><p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer<br>OPR/WPR g, o, l, d, a, e, f, u. They both are &nbsp;a bit shaky for a, e, and u sounds.&nbsp;<br>morphology activity 6 for Mia. Tom-written focus g. Thomas still likes to write letters from bottom to top for line letters and he still can\'t write a or g without lifting his pencil.&nbsp;<br>rule 4, 5, 6, 17 with activity. Thomas has a great memory and understanding ability, yet Mia can retain knowledge longer than Thomas. They two make a great team for learning together.&nbsp;<br>SD: my, will, a go, bad, red, of, be<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-22 15:27:24', '2022-09-07 10:11:46'),
(3013, '2022/08/22', '03:29 pm', '3', '5', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Mia and Thomas have been working together for a while and lately, I noticed that the two can be disturbing to each other sometimes. Thomas tends to make lots of noises and Mia is a bit bothered. They two are still a good pair for the work and they share each other stories.&nbsp;</p><p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer. Both are doing great.<br>OPR/WPR 27-45 . &nbsp;They both are not good at ea, wor and ear. They are struggling with the written form of wor and ear, as well as ur. &nbsp;Thomas cannot remeber the sounds of oo.<br>rule 7: sfe activity-clip the magic e. Marking sfe. Thomas understands the knowledge and concepts yet Mia seems a bit confused with the concepts. Thomas sometiems helps her to understand. They both need more practice to understand silent final es.&nbsp;<br>SD: sfe reviewing activity<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-22 15:29:10', '2022-08-24 09:19:56'),
