(3032, '2022/08/23', '04:29 pm', '3', '5', 'Lachlan Prior', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-23 16:29:18', '2022-08-23 16:29:18'),
(3033, '2022/08/23', '04:56 pm', '3', '5', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 100', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>Lucy\'s performance on MMM today was markedly improved on that of last week. &nbsp;A solid result with just a couple of errors in additional and subtraction facts to 100.</p><p>Review simplification of fractions from last week - review greatest common factor, use GCF to simplifying given fractions (recognising the division process and checking with the multiplication process) . &nbsp;ID GCF for second set of practice conversions, but do not record the GCF - convert without workings. &nbsp;Recognise when GCF was not selected for the first simplification. &nbsp;Show how the additional simplification multiplied by the original = GCF for the original numerator and denominator.</p><p>Using Key Math practice pages, began applying the given rule, completing the x/y table and plotting points on the first quadrant of the Cartesian Plane. &nbsp;Nil difficulties with this task.</p>', NULL, '<p>Today was a catch up for one of the two lessons that were rescheduled - x1 due to Naomi and x1 due to Lucy.</p>', '2022-08-23 16:58:38', '2022-08-23 23:32:52'),
(3034, '2022/08/24', '08:32 am', '3', '5', 'Callan Bartlett', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 46 > 54', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callan is a very polite and lovely kid. He can concentrate very well in our one hour session. He follows instrustions well and can usually finish tasks independently. Yet he needs encouragement to ask for help. He loved to talk about what he likes to do. He likes art, bushes and ball games.&nbsp;</p><p>opr/wpr: 1-65. Callan can get 50% of them right yet he is struggling with the other 50%, which is also the reason why his spelling is so behind. He is especially confused with ui/ew, aw/au, ow/ou, ie/ey.&nbsp;</p><p>SD: Morrison spelling assessment list 1. His result is in section J. Spelling age is 7 years and 7 month, grade level is 1.5.&nbsp;</p><p>Writing: Drastura paragragh writing. He did background reading and first draft today. Callan spelt sed for said, secs for seconds, ther for there, warc for walk, poors for pause.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-24 08:32:58', '2022-08-24 09:06:23'),
