(3045, '2022/08/24', '04:24 pm', '3', '5', 'Angus Zeeman', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: NA</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ough ci ea ch ai&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Spell Check: refer minute ought absent absence conference. Some trouble on conference/needed prompting.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 19</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Wednesday-amusement</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Writing Process: Compose a short narrative using Ayres words for inspiration. Revise, edit and discuss as necessary.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Comp: Key Into Inference task. Discuss evaluation, inference, and mental actions. Read aloud.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>N-8 A-7</td></tr><tr><td>Angus agreeable as always. He made some good connections during spelling between rules, even when they weren\'t quite right. The key into inference activities were also completed with more accuracy than they were when we initially started, which makes me wonder if it was just that particular passage that was difficult.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-24 16:24:37', '2022-08-24 17:31:37'),
(3046, '2022/08/24', '04:30 pm', '3', '2', 'Eloise Bowden', 'Mathematics', 'Fractions', 'Proper, improper, mixed number, equivalent', 'Discussion & Practise (on board/in book)', 'Kieran Oates', 'In Progress', 'In Progress', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Eloise did very well today. She is very eager and attentive. The fractions we covered I think were a bit beyond what she was doing but she kept up well. As a student, Eloise lacks confidence and I hope to be able to help her improve on that.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-24 16:30:41', '2022-08-31 21:15:09'),
(3048, '2022/08/24', '04:33 pm', '3', '5', 'Xavier Schmidt', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics & Morphology - The Vocabulary of Word Structure', 'Word roots hold meaning but cannot stand/be used alone (add a prefix or a suffix)', 'Identify word roots in spelling dictation words', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Xavier did not have any outstanding school tasks today.</p><p>We focused on spelling strategies using his knowledge of rules 7, 9,10,11,24, 14 (adding vowel endings), rules 25 (ck/dge), suffixes, prefixes, word roots or base words, and syllabification.</p><p>In isolation Xavier can correctly spell the words below:</p><p>setting wettest beginning writing writer cried crying</p><p>If given the base word and the rule - choose ti, si, ci by looking at the word root/base word he can correctly spell the words below:</p><p>vise vision, space spacious, face facial, state station</p><p>We have discussed choosing ti for words ending in ‘d’ eg divide -division&nbsp;</p><p>Discussion around how adding the suffix can change the POS and meaning of a word.&nbsp;</p><p>Review of when to use ck/c/k and j/g/dge Rule 25</p><p>Review of common ways to spell ‘ai’ - a (r.4) ai ay (r18) a_e (job 1)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-24 16:33:08', '2022-08-25 15:58:23'),
