(3067, '2022/08/29', '08:42 am', '3', '6', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Six, Lesson One</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 29 August 2022</td></tr><tr><td>NM relief</td></tr><tr><td>(syllables/sounds - will need finger scaffold) PA: serve (1/3), circle (2/4), church (1/3), worth (1/3), search (1/3)</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick E2 set 4</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #18</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: er x5 - focus on cues</td></tr><tr><td>Will likely need prompting for WPR, which is fine. Focus is on handwriting</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Dictate er words into rule page 2 (at least one row)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>LP dictate sentence to NM</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Home support pack</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Lewis had to separate words into sounds before IDing syllable types. He could easily distinguish between open/closed. He was incredibly chatty and I probably did not do a good enough job at keeping us on a roll. He was able to connect the er phonograms to their clue words by the end of the lesson. Lewis had some trouble with spelling dictation -- I don\'t know how much you\'ve done with him, he was a little confused about the syllable break in early. He also struggled to encode works (w wor cs) initially. I also wasn\'t sure where to put rule page 2 in his book so just found a double page spread and hoped for the best! Didn\'t really spend much time on syllable types, sorry! Lewis wrote a sentence but I modelled it on the board for him as we only had a couple of minutes left, then he copied it into his book.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Six, Lesson One</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 29 August 2022</td></tr><tr><td>NM relief</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-08-29 08:42:44', '2022-09-17 16:25:50'),
