(3070, '2022/08/29', '02:45 pm', '3', '6', 'Luna Shapiro', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick G2</td></tr><tr><td>Word recognition: Fitzroy flashcards</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8,b h k m n p r sh th ee ow oo ch er ck ed</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: g r o c a b h k m n p r</td></tr><tr><td>HF: formation</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Game of Luna\'s choice.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>WPR Assessment -- on a whim because I happened to see her old one in her folder.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: Fitzroy 5</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>From WPR assessment: b p, j, k v, w worth focusing on. If I focus on p and k initially (as jumping letters) then I should be able to keep them going alongside pointy letters (v, w, y). Worth noting that she did okay with b and p in her WPR. I imagine it\'s the same problem we\'ve had in the past of repeating activities/instruction enough that she is able to carry it over independently.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-29 14:45:59', '2022-09-13 16:46:13'),
(3071, '2022/08/29', '03:27 pm', '3', '6', 'Mia Harvey', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 31 > 45', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Thomas and Mia has been developing a competitive learnign atmosphere, however, this competition has gone too far that sometimes they are not very nice to each other. I will have to figure out what to do with this situation soon.&nbsp;</p><p>Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer<br>OPR/WPR i, a, v, ch, c, ar, g, They both need to work on g.&nbsp;<br>morphology activity 5 for Mia. Tom-written focus a. Thomas still writes a and g in the wrong way. we will have to emphasize this quite often.&nbsp;<br>rule 7: sfe activity-clip the magic e. Marking sfe. They have graspped the sfe awarness and function well during the activity.&nbsp;<br>SD: sfe words. They both still write s for c. eg. chanse</p><p>&nbsp;compose sentences using SD words.</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-29 15:27:36', '2022-08-31 09:51:23'),
