(3089, '2022/08/29', '03:36 pm', '3', '6', 'Elsa Clennet', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete final sound in word or final blend - Kilpatrick Level I', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick I</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 42-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: ph ough ed or ir gu ar ci er kn gn</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 26 4 11 28&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: United States-circle</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Sentence Structure: Use Ayres words in sentences.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Writing Process: Chat to Elsa about how we\'re going to progress with her informative writing. Perhaps a 3 week writing project on a topic of her choice.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>A fun lesson from Elsa! We didn\'t get through quite as much as I wanted to, but Elsa was a little late and very tired from school. We also had an instance of her using a word incorrectly, but I\'ve postponed our chat about that to next week where she won\'t be in an observed lesson (as I think it made her a little nervous!)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-29 15:36:30', '2022-09-05 16:41:25'),
