(3092, '2022/08/29', '04:33 pm', '3', '6', 'Arlo Clark', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 4: vowels a, e, o, u say their second (long) sound at the end of a syllable', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpattrick &nbsp;F1<br>OPR/WPR:o, u, g, b, d, e, f, &nbsp;Arlo still needs to work on u and e</p><p>morphology activity 2. He usually can do the first two activities but the third one can be difficult for him.<br>rule review: rule 4 colour code activity(pink book page 1). He mastered rule 4<br>SD: &nbsp;a go, bad, red, of, be, but. He wrote rad for red.&nbsp;<br>online spelling game/ SD words sentence. He made a great compound sentence.&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-29 16:33:46', '2022-08-31 09:09:08'),
(3093, '2022/08/30', '07:44 am', '3', '6', 'Henry  Badock', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Recognise and represent multiplication as repeated addition, groups and arrays', 'TEXT BOOK - EXERCISES, QUESTIONS, ACTIVITIES', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3W6</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Subtraction on white board no regrouping</li><li>Subtracting modelling using base 10 blocks for regrouping– Henry resistant to even trying to model a number. I scaffolded every step of the first problem. Henry refused to use the blocks and instead wanted to answer the problems on the sheet. He subsequently rushed through as he did not understand the process of regrouping. Henry swaps the smaller number for the larger number and then subtracts.</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Eg 55-19 H starts at tens and says 50-10 = 40 then 9 – 1 = 8 answer is 48&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>He will not consider using manipulatives for these problems at all. If shown on paper he will copy the action but does not understand the process.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Multiplication – Henry finally moved past his block with this and willingly engaged in the same cup and peg activity from last week. He used the correct language and modelled each problem, articulating the steps for me to scribe. Hurray!!</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Pirate pete to finish 2 dice we used the language of multiplication – 5 x 4&nbsp; -not focused on answer but Henry was able to produce an answer using fingers to assist in counting in 3/5/4/2</p>', NULL, '2022-08-30 07:44:18', '2022-08-31 17:49:10'),
