(3098, '2022/08/30', '03:33 pm', '3', '6', 'Esther Mclver', 'English', 'Writing - High Frequency Vocabulary + Sentence Construction', 'Elements of a complex sentence > Capital letter, one independent clause, one dependent clause containing a subordinate conjunction, ending punctuation', 'Recognise/Analyse/Model/Compose compound sentences that include subject nouns/pronouns and subordinating conjunctions if, after, when, than, unless, because, however', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>T3W6</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>OPR&nbsp;</strong> vowels sh ti si ci ow ou ng ed ie ei ey&nbsp;</p><p><strong>WPR</strong> as above&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Rule Review: &nbsp;&amp; Spelling Dictation</strong></p><p>Continue Rule 11 and rule page.&nbsp;</p><p>Rule 11 worksheet adding suffixes&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Writing:</strong></p><p>Complex sentences model with blocks. Focus on the language – Independent+ subbie + dependent Clause</p><p><strong>Dictation</strong>: The bike rider raced around the track bravely, even though he was tired from racing&nbsp;yesterday.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Reading</strong> – OF 112 N (Last week 1 min 0 errors, 0 sc, 97/97 words)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>HW</strong> &nbsp;Sentences Rule 11 Worksheet.</p><p><strong>Game</strong> Rule 11 Flip a card to match with suffixes. How many words can you say/write correctly?</p>', NULL, '2022-08-30 15:33:17', '2022-09-02 21:21:12'),
