(3101, '2022/08/30', '04:28 pm', '3', '6', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - Precisely say, write and read words in Section M', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>kilpatrick i<br>OPR/WPR: u, th, oo, ai, or, o, ar. Callum is still confused by the 3 sounds of u.&nbsp;<br><br>rule review4, 19, sfe job 2<br>SD: true, truth, took, a gain, in form, both, heart<br>read for spelling and reading; &nbsp; &nbsp; understanding words and word class; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><br>write a complex sentence with sd words, find the noun and verbs. Callum is not aware of subordinating words.&nbsp;<br>analyze parts of speech<br>writing process step 2-write a draft paragragh for the world of Drastura<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-30 16:28:37', '2022-08-31 09:36:03'),
