(3103, '2022/08/30', '04:58 pm', '3', '5', 'Shay Douglas', 'Academic Coaching', 'Independent Study', 'School Assigned Worksheet or Assignment', 'See Notes', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>WEEK SIX – 30 AUGUST</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Maths</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Shay\'s maths assignment.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Activity: Shay worked through a measurement homework assignment for his maths class. He required very little help with this activity.</td></tr><tr><td>One area of note was that he was doubting his work because it didn\'t \"feel\" right when compared with the picture (the question was on surface area). We double checked his maths and then talked about how the diagram was not drawn to scale.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Shay also needed some prompting for formulas (e.g. for circumference).&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-30 16:58:33', '2022-09-27 15:27:29'),
(3104, '2022/08/30', '05:28 pm', '3', '6', 'Lucy Crosswell', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Not Yet', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kipatrick H</td></tr><tr><td>Applied a scaffold for Lucy which helped, but she didn\'t have 100% accuracy.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8, 27-38</td></tr><tr><td>WPR:g a c sh th ou e oo ch ar</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule 2 and 3 review with Cyclops and Giants. Beautiful articulation from Lucy with every card she played.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SD: Rule Page 1 -- vowel sounds</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Recap simple sentences and model on the SBB. Subject/action connection. Compose&nbsp; simple sentences and articulate after each the subject/action (or noun/verb) and colour code.</td></tr><tr><td>Dictate sentence to Lucy: I put my navy skirt on last. Oral work with sentence before writing. ID and colour code subject noun and verb</td></tr><tr><td>Explain what the punctuation tells us about how the words should be read/what instruction the punctuation gives to the reader. Read Lucy\'s sentences aloud with full stop&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Email from Lucy\'s teacher recommending these areas for focus:&nbsp;<br>Segmenting<br>Blending<br>Diagraphs<br>Simple sentences&nbsp; with correct punctuation<br>Reading fluency<br>\"explanation writing\"</td></tr><tr><td>Still having trouble with applying rule 4, which fits in with Lucy\'s difficulty with visual/spatial awareness and transferring concepts. Skirt &gt; discussion as Lucy asked for help, we sounded out. She initially wrote scirt. We then talked about rule 2 and how that would effect the sound of c.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-30 17:28:45', '2022-08-30 18:43:13'),
(3105, '2022/08/31', '08:38 am', '3', '3', 'James Levings', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Ivan Botero', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-08-31 08:38:53', '2022-08-31 08:38:53'),
(3106, '2022/08/31', '09:23 am', '3', '6', 'Callan Bartlett', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 6: English words don\'t end with i - use y', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callan does great listening during our lesson and he really enjoys the writing activity.&nbsp;</p><p>PA: Kilpatrick&nbsp;</p><p>opr/wpr: s, e, or, a, y, oo, th, i, er</p><p>Rule review: 29, 6<br>SD: sev en, for get, hap py, noon, think, sis ter<br>Writing activities: callan-publishing a paragrgh for the world of Drastura<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-31 09:24:13', '2022-08-31 09:27:48'),
(3107, '2022/08/31', '09:40 am', '3', '6', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Essay Structure', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Luke\'s father forgot to take him to the lesson last week and this week they were quite late too. Luke really enjoys the writing activity-The World of Drastura. He was quite late so we have only donw a bit of writing process step 1 for researching information for this activity. He &nbsp;created his character and named him on a draft.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-31 09:41:43', '2022-08-31 09:44:47'),
(3108, '2022/08/31', '01:48 pm', '3', '6', 'Angel King', 'English Assessment', 'Decoding and encoding words for spelling', 'Spelling Assessment for Ayres Placement', 'Morrison McCall Spelling Assessment - List 2', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3W6</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Review of JOSE, Rule 4 plus 9/10/11/24</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>As indicated by last weeks MMC.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Morrison McCall List 2</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Holborn Reading – Angel read carefully and was keeping track of the meaning by reading ahead and then returning to a difficult or unknown word. She was visibly sounding words under her breathe.&nbsp;</p><p>Eleanor still lacks confidence. She is not recognising JOSE when reading words and does not use any strategies to help decipher unknown words. Reading on does not occur to her, even with prompting.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Waddington Reading 2</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OF – Angel read her passage rapidly and substituted several ands for full stops. On her second attempt she slowed down and sc when she heard herself make a mistake!&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Eleanor read very quietly and used a pencil to track. She also substituted ands for fullstops and missed several words completely which meant the text did not make sense. She seemed oblivious to this.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-31 13:48:25', '2022-08-31 17:31:46'),
(3109, '2022/08/31', '01:48 pm', '3', '6', 'Eleanor  Stam', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Various rules (see notes)', 'See notes', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>T3W6</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Review of JOSE, Rule 4 plus 9/10/11/24</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>As indicated by last weeks MMC.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Morrison McCall List 2</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Holborn Reading – Angel read carefully and was keeping track of the meaning by reading ahead and then returning to a difficult or unknown word. She was visibly sounding words under her breathe.&nbsp;</p><p>Eleanor still lacks confidence. She is not recognising JOSE when reading words and does not use any strategies to help decipher unknown words. Reading on does not occur to her, even with prompting.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Waddington Reading 2</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OF – Angel read her passage rapidly and substituted several ands for full stops. On her second attempt she slowed down and sc when she heard herself make a mistake!&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Eleanor read very quietly and used a pencil to track. She also substituted ands for fullstops and missed several words completely which meant the text did not make sense. She seemed oblivious to this.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-31 13:48:53', '2022-08-31 17:35:48'),
