(3113, '2022/08/31', '03:32 pm', '3', '6', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Fitzroy CVC word flashcards.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8, 27-38, u , w</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: w u ee ow ai c oy ar ou sh th er</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Fitzroy #8</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: \"Words We Know\" words</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD:&nbsp; have go said for to with</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use spelling words in sentences. Max had talked about a teacher at school making him write sentences by himself, which he didn\'t like because he couldn\'t do it. I told him that he could and that he had done it here (although Max didn\'t believe me). For these sentences I asked him to write it by himself with no help.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Max asked me how to spell \'if\' and I said \"I know you have enough knowledge in your brain to figure that out yourself\", and then he did!</td></tr><tr><td>Max asked for help with \"imaginary friend\". I reminded him that he was writing this by himself and to have a go, and that it was okay if it wasn’t spelled correctly. Max got a bit upset so we decided to write IF to stand for it instead.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Max was difficult today. He was generally in quite a happy mood, but not concentrating. He was ignoring instructions and my normal strategies for getting him back on track were not working (e.g. What did I just ask you to do? I\'ve asked you three times now to do X, what are you supposed to be doing now?). His handwriting was also all over the place and Max was making up little stories (e.g. writing the a under the line and saying \"It\'s digging!! It\'s diging into the GROOOOUUUUNNNDDD!!!\").</td></tr><tr><td>Surprisingly what got Max to focus a little more during WPR was when I went ahead without waiting for him to have written the phonogram down. He suddenly picked up and wrote them all down in one hit.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-08-31 15:32:00', '2022-08-31 17:04:32'),
(3114, '2022/08/31', '03:33 pm', '3', '6', 'Luke Gomer', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 14: Write ti/si/ci at the beginning of a second or subsequent syllable', 'Spelling Notebook - Rule Page 6', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p><strong>T3 W6 x2 lessons (catchup on 30/8/22 from week 9 of term 2)</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>OPR</strong> /<strong>WPR</strong>ai ay ey or ar w ough ie ei + Vowels<strong> /</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ie ei ey eigh ti si ci vowels ew ui</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Rule Review</strong></p><p>Disclose Job 1&nbsp;</p><p>Ful/al&nbsp;</p><p>Apple Rule 29&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Spelling Dictation</strong></p><p>Enclose await suppose wonderful forward backward toward &nbsp;although prompt attempt&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Spelling Dictation – continue rule page for rules 14/15/16</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Suffix /sentence worksheet: complete 5 and the remainder for HW</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Writing – 2 sentence stories continue from Week 5&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Reading – 515 completed</p><p>NW 516</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>HW suffix and complex sentence worksheet&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-08-31 15:33:09', '2022-08-31 16:58:37'),
