(3126, '2022/09/01', '08:43 am', '3', '6', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Six, Lesson Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 1 September 2022</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick E2 set 5</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #19</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>OPR: er x5, ou, a, intro our</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: our (had rolled dice)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Review rule 17, SD: all, your, you</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Home support pack</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>LP was really not doing well today. He said multiple times that he was \"grumpy\" or \"angry\", and shut down to the point where he was even refusing to speak. I tried all my usual strategies of joking around, distracting him, encouraging him, directly addressing his behaviour, but couldn\'t seem to get through to him. Lewis was essentially ignoring/refusing to follow instructions, e.g. me asking him to leave lines on his spelling page for other words. After PA, OPR/WPR, and 3 SD words, LP eventually told me that he was feeling sad. I asked him if he wanted to talk about it, and he started telling me (tearfully) that his big brother was really mean to him, this morning saying that Lewis\' show was \"dumb\". Lewis was pretty upset, so I chatted to him about how big brothers can be nasty, but that doesn\'t mean that they\'re right. I also asked Lewis to show me the show, and we watched five mins of one together, which Lewis loved. He had perked right up by the end. I explained all this to Alysia, who mentioned that Lewis has been dealing with the effects of his new medication which allows him to feel more emotions and more deeply.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Six, Lesson Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 1 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-01 08:43:13', '2022-09-17 16:26:11'),
(3127, '2022/09/01', '02:43 pm', '3', '6', 'Mia Harvey', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-01 14:43:15', '2022-09-01 14:43:15'),
(3128, '2022/09/01', '03:27 pm', '3', '6', 'James  Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Six</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 1 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #30</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Challenge word: tension</td></tr><tr><td>Discuss base word and suffix</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: wr oa ay oe ey gn ie dge eigh ti ci si</td></tr><tr><td>Prompting with ey</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 13 (tells us what we can\'t use), 14 (three options), rule 15 (narrows it down), rule 16 (makes two sounds)</td></tr><tr><td>SD: rule page 6 - si (2nd sound) rule 16 words: vision, division, occasion, explosion</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr><tr><td>Discuss rule 16 and dictated words - including morphology. I.e. what changes when we add the suffix? If time, dictate the final few \'ti\' words in the first column&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ORF x3</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule 15 &amp; 16 spelling words activity</td></tr><tr><td>James was pretty slow and tired today, still recovering from his illness most likely. Good with PA, MA and phonos - prompting with ey (might need practice page?). Able to make good connections to knowledge with challenge word (i.e. identifying rule 14). Could articulate rules 13-15 and the connection between them. Intro\'d rule 16, which James was fine with and was able to apply. No issues with SD, we powered through. James a little distracted and fiddly but fine with me redirecting him to the task. Talked a bit about morphology of the words we\'d done, but James was very much disengaged. Finished with some ORF.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Six</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 1 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-01 15:27:25', '2022-09-17 12:43:30'),
(3129, '2022/09/01', '03:30 pm', '3', '5', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-01 15:30:19', '2022-09-01 15:30:19'),
(3130, '2022/09/01', '03:34 pm', '3', '1', 'Stella Bowerman', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-01 15:34:15', '2022-09-01 15:34:15'),
(3131, '2022/09/01', '03:35 pm', '3', '6', 'Cara Lashmar', 'English', 'Writing - High Frequency Vocabulary + Sentence Construction', 'Sentence structure - there are three ways to construct a sentence > simple, compound, complex', 'Recognise/Analyse/Compose/Model simple/compound/complex sentences that demonstrate meaning & usage of unfamiliar spelling words', 'Laree Thorsby', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Focus was review of parts of speech leading to a formalised session on sentence structure, as requested by her teacher.</p><p>All three sentence structures were introduced, including the language (independent and dependent clauses, fanboys, subbies, conjunctions, and relevant punctuation). Cara then practicesed forming each type.&nbsp;</p><p>NW another review of this and then look at a piece of her writing to recognise and analyse for each sentence structure.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-01 15:35:07', '2022-09-02 15:54:17'),
(3133, '2022/09/01', '03:38 pm', '3', '6', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Measurement', 'Convert between common metric units of length, mass and capacity', 'Text book - Exercises, Questions, Activities', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>NSPM Level 3 Measurement conversions (review homework). &nbsp;Lucy has not yet grasped the full understanding of converting between units and is not always looking at the scale provided. &nbsp;Additionally, working out the intervals between full units recorded on the scale (eg between the 1kg, 2kg, 3kg marks). &nbsp;Today\'s work was most supportive of her decoding these measurement readings.&nbsp;</p><p>The following steps were taught:</p><ul><li>Guess an interval number</li><li>Test the interval number</li><li>Revise interval number if needed</li><li>Label intervals</li><li>Calculate total by adding larger intervals with smaller to identify the total measurement shown</li><li>At times, Lucy was required to find the sum of three large numbers</li></ul><p>Each layer of this working provided a good opportunity to practice working with and manipulating large numbers.</p><p>See Lucy\'s workbook for the tasks completed.</p>', NULL, '<p>Extra 15 minutes added to today\'s lesson as we make up a previously missed lesson.</p>', '2022-09-01 15:38:53', '2022-09-01 17:00:45'),
