(3165, '2022/09/05', '04:34 pm', '3', '7', 'Arlo Clark', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 5: i and y may say their second (long) sound at the end of a syllable', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Kilpattrick &nbsp;F1<br>OPR/WPR:u, y, th, i, s, w, l. &nbsp; Arlo has a hard time to pronounce th because he needs to physically see me putting my tongue between my teeth and remind him of how to say this sound. He is shaky at the 3 sounds of u.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Marking red book page 2.&nbsp;<br>morphology activity 2<br>rule review: rule5,6,with activity<br>SD: &nbsp;my, this, be<br>SD words sentence. Arlo usually can make good sentence yet his spelling needs improvements. &nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-05 16:34:06', '2022-09-06 15:32:32'),
