(3167, '2022/09/06', '08:44 am', '3', '7', 'Luna Shapiro', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilaptrick G2. Luna did really well with these! She had 80% accuracy (the most she\'s had on this set).</td></tr><tr><td>Word recognition: Fitzroy flashcards</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8,b h k m n p r sh th ee ow oo ch</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: m n r h p b&nbsp; g a c s qu sh ch</td></tr><tr><td>Luna independently chose to write both upper and lowercase for all her single letter phonograms. Her formation for all was perfect except for an \"s\" reversal!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Fitzroy #6</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: \"Words We Know\" words</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: N/A</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD -- Word\'s We\'ve Used: big bag top dig lid&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Luna misheard (?) bag as big and encoded accordingly, then did not recognise her mistake and assumed the word was big. I did not mention it and just repeated bag as the next word.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use spelling words in oral sentences: I can see a big cat. I can see a cat with a top. I can see a lady coming out of the grocery shop with a bag. I can see a dog coming to get into a jar but it has a very tight lid. I can see a builder digging a big hole.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: Fitzroy 5</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Luna saw that we had some Harry Potter magic builders out for the taking. She put two together while doing the Kilpatrick task. One with help, one independently. I chose to give her some time to work through this task even though it sounds frivolous, as she couldn\'t immediately see the connections between pieces. Without my interference, she identified her errors independently and&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Luna had an hour lesson today for the first time in the while. The morning session seemed to make her more focused and settled. She was quite happy to complete her tasks and needed much less bribery. I could also shorten the length of games without her noticing. I did give her a few intervals to do something of her choice, usually when she brought it up. This included putting together the HP figure and later drawing Hermione by copying the figure.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-09-06 08:44:33', '2022-09-13 16:42:29'),
(3168, '2022/09/06', '08:44 am', '3', '3', 'Max Shapiro', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-06 08:44:51', '2022-09-06 08:44:51'),
(3169, '2022/09/06', '03:32 pm', '3', '7', 'Sophie Mirowski', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick H</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-50</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: sh ng qu or er th ur ow oo&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: Create rule cards to use as prompts. Framed as a craft activity.</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 4 14 2 26</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD:among-tax</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Had a timeline on the board today with times and activities to see if that might keep Sophie engaged. I knew that she would be enthusiastic for \"craft time\", but there wasn\'t a noticeable difference in her trying to keep herself in check.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>The craft activity was a good idea, but I don\'t know if the time we spent on it justifies the activity. Perhaps if we only do the last fifteen minutes? Gives her something to look forward to and a time frame to work in (we have to get through this job, this job, and this job before working on our craft activities).</td></tr><tr><td>We didn\'t have time for spelling, which was disappointing. I\'m really struggling at the moment to get Sophie through as much work as I want to.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-09-06 15:32:58', '2022-09-06 17:57:36'),
