(3172, '2022/09/06', '04:33 pm', '3', '7', 'Shay Douglas', 'Chemistry', 'Chemistry', 'Chemistry', 'Chemistry', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Subject: Chemistry</td></tr><tr><td>Focus: Shay\'s Chemistry Homework</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>This was a tricky lesson with Shay today. He hadn\'t given me a heads up about what he wanted to cover (moles and stoichiometric equations) and I was totally lost! It wasn\'t a total disaster and we managed to work out some of the problems, but definitely not my finest hour. I don\'t think I ever even covered this in school! He\'s working on extended problems now.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-09-06 16:33:47', '2022-09-06 18:05:21'),
(3173, '2022/09/06', '05:06 pm', '3', '7', 'Callum Coulson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - Precisely say, write and read words in Section M', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>kilpatrick i<br>OPR/WPR: ou, th, ch, i, ui, u, er, o, ow. Callum struggles with 3 sounds for u. He needs more exposure to words that have ui, ow, and ou.&nbsp;<br>rule review 19, 29<br>SD: month, chil dren, child, build, built, un der stand, fol low.<br>read for spelling and reading; &nbsp; &nbsp; understanding words and word class; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br>complex sentence subbie activity<br>writing process step 3-revising,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-06 17:07:50', '2022-09-07 10:05:03'),
(3174, '2022/09/06', '05:26 pm', '3', '7', 'Lucy Crosswell', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Neve Mitchell', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick H</td></tr><tr><td>Lucy did okay with the set, but did make some errors.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8, 27-38</td></tr><tr><td>WPR:&nbsp; a o e u sh th ow oo ch ar</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule 17 Review -- Create rule card.</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review: 17 (using above activity)</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Rule 17 Review Worksheet</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use words in sentences x2.</td></tr><tr><td>Lucy wrote the sentence \"I am a bit of a mess.\" When reading the sentence aloud to me, she stumbled over her words and when she reached \'of a\' said, \"Oh, I have two words I don\'t need.\" She \'corrected\' her sentence to \"I am a bit mess.\" When she then read the sentence aloud again, she exclaimed: \"Dammit, I needed those words!\"&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>I let Lucy work through this thought process on her own to see if she would self-correct, rather than jumping in to point out when she had made a mistake.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>In general quite a typical lesson for Lucy. She is still showing signs of struggle with the concept of rules. Hopefully using her rule prompt cards we can return to the Ayres list soon. Need to first cover rules 5/6 (next week). Then Ayres list, potentially alongside introducing SFE? Or can teach SFe when it comes up in the Ayres list? Potentially -- use SFe on Rule Page 1 before holidays, then can cover it in the Ayres list after T4 resumes.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-09-06 17:26:54', '2022-09-13 17:19:40'),
