(3177, '2022/09/07', '07:46 am', '3', '7', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 28: Read ed as /ed/ if the base word ends in d or t, as /d after a voiced consonant, /t/ after an unvoiced consonant', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Tardy', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Luke did great siting down and learning today. Callan was sick so we had an one on one session. He did not move around until the game. He can still be impatient when he gets something wrong but he handled it well today.&nbsp;</p><p>Luke-OPR/WPR: or, c, ie, ed, y, o, s<br>Rule review: 6, 17,24,28.29<br>SD: en trance, im por tance, im por tant, car ried, car ry, loss. Luke did not know the word importance(inportants)<br>online verb game for Luke<br>Writing activities: step 1-background reading and step 2-composing parts of bits.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-07 07:46:47', '2022-09-07 10:10:06'),
