(3179, '2022/09/07', '09:00 am', '3', '7', 'Callan Bartlett', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - Precisely say, write and read words in Section J', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callan is sick this week so we had a zoom session and he always does great listening and sitting. Callan is very good with concepts of parts of speech and he can usually understand concepts quite well and be able to finish all tasks on his own. He also has good language for sentence writing. He can compose complex sentence that contrains advanced vocabularies. We will mostly need to help him with his phonograms and spelling skill.&nbsp;</p><p>PA: Kilpatrick&nbsp;<br>i</p><p>OPR/WPR: c, a, s, ar, ou, th, ee, i, l, u. He is shaky at ou(aw)<br>Rule review: job 2<br>SD: cast, card, south, deep, in side, blue<br>Sd compound sentence<br>online noun game for Callan</p><p>Read out loud other students\' writing in our writing activity. Callan\'s oral fluency needs some work on.&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-07 09:00:47', '2022-09-07 10:18:44'),
