(3181, '2022/09/07', '03:30 pm', '3', '7', 'Max Brookfield', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Neve Mitchell', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilatrick E3</td></tr><tr><td>Fitzroy CVC word flashcards.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 1-8, 27-38, u , w</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: c ow ou ar ch ck ay w u er&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Fitzroy #8</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S: Current Ayres Column</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule review:</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD:&nbsp; was pond as picnic bell well fell&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use spelling words in sentences: \"I was in the pond but then the bell rang. On my way back I fell in a well.\" Max came up with this sentence and had me dictate it back to him because he couldn\'t remember it in its entirety.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Oral Fluency: Fitzroy 8 untimed. Max had to sound out the names many times. He also sounded out other words such as let. He was stilted in his reading but had good expression. With increased fluency I think he will make an enjoyable reader to listen to. Max also made some good connections and observations about the text.</td></tr><tr><td>Reading: SCORE 2.1</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Max was better than last week, still quite distracted though. He was less wriggly but tended to go off on tangents. It was also tricky to get the most out of spelling because he kept stopping halfway through writing a word to talk to me about something.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-09-07 15:30:46', '2022-09-07 16:30:26'),
