(3201, '2022/09/12', '03:28 pm', '3', '8', 'Thomas Johnson', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 5: i and y may say their second (long) sound at the end of a syllable', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>I might need to have some seperate time with Mia and Thomas next term as they two have shown lots of difference on their strength and weakness. Mia is good at handwriting and spelling. She can also naturally read in simple readings yet she tends to struggle with retaining the knowledge. Thomas is smart and can usually comprehend quicker yet he needs some more work on his handwriting and spelling. He also needs help with reading.</p><p>&nbsp;Kilpattrick F &nbsp;with timer</p><p>OPR/WPR u, th, i, s, y, ou. They both are shaky at ou<br>morphology activity 7 for Mia. Tom-written focus because Thomas tends to write letters from bottom to top, and from back to front.&nbsp;<br>rule 17 with activity will<br>SD: but, this, all, your, you, out &nbsp;Thomas wrote owt for out.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;compose sentences using SD words.</p><p>reading: ‘hey Jack’- blue. Thomas needs a lot of practice on his spelling and oral fluency.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-12 15:28:41', '2022-09-13 16:28:28'),
