(3233, '2022/09/14', '08:42 am', '3', '8', 'Callan Bartlett', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 19: i may say /I/ and o may say /O/ when followed by two consonants', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callan is very dedicated to his learning and he can usually retain concept very well. He understands rules, parts of speech and sentence structures. He mostly needs help with word spelling as he can be confused with similar phonograms. Callan can be taltive when he is with me alone and sometimes I need to pull him back to the tasks from chatting.&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR: c, o, ow, ay, a, g, ou, i, ar. Callan is confused with the usage of ow and ou.&nbsp;<br>Rule review: job 1, 18, 19<br>SD: post, town, stay, grand, out side, dark, band. He wrote toun for town.&nbsp;<br>Read R&amp;S<br>Explain/discuss the meanings and word class of analysed words.<br>online adj game for Callan<br>Sentence structure: He understands the elements of complex sentence yet his sentence tend to be less expressive, which means he does not use adjs or other expressive words in his sentences.&nbsp;</p><p>Writing: write a paragragh for The World of Drastura.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-14 08:42:37', '2022-09-14 08:49:23'),
