(3267, '2022/09/16', '04:29 pm', '3', '8', 'Nate Betros', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: 27-70</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 27-50</td></tr><tr><td>Errors: oi (reversed), aw</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 29 6 17 26 4</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: sorry-study</td></tr><tr><td>Read R&amp;S</td></tr><tr><td>Explain/discuss the markings and meanings of analysed words.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Rule Intro: NA</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use Ayres words in sentences and model on SBB for parts of speech. Recap some parts of speech where necessary -- including object nouns, prepositions. Nate needed the refresher. Possibly as some homework?</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>Notes</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Nate was good this lesson! He had brought in some picture books to share that he really likes, which has given me some ideas for narrative writing. We talked about it briefly and Nate mentioned being interested in writing the \"unofficial third book\" in this picture book series, but I think I would like to encourage him to come up with his own ideas. He may actually be interested in a personification lesson since he tends to do that with a lot of objects/concepts himself already (I hadn\'t thought of this before...!).</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-09-16 16:29:06', '2022-09-16 17:43:09'),
(3268, '2022/09/16', '04:20 pm', '3', '1', 'Freya McIver', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Essay Structure', 'See Notes', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week One, Lesson One</td></tr><tr><td>Friday, 29 July 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Essay writing - Sushi</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Freya brought along a partially completed task from school, where she was asked to write a passage about sushi for her Japanese class. This was a pretty flexible task, as the teacher was seemingly just filling in time! I decided to run with it, though, and we spent the lesson using the Writing Process principles to create a well-fleshed out plan for a hypothetical sushi essay.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week One, Lesson One</td></tr><tr><td>Friday, 29 July 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-16 16:38:36', '2022-09-16 16:40:11'),
(3269, '2022/09/16', '04:40 pm', '3', '3', 'Freya McIver', 'English', 'English Literature', 'novel study', 'Character Study/Analysis', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Four, Lesson Three</td></tr><tr><td>Friday, 12 August 2022</td></tr><tr><td>PA: M1 p.223 &amp; Donah #63</td></tr><tr><td>Morphology - use word matrix then discuss meanings and changed meanings.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Analysis of narrative text using Juno\'s Writing Program lessons</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Freya didn\'t bring anything from school again today, so I had to pull together a lesson plan pretty quickly! Did a PA and MA - Freya totally fine with these. She filled out a word matrix sheet, building words from the base \"struct\". Good convo around this and what changes with prefixes or suffixes. Then moved onto looking at narrative text and an analysis. Used \"The Strange Library\" excerpt and talked through the prompts on the accompanying analysis page.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Four, Lesson Three</td></tr><tr><td>Friday, 12 August 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-16 16:41:21', '2022-09-16 16:44:30'),
