(3275, '2022/09/17', '04:13 pm', '3', '7', 'Lachlan  Smith', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Seven</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 5 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>PAIRED</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Recap sentence structures (booklet)<br>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Continued sentence structure booklets. Boys are really bored with this task and don\'t seem to enjoy it! As a result, it\'s a bit of an effort to keep them engaged and make sure that this is a productive time. Regardless, we did get through a bit today and had good convos about sentence structure. Neither Connor nor Lachlan can confidently tell me about any sentence structures or parts of speech, but in application can actually demonstrate some knowledge. E.g. when marking the PoS in sentences, both boys were fine working independently. Connor was especially distracted today and kept trying to talk over me or to me - I had to get a bit snappy once or twice when they repeatedly ignored my instructions or weren\'t listening to what I was saying. Can be especially frustrating as I know we spent so long on sentences in the past.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>LS INDIV</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick G2</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #32</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: oy aw u ai au ti th er sh ee ow ou oo ch ar</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: oy aw ai au ti th er&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 22, 4, 11, 14</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. P - spend, enjoy, awful, awe, usual, complaint, auto, vacation</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use \'vacation\' and \'vacate\' in sentences</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Lachlan was a little flat today (especially in the paired portion of the session), but I actually think that Aimee observing was useful. She laughed at his jokes and generally uplifted the mood, which was great! Lachlan did a great job with PA, MA, phonos and SD. With a couple of SD words, he was almost textbook in the structure of his responses - very helpful for Aimee. He\'s starting to apply morphology knowledge to spelling words with more ease, so now the focus is on encouraging him to do it independently. I also think that a greater exposure to more unfamiliar words would be positive for Lachie.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Seven</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 5 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-17 16:14:20', '2022-09-17 16:17:27'),
