(3280, '2022/09/19', '08:40 am', '3', '9', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Nine, Lesson One</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 19 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: by, have, are, had, over, must, make</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick E2 set 8</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #22</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR: y ar er dge igh ey o</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: y ar er dge igh ey o</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 4, 5, 6</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. A-G: by, have, are, had, over, must, make</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Use spelling words in sentences</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Read a Pip &amp; Tim</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Game</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Home support pack</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Lewis was a little wobbly to start - pulling out Uno cards and asking to play a game pretty constantly. Once we got into the phonograms he settled a bit, and I was especially impressed with his focus during the SD. Struggled to articulate understanding of rules 4, 5, 6, but able to apply knowledge with some prompting. Lewis was really concentrating deeply during SD, and even though we did more words than he anticipated, he didn\'t even notice! I was very impressed. It seems like the structure and routine is settling for him. He struggled to use his spelling words in sentences, so needed a little prompting. He dictated one sentence for me to write in his book, then he wrote another himself. Read a Pip and Tim, then played a quick game of Uno to finish.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Nine, Lesson One</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 19 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-19 08:40:15', '2022-09-19 14:21:39'),
