(3309, '2022/09/21', '08:26 am', '3', '8', 'Molly  Jackson', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-21 08:26:59', '2022-09-21 08:26:59'),
(3310, '2022/09/21', '12:05 pm', '3', '9', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - Precisely say, write and read words in Section N', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Brock returned to our tutoring today after 2 week\'s illness and he was doing ok. He tends to be frustrated when he is not farmiiar with the task we were doing yet he usually follows instructions well to finish what he has to do.&nbsp;</p><p>Kilpatrick H1<br>OPR/WPR: ee, u, th, w, ou, ng, ai, He was a bit confused with the written form of ou.<br><br>rule review rule 30, 32, job 1</p><p>SD: need, thus, wom an wom en, young, fair fare. Brock did not know the word thus and he was frustrated.&nbsp;<br>read for spelling<br>read for reading&nbsp;<br>Writing: step 1 and step 2. We have been reading and collecting information for his writing for The World of Dratsura. He engkoys this imaginative writing.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-21 12:07:49', '2022-09-21 12:14:12'),
(3311, '2022/09/21', '12:14 pm', '3', '9', 'Callan Bartlett', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - Precisely say, write and read words in Section J', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Callan is so dedicated to his learning yet sometimes when we chat about other things, he usually keeps on talking and needs to be pulled into the session again. He likes reading.&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR oa, e, s, ea, u, Callan needed reminders of oa and ea but he is good at writing them down.&nbsp;</p><p>SD: game, boat, rest, east, son sun, help, hard. He needed help with the phonogram ea in the word east.&nbsp;</p><p>Read R&amp;S<br>Explain/discuss the meanings and word class of analysed words.<br>add suffix/preffix: hard+er</p><p>online adv game for Callan<br>reading : C-reference . We went up to level 2 fiction paragraghs.&nbsp;<br><br><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-21 12:15:56', '2022-09-21 12:22:25'),
(3312, '2022/09/21', '12:30 pm', '3', '9', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spelling Dictation - Precisely say, write and read words in Section P', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Luke tends to be quite anxious each session and he usually needs time to stand up and walk around or play sports. He enjoys games with Callan yet he is a bit holding back for making friends with Callan. He can be quite competitive, and he can be very distractive too.&nbsp;</p><p>PA: Kilpatrick&nbsp;<br>i<br>Luke-OPR/WPR: u, i, ay, ai, e, ee, s, g<br>Rule review: rule 4, sfe 5<br>SD: for tune &nbsp;em pire, may or, wait, de gree, pris on, en gine &nbsp;Luke is quite advanced for his spelling skills now and he can usually write these words without help.&nbsp;<br>Read R&amp;S<br>Explain/discuss the meanings and word class of analysed words.<br>add suffix/preffix &nbsp;prison+er<br>online adj game for Luke</p><p><br>reading : C-reference. We did level two fiction paragragh today and Luke had a hard time to find key words in a paragragh.&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-21 12:31:38', '2022-09-21 12:38:19'),
