(3321, '2022/09/22', '07:45 am', '3', '6', 'Chester  Vincent', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Campbell Jepson', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-22 07:45:40', '2022-09-22 07:45:40'),
(3322, '2022/09/22', '08:11 am', '3', '9', 'Lucy Fairbrother', 'Mathematics', 'Number & Place Value', 'Mental Computation', 'Mad Minute Maths - Facts to 100', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>The lesson today continued with the NSPM workbook solving worded problems requiring conversion of units between grams and kilograms. &nbsp;Lucy was completely independent in modelling, workings, calculations and conversions. &nbsp;Very solid workings. &nbsp;Lucy takes time to process and on occasions appears uncertain about what to do next, but when she asks the question to clarify, is accurate in her thinking.</p><p>Key Maths Essential Resources: Review expansion and simplification of fractions - Numeration Concept Cluster 4, Lesson 1, Independent Practice 4, Level II AND Lesson 2 - to complete next lesson.</p>', NULL, '<p>Today is a public holiday. &nbsp;Lucy\'s lesson was held at 8:00 at Kingston AR office. &nbsp;</p>', '2022-09-22 08:15:41', '2022-09-22 09:05:36'),
(3323, '2022/09/22', '08:49 am', '3', '9', 'Lewis Prevost', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete syllable from three syllable word - Kilpatrick Level E', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Nine, Lesson Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 22 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: street, say, come, hand, ring, live, live</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick E2 set 9</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #23</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: ee ay ng dge ey igh</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 18</td></tr><tr><td>SD: Sec. A-G: street, say, come, hand, ring, live, live</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>ID subject and verb in sentences</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Home support pack</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Lewis struggled to settle today, and I really had to work to get him to listen and respond to my instructions. Fine with the actual work itself i.e. PA, MA, phonos, but behaviour was a little tricky this morning. Normally Lewis understands when it\'s time to stop chatting or moving and start working, but today he really didn\'t settle easily into the work. Really good with SD esp once we got into the groove. After SD LP wanted to draw and he\'d done really well with SD so I gave him a couple minutes of drawing time while I prepared the next task. I then asked him to read given sentences (well within his scope of decoding), ID the subject noun, action verb, then the spelling words I\'d used. For some reason Lewis was REALLY resistant to reading the sentences, and fully refused, saying \"no. I\'m not going to read it ever\". He also didn\'t want to read a reader instead, or handwrite sentences, despite my reasoning with him and explaining that they were easy. Eventually he decided that he would read the sentences if I \"did the circling\", and we got through two sentences (easily). Will revisit these next week.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Nine, Lesson Two</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 22 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-22 08:49:09', '2022-09-22 09:49:32'),
(3324, '2022/09/22', '09:14 am', '3', '4', 'Angel King', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Delete final sound in word or final blend - Kilpatrick Level I', 'Laree Thorsby', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', '<p>Phonological Awareness - Kilpatrick D2 - nil difficulties at all. &nbsp;I1 - Mixed Level Page 182. &nbsp;Reviewed previously completed set. &nbsp;Same errors made. &nbsp;When scaffolding sound placement on fingers made this a fully accessible task for Angel. &nbsp;More practice needed on substituting initial sound, and deleting first sound of initial consonant blend. &nbsp;Reviewed tricky manipulations a second time using finger scaffold and for a third time without finger scaffold. &nbsp;Angel became increasingly accurate and fluent and did not need finger scaffold for the third practice.</p><p>OPR - using cards in folder prepared in past lessons. &nbsp;Check for understanding quesitons. &nbsp;Discussed the two jobs of y - consonant and vowel, and Rule 25 - ck after a vowel saying its first sound. &nbsp;Dicussed vowel sounds/letters and identify the sound of the vowel being made in duck and quack.</p><p>Discussed the spelling of ‘you’ - ending in a u when english words can\'t do that. &nbsp;Looked up etymology (thou and ye) and discussed the ‘w’ helper letter (being a “double u”).</p><p>WPR - ea, ck, y, oa, a, k, qu, e, z, ee, t, i, o - midpoint focus - difficulty recalling many of these phonograms including z, qu.</p><p>Spelling Dictation: rock, rocket, thick, thicket, tick, ticket.</p><p>Sentence composition: I gave the ticket to the rocket. &nbsp;(What if you were to buy a ticket?) &nbsp;I bought a ticket to go on the rocket. &nbsp;(Turn the sentence into a compound sentence.) &nbsp;Lizzy, wanted to get a ticket for free. &nbsp;(Prompted) &nbsp;I bought a ticket to go on the rocket, but I did not have enough money for two.</p><p>* Play a game for next lesson &nbsp;(See Lottie\'s folder)</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-22 09:14:02', '2022-09-22 10:13:33'),
(3325, '2022/09/22', '03:25 pm', '3', '8', 'Reuben Shelverton', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-22 15:25:54', '2022-09-22 15:25:54'),
