(3343, '2022/09/26', '03:42 pm', '3', '10', 'Connor McLaren', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Ten</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 26 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #36</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: ei th er ur ou ti or ay ee</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule review: 12, 4, 29, 24, 6, 15</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: particular, affair, course, coarse, neither, local, further, serious</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Connor did really well today. He was super calm and focused, and I could see that he was taking great care with his handwriting and work today. Very impressed! Even though he was late, we got through heaps of work.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Write a compound, interrogative, complex, declarative sentences using the word visit as a noun, wait as a verb and fortune</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Lachlan struggled with this activity, so I spent some time working one-on-one with him. Connor needed a recap of sentence structures, but seemed to be fine once he got going. I recapped all three structures with Lachlan, working from simple through to complex.&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Ten</td></tr><tr><td>Monday, 26 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-26 15:42:38', '2022-09-26 17:14:45'),
