(3347, '2022/09/26', '05:15 pm', '3', '10', 'Arlo Clark', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 19: i may say /I/ and o may say /O/ when followed by two consonants', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR: o, i, x, oy, s, oo, y, a. Arlo needs more work with oo<br>New phonograms: her first nurse works early. ---We will need more practice on this.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p><p><br>rule review: 19, 5, 6. Arlo can retain these rules very well and he shared with his mother too.&nbsp;<br>SD: &nbsp;old, six, boy, book, by, had<br>2nd reading hot dog bob. He can read this story fluently and naturally.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-26 17:15:48', '2022-09-28 11:46:53'),
(3348, '2022/09/27', '07:51 am', '3', '1', 'Millicent Fyshe', 'Mathematical Assessment', 'Waddington Module', 'Module 1 - 15', 'Module 1 - 15', 'Sang Nguyen', 'Achieved', 'In Progress', 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>Millie had been given Waddington assessment module 4 and 5.</p><p>&nbsp;Module 5 outcomes:</p><p>Millie is pretty confident in number concepts with lower number. She is also confident identifying shapes.</p><p>Millie seems to be confused by the question and didn\'t understand the question and jumped right into solving questions while she didn\'t get them.</p><p>Millie needs to practice more in the concepts of tens and units.</p><p>At the end of the lesson, educator went through the assessment with Millie and worked through the question that she struggled.</p><p>We had worked on the concepts of tens and units. Millie was getting more confident with the concept and she was able to solve the related questions.</p><p>Millie was also catching up on the concepts of ordinal number and was able to answer the practice question correctly at the end of the lesson.</p><p>Millie and educator also went through the concepts of small, smaller and smallest.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-27 07:51:55', '2022-09-27 09:04:59'),
(3349, '2022/09/27', '09:11 am', '3', '10', 'Luna Shapiro', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Neve Mitchell', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick G2</td></tr><tr><td>Word recognition: Fitzroy flashcards</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Showed big and Luna said&nbsp; \"We already said did\"</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR:&nbsp; 1-8,b h k m n p r sh th ee ow oo&nbsp; ch ay ai ar oy oi er ck</td></tr><tr><td>WPR: 1-8 (prompt clockface for d, s), b h m n p r sh (prompt for clockface)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SD: bag bed den dot big</td></tr><tr><td>Prompt for handwriting formation before Luna writes b/d. Bat/ball analogy is working for her (she must be using it at school?)</td></tr><tr><td>I made some mix ups with my b formation and asked Luna for help. She said, \"okay, I\'ll help you\" and wrote a d with a little arrow to help show me the direction of my circle.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Write and illustrate a story. Luna was determined to keep going with her book from last time, but she had lost it at home! She rewrote her title today \"The dog went to the vet.\"</td></tr><tr><td>Luna did a great job with leaving finger spaces, precise and accurate handwriting, and using full stops.&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>She also did really well with sounding out her words. \"How do I spell went? Wait, I know! w/e/n/t\"</td></tr><tr><td>She was also very conscious of her spelling, often asking for help with unfamiliar words (they, waited). In waited she asked \"is that the ai digraph?\"</td></tr><tr><td>She ALSO kept reading back through her work to make sure it made sense and she hadn\'t missed any words!!!</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>SCORE</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>I am really proud of Luna and how she\'s going with her tutoring. I don\'t think it will eve be a \'one and done\' scenario, but with continual support to keep her out of undesirable habits I think we can keep her on the right track. Hopefully her ability will also mean that she keeps her enjoyment of reading and writing (instead of losing interest like Max).</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', NULL, '2022-09-27 09:24:22', '2022-09-27 09:54:09'),
