(3359, '2022/09/28', '07:25 am', '3', '10', 'Brock Smith', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phongram Review (OPR) - Cards 1 > 70', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR 1-70. &nbsp;Brock will need more work with phonograms &nbsp;ie, ei, ea, ui, ew, si, ci, eigh as he barely see them now due to his vacabulary level and grade.&nbsp;<br><br>rule review 29 of fer</p><p>SD: dol lar, eve ning, plan, broke, feel, sure, sug ar<br>read for spelling<br>read for reading</p><p>Writing: step 1 and step 2 the tale of Drastura&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-28 07:26:02', '2022-09-28 11:48:40'),
(3360, '2022/09/28', '07:27 am', '3', '10', 'Callan Bartlett', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 19: i may say /I/ and o may say /O/ when followed by two consonants', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>OPR/WPR: a, c, o, er, i,&nbsp;</p><p>Rule review 19<br>SD: race, cov er, fire,wire,ture, age,gold<br>add suffix/preffix Callan is good at this. recovery</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>reading : C-reference &nbsp;He struggles with word means hence he could not summarize the main topic in the fiction paragrgh we were doing&nbsp;</p><p>writing -drawing artwork introduction. We did not have time to write.&nbsp;<br><br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-28 07:28:06', '2022-09-28 11:51:15'),
(3361, '2022/09/28', '09:01 am', '3', '10', 'Luke  Vandenberg', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Language Rules (Pronunciation/Spelling/Grammar)', 'Rule 17: Double the l, f, s or z at the end of syllable with a single one vowel saying its first sound', 'See Notes', 'Yina Peng', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<p>As Luke mentioned today that he just moved house lately and last night was the first night at the new house so he does not feel well rencently. He did not want any work today and spent nearlt 20 minutes for his artwork drawing idea so he did not have time to write a paragragh. He looked anxious and quiet at the beginning, but after a soccer game with Callan, he got better.&nbsp;</p><p>Luke-OPR/WPR: i, s, gu, e, ar, ai, y, or<br>Rule review: rule 4, 6,17<br>SD: visit, guest, guess, de part ment, ob tain, fam i ly, fa vor Luke is ready to move up to a higher level for his spelling dictation.&nbsp;<br>reading : C-reference &nbsp;writing -drawing artwork introduction<br>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, '2022-09-28 09:02:22', '2022-09-28 11:57:22'),
