(3381, '2022/09/30', '07:46 am', '3', '10', 'Archie Lester', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute vowel phoneme - Kilpatrick Level J', 'Naomi Wright', 'In Progress', NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', '<p>PA - Section J Set 6. &nbsp;Archie needed to think intentionally about the sounds in some of these words&nbsp;</p><p>Sandra Donah: &nbsp;Activity 20.</p><p>Spelling dictation - ‘qu’ words. &nbsp;Archie had some difficulty with the ‘ck’ in quick and quack &nbsp;needing reminding. &nbsp;He also needed prompting with SFe.</p><p>Write a simple sentence using the words ‘queen’ and ‘quack’ - include an interjection (inter = between, ject = to throw, ion = noun - a word that throws emotion/feeling into the sentence. &nbsp;Add a related compound sentence. &nbsp;Archie had to consider tense.&nbsp;</p><p>Review where there and here connections to prepare for encoding ‘were’</p><p>Review sentence elements and spelling rules that need to be considered when recording the sentence composed below: &nbsp;Wow!The queen had lots of ducks that quack. &nbsp;The queen\'s ducks were fat and unhealthy, but now they are dead and rotting with maggots coming out of their eye sockets.</p><p>Review punctuation used and reason why needed, clauses and information elements communicating to the reader.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-30 07:46:30', '2022-09-30 09:58:49'),
(3382, '2022/09/30', '01:41 pm', '3', '1', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Adelaide and I conducted a regular lesson, but of importance was the Adelaide opened up today about her struggles with dyslexia. Mum was happy for us to go through a plan going forward that would cater to her strengths and gently deal with difficulties in a practical way. This included:</p><p>Dyslexia Reading Strategies:<br>Line by line divider</p><p>Further planning:<br>Phonograms<br>Inferences<br>Vocabulary</p>', '2022-09-30 13:42:25', '2022-09-30 13:44:56'),
(3383, '2022/09/30', '01:47 pm', '3', '2', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Oral Phonogram Review (OPR) - Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>For her writing task, Adelaide was encouraged to embark on some fantasy creative writing! Her unedited version is below - we then addressed the issues in her spelling afterwards.</p><p>“Maggie was staning ontop of the tall,old church buliding, her leges slowly being grabed and spun in the vines. Maggies emerald, summer gren eyes glistening in the hot sun like diamonds. Maggie waves her hands in the air signling for her army to “fall back, leave the poor crecher akkone!” maggie cies to the ary bellow her towering shadow. Suddenly her ears pick up the sound of donald and hunter arguing at eachother. Maggie reaches for her staf and telapad waist she cales her pet dogan. “Come her boy lets go down” shouts maggie to her pet chile.”woof”says chile as he chofs out his smoky barck. Maggie glides down to the two &nbsp;flushed men. “Its clarified as a crime to kill insent anials you know!” shouted maggie.”</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>OPR/WPR: /ew ui or au aw/</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2022-09-30 13:49:44', '2022-09-30 13:52:16'),
(3384, '2022/09/30', '01:59 pm', '3', '3', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Analysis of word structure and application of learned concepts (sounds, phonograms, rules)', 'Spell Check', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Adelaide worked on her humanities assignment today with minimal input - she was confident regarding her comprehension of the task, but just needed some help editing!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>We also continued on her fantasy writing task. Unedited version below, which was discussed and edited for grammar and spelling:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Maggie herd hunters quick and suspicious footsteps speeding off into the wild woods, waislt she was rounding up chilly as well as inhaste to put chilies tutu on. Her large ears pick up the noise.”woof!” barkes chile “ shhh calm down boy i am trying to listen to hunter.” “gruuu” snarles chile in discuss to hunters name. maggie wandered towards the sound of hunters footsteps. “Wo!” maggie fastly places her hand over chilies mouth as he lets out a playful bark. Maggie hid behind an old brick house. “ you ok there luv” askes the homoeowner maggie runs of as she relizes that hunter was heading to the wild woods. “ chili come here, today might finally be the day i get to eet peter i have always wanted to be his friend!” maggie slowly creeps up to hunter but stopped in her trackes suddenly.</p>', '2022-09-30 13:59:38', '2022-09-30 14:01:39'),
(3385, '2022/09/30', '01:59 pm', '3', '4', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Accurate use of analysed words', 'Spell Check', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>This week\'s lesson was very similar to last week! Adelaide finished off her humanities assignment from last week. It is noted that she is extremely high-achieving and ambitious, which causes her to aim higher in an idealistic manner - sometimes, given her workload and time frame, this is not practical! She then ends up being quite stressed. Study skills lesson might be in order.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Her entry this week for the fantasy narrative is below, pre-editing:</p><p>Maggie turns around to see Fern waving excitedly at her. Maggie drops her telepad and her magic crystal staff, hand crafted as agirft from the earth fires she got when she was 17. Thehistoric wood rattled as it hi the floor and the crystal sine disappeared as magie let go. “Hi fern i did not know you where there. i waas just following hunter because he was taking peter off to his leson and i realy,desprtly want to be his friend, but i got sidtrcked and chillie went after hunter. You know how chilli is he wants nothing to do with-!” “woof, grrr” chilli growls and snarls”oh no” shouted maggie.” i am so sorry fern i gotta go bye” chillies size &nbsp;multiplied, the once cute, adorable and cuddly friendly chilli had disappeared at insed there stood a “gacarancha!” screamed the croud. Maggie grabbed her staff and started talking to chillie and casting her spell.<br>&nbsp;</p>', '2022-09-30 14:05:16', '2022-09-30 14:14:46'),
(3386, '2022/09/30', '02:05 pm', '3', '5', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - High Frequency Vocabulary', 'Accurate use of analysed words', 'Spell Check', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, we extended Adelaide\'s current fantasy narrative project to Worldbuilding. This involved character creation of other species and forayed lightly into Informative Narrative. Adelaide has a very strong author\'s voice, so this task was quite enjoyable! We worked further on spelling and linking her ideas with the ongoing plot as she can be quite distracted by new ideas and forget the initial purpose of the activity.</p>', '2022-09-30 14:19:59', '2022-09-30 14:27:45'),
(3387, '2022/09/30', '02:20 pm', '3', '6', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Essay Structure', 'See Notes', 'Juno Galang', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Adelaide worked on another humanities assignment today. It was a Mega fauna report detailing how they went extinct. She originally had 3 arguments, however needed help refining the third argument as it was the same as the first one, just worded differently. In the end, we composed 3 arguments:</p><p>1. Climate change<br>No food, change of environment</p><p>2. Hunted by humans</p><p>3. Loss of water source</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Adelaide is just starting on writing using the TEEL structure, so we went through a quick overview of Topic sentences and Evidence!</p>', '2022-09-30 14:28:09', '2022-09-30 14:34:14'),
(3388, '2022/09/30', '02:29 pm', '3', '10', 'Molly  Jackson', 'English', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Neve Mitchell', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-30 14:29:41', '2022-09-30 14:29:41'),
(3389, '2022/09/30', '02:28 pm', '3', '7', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Systematic Phonics - Sounds/Symbols (phonograms)', 'Precisely say and write common phonograms (include purpose - to connect speech sounds to their written symbol which helps with reading, writing and spelling)', 'Written Phonogram Review (WPR) with Handwriting Focus - Delayed Feedback > Various Phonograms (see notes)', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today was more of a standard literacy lesson! We did phonogram work: /ow ou ough/ and SD in relation:</p><ul><li>though<br>through<br>rough<br>cough<br>thought<br>drought<br>dough<br>sourdough<br>thought<br>thoughtful</li></ul><p>We also continued her narrative story, with Aimee here to observe!</p>', '2022-09-30 14:57:06', '2022-09-30 15:06:57'),
(3390, '2022/09/30', '02:57 pm', '3', '8', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute vowel phoneme - Kilpatrick Level J', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'Achieved', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Today, Adelaide tacked the /ough/ phonogram for the second time! She did very well, but struggled a little with any ending sounds after /ough/.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Kilpatrick J</li><li>/ow ou ough/<br><ul><li>though<br>through<br>thought<br>rough<br>cough<br>drought</li></ul></li><li>4 sounds of \"er\"<br><ul><li>earth, fur, number, girl, world</li></ul></li><li>Fiction writing<ul><li>Editing:<br>Capital letters</li></ul></li></ul>', '2022-09-30 15:08:52', '2022-09-30 15:12:15'),
(3391, '2022/09/30', '03:08 pm', '3', '9', 'Adelaide Brown', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Cancelled - No Show', 'N/A', 'Cancelled', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-30 15:16:15', '2022-09-30 15:16:15'),
(3392, '2022/09/30', '03:16 pm', '3', '10', 'Adelaide Brown', 'English', 'Writing - Paragraph & Composition Construction', 'Essay Structure', 'See Notes', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Adelaide worked on her English assginment today (due tomorrow)! It is a persuasive text. Similar to the last essay, Adelaide had no trouble understanding the question, but needed refinement of her arguments as they were similar and repetitive. We were able to identify three separate arguments. We also addressed TEEL with more detail, as this structure has not been fully explained to Adelaide in relation to actually planning and organising her information in this way!</p>', '2022-09-30 15:16:44', '2022-09-30 15:19:13'),
(3393, '2022/09/30', '03:16 pm', '3', '1', 'Nina Grun', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute vowel phoneme - Kilpatrick Level J', 'Juno Galang', 'Achieved', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Phonemic Awareness</p><ul><li>Kilpatrick Level J</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed at a regular pace</li><li>The student found some difficulty with tip to tap</li><li>However, the student showed confidence with the rest of the task once the difficulty was explained</li></ul><p>OPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /oa, ck, wh, ng/</li><li>Self-Corrected /wh/</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed at a regular pace. Nina was tentatively familiar with some of these but needed clarification!</li></ul><p>WPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /oa, ck, wh, ng/</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly and perfectly.</li></ul><p>Morphology</p><ul><li>Base word Donah 10</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly and without error</li></ul><p>Spelling Dictation<br>Rules: 2, 3, 7</p><ul><li>page</li><li>face</li><li>cage</li><li>ice</li><li>age</li><li>dice</li><li>large</li><li>space</li><li>huge (hyge)</li><li>dance<ul><li>Self-Corrected \"huge\" after prompting</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed at a regular pace</li><li>The student found some difficulty with /y/ vs /u/</li><li>However, the student showed confidence with the functions of SFE in jobs 2 &amp; 3.</li></ul></li></ul><p>Oral Fluency<br>Passage: 200<br>Line: 72</p><ul><li>Errors \"tortoise\" \"predators\" \"cause\"</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed at a regular pace</li><li>The student found some difficulty with some of the longer words.</li><li>However, the student showed confidence in prosody!<br>&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2022-09-30 15:22:10', '2022-09-30 16:09:34'),
