(3397, '2022/09/30', '03:34 pm', '3', '8', 'Archie Seelig', 'Mathematics', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Madeleine Foster', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'No', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-09-30 15:34:22', '2022-09-30 15:34:22'),
(3398, '2022/09/30', '03:22 pm', '3', '2', 'Nina Grun', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>/oa ng wh ck/<br>SD<br>goat<br>long<br>why<br>back<br>r. 23<br>ck is only at the end of words</p><p><br>-------------</p><p>Letter</p><p>\"m\" formation<br>\"f\" formation - explained that \"r\" f\'s were like training wheels for grown up f\'s!</p><p><br>\"your\"<br>\"si\"</p><p>Nina was very tired today and even forgot how to spell her name! But she was encouraged to keep going and eventually corrected her mistakes!</p><p>----------</p><p>Syllable - open &amp; closed<br>Nina was a bit confused but we will go over this next week as well!</p><p>----------</p><p>OF</p><p>E \"predators\" \"<br>SC \"shrubs\" \"even\"</p>', '2022-09-30 16:12:34', '2022-09-30 16:13:48'),
(3399, '2022/09/30', '04:12 pm', '3', '3', 'Nina Grun', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Phonemic Awareness</p><p>Kilpatrick Level J</p><ul><li>(Speed) This task was completed perfectly without error</li></ul><p>OPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /oa ck ng wh/</li></ul><p>WPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /oa ck ng wh/</li><li>Self-Corrected \"wh\" (from \"h\")</li></ul><p>Morphology AffixesCompound Words</p><ul><li>Base word Donah 3</li></ul><p>Spelling Dictation</p><ul><li>what</li><li>when</li><li>where (whar)</li><li>why</li><li>who<ul><li>(Speed) This task was completed quickly</li><li>The student found some difficulty with the word \"where\". Nina is aware that there are different ways to spell where, but was unsure of their definitions. Something to address next week!</li></ul></li></ul><p>Oral Fluency</p><ul><li>Passage: 124<br>Self-Corrected \"predators\" \"cause\"</li><li>Errors \"high\" \"put = pulled\" \"choice\" \"of = for\"</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed at a regular pace.</li><li>However, the student showed confidence with a high level of prosody and tone!</li></ul><p>Writing</p><ul><li>Other Activity: Creative Writing - Fantasy<br>Self-Corrected \"her\"</li><li>Errors \"commotion\" \"laughed\" \"said\"</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed slowly, but with great enthusiasm</li><li>The student found some difficulty with spelling more complex words, and needed to be reminded to sound out her phonograms</li><li>However, the student showed confidence with plot and the direction of her character<br>&nbsp;</li></ul>', '2022-09-30 16:14:13', '2022-09-30 16:15:03'),
(3400, '2022/09/30', '04:14 pm', '3', '4', 'Nina Grun', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick Level J</p><p>OPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /ng oa wh ea ck/</li></ul><p>WPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /ng oa wh ea ck/</li></ul><p>Morphology AffixesCompound Words</p><ul><li>Base word Donah 4 + \"-ing\"</li></ul><p>Spelling Dictation</p><ul><li>Rules: 9<br>hop</li><li>begin</li><li>wag</li><li>get</li><li>forget</li><li>(+ing)</li></ul><p>Oral Fluency</p><ul><li>Passage: 124<br>Self-Corrected \"protecting\"</li><li>Errors \"cause\"</li><li>However, the student showed confidence with \"tortoise\", \"directly\" \"stubby\"</li></ul><p>Writing</p><ul><li>Writing Program Section: Creative writing<br>Errors Nina is starting to become confused with SFE and when to use them. This probably needs to be revisited.</li></ul>', '2022-09-30 16:15:26', '2022-09-30 16:16:27'),
(3401, '2022/09/30', '04:15 pm', '3', '5', 'Nina Grun', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Assigned', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>In addition to our normal lesson, we focused on SFE today as I\'ve noticed that Nina has started to randomly use SFE in different words!</p><ul><li>SFE - Which words have the SFE?<br>tim<br>great<br>hav<br>blu<br>frog<br>chanc<br>charg<br>littl<br>seat<br>ar<br>arrow<br>rabbit<br>how</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '2022-09-30 16:20:42', '2022-09-30 16:21:07'),
(3402, '2022/09/30', '04:20 pm', '3', '6', 'Nina Grun', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'To Be Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Nina was very tired today and a little emotional, so we mainly focused on reading and breaking down the words she had trouble with. Nina had mentioned that she hadn\'t had enough sleep and was very fidgety!</p><p>OF&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>Self-corrected:</strong><br>interesting<br>science &gt; scientist<br>can\'t &gt; can<br>after</li><li><strong>Errors:</strong><br>answer<br>penguin<br>questions<br>keeping</li></ul>', '2022-09-30 16:29:35', '2022-09-30 16:30:19'),
