(3404, '2022/09/30', '04:39 pm', '3', '10', 'James  Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Manipulate (delete or substitute) initial phoneme in initial blend - Kilpatrick Level H', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Attended Ontime', 'Yes', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Ten</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 29 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #35</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: gu ai ui ch ough ck ey kn ear gn ea&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>Needed prompting with first sound of ey and ough, then was fine.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 25</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: pair, pear, pare, check, prove, heard, hear, inspect, itself</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Used homophones pear/pare/pair in sentences to demo understanding of meaning</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>James did really well with PA and MA. He was very fiddly today and struggled to not do anything messy or destructive - his go to things are to push his pencil into his rubber, draw or wipe the desk with his pencil or fingers, mark his book or go over writing with his pencil. He typically stops when I ask him to, but then will restart shortly after if I don\'t continue prompting. He was pretty good with OPR/WPR, although did need prompting for initial sound of ey and ough. Good with SD words and able to ID marking. Good convo about pear/pare/pair, and James used these in sentences to show the meaning. He was able to ID the parts of speech, sentence type and sentence structure for both of the sentences he wrote, which I was very excited about.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Week Ten</td></tr><tr><td>Thursday, 29 September 2022</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-30 16:41:23', '2022-09-30 16:43:50'),
(3405, '2022/09/30', '04:30 pm', '3', '8', 'Nina Grun', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Kilpatrick Level K1</p><p>OPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /gu ey ed/</li></ul><p>WPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /gu ey ed/</li></ul><p>Spelling Dictation</p><ul><li>Rules: /gu ey ed/<br>loved</li><li>they</li><li>key</li><li>guess</li><li>Errors none! Super impressed with Nina!</li></ul><p>Oral Fluency</p><ul><li>Passage: 206<br>&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Writing</p><ul><li>Writing Program Section: Handwriting - V</li><li>Other Activity: Chaarcter Creation</li><li>Errors \"villain\" \"obnoxious\"</li><li>(Speed) This task was completed Slowly. Nina has not created many characters, but she seemed to have fun! This was a side villain named Slug.</li></ul>', '2022-09-30 16:43:11', '2022-09-30 16:43:59'),
(3406, '2022/09/30', '04:43 pm', '3', '9', 'James  Coleman', 'English', 'Phonological & Phonemic Awareness', 'Understand that spoken words consist of sequences of sounds called phonemes', 'Substitute onset & rime - Kilpatrick Level G', 'Ellie Connor', 'In Progress', 'N/A', 'Rescheduled', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Catch-up for W7 &amp; 9</td></tr><tr><td>Friday, 30 September 2022</td></tr><tr><td>1.5hrs</td></tr><tr><td>PA: Kilpatrick</td></tr><tr><td>MA: Donah #35</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>OPR/WPR: ay th ew ng ey ti wr ee ou ai ea&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Rule Review: 21, 20</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>SD: always, something, expect, need, thus, woman, women, young, fair, fare</td></tr><tr><td>Read S&amp;R</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Use woman/women in sentences to demo understanding of different meanings&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Recap narrative structure and WP, do plan for narrative</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>James did really well with PA &amp; MA - I bumped him up to a harder MA after finishing the easier one. Good with phonos, needed prompting with initial sound of ey but eventually did it independently. Very quick with spelling portion of the lesson which was great. James seemed more focused and engaged this session, which is great. I wasn\'t expecting that to be the case given it being the last day of school! Able to construct interesting and accurate sentences using spelling words and demonstrating their meaning. Able to ID elements of narrative texts and discuss in relation to narrative ORF, but then really struggled to articulate writing process steps and needed lots of prompting with these. I was so impressed with James\' creativity and how much it\'s improved since the last narrative we wrote. He created a plan for the second instalment of Bob &amp; Jeff\'s adventures, and almost seemed to enjoy coming up with different scenarios and antics. He was definitey engaged in this portion of the lesson. Finished the lesson with a game.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '<figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td>Catch-up for W7 &amp; 9</td></tr><tr><td>Friday, 30 September 2022</td></tr><tr><td>1.5hrs</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>', '2022-09-30 16:44:27', '2022-09-30 17:15:31'),
(3407, '2022/09/30', '04:43 pm', '3', '9', 'Nina Grun', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Juno Galang', NULL, NULL, 'Attended Ontime', 'N/A', 'Completed', 'N/A', 'N/A', NULL, NULL, '<p>Phonemic Awareness</p><ul><li>Kilpatrick Level K1</li></ul><p>OPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /ou ow ough/</li></ul><p>WPR</p><ul><li>Specific Phonograms /ow ou ough/</li></ul><p>Spelling Dictation</p><ul><li>Rules: /ough/<br>though</li><li>through</li><li>rough</li><li>cough</li><li>thought</li><li>drought</li><li>Errors last \"t\" in thought and drought</li><li>The student found some difficulty concentrating! Nina was very tired today as she did not get much sleep last night.</li></ul><p>Oral Fluency</p><ul><li>Passage: 206</li></ul><p><br>Writing</p><ul><li>Writing Program Section: Letter writing<br>Errors \"favourite = favrit\" \"mob = moob\" \"what = wate\"</li></ul>', '2022-09-30 16:44:49', '2022-09-30 16:45:42'),
